B040C001V001	40	1	1	The book of the genealogy of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham became the father of Isaac, and Isaac became the father of Jacob, and Jacob became the father of Judah and his brothers,
B040C001V003	40	1	3	and Judah became the father of Perez and Zerah by Tamar, and Perez became the father of Hezron, and Hezron became the father of Aram,
B040C001V004	40	1	4	and Aram became the father of Amminadab, and Amminadab became the father of Nahshon, and Nahshon became the father of Salmon,
B040C001V005	40	1	5	and Salmon became the father of Boaz by Rahab, and Boaz became the father of Obed by Ruth, and Obed became the father of Jesse,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	and Jesse became the father of David the king.And David became the father of Solomon by the wife of Uriah,
B040C001V007	40	1	7	and Solomon became the father of Rehoboam, and Rehoboam became the father of Abijah, and Abijah became the father of Asa,
B040C001V008	40	1	8	and Asa became the father of Jehoshaphat, and Jehoshaphat became the father of Joram, and Joram became the father of Uzziah,
B040C001V009	40	1	9	and Uzziah became the father of Jotham, and Jotham became the father of Ahaz, and Ahaz became the father of Hezekiah,
B040C001V010	40	1	10	and Hezekiah became the father of Manasseh, and Manasseh became the father of Amon, and Amon became the father of Josiah,
B040C001V011	40	1	11	and Josiah became the father of Jechoniah and his brothers, at the time of the deportation to Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the deportation to Babylon, Jechoniah became the father of Shealtiel, and Shealtiel became the father of Zerubbabel,
B040C001V013	40	1	13	and Zerubbabel became the father of Abiud, and Abiud became the father of Eliakim, and Eliakim became the father of Azor,
B040C001V014	40	1	14	and Azor became the father of Zadok, and Zadok became the father of Achim, and Achim became the father of Eliud,
B040C001V015	40	1	15	and Eliud became the father of Eleazar, and Eleazar became the father of Matthan, and Matthan became the father of Jacob,
B040C001V016	40	1	16	and Jacob became the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary by whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	Therefore all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations, and from David to the deportation to Babylon are fourteen generations, and from the deportation to Babylon to the Christ are fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ occurred in this way. His mother Mary had been betrothed to Joseph, but before they came together, she was found ˻to be pregnant˼ by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	So Joseph her husband, being righteous and not wanting to disgrace her, intended to divorce her secretly.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But as he was considering these things, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying, “Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife, for what has been conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	And she will give birth to a son, and you will call his name ‘Jesus,’ because he will save his people from their sins.”
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this happened in order that what was spoken by the Lord through the prophet would be fulfilled, saying,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	“Behold, the virgin ˻will become pregnant˼ and will give birth to a son,and they will call his name Emmanuel,”which is translated, “God with us.”
B040C001V024	40	1	24	And Joseph, when he woke up from sleep, did as the angel of the Lord commanded him, and he took his wife
B040C001V025	40	1	25	and ˻did not have sexual relations with˼ her until she gave birth to a son. And he called his name Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	Now after Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of Herod the king, behold, wise men from the east came to Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	saying, “Where is the one who has been born king of the Jews? For we have seen his star at its rising and have come to worship him.”
B040C002V003	40	2	3	And when King Herod heard it, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him,
B040C002V004	40	2	4	and after calling together all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he inquired from them where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	So they said to him, “In Bethlehem of Judea, for thus it is written by the prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	‘And you, Bethlehem, land of Judah,are by no means least among the rulers of Judah,for from you will go out a rulerwho will shepherd my people Israel.’ ”
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod secretly summoned the wise men and determined precisely from them the time when the star appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	And he sent them to Bethlehem and said, “Go, inquire carefully concerning the child, and when you have found him, report to me so that I also may come and worship him.”
B040C002V009	40	2	9	After they listened to the king, they went out, and behold, the star which they had seen at its rising led them until it came and stood above the place where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	Now when they saw the star, they rejoiced with very great joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And when they came into the house, they saw the child with Mary his mother, and they fell down and worshiped him. And opening their treasure boxes, they offered him gifts of gold and frankincense and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And being warned in a dream not to return to Herod, they went back to their own country by another route.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	Now after they had gone away, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph, saying, “Get up, take the child and his mother and flee to Egypt, and stay there until I tell you. For Herod is about to seek the child to destroy him.”
B040C002V014	40	2	14	So he got up and took the child and his mother during the night and went away to Egypt.
B040C002V015	40	2	15	And he was there until the death of Herod, in order that what was said by the Lord through the prophet would be fulfilled, saying,“Out of Egypt I called my son.”
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, when he saw that he had been deceived by the wise men, became very angry, and he sent soldiersand executed all the children in Bethlehem and in all the region around it from the age of two years old and under, according to the time which he had determined precisely from the wise men.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then what was spoken by the prophet Jeremiah was fulfilled, saying,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	“A voice was heard in Ramah,weeping and great mourning,Rachel weeping for her children,and she did not want to be comforted,because ˻they exist no longer˼.”
B040C002V019	40	2	19	Now after Herod had died, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	saying, “Get up, take the child and his mother and go to the land of Israel, for those who were seeking the life of the child are dead.”
B040C002V021	40	2	21	So he got up and took the child and his mother and ˻entered˼ the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Archelaus was reigning over Judea in place of his father Herod, he was afraid to go there, and being warned in a dream, he took refuge in the regions of Galilee.
B040C002V023	40	2	23	And he came and lived in a town called Nazareth, in order that what was said by the prophets would be fulfilled: “He will be called a Nazarene.”
B040C003V001	40	3	1	Now in those days John the Baptist came preaching in the Judean wilderness
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, “Repent, for the kingdom of heaven has come near!”
B040C003V003	40	3	3	For this is the one who was spoken about by the prophet Isaiah, saying,“The voice of one crying out in the wilderness,‘Prepare the way of the Lord,make his paths straight.’ ”
B040C003V004	40	3	4	Now John himself had his clothing made from camel’s hair and a belt made of leather around his waist, and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then Jerusalem and all Judea and all the district around the Jordan were going out to him,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and they were being baptized by him in the Jordan River as they confessed their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to his baptism, he said to them, “Offspring of vipers! Who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Therefore produce fruit worthy of repentence!
B040C003V009	40	3	9	And do not think to say to yourselves, ‘We have Abraham as father.’ For I say to you that God is able to raise up children for Abraham from these stones!
B040C003V010	40	3	10	Already now the ax is positioned at the root of the trees; therefore every tree not producing good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I baptize you with water for repentence, but the one who comes after me is more powerful than I am, whose sandals I am not worthy to carry. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing shovel is in his hand, and he will clean out his threshing floor and will gather his wheat into the storehouse, but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.”
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan to John in order to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John tried to prevent him, saying, “˻I need˼ to be baptized by you, and do you come to me?”
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jesus answered and said to him, “Permit it now, for in this way it is right for us to fulfill all righteousness.” Then he permitted him.
B040C003V016	40	3	16	Now after he was baptized, Jesus immediately went up from the water, and behold, the heavens opened to him and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and coming upon him.
B040C003V017	40	3	17	And behold, there was a voice from heaven saying, “This is my beloved Son, with whom I am well pleased.”
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led up into the wilderness by the Spirit to be tempted by the devil,
B040C004V002	40	4	2	and after he had fasted forty days and forty nights, then he was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And the tempter approached and said to him, “If you are the Son of God, order that these stones become bread.”
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answered and said, “It is written, ‘Man will not live on bread alone, but on every word that comes out of the mouth of God.”
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil took him to the holy city and placed him on the highest point of the temple
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to him, “If you are the Son of God, throw yourself down! For it is written,‘He will command his angels concerning you,’and‘On their hands they will lift you up,lest you strike your foot against a stone.’ ”
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him, “On the other hand it is written, ‘You are not to put the Lord your God to the test.’ ”
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again the devil took him to a very high mountain and showed him all the kingdoms of the world and their glory,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and he said to him, “I will give to you all these things, if you will fall down and worship me.”
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then Jesus said to him, “Go away, Satan, for it is written, ‘You shall worship the Lord your God and serve only him.’ ”
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil left him, and behold, angels came and began ministering to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now when he heard that John ˻had been arrested˼, he withdrew into Galilee.
B040C004V013	40	4	13	And leaving Nazareth, he went and lived in Capernaum by the sea, in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	in order that what was spoken by the prophet Isaiah would be fulfilled, who said,
B040C004V015	40	4	15	“Land of Zebulun and land of Naphtali,˻toward the sea˼, on the other side of the Jordan,Galilee of the Gentiles—
B040C004V016	40	4	16	the people who sit in darknesshave seen a great light,and the ones who sit in the land and shadow of death,a light has dawned on them.”
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time on, Jesus began to preach and to say, “Repent, because the kingdom of heaven is near.”
B040C004V018	40	4	18	Now as he was walking beside the Sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon called Peter and his brother Andrew, throwing a casting net into the sea (for they were fishermen).
B040C004V019	40	4	19	And he said to them, “˻Follow me˼ and I will make you fishers of people.”
B040C004V020	40	4	20	And immediately they left their nets and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And going on from there, he saw two other brothers, James the son of Zebedee and his brother John, in the boat with their father Zebedee, mending their nets, and he called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	And immediately they left the boat and their father and followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And he went around through all of Galilee, teaching in their synagogues and proclaiming the good news of the kingdom and healing every disease and every sickness among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And a report about him went out ˻throughout˼ Syria, and they brought to him all those ˻who were sick˼ with various diseases and afflicted by torments and demon-possessed and epileptics and paralytics, and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And large crowds followed him from Galilee, Decapolis, Jerusalem, Judea, and from the other side of the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	Now when he saw the crowds, he went up the mountain and after he sat down, his disciples approached him.
B040C005V002	40	5	2	And opening his mouth he began to teach them, saying,
B040C005V003	40	5	3	“Blessed are the poor in spirit,because theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	Blessed are the ones who mourn,because they will be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	Blessed are the meek,because they will inherit the earth.
B040C005V006	40	5	6	Blessed are the ones who hunger and thirst for righteousness,because they will be satisfied.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	Blessed are the merciful,because they will be shown mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	Blessed are the pure in heart,because they will see God.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	Blessed are the peacemakers,because they will be called sons of God.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	Blessed are those who are persecuted because of righteousness,because theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	Blessed are youwhen they insult you and persecute you and say all kinds of evil things against you, lying on account of me.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	Rejoice and be glad, because your reward is great in heaven, for in the same way they persecuted the prophets before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	“You are the salt of the earth. But if salt becomes tasteless, by what will it be made salty? It is good for nothing any longer except to be thrown outside and trampled under foot by people.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	You are the light of the world. A city located on top of a hill cannot be hidden,
B040C005V015	40	5	15	nor do they light a lamp and place it under a basket, but on a lampstand, and it shines on all those in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	In the same way let your light shine before people, so that they can see your good works and glorify your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	“Do not think that I have come to destroy the law or the prophets. I have not come to destroy them but to fulfill them.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	For truly I say to you, until heaven and earth pass away, not one tiny letter or one stroke of a letter will pass away from the law until all takes place.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Therefore whoever abolishes one of the least of these commandments and teaches people to do so will be called least in the kingdom of heaven, but whoever keeps them and teaches them, this person will be called great in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	For I say to you that unless your righteousness greatly surpasses that of the scribes and Pharisees, you will never enter into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	“You have heard that it was said to the ˻people of old˼, ‘Do not commit murder,’ and ‘whoever commits murder will be subject to judgment.’
B040C005V022	40	5	22	But I say to you that everyone who is angry at his brother will be subject to judgment, and whoever says to his brother, ‘Stupid fool!’ will be subject to the council, and whoever says, ‘Obstinate fool!’ will be subject to fiery hell.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	Therefore if you present your gift at the altar and there remember that your brother has something against you,
B040C005V024	40	5	24	leave your gift there before the altar and first go be reconciled to your brother, and then come and present your gift.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	˻Settle the case quickly with your accuser˼ while you are with him on the way, lest your accuser hand you over to the judge, and the judge to the officer, and you be thrown into prison.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	Truly I say to you, you will never come out of there until you have paid back the last penny!
B040C005V027	40	5	27	“You have heard that it was said, ‘Do not commit adultery.’
B040C005V028	40	5	28	But I say to you that everyone who looks at a woman to lust for her has already committed adultery with her in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	And if your right eye causes you to sin, tear it out and throw it from you! For it is better for you that one of your members be destroyed than your whole body be thrown into hell.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if your right hand causes you to sin, cut it off and throw it from you! For it is better for you that one of your limbs be destroyed than your whole body go into hell.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	“And it was said, ‘Whoever divorces his wife must give her a certificate of divorce.’
B040C005V032	40	5	32	But I say to you that everyone who divorces his wife, except for a matter of sexual immorality, causes her to commit adultery, and whoever marries a divorced woman commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	“Again you have heard that it was said to the ˻people of old˼, ‘Do not swear falsely, but fulfill your oaths to the Lord.’
B040C005V034	40	5	34	But I say to you, do not swear at all, either by heaven, because it is the throne of God,
B040C005V035	40	5	35	or by the earth, because it is the footstool of his feet, or by Jerusalem, because it is the city of the great king.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	And do not swear by your head, because you are not able to make one hair white or black.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	But let your statement be ‘Yes, yes; no, no,’ and anything beyond these is from the evil one.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	“You have heard that it was said, ‘An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth.’
B040C005V039	40	5	39	But I say to you, do not resist the evildoer, but whoever strikes you on your right cheek, turn the other to him also.
B040C005V040	40	5	40	And the one who wants to go to court with you and take your tunic, ˻let him have˼ your outer garment also.
B040C005V041	40	5	41	And whoever forces you to go one mile, go with him two.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	Give to the one who asks you, and do not turn away from the one who wants to borrow from you.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	“You have heard that it was said, ‘Love your neighbor’ and ‘Hate your enemy.’
B040C005V044	40	5	44	But I say to you, love your enemies and pray for those who persecute you,
B040C005V045	40	5	45	in order that you may be sons of your Father who is in heaven, because he causes his sun to rise on the evil and the good, and he sends rain on the just and the unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	For if you love those who love you, what reward do you have? Do not the tax collectors also do the same?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	And if you greet only your brothers, what are you doing that is remarkable? Do not the Gentiles also do the same?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	Therefore you be perfect as your heavenly Father is perfect.
B040C006V001	40	6	1	“And take care not to practice your righteousness before people to be seen by them; ˻otherwise˼ you have no reward from your Father who is in heaven.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	Therefore whenever you practice charitable giving, do not sound a trumpet in front of you, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, in order that they may be praised by people. Truly I say to you, they have received their reward in full!
B040C006V003	40	6	3	But you, when you practice charitable giving, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing,
B040C006V004	40	6	4	in order that your charitable giving may be in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	And whenever you pray, do not be like the hypocrites, because they love to stand and pray in the synagogues and on the corners of the streets, in order that they may be seen by people. Truly I say to you, they have received their reward in full!
B040C006V006	40	6	6	But whenever you pray, enter into your inner room and shut your door and pray to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	“But when you pray, do not babble repetitiously like the pagans, for they think that because of their many words they will be heard.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Therefore do not be like them, for your Father knows ˻what you need˼ before you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	Therefore you pray in this way:“Our Father who is in heaven,may your name be treated as holy.
B040C006V010	40	6	10	May your kingdom come,may your will be doneon earth as it is in heaven.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give us today our daily bread,
B040C006V012	40	6	12	and forgive us our debts,as we also have forgiven our debtors.
B040C006V013	40	6	13	And do not bring us into temptation,but deliver us from the evil one.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	For if you forgive people their sins, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.
B040C006V015	40	6	15	But if you do not forgive people, neither will your Father forgive your sins.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	“Whenever you fast, do not be sullen like the hypocrites, for they make their faces unrecognizable in order that they may be seen fasting by people. Truly I say to you, they have received their reward in full!
B040C006V017	40	6	17	But when you are fasting, ˻put olive oil on your head˼ and wash your face
B040C006V018	40	6	18	so that you will not be seen by people as fasting, but to your Father who is in secret, and your Father who sees in secret will reward you.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	“Do not store up for yourselves treasures on earth, where moth and consuming insect destroy and where thieves break in and steal,
B040C006V020	40	6	20	but store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor consuming insect destroy and where thieves do not break in or steal.
B040C006V021	40	6	21	For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	“The eye is the lamp of the body. Therefore if your eye is sincere, your whole body will be full of light.
B040C006V023	40	6	23	But if your eye is evil, your whole body will be dark. Therefore if the light in you is darkness, how great is the darkness!
B040C006V024	40	6	24	“No one is able to serve two masters. For either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will be devoted to one and despise the other. You are not able to serve God and money.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	“For this reason I say to you, do not be anxious for your life, what you will eat or what you will drink, and not for your body, what you will wear. Is your life not more than food and your body more than clothing?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	Consider the birds of the sky, that they do not sow or reap or gather produce into barns, and your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not worth more than they are?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	And who among you, by being anxious, is able to add one hour to his life span?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	And why are you anxious about clothing? Observe the lilies of the field, how they grow: they do not toil or spin,
B040C006V029	40	6	29	but I say to you that not even Solomon in all his glory was dressed like one of these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	But if God dresses the grass of the field in this way, although it is here today and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, will he not do so much more for you, you of little faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	Therefore do not be anxious, saying, ‘What will we eat?’ or ‘What will we drink?’ or ‘What will we wear?,’
B040C006V032	40	6	32	for the pagans seek after all these things. For your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	But seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness, and all these things will be added to you.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	Therefore do not be anxious for tomorrow, because tomorrow will be anxious for itself. ˻Each day has enough trouble of its own.˼
B040C007V001	40	7	1	“Do not judge, so that you will not be judged.
B040C007V002	40	7	2	For by what judgment you judge, you will be judged, and by what measure you measure out, it will be measured out to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	And why do you see the speck that is in your brother’s eye, but do not notice the beam of wood in your own eye?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	Or how will you say to your brother, ‘Allow me to remove the speck from your eye,’ and behold, the beam of wood is in your own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	Hypocrite! First remove the beam of wood from your own eye and then you will see clearly to remove the speck from your brother’s eye!
B040C007V006	40	7	6	“Do not give what is holy to dogs, or throw your pearls in front of pigs, lest they trample them with their feet, and turn around and tear you to pieces.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	“Ask and it will be given to you; seek and you will find; knock and it will be opened for you.
B040C007V008	40	7	8	For everyone who asks receives, and the one who seeks finds, and to the one who knocks it will be opened.
