B040C007V012	40	7	12	Therefore in all things, whatever you want that people should do to you, thus also you do to them. For this is the law and the prophets.
B040C007V013	40	7	13	“Enter through the narrow gate, because broad is the gate and spacious is the road that leads to destruction, and there are many who enter through it.
B040C007V014	40	7	14	How narrow is the gate and constricted the road that leads to life, and there are few who find it!
B040C007V015	40	7	15	“Beware of false prophets who come to you in sheep’s clothing, but inside are ravenous wolves.
B040C007V016	40	7	16	You will recognize them by their fruits: they do not gather grapes from thorn bushes or figs from thistles, do they?
B040C007V017	40	7	17	In the same way, every good tree produces good fruit, but a bad tree produces bad fruit.
B040C007V018	40	7	18	A good tree is not able to produce bad fruit, nor a bad tree to produce good fruit.
B040C007V019	40	7	19	Every tree that does not produce good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.
B040C007V020	40	7	20	As a result, you will recognize them by their fruits.
B040C007V021	40	7	21	“Not everyone who says to me, ‘Lord, Lord,’ will enter into the kingdom of heaven, but the one who does the will of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C007V022	40	7	22	On that day many will say to me, ‘Lord, Lord, did we not prophesy in your name, and expel demons in your name, and perform many miracles in your name?’
B040C007V023	40	7	23	And then ˻I will say to them plainly˼, ‘I never knew you. Depart from me, you who practice lawlessness!’
B040C007V024	40	7	24	“Therefore everyone who hears these words of mine and does them will be like a wise man who built his house on the rock.
B040C007V025	40	7	25	And the rain came down and the rivers came and the winds blew and beat against that house, and it did not collapse, because its foundation was laid on the rock.
B040C007V026	40	7	26	And everyone who hears these words of mine and does not do them will be like a foolish man who built his house on the sand.
B040C007V027	40	7	27	And the rain came down and the rivers came and the winds blew and beat against that house, and it collapsed, and its fall was great.”
B040C007V028	40	7	28	And it happened when Jesus finished these words the crowds were amazed at his teaching,
B040C007V029	40	7	29	because he was teaching them like one who had authority, and not like their scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	And when he came down from the mountain, large crowds followed him.
