B040C010V005	40	10	5	Jesus sent out these twelve, instructing them saying, “Do not go on the road to the Gentiles, and do not enter into a city of the Samaritans,
B040C010V006	40	10	6	but go instead to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you are going, preach, saying, ‘The kingdom of heaven has come near!’
B040C010V008	40	10	8	Heal those who are sick, raise the dead, cleanse lepers, expel demons. Freely you have received; freely give.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	Do not procure gold or silver or copper for your belts.
B040C010V010	40	10	10	Do not take a traveler’s bag for the road, or two tunics, or sandals, or a staff, for the worker is deserving of his provisions.
B040C010V011	40	10	11	And into whatever town or village you enter, inquire who in it is worthy, and stay there until you depart.
B040C010V012	40	10	12	And when you enter into the house, greet it.
B040C010V013	40	10	13	And if the house is worthy, let your peace come upon it, but if it is not worthy, let your peace return to you.
