B040C013V004	40	13	4	and while he was sowing, ˻some seed˼ fell on the side of the path, and the birds came and devoured it.
B040C013V005	40	13	5	And other seed fell on the rocky ground, where it did not have much soil, and it sprang up at once because it did not have any depth of soil.
B040C013V006	40	13	6	But when the sun rose it was scorched, and because it did not have enough root, it withered.
B040C013V007	40	13	7	And other seed fell among the thorn plants, and the thorn plants came up and choked it.
B040C013V008	40	13	8	But other seed fell on the good soil and produced grain, this one a hundred times as much and this one sixty and this one thirty.
B040C013V009	40	13	9	The one who has ears, let him hear!”
B040C013V010	40	13	10	And the disciples came up and said to him, “˻Why˼ do you speak to them in parables?”
B040C013V011	40	13	11	And he answered and said to them, “To you it has been granted to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to those people it has not been granted.
B040C013V012	40	13	12	For whoever has, to him more will be given, and he will have an abundance. But whoever does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him.
B040C013V013	40	13	13	For this reason I speak to them in parables, because seeing they do not see, and hearing they do not hear, nor do they understand,
B040C013V014	40	13	14	and with reference to them the prophecy of Isaiah is fulfilled that says,“˻You will listen carefully˼ and will never understand,and ˻you will look closely˼ and will never perceive.
