B040C017V001	40	17	1	And after six days Jesus took along Peter and James and John his brother, and led them up on a high mountain by themselves.
B040C017V002	40	17	2	And he was transfigured before them, and his face shone like the sun, and his clothing became bright as the light.
B040C017V003	40	17	3	And behold, Moses and Elijah appeared to them, talking with him.
B040C017V004	40	17	4	So Peter answered and said to Jesus, “Lord, it is good that we are here! If you want, I will make here three shelters, one for you and one for Moses and one for Elijah.”
B040C017V005	40	17	5	While he was still speaking, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them, and behold, a voice from the cloud said, “This is my beloved Son, with whom I am well pleased. Listen to him!”
B040C017V006	40	17	6	And when the disciples heard this, they fell down on their faces and were extremely frightened.
B040C017V007	40	17	7	And Jesus came and touched them and said, “Get up and do not be afraid.”
B040C017V008	40	17	8	And when they lifted up their eyes they saw no one except him—Jesus alone.
B040C017V009	40	17	9	And as they were coming down from the mountain, Jesus commanded them saying, “Tell no one the vision until the Son of Man is raised from the dead.”
B040C017V010	40	17	10	And the disciples asked him, saying, “Then why do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?”
B040C017V011	40	17	11	And he answered and said, “Elijah indeed is coming, and will restore all things.
B040C017V012	40	17	12	But I say to you that Elijah has already come, and they did not recognize him, but did with him whatever they wanted. In the same way also the Son of Man is going to suffer at their hands.”
B040C017V013	40	17	13	Then the disciples understood that he had spoken to them about John the Baptist.
B040C017V014	40	17	14	And when they came to the crowd, a man approached him, kneeling down before him
B040C017V015	40	17	15	and saying, “Lord, have mercy on my son, because he has seizures and suffers severely, for often he falls into the fire and often into the water.
B040C017V016	40	17	16	And I brought him to your disciples, and they were not able to heal him.”
B040C017V017	40	17	17	And Jesus answered and said, “O unbelieving and perverse generation! ˻How long˼ will I be with you? ˻How long˼ must I put up with you? Bring him here to me!”
B040C017V018	40	17	18	And Jesus rebuked him, and the demon came out of him and the boy was healed from that hour.
B040C017V019	40	17	19	Then the disciples approached Jesus privately and said, ˻Why˼ were we not able to expel it?”
B040C017V020	40	17	20	And he said to them, “Because of your little faith. For truly I say to you, if you have faith like a mustard seed, you will say to this mountain, ‘Move from here to there,’ and it will move, and nothing will be impossible for you.”
B040C017V022	40	17	22	Now as they were gathering in Galilee, Jesus said to them, “The Son of Man is going to be betrayed into the hands of men,
B040C017V023	40	17	23	and they will kill him, and on the third day he will be raised.” And they were extremely distressed.
B040C017V024	40	17	24	Now when they arrived in Capernaum, the ones who collected the double drachma tax came up to Peter and said, “Does your teacher not pay the double drachma tax?”
B040C017V025	40	17	25	He said, “Yes.” And when he came into the house, Jesus spoke to him first, saying, “What do you think, Simon? From whom do the kings of the earth collect tolls or taxes—from their own sons, or from foreigners?”
B040C017V026	40	17	26	And when he said, “From foreigners,” Jesus said to him, “Then the sons are free.
B040C017V027	40	17	27	But so that we do not give offense to them, go out to the sea, cast a line with a hook, and take the first fish that comes up. And when you open its mouth, you will find a four-drachma coin. Take that and give it to them for me and you.”
B040C018V001	40	18	1	At that time the disciples came up to Jesus, saying, “Who then is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?”
B040C018V002	40	18	2	And calling a child to himself, he had him stand in their midst
B040C018V003	40	18	3	and said, “Truly I say to you, unless you turn around and become like young children, you will never enter into the kingdom of heaven!
B040C018V004	40	18	4	Therefore whoever humbles himself like this child, this person is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven,
B040C018V005	40	18	5	and whoever welcomes one child such as this in my name welcomes me.
B040C018V006	40	18	6	But whoever causes one of these little ones who believe in me to sin, it would be better for him that ˻a large millstone˼ be hung around his neck and he be drowned in the depths of the sea.
B040C018V007	40	18	7	Woe to the world because of causes for stumbling, for it is a necessity that causes for stumbling come; nevertheless, woe to the person through whom the cause for stumbling comes.
B040C018V008	40	18	8	And if your hand or your foot causes you to sin, cut it off and throw it from you! It is better for you to enter into life crippled or lame than, having two hands or two feet, to be thrown into the eternal fire!
B040C018V009	40	18	9	And if your eye causes you to sin, tear it out and throw it from you! It is better for you to enter into life one-eyed than, having two eyes, to be thrown into fiery hell!
B040C018V010	40	18	10	“See to it that you do not despise one of these little ones, for I tell you that their angels in heaven constantly see the face of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V012	40	18	12	What do you think? If ˻a certain man has˼ a hundred sheep, and one of them wanders away, will he not leave the ninety-nine on the hills and go and look for the one that wandered away?
B040C018V013	40	18	13	And if he happens to find it, truly I say to you that he rejoices over it more than over the ninety-nine that did not wander away.
B040C018V014	40	18	14	In the same way it is not the will ˻of˼ your Father who is in heaven that one of these little ones perish.
B040C018V015	40	18	15	“Now if your brother sins against you, go correct him between you and him alone. If he listens to you, you have gained your brother.
B040C018V016	40	18	16	But if he does not listen, take with you in addition one or two others, so that by ˻the testimony˼ of two or three witnesses every matter may be established.
B040C018V017	40	18	17	And if he refuses to listen to them, tell it to the church. But if he refuses to listen to the church also, let him be to you as a Gentile and a tax collector.
B040C018V018	40	18	18	“Truly I say to you, whatever you bind on earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever you release on earth will be released in heaven.
B040C018V019	40	18	19	Again, truly I say to you that if two of you agree on earth about any matter that they ask, it will be done for them from my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V020	40	18	20	For where two or three are gathered in my name, I am there in the midst of them.”
B040C018V021	40	18	21	Then Peter came up and said to him, “Lord, how many times will my brother sin against me and I will forgive him? Up to seven times?”
B040C018V022	40	18	22	Jesus said to him, “I do not say to you up to seven times, but up to seventy times seven!
B040C018V023	40	18	23	“For this reason the kingdom of heaven may be compared to a man—a king—who wanted to settle accounts with his slaves.
B040C018V024	40	18	24	And when he began to settle them, someone was brought to him who owed ten thousand talents.
B040C018V025	40	18	25	And because he did not have enough to repay it, the master ordered him to be sold, and his wife and his children and everything that he had, and to be repaid.
B040C018V026	40	18	26	Then the slave threw himself to the ground and began to do obeisance to him, saying, ‘Be patient with me, and I will pay back everything to you!’
B040C018V027	40	18	27	So the master of that slave, because he had compassion, released him and forgave him the loan.
B040C018V028	40	18	28	But that slave went out and found one of his fellow slaves who owed him a hundred denarii, and taking hold of him, he began to choke him, saying, ‘Pay back everything that you owe!’
B040C018V029	40	18	29	Then his fellow slave threw himself to the ground and began to implore him, saying, ‘Be patient with me and I will repay you!’
B040C018V030	40	18	30	But he did not want to, but rather he went and threw him into prison until he would repay what was owed.
B040C018V031	40	18	31	So when his fellow slaves saw what had happened, they were extremely distressed, and went and reported to their master everything that had happened.
B040C018V032	40	18	32	Then his master summoned him and said to him, ‘Wicked slave! I forgave you all that debt because you implored me!
B040C018V033	40	18	33	Should you not also have shown mercy to your fellow slave as I also showed mercy to you?’
B040C018V034	40	18	34	And because he was angry, his master handed him over to the merciless jailers until he would repay everything that was owed.
B040C018V035	40	18	35	So also my heavenly Father will do to you, unless each of you forgives his brother from your hearts!”
B040C019V001	40	19	1	And it happened that when Jesus had finished these statements, he went away from Galilee and came into the region of Judea on the other side of the Jordan.
B040C019V002	40	19	2	And large crowds followed him, and he healed them there.
B040C019V003	40	19	3	And Pharisees came up to him in order to test him, and asked if it was permitted for a man to divorce his wife for any cause.
B040C019V004	40	19	4	And he answered and said, “Have you not read that the one who created them from the beginning made them male and female
B040C019V005	40	19	5	and said, ‘On account of this a man will leave his father and his mother and will be joined to his wife, and the two will become one flesh’?
B040C019V006	40	19	6	So then, they are no longer two but one flesh. Therefore what God has joined together, man must not separate.”
B040C019V007	40	19	7	They said to him, “Why then did Moses command us to give a document—a certificate of divorce—and to divorce her?”
B040C019V008	40	19	8	He said to them, “Moses, with reference to your hardness of heart, permitted you to divorce your wives, but from the beginning it was not like this.
B040C019V009	40	19	9	Now I say to you that whoever divorces his wife, except on the basis of sexual immorality, and marries another commits adultery.”
B040C019V010	40	19	10	His disciples said to him, “If this is the case of a man with his wife, it would be better not to marry!”
B040C019V011	40	19	11	But he said to them, “Not everyone can accept this saying but those to whom it has been given.
B040C019V012	40	19	12	For there are eunuchs who were born as such from their mother’s womb, and there are eunuchs who were made eunuchs by people, and there are eunuchs who have made themselves eunuchs for the sake of the kingdom of heaven. The one who is able to accept this, let him accept it.”
B040C019V013	40	19	13	Then children were brought to him so that he could lay his hands on them and pray, but the disciples rebuked them.
B040C019V014	40	19	14	But Jesus said, “Allow the children, and do not forbid them to come to me, ˻for to such belongs˼ the kingdom of heaven.”
B040C019V015	40	19	15	And he laid his hands on them and traveled on from there.
B040C019V016	40	19	16	And behold, someone came up to him and said, “Teacher, what good thing must I do so that I will have eternal life?”
B040C019V017	40	19	17	And he said to him, “Why are you asking me about what is good? There is one who is good. But if you want to enter into life, keep the commandments!”
B040C019V018	40	19	18	He said to him, “Which ones?” And Jesus said, “Do not commit murder, do not commit adultery, do not steal, do not give false testimony,
B040C019V019	40	19	19	honor your father and your mother, and love your neighbor as yourself.”
B040C019V020	40	19	20	The young man said to him, “All these I have observed. What do I still lack?”
B040C019V021	40	19	21	Jesus said to him, “If you want to be perfect, go, sell your possessions and give the proceeds to the poor—and you will have treasure in heaven—and come, follow me.”
B040C019V022	40	19	22	But when the young man heard the statement, he went away sorrowful, because he was one who had many possessions.
B040C019V023	40	19	23	And Jesus said to his disciples, “Truly I say to you that with difficulty a rich person will enter into the kingdom of heaven!
B040C019V024	40	19	24	And again I say to you, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich person to enter into the kingdom of God.”
B040C019V025	40	19	25	So when the disciples heard this, they were extremely amazed, saying, “Then who can be saved?”
B040C019V026	40	19	26	But Jesus looked at themand said to them, “With human beings this is impossible, but with God all thingsare possible.”
B040C019V027	40	19	27	Then Peter answered and said to him, “Behold, we have left everything and followed you. What then will there be for us?”
B040C019V028	40	19	28	And Jesus said to them, “Truly I say to you that in the renewal of the world, when the Son of Man sits on his glorious throne, you who have followed me—you also will sit on twelve thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
B040C019V029	40	19	29	And everyone who has left houses or brothers or sisters or father or mother or children or fields on account of my name will receive a hundred times as much, and will inherit eternal life.
B040C019V030	40	19	30	But many who are first will be last, and the last first.
B040C020V001	40	20	1	“For the kingdom of heaven is like a man—the master of the house—who went out early in the morning to hire workers for his vineyard.
B040C020V002	40	20	2	And after coming to an agreement with the workers for a denarius per day, he sent them into his vineyard.
B040C020V003	40	20	3	And going out about the third hour, he saw others standing idle in the marketplace.
B040C020V004	40	20	4	And to those people he said, ‘You also go into the vineyard, and I will give you whatever is right.’
B040C020V005	40	20	5	So they went. And going out again about the sixth and ninth hour he did the same thing.
B040C020V006	40	20	6	And about the eleventh hour he went out and found others standing there and said to them, ‘Why are you standing here the whole day unemployed?’
B040C020V007	40	20	7	They said to him, ‘Because no one hired us.’ He said to them, ‘You go also into the vineyard.’
B040C020V008	40	20	8	And when evening came, the owner of the vineyard said to his manager, ‘Call the workers and pay them their wages, beginning from the last up to the first.’
B040C020V009	40	20	9	And when the ones hired about the eleventh hour came, they received a denarius apiece.
B040C020V010	40	20	10	And when the first came, they thought that they would receive more, and they also received a denarius apiece.
B040C020V011	40	20	11	And when they received it, they began to complain against the master of the house,
B040C020V012	40	20	12	saying, ‘These last people worked one hour and you made them equal to us who have endured the burden of the day and the burning heat!’
B040C020V013	40	20	13	But he answered one of them and said, ‘Friend, I am not doing you wrong. Did you not come to an agreement with me for a denarius?
B040C020V014	40	20	14	Take what is yours and go! But I want to give to this last personthe same as I gave to you also.
B040C020V015	40	20	15	Or is it not permitted for me to do whatever I want with what is mine? Or is your eye evil because I am generous?’
B040C020V016	40	20	16	Thus the last will be first and the first last.”
B040C020V017	40	20	17	And as Jesus was going up to Jerusalem, he took the twelve disciples by themselves and said to them on the way,
B040C020V018	40	20	18	“Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and the Son of Man will be handed over to the chief priests and scribes, and they will condemn him to death,
B040C020V019	40	20	19	and will hand him over to the Gentiles to mock him and flog him and crucify him, and on the third day he will be raised.”
B040C020V020	40	20	20	Then the mother of the sons of Zebedee came up to him with her sons, and kneeling down she asked something of him.
B040C020V021	40	20	21	And he said to her, “What do you want?” She said to him, “Say that these two sons of mine may sit one at your right hand and one at your left in your kingdom.”
B040C020V022	40	20	22	But Jesus answered and said, “You do not know what you are asking! Are you able to drink the cup that I am about to drink?” They said to him, “We are able.”
B040C020V023	40	20	23	He said to them, “You will indeed drink my cup, but to sit at my right hand and at my left—this is not mine to grant, but is for those for whom it has been prepared by my Father.”
B040C020V024	40	20	24	And when the ten heard this, they were indignant concerning the two brothers.
B040C020V025	40	20	25	But Jesus called them to himself and said, “You know that the rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them, and those in high positions exercise authority over them.
B040C020V026	40	20	26	It will not be like this among you! But whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant,
B040C020V027	40	20	27	and whoever wants to be most prominent among you must be your slave—
B040C020V028	40	20	28	just as the Son of Man did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.”
B040C020V029	40	20	29	And as they were going out of Jericho, a large crowd followed him.
B040C020V030	40	20	30	And behold, there were two blind men sitting beside the road. When they heard that Jesus was passing by, they called out, saying, “Have mercy on us, Lord, Son of David!”
B040C020V031	40	20	31	And the crowd rebuked them so that they would be quiet. But they called out all the more, saying, “Have mercy on us, Lord, Son of David!”
B040C020V032	40	20	32	And Jesus stopped, called them, and said, “What do you want me to do for you?”
B040C020V033	40	20	33	They said to him, “Lord, that our eyes be opened!”
B040C020V034	40	20	34	And having compassion, Jesus touched their eyes, and immediately they received their sight and followed him.
B040C021V001	40	21	1	And when they drew near to Jerusalem and came to Bethphage at the Mount of Olives, then Jesus sent two disciples,
B040C021V002	40	21	2	saying to them, “Go into the village before you, and right away you will find a donkey tied and a colt with her. Untie themand bring them to me.
B040C021V003	40	21	3	And if anyone says anything to you, you will say, ‘The Lord ˻needs them˼,’ and he will send them at once.”
B040C021V004	40	21	4	Now this took place so that what was spoken through the prophet would be fulfilled, saying,
B040C021V005	40	21	5	“Say to the daughter of Zion,‘Behold, your king is coming to you,humble and mounted on a donkey,and on a colt, the foal of a pack animal.’ ”
B040C021V006	40	21	6	So the disciples went and did just as Jesus directed them,
B040C021V007	40	21	7	and brought the donkey and the colt and put their cloaks on them, and he sat on them.
B040C021V008	40	21	8	And a very large crowd spread their cloaks on the road, and others were cutting branches from the trees and spreading them on the road.
B040C021V009	40	21	9	And the crowds who went ahead of him and the ones who followed were shouting, saying,“Hosanna to the Son of David!Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord!Hosanna in the highest heaven!”
B040C021V010	40	21	10	And when he entered into Jerusalem, the whole city was stirred up, saying, “Who is this?”
B040C021V011	40	21	11	And the crowds were saying, “This is the prophet Jesus from Nazareth of Galilee!”
B040C021V012	40	21	12	And Jesus entered the temple courts and drove out all those who were selling and buying in the temple, and overturned the tables of the money changers and the chairs of those who were selling doves.
B040C021V013	40	21	13	And he said to them, “It is written, ‘My house will be called a house of prayer,’ but you have made it a cave of robbers!”
B040C021V014	40	21	14	And the blind and the lame came up to him in the temple courts and he healed them.
B040C021V015	40	21	15	But when the chief priests and the scribes saw the wonderful things that he did, and the children shouting in the temple courts and saying, “Hosanna to the Son of David!” they were indignant.
B040C021V016	40	21	16	And they said to him, “Do you hear what these children are saying?” So Jesus said to them, “Yes, have you never read, ‘Out of the mouths of children and nursing babies you have prepared for yourself praise’?”
B040C021V017	40	21	17	And leaving them, he went outside of the city to Bethany and spent the night there.
B040C021V018	40	21	18	Now early in the morning, as he was returning to the city, he was hungry.
B040C021V019	40	21	19	And seeing a single fig tree by the road, he went to it and found nothing on it except leaves only. And he said to it, “May there be no more fruit from you ˻forever˼, and the fig tree withered at once.
B040C021V020	40	21	20	And when they saw it, the disciples were astonished, saying, “How did the fig tree wither at once?”
B040C021V021	40	21	21	And Jesus answered and said to them, “Truly I say to you, if you have faith and do not doubt, you will do not only what was done to the fig tree, but even if you say to this mountain, ‘Be lifted up and thrown into the sea,” it will happen!
B040C021V022	40	21	22	And whatever you ask in prayer, if you believe, you will receive.”
B040C021V023	40	21	23	And after he arrived at the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came up to him while he was teaching, saying, “By what authority are you doing these things? And who gave you this authority?”
B040C021V024	40	21	24	And Jesus answered and said to them, “I also will ask you one question. If you tell the answer to me, I also will tell you by what authority I am doing these things.
B040C021V025	40	21	25	From where was the baptism of John—from heaven or from men?” And they began to discuss this among themselves, saying, “If we say ‘From heaven,’ he will say to us, ‘Why then did you not believe him?’
B040C021V026	40	21	26	But if we say, ‘From men,’ we are afraid of the crowd, because they all look upon John as a prophet.”
B040C021V027	40	21	27	And they answered and said to Jesus, “We do not know.” And he said to them, “Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things.
B040C021V028	40	21	28	“Now what do you think? A man had two sons. And he approached the first and said, ‘Son, go work in the vineyard today.’
B040C021V029	40	21	29	And he answered and said, ‘I do not want to!’ But later he changed his mind and went.
B040C021V030	40	21	30	And he approached the other and said the same thing. So he answered and said, ‘I will, sir,’ and he did not go.
B040C021V031	40	21	31	Which of the two did the will of his father?” They said, “The first.” Jesus said to them, “Truly I say to you that the tax collectors and the prostitutes are going ahead of you into the kingdom of God!
B040C021V032	40	21	32	For John came to you in the way of righteousness and you did not believe him, but the tax collectors and the prostitutes did believe him. And when you saw it, you did not even change your minds later so as to believe in him.
B040C021V033	40	21	33	“Listen to another parable: There was a man—a master of a house—who planted a vineyard, and put a fence around it, and dug a winepress in it, and built a watchtower, and leased it to tenant farmers, and went on a journey.
B040C021V034	40	21	34	And when the season of fruit drew near, he sent his slaves to the tenant farmers to collect his fruit.
B040C021V035	40	21	35	And the tenant farmers seized his slaves, one of whom they beat, and one of whom they killed, and one of whom they stoned.
B040C021V036	40	21	36	Again, he sent other slaves, more than the first ones, and they did the same thing to them.
B040C021V037	40	21	37	So finally he sent his son to them, saying, ‘They will respect my son.’
B040C021V038	40	21	38	But when the tenant farmers saw the son, they said among themselves, ‘This is the heir. Come, let us kill him and have his inheritance!’
B040C021V039	40	21	39	And they seized him and threw him out of the vineyard and killed him.
B040C021V040	40	21	40	Now when the master of the vineyard arrives, what will he do to those tenant farmers?”
B040C021V041	40	21	41	They said to him, “He will destroy those evil men completely and lease the vineyard to other tenant farmers who will give him the fruits in their season.”
B040C021V042	40	21	42	Jesus said to them, “Have you never read in the scriptures,‘The stone which the builders rejected,this has become ˻the cornerstone˼.This came about from the Lord,and it is marvelous in our eyes’?
