B040C021V046	40	21	46	and although they wanted to arrest him, they were afraid of the crowds, because they looked upon him as a prophet.
B040C022V001	40	22	1	And continuing, Jesus spoke to them again in parables, saying,
B040C022V002	40	22	2	“The kingdom of heaven may be compared to a man—a king—who gave a wedding celebration for his son.
B040C022V003	40	22	3	And he sent his slaves to summon those who had been invited to the wedding celebration, and they did not want to come.
B040C022V004	40	22	4	Again he sent other slaves, saying, ‘Tell those who have been invited, “Behold, I have prepared my dinner; my oxen and fattened cattle have been slaughtered, and everything is ready. Come to the wedding celebration!” ’
B040C022V005	40	22	5	But they paid no attention and went away—this one to his own field, that one to his business.
B040C022V006	40	22	6	And the others, seizing his slaves, mistreated them and killed them.
B040C022V007	40	22	7	And the king was angry and sent his troops and destroyed those murderers and burned their city.
B040C022V008	40	22	8	Then he said to his slaves, ‘The wedding celebration is ready, but those who had been invited were not worthy.
B040C022V009	40	22	9	Therefore, go out to the places where the roads exit the city and invite to the wedding celebration as many people as you find.’
B040C022V010	40	22	10	And those slaves went out into the roads and gathered everyone whom they found, both evil and good, and the wedding celebration was filled ˻with dinner guests˼.
B040C022V011	40	22	11	But when the king came in to see the ˻dinner guests˼, he saw a man there not dressed in wedding clothes.
B040C022V012	40	22	12	And he said to him, ‘Friend, how did you come in here, not having wedding clothes?’ But ˻he could say nothing˼.
B040C022V013	40	22	13	Then the king said to the servants, ‘Tie him up ˻hand and foot˼and throw him into the outer darkness. In that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth!’
B040C022V014	40	22	14	For many are called but few are chosen.”
B040C022V015	40	22	15	Then the Pharisees went ˻and consulted˼ so that they could entrap him with a statement.
B040C022V016	40	22	16	And they sent their disciples to him with the Herodians, saying, “Teacher, we know that you are truthful and teach the way of God in truth, and ˻you do not care what anyone thinks˼, ˻because you do not regard the opinion of people˼.
B040C022V017	40	22	17	Therefore tell us what you think. Is it permitted to pay taxes to Caesar or not?”
B040C022V018	40	22	18	But because he knew their maliciousness, Jesus said, “Hypocrites! Why are you testing me?
B040C022V019	40	22	19	Show me the coin for the tax!” So they brought him a denarius.
B040C022V020	40	22	20	And he said to them, “Whose image and inscription is this?”
B040C022V021	40	22	21	They said to him, “Caesar’s.” Then he said to them, “Therefore give to Caesar the things of Caesar, and to God the things of God!”
B040C022V022	40	22	22	And when they heard this, they were astonished, and they left him and went away.
B040C022V023	40	22	23	On that day Sadducees—who say there is no resurrection—came up to him and asked him,
B040C022V024	40	22	24	saying, “Teacher, Moses said if someone dies without having children, his brother is to marry his wife and ˻father˼ descendants for his brother.
B040C022V025	40	22	25	Now there were seven brothers with us. And the first died after getting married, and because he did not have descendants, he left his wife to his brother.
B040C022V026	40	22	26	So also the second and the third, up to the seventh.
B040C022V027	40	22	27	And last of all the woman died.
B040C022V028	40	22	28	In the resurrection, therefore, whose wife of the seven will she be? For they all had her as wife.”
B040C022V029	40	22	29	But Jesus answered and said to them, “You are mistaken, because you do not know the scriptures or the power of God!
B040C022V030	40	22	30	For in the resurrection they neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.
B040C022V031	40	22	31	Now concerning the resurrection of the dead, have you not read what was spoken to you by God, who said,
B040C022V032	40	22	32	“I am the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob”? He is not the God of the dead, but of the living!”
B040C022V033	40	22	33	And when the crowds heard this, they were amazed at his teaching.
B040C022V034	40	22	34	Now when the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees, they assembled at the same place.
B040C022V035	40	22	35	And one of them, a legal expert, put a question to him to test him:
B040C022V036	40	22	36	“Teacher, which commandment is greatest in the law?”
B040C022V037	40	22	37	And he said to him, “ ‘You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your mind.’
B040C022V038	40	22	38	This is the greatest and first commandment.
B040C022V039	40	22	39	And the second is like it: ‘You shall love your neighbor as yourself.’
B040C022V040	40	22	40	On these two commandments depend all the law and the prophets.”
B040C022V041	40	22	41	Now while the Pharisees were assembled, Jesus asked them,
B040C022V042	40	22	42	saying, “What do you think about the Christ? Whose son is he?” They said to him, “David’s.”
B040C022V043	40	22	43	He said to them, “How then does David, by the Spirit, call him ‘Lord,’ saying,
B040C022V044	40	22	44	‘The Lord said to my Lord,“Sit at my right handuntil I put your enemiesunder your feet” ’?
B040C022V045	40	22	45	If then David calls him ‘Lord,’ how is he his son?”
B040C022V046	40	22	46	And no one was able to answer him a word, nor did anyone dare from that day on to ask him any more questions.
B040C023V001	40	23	1	Then Jesus spoke to the crowds and to his disciples,
B040C023V002	40	23	2	saying, “The scribes and the Pharisees sit on the seat of Moses.
B040C023V003	40	23	3	Therefore do and observe everything that they tell you, but do not do as ˻they do˼, for they tell others to do something and do not do it themselves.
B040C023V004	40	23	4	And they tie up burdens that are heavy and hard to bear, and put them on people’s shoulders, but they themselves are not willing with their finger to move them.
B040C023V005	40	23	5	And they do all their deeds in order to be seen by people, for they make their phylacteries broad and make their tassels long.
B040C023V006	40	23	6	And they love the place of honor at banquets and the best seats in the synagogues
B040C023V007	40	23	7	and the greetings in the marketplaces and to be called ‘Rabbi’ by people.
B040C023V008	40	23	8	But you are not to be called ‘Rabbi,’ because one is your teacher, and you are all brothers,
B040C023V009	40	23	9	And do not call anyone your father on earth, for one is your heavenly Father.
B040C023V010	40	23	10	And do not be called teachers, because one is your teacher, the Christ.
B040C023V011	40	23	11	And the greatest among you will be your servant.
B040C023V012	40	23	12	And whoever exalts himself will be humbled, and whoever humbles himself will be exalted.
B040C023V013	40	23	13	“But woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you shut the kingdom of heaven before people! For you do not enter, nor permit those wanting to go in to enter.
B040C023V015	40	23	15	“Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you travel around the sea and the dry land to make one convert, and when he becomes one, you make him twice as much a son of hell as you are!
B040C023V016	40	23	16	“Woe to you, blind guides, who say, ‘Whoever swears by the temple, it is nothing! But whoever swears by the gold of the temple is bound by his oath.’
B040C023V017	40	23	17	Fools and blind people! For which is greater, the gold or the temple that makes the gold holy?
B040C023V018	40	23	18	And, ‘Whoever swears by the altar, it is nothing! But whoever swears by the gift that is on it is bound by his oath.’
B040C023V019	40	23	19	Blind people! For which is greater, the gift or the altar that makes the gift holy?
B040C023V020	40	23	20	Therefore the one who swears by the altar swears by it and by everything that is on it.
B040C023V021	40	23	21	And the one who swears by the temple swears by it and by the one who dwells in it.
B040C023V022	40	23	22	And the one who swears by heaven swears by the throne of God and by the one who sits on it.
B040C023V023	40	23	23	“Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you pay a tenth of mint and dill and cumin, and neglect the more important matters of the law—justice and mercy and faithfulness! But it was necessary to do these things˻while not neglecting those˼.
B040C023V024	40	23	24	Blind guides who filter out a gnat and swallow a camel!
B040C023V025	40	23	25	“Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you cleanse the outside of the cup and the dish, but inside they are full of greed and self-indulgence!
B040C023V026	40	23	26	Blind Pharisee! First clean the inside of the cup, so that the outside of it may become clean also.
B040C023V027	40	23	27	“Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you are like whitewashed tombs which on the outside appear beautiful, but on the inside are full of the bones of the dead and of everything unclean!
B040C023V028	40	23	28	In the same way, on the outside you also appear righteous to people, but inside you are full of hypocrisy and lawlessness.
B040C023V029	40	23	29	“Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees—hypocrites!—because you build the tombs of the prophets and decorate the graves of the righteous,
B040C023V030	40	23	30	and you say, ‘If we had lived in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partners with them in the blood of the prophets!’
B040C023V031	40	23	31	Thus you testify against yourselves that you are descendants of those who murdered the prophets!
B040C023V032	40	23	32	And you—fill up the measure of your fathers!
B040C023V033	40	23	33	Serpents! Offspring of vipers! How will you escape from the condemnation to hell?
B040C023V034	40	23	34	For this reason, behold, I am sending to you prophets and wise men and scribes. Some of them you will kill and crucify, and some of them you will flog in your synagogues and will pursue from town to town,
B040C023V035	40	23	35	so that upon you will come all the righteous blood shed on the earth from the blood of righteous Abel up to the blood of Zechariah son of Barachiah, whom you murdered between the temple and the altar.
B040C023V036	40	23	36	Truly I say to you, all these things will come upon this generation!
B040C023V037	40	23	37	“Jerusalem, Jerusalem, who kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to her! How many times I wanted to gather your children together ˻the way˼ a hen gathers her young together under her wings, and you were not willing!
B040C023V038	40	23	38	Behold, your house has been left to you desolate!
B040C023V039	40	23	39	For I tell you, you will never see me from now on until you say,‘Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord!’ ”
B040C024V001	40	24	1	And as Jesus went out of the temple courts he was going along, and his disciples came up to point out to him the buildings of the temple.
B040C024V002	40	24	2	But he answered and said to them, “Do you not see all these things? Truly I say to you, not one stone will be left here on another stone that will not be thrown down!”
B040C024V003	40	24	3	And as he was sitting on the Mount of Olives, the disciples came up to him privately, saying, “Tell us, when will these things happen, and what will be the sign of your coming and of the end of the age?”
B040C024V004	40	24	4	And Jesus answered and said to them, “Watch out that no one deceives you!
B040C024V005	40	24	5	For many will come in my name, saying, ‘I am the Christ,’ and they will deceive many.
B040C024V006	40	24	6	And you are going to hear about wars and rumors of wars. See to it that you are not alarmed, for this must happen, but the end is not yet.
B040C024V007	40	24	7	For nation will rise up against nation and kingdom against kingdom, and there will be famines and earthquakes in various places.
B040C024V008	40	24	8	But all these thingsare the beginning of birth pains.
B040C024V009	40	24	9	“Then they will hand you over to persecution and will kill you, and you will be hated by all the nations because of my name.
B040C024V010	40	24	10	And then many will be led into sin and will betray one another and will hate one another,
B040C024V011	40	24	11	and many false prophets will appear and will deceive many,
B040C024V012	40	24	12	and because lawlessness will increase, the love of many will grow cold.
B040C024V013	40	24	13	But the one who endures to the end—this person will be saved.
B040C024V014	40	24	14	And this gospel of the kingdom will be proclaimed in the whole inhabited earth for a testimony to all the nations, and then the end will come.
B040C024V015	40	24	15	“So when you see the abomination of desolation spoken about by the prophet Daniel standing in the holy place” (let the one who reads understand),
B040C024V016	40	24	16	“then those in Judea must flee to the mountains!
B040C024V017	40	24	17	The one who is on his housetop must not come down to take things out of his house,
B040C024V018	40	24	18	and the one who is in the field must not turn back to pick up his cloak.
B040C024V019	40	24	19	And woe to those ˻who are pregnant˼ and to those who are nursing their babies in those days!
B040C024V020	40	24	20	But pray that your flight may not happen in winter or on a Sabbath.
B040C024V021	40	24	21	For at that time there will be great tribulation, such as has not happened from the beginning of the world until now, nor ever will happen.
B040C024V022	40	24	22	And unless those days had been shortened, ˻no human being would be saved˼. But for the sake of the elect, those days will be shortened.
B040C024V023	40	24	23	“At that time if anyone should say to you, ‘Behold, here is the Christ,’ or ‘Here he is,’ do not believe him!
B040C024V024	40	24	24	For false messiahs and false prophets will appear, and will produce great signs and wonders in order to deceive, if possible, even the elect.
B040C024V025	40	24	25	Behold, I have told you ahead of time!
B040C024V026	40	24	26	Therefore if they say to you, ‘Behold, he is in the wilderness,’ do not go out, or ‘Behold, he is in the inner rooms,’ do not believe it!
B040C024V027	40	24	27	For just as the lightning comes from the east and flashes to the west, so the coming of the Son of Man will be.
B040C024V028	40	24	28	Wherever the corpse is, there the vultures will gather.
B040C024V029	40	24	29	“And immediately after the tribulation of those days,‘the sun will be darkenedand the moon will not give its light,and the stars will fall from heaven,and the powers of heaven will be shaken.’
B040C024V030	40	24	30	And then the sign of the Son of Man will appear in heaven, and then all the tribes of the earth will mourn, and they will see the Son of Man arriving on the clouds of heaven with power and great glory.
B040C024V031	40	24	31	And he will send out his angels with a loud trumpet call, and they will gather his elect together from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other end of it.
B040C024V032	40	24	32	“Now learn the parable from the fig tree: Whenever its branch has already become tender and puts forth its leaves, you know that summer is near.
B040C024V033	40	24	33	So also you, when you see all these things, know that he is near, at the door.
B040C024V034	40	24	34	Truly I say to you that this generation will never pass away until all these things take place!
B040C024V035	40	24	35	Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will never pass away.
B040C024V036	40	24	36	“But concerning that day and hour no one knows—not even the angels of heaven nor the Son—except the Father alone.
B040C024V037	40	24	37	For just as the days of Noah were, so the coming of the Son of Man will be.
B040C024V038	40	24	38	For as in those days before the flood they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day Noah entered into the ark.
B040C024V039	40	24	39	And they did not know anything until the deluge came and swept them all away. So also the coming of the Son of Man will be.
B040C024V040	40	24	40	Then there will be two men in the field; one will be taken and one left.
B040C024V041	40	24	41	Two women will be grinding at the mill; one will be taken and one left.
B040C024V042	40	24	42	Therefore be on the alert, because you do not know what day your Lord is coming!
B040C024V043	40	24	43	But understand this: that if the master of the house had known what watch of the night the thief was coming, he would have stayed awake and would not have let his house be broken into.
B040C024V044	40	24	44	For this reason you also must be ready, because the Son of Man is coming at an hour that you do not think he will come.
B040C024V045	40	24	45	“Who then is the faithful and wise slave whom the master has put in charge of his household slaves to give them their food at the right time?
B040C024V046	40	24	46	Blessed is that slave whom his master will find so doing when he comes back.
B040C024V047	40	24	47	Truly I say to you that he will put him in charge of all his possessions.
B040C024V048	40	24	48	But if that evil slave should say ˻to himself˼, ‘My master is staying away for a long time,’
B040C024V049	40	24	49	and he begins to beat his fellow slaves and eats and drinks with drunkards,
B040C024V050	40	24	50	the master of that slave will come on a day that he does not expect and at an hour that he does not know,
B040C024V051	40	24	51	and will cut him in two and assign his place with the hypocrites. In that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth!
B040C025V001	40	25	1	“Then the kingdom of heaven may be compared to ten virgins who took their lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom.
B040C025V002	40	25	2	Now five of them were foolish and five were wise.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	For when the foolish ones took their lamps, they did not take olive oil with them.
B040C025V004	40	25	4	But the wise ones took olive oil in flasks with their lamps.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	And when the bridegroom was delayed, they all became drowsy and fell asleep.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	But in the middle of the night there was a shout, ‘Behold, the bridegroom! Come out to meet him!’
B040C025V007	40	25	7	Then all those virgins woke up and trimmed their lamps.
B040C025V008	40	25	8	And the foolish ones said to the wise ones, ‘Give us some of your olive oil, because our lamps are going out!’
B040C025V009	40	25	9	But the wise ones answered saying, “Certainly there will never be enough for us and for you! Go instead to those who sell olive oil and buy some for yourselves.’
B040C025V010	40	25	10	But while they had gone away to buy it the bridegroom arrived, and those who were ready went inside with him to the wedding celebration, and the door was shut.
B040C025V011	40	25	11	And later the other virgins came also, saying, ‘Lord, lord, open the door for us!’
B040C025V012	40	25	12	But he answered and said, ‘Truly I say to you, I do not know you!’
B040C025V013	40	25	13	Therefore be on the alert, because you do not know the day or the hour!
B040C025V014	40	25	14	For it is like a man going on a journey. He summoned his own slaves and handed over his property to them.
B040C025V015	40	25	15	And to one he gave five talents, and to another two, and to another one, to each one according to his own ability, and he went on a journey immediately.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	The one who had received the five talents went out and traded with them and gained five more.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	In the same way the one who had the two gained two more.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	But the one who had received the one went away and dug up the ground and hid his master’s money.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	Now after a long time, the master of those slaves came and settled accounts with them.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	And the one who had received the five talents came up and brought five more talents, saying, ‘Master, you handed over to me five talents. See, I have gained five more talents!’
B040C025V021	40	25	21	His master said to him, ‘Well done, good and faithful slave! You were faithful over a few things; I will put you in charge over many things. Enter into the joy of your master!’
B040C025V022	40	25	22	And the one who had the two talents also came up and said, ‘Master, you handed over to me two talents. See, I have gained two talents more!’
B040C025V023	40	25	23	His master said to him, ‘Well done, good and faithful slave! You were faithful over a few things; I will put you in charge over many things. Enter into the joy of your master!’
B040C025V024	40	25	24	And the one who had received the one talent came up also and said, ‘Master, because I knew you, that you are a hard man, reaping where you did not sow and gathering from where you did not scatter seed.
B040C025V025	40	25	25	And because I was afraid, I went away and hid your talent in the ground. See, you have what is yours!’
B040C025V026	40	25	26	But his master answered and said to him, ‘Evil and lazy slave! You knew that I reap where I did not sow and gather from where I did not scatter seed.
B040C025V027	40	25	27	Then you ought to have deposited my money with the bankers, and when I returned I would have gotten back what was mine with interest!
B040C025V028	40	25	28	Therefore take the talent from him and give it to the one who has the ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	For to everyone who has, more will be given, and he will have an abundance. But from the one who does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him.
B040C025V030	40	25	30	And throw the worthless slave into the outer darkness—in that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth!’
B040C025V031	40	25	31	Now when the Son of Man comes in his glory and all the angels with him, then he will sit on his glorious throne.
B040C025V032	40	25	32	And all the nations will be gathered before him, and he will separate them from one another like a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.
B040C025V033	40	25	33	And he will place the sheep on his right and the goats on the left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	Then the king will say to those on his right, ‘Come, you who are blessed by my Father. Inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world!
B040C025V035	40	25	35	For I was hungry and you gave me something to eat, I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink, I was a stranger and you welcomed me as a guest,
B040C025V036	40	25	36	I was naked and you clothed me, I was sick and you cared for me, I was in prison and you came to me.’
B040C025V037	40	25	37	Then the righteous will answer him, saying, ‘Lord, when did we see you hungry and feed you, or thirsty and give you something to drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	And when did we see you a stranger and welcome you as a guest, or naked and clothe you?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	And when did we see you sick or in prison and come to you?’
B040C025V040	40	25	40	And the king will answer and say to them, ‘Truly I say to you, in as much as you did it to one of the least of these brothers of mine, you did it to me.’
B040C025V041	40	25	41	Then he will also say to those on his left, ‘Depart from me, you accursed ones, into the eternal fire that has been prepared for the devil and his angels!
B040C025V042	40	25	42	For I was hungry and you did not give me anything to eat, I was thirsty and you did not give me anything to drink,
B040C025V043	40	25	43	I was a stranger and you did not welcome me as a guest, naked and you did not clothe me, sick and in prison and you did not care for me.’
B040C025V044	40	25	44	Then they will also answer, saying, ‘Lord, when did we see you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison and not serve you?’
B040C025V045	40	25	45	Then he will answer them, saying, ‘Truly I say to you, in as much as you did not do it to one of the least of these, you did not do it to me.’
B040C025V046	40	25	46	And these will depart into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life.”
B040C026V001	40	26	1	And it happened that when Jesus had finished all these sayings, he said to his disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	“You know that after two days the Passover takes place, and the Son of Man will be handed over in order to be crucified.”
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then the chief priests and the elders of the people assembled in the palace of the high priest, who was named Caiaphas,
B040C026V004	40	26	4	and plotted in order that they could arrest Jesus by stealth and kill him.
B040C026V005	40	26	5	But they were saying, “Not during the feast, so that there will not be an uproar among the people.”
B040C026V006	40	26	6	Now while Jesus was at Bethany in the house of Simon the leper,
B040C026V007	40	26	7	a woman came up to him holding an alabaster flask of very expensive perfumed oil, and poured it out on his head while he was reclining at table.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	And when the disciples saw it they were indignant, saying, “˻Why˼ this waste?
B040C026V009	40	26	9	For this could have been sold for a large sum and given to the poor!”
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But Jesus, knowing this, said to them, “Why do you cause trouble for the woman? For she has done a good deed for me.
B040C026V011	40	26	11	For the poor you always have with you, but you do not always have me.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	For when this woman poured this ointment on my body, she did it in order to prepare me for burial.
B040C026V013	40	26	13	Truly I say to you, wherever this gospel is proclaimed in the whole world, what this woman has done will also be told in memory of her.”
B040C026V014	40	26	14	Then one of the twelve, the one named Judas Iscariot, went to the chief priests
B040C026V015	40	26	15	and said, “What are you willing to give me if I in turn deliver him to you?” So they set out for him thirty silver coins.
B040C026V016	40	26	16	And from that time on, he began seeking a favorable opportunity in order that he could betray him.
B040C026V017	40	26	17	Now on the first day of the feast of Unleavened Bread the disciples came up to Jesus, saying, “Where do you want us to prepare for you to eat the Passover?”
B040C026V018	40	26	18	And he said, “Go into the city to a certain man and tell him, ‘The Teacher says, “My time is near. I am celebrating the Passover with you with my disciples.” ’
B040C026V019	40	26	19	And the disciples did as Jesus directed them, and they prepared the Passover.
B040C026V020	40	26	20	And when it was evening, he was reclining at table with the twelve.
B040C026V021	40	26	21	And while they were eating he said, “Truly I say to you, that one of you will betray me.”
B040C026V022	40	26	22	And greatly distressed, each one began to say to him, “˻Surely I am not he, am I˼, Lord?”
B040C026V023	40	26	23	And he answered and said, “The one who dips his hand in the bowl with me—this one will betray me.
B040C026V024	40	26	24	The Son of Man is going just as it is written about him, but woe to that man by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It would be better for him if that man had not been born.”
B040C026V025	40	26	25	And Judas, the one who was betraying him, answered and said, “˻Surely I am not he, am I˼, Rabbi?” He said to him, “You have said it.”
B040C026V026	40	26	26	Now while they were eating Jesus took bread and, after giving thanks, he broke it, and giving it to the disciples, he said, “Take, eat, this is my body.”
B040C026V027	40	26	27	And after taking the cup and giving thanks he gave it to them, saying, “Drink from it, all of you,
B040C026V028	40	26	28	for this is my blood of the covenant which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins.
B040C026V029	40	26	29	But I tell you, from now on I will never drink of this fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new with you in the kingdom of my Father.”
B040C026V030	40	26	30	And after they had sung the hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.
B040C026V031	40	26	31	Then Jesus said to them, “You will all fall away because of me during this night, for it is written,‘I will strike the shepherdand the sheep of the flock will be scattered.’
B040C026V032	40	26	32	But after I am raised, I will go ahead of you into Galilee.”
B040C026V033	40	26	33	But Peter answered and said to him, “If they all fall away because of you, I will never fall away!”
B040C026V034	40	26	34	Jesus said to him, “Truly I say to you that during this night, before the rooster crows, you will deny me three times!”
B040C026V035	40	26	35	Peter said to him, “Even if it is necessary for me to die with you, I will never deny you!” And all the disciples said the same thing.
B040C026V036	40	26	36	Then Jesus went with them to a place called Gethsemane, and he said to the disciples, “Sit here while I go over there and pray.”
B040C026V037	40	26	37	And taking along Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, he began to be distressed and troubled.
B040C026V038	40	26	38	Then he said to them, “My soul is deeply grieved, to the point of death. Remain here and stay awake with me.”
B040C026V039	40	26	39	And going forward a little he fell down on his face, praying and saying, “My Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass from me. Nevertheless, not as I will, but as you will.”
B040C026V040	40	26	40	And he came to the disciples and found them sleeping, and he said to Peter, “So, were you not able to stay awake with me one hour?
B040C026V041	40	26	41	Stay awake and pray that you will not enter into temptation. The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak!”
B040C026V042	40	26	42	Again for the second time he went away and prayed, saying, “My Father, if this cannot pass unless I drink it, your will must be done.”
B040C026V043	40	26	43	And he came again and found them sleeping, ˻for they could not keep their eyes open˼.
B040C026V044	40	26	44	And leaving them again, he went away and prayed for the third time, saying the same thing again.
B040C026V045	40	26	45	Then he came to the disciples and said to them, “Are you still sleeping and resting? Behold, the hour is near, and the Son of Man is being betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B040C026V046	40	26	46	Get up, let us go! Behold, the one who is betraying me is approaching!”
B040C026V047	40	26	47	And while he was still speaking, behold, Judas—one of the twelve—arrived, and with him a large crowd with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and elders of the people.
B040C026V048	40	26	48	Now the one who was betraying him had given them a sign, saying, “The one whom I kiss—he is the one. Arrest him!”
B040C026V049	40	26	49	And he came up to Jesus immediately and said, “Greetings, Rabbi,” and kissed him.
B040C026V050	40	26	50	And Jesus said to him, “Friend, do that for which you have come.” Then they came up and laid hands on Jesus and arrested him.
B040C026V051	40	26	51	And behold, one of those with Jesus extended his hand and drew his sword, and striking the slave of the high priest, cut off his ear.
B040C026V052	40	26	52	Then Jesus said to him, “Put your sword back into its place! For all who take up the sword will die by the sword.
B040C026V053	40	26	53	Or do you think that I cannot call upon my Father, and he would put at my disposal at once more than twelve legions of angels?
B040C026V054	40	26	54	How then would the scriptures be fulfilled that it must happen in this way?”
B040C026V055	40	26	55	At that time Jesus said to the crowds, “Have you come out with swords and clubs, as against a robber, to arrest me? Every day in the temple courts I sat teaching, and you did not arrest me!
B040C026V056	40	26	56	But all this has happened in order that the scriptures of the prophets would be fulfilled.” Then the disciples all abandoned him and fled.
B040C026V057	40	26	57	Now those who had arrested Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders had gathered.
B040C026V058	40	26	58	But Peter was following him from a distance, as far as the courtyard of the high priest. And he went inside and was sitting with the officers to see the outcome.
B040C026V059	40	26	59	Now the chief priests and the whole Sanhedrin were looking for false testimony against Jesus in order that they could put him to death.
B040C026V060	40	26	60	And they did not find it, although many false witnesses came forward. And finally two came forward
B040C026V061	40	26	61	and said, “This man said, ‘I am able to destroy the temple of God and rebuild it within three days.’ ”
B040C026V062	40	26	62	And the high priest stood up and said to him, “Do you reply nothing? What are these people testifying against you?”
B040C026V063	40	26	63	But Jesus was silent. And the high priest said to him, “I put you under oath by the living God, that you tell us if you are the Christ, the Son of God!”
B040C026V064	40	26	64	Jesus said to him, “You have said it. But I tell you, from now on you will see the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of the Power and coming on the clouds of heaven.”
B040C026V065	40	26	65	Then the high priest tore his robes, saying, “He has blasphemed! What further need do we have of witnesses? Behold, you have just now heard the blasphemy!
B040C026V066	40	26	66	What do you think?” And they answered and said, “˻He deserves death˼!”
B040C026V067	40	26	67	Then they spat in his face and struck him with their fists, and they slapped him,
B040C026V068	40	26	68	saying, “Prophesy for us, you Christ! Who is it who hit you?”
B040C026V069	40	26	69	Now Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard, and a female slave came up to him and said, “You also were with Jesus the Galilean.”
B040C026V070	40	26	70	But he denied it in the presence of them all, saying, “I do not know what you mean!”
B040C026V071	40	26	71	And when he went out to the gateway, another female slave saw him and said to those who were there, “This man was with Jesus the Nazarene.”
B040C026V072	40	26	72	And again he denied it with an oath, “I do not know the man!”
B040C026V073	40	26	73	And after a little while those who were standing there came up and said to Peter, “You really are one of them also, because even your accent ˻reveals who you are˼.”
B040C026V074	40	26	74	Then he began to curse and to swear with an oath, “I do not know the man!” And immediately a rooster crowed.
B040C026V075	40	26	75	And Peter remembered the statement Jesus had said, “Before the rooster crows, you will deny me three times,” and he went outside and wept bitterly.
B040C027V001	40	27	1	Now when it was early morning, all the chief priests and the elders of the people took counsel against Jesus in order to put him to death.
B040C027V002	40	27	2	And after tying him up, they led him away and handed him over to Pilate the governor.
B040C027V003	40	27	3	Then when Judas, the one who had betrayed him, saw that he had been condemned, he regretted what he had doneand returned the thirty silver coins to the chief priests and elders,
B040C027V004	40	27	4	saying, “I have sinned by betraying innocent blood!” But they said, “What is that to us? You see to it!”
B040C027V005	40	27	5	And throwing the silver coins into the temple he departed. And he went away and hanged himself.
B040C027V006	40	27	6	But the chief priests took the silver coins and said, “It is not permitted to put them into the temple treasury, because it is ˻blood money˼.”
B040C027V007	40	27	7	And after taking counsel, they purchased ˻with˼ them the Potter’s Field, for a burial place for strangers.
B040C027V008	40	27	8	(For this reason that field has been called the Field of Blood until today.)
B040C027V009	40	27	9	Then what was spoken by the prophet Jeremiah was fulfilled, who said, “And they took the thirty silver coins, the price of the one who had been priced, on whom a price had been set by the sons of Israel,
B040C027V010	40	27	10	and they gave them for the potter’s field, just as the Lord directed me.”
B040C027V011	40	27	11	So Jesus stood before the governor, and the governor asked him, saying, “Are you the king of the Jews?” And Jesus said, “You say so.”
B040C027V012	40	27	12	And ˻when he was being accused˼ by the chief priests and elders he answered nothing.
B040C027V013	40	27	13	Then Pilate said to him, “Do you not hear how many things they are testifying against you?”
B040C027V014	40	27	14	And he did not reply to him, not even with reference to one statement, so that the governor was very astonished.
B040C027V015	40	27	15	Now at each feast, the governor was accustomed to release one prisoner to the crowd—the one whom they wanted.
B040C027V016	40	27	16	And at that time they had a notorious prisoner named Jesus Barabbas.
B040C027V017	40	27	17	So after they had assembled, Pilate said to them, “Whom do you want me to release for you—Jesus Barabbas or Jesus who is called Christ?”
B040C027V018	40	27	18	(For he knew that they had handed him over because of envy.
B040C027V019	40	27	19	And while he was sitting on the judgment seat, his wife sent a message to him, saying, “˻Have nothing to do with that righteous man˼, for I have suffered much as a result of a dream today because of him.”)
B040C027V020	40	27	20	But the chief priests and the elders persuaded the crowds that they should ask for Barabbas and put Jesus to death.
B040C027V021	40	27	21	So the governor answered and said to them, “Which of the two do you want me to release for you?” And they said, “Barabbas!”
B040C027V022	40	27	22	Pilate said to them, “What then should I do with Jesus, the one who is called Christ?” They all said, “Let him be crucified!”
B040C027V023	40	27	23	And he said, “Why? What wrong has he done?” But they began to shout even louder, saying, “Let him be crucified!”
B040C027V024	40	27	24	So Pilate, when he saw that he was accomplishing nothing, but instead an uproar was developing, took water and washed his hands before the crowd, saying, “I am innocent of the blood of this man. You see to it!”
B040C027V025	40	27	25	And all the people answered and said, “His blood be on us and on our children!”
B040C027V026	40	27	26	Then he released Barabbas for them, but after he had Jesus flogged, he handed him over so that he could be crucified.
B040C027V027	40	27	27	Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the governor’s residence and gathered the whole cohort to him.
B040C027V028	40	27	28	And they stripped him and put a scarlet military cloak around him,
B040C027V029	40	27	29	and weaving a crown of thorns, they put it on his head, and put a reed in his right hand. And kneeling down before him, they mocked him, saying, “Hail, king of the Jews!”
B040C027V030	40	27	30	And they spat on him and took the reed and repeatedly struck him on his head.
B040C027V031	40	27	31	And when they had mocked him, they stripped him of the military cloak and put his own clothes on him, and led him away in order to crucify him.
B040C027V032	40	27	32	And as they were going out, they found a man of Cyrene ˻named˼ Simon. They forced this man to carry his cross.
B040C027V033	40	27	33	And when they came to a place called Golgotha (which ˻means Place of a Skull˼),
B040C027V034	40	27	34	they gave him wine mixed with gall to drink, and when he tasted it he did not want to drink it.
B040C027V035	40	27	35	And when they had crucified him, they divided his clothes among themselves by casting lots.
B040C027V036	40	27	36	And they sat down and were watching over him there.
B040C027V037	40	27	37	And they put above his head the charge against him ˻in writing˼: “This is Jesus, the king of the Jews.”
B040C027V038	40	27	38	Then two robbers were crucified with him, one on his right and one on his left.
B040C027V039	40	27	39	And those who passed by reviled him, shaking their heads
B040C027V040	40	27	40	and saying, “The one who would destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days, save yourself! If you are the Son of God, come down from the cross!”
B040C027V041	40	27	41	In the same way also the chief priests, along with the scribes and elders, were mocking him, saying,
B040C027V042	40	27	42	“He saved others; he is not able to save himself! He is the king of Israel! Let him come down now from the cross, and we will believe in him!
B040C027V043	40	27	43	He trusts in God; let him deliver him now if he wants to, because he said, ‘I am the Son of God’!”
B040C027V044	40	27	44	And in the same way even the robbers who were crucified with him were reviling him.
B040C027V045	40	27	45	Now from the sixth hour, darkness came over all the land until the ninth hour.
B040C027V046	40	27	46	And about the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, saying, “Eli, Eli, lema sabachthani?” (that is, “My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?”)
B040C027V047	40	27	47	And some of those who were standing there, when they heard it, said, “This man is summoning Elijah!”
B040C027V048	40	27	48	And immediately one of them ran and took a sponge and filled it with sour wine and put it on a reed and gave it to him to drink.
B040C027V049	40	27	49	But the others said, “Leave him alone! let us see if Elijah is coming to save him.”
B040C027V050	40	27	50	And Jesus cried out again with a loud voice and gave up his spirit.
B040C027V051	40	27	51	And behold, the curtain of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom, and the earth shook and the rocks were split.
B040C027V052	40	27	52	And the tombs were opened, and many bodies of the saints who had fallen asleep were raised,
B040C027V053	40	27	53	and coming out of the tombs after his resurrection, they went into the holy city and appeared to many.
B040C027V054	40	27	54	Now the centurion and those with him who were guarding Jesus, when they saw the earthquake and the things that took place, were extremely frightened, saying, “Truly this man was God’s Son!”
B040C027V055	40	27	55	And there were many women there, observing from a distance, who had followed Jesus from Galilee, serving him,
B040C027V056	40	27	56	among whom were Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the mother of the sons of Zebedee.
B040C027V057	40	27	57	Now when it was evening, a rich man from Arimathea named Joseph came, who also was a disciple of Jesus himself.
B040C027V058	40	27	58	This man approached Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus. Then Pilate ordered it to be given to him.
B040C027V059	40	27	59	And Joseph took the body and wrapped it in a clean linen cloth,
B040C027V060	40	27	60	and placed it in his own new tomb that he had cut in the rock. And he rolled a large stone to the entrance of the tomb and went away.
B040C027V061	40	27	61	Now Mary Magdalene and the other Mary were there, sitting opposite the tomb.
B040C027V062	40	27	62	Now on the next day, which is after the day of preparation, the chief priests and the Pharisees assembled before Pilate,
B040C027V063	40	27	63	saying, “Sir, we remember that while that deceiver was still alive he said, ‘After three days I will rise.’
B040C027V064	40	27	64	Therefore give orders that the tomb be made secure until the third day, lest his disciples come and steal him and tell the people, ‘He has been raised from the dead,’ and the last deception will be worse than the first.”
B040C027V065	40	27	65	Pilate said to them, “You have a guard of soldiers. Go, make it as secure as you know how.”
B040C027V066	40	27	66	So they went with the guard of soldiers and made the tomb secure by sealing the stone.
B040C028V001	40	28	1	Now after the Sabbath, at the dawning on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary came to view the tomb.
B040C028V002	40	28	2	And behold, there was a great earthquake, for an angel of the Lord descended from heaven and came up and rolled away the stone and sat down on it.
B040C028V003	40	28	3	Now his appearance was like lightning and his clothing white as snow.
B040C028V004	40	28	4	And the guards trembled from the fear of him and became like dead men.
B040C028V005	40	28	5	But the angel answered and said to the women, “Do not be afraid, for I know that you are looking for Jesus, who was crucified.
B040C028V006	40	28	6	He is not here, for he has been raised, just as he said. Come, see the place where he was lying.
B040C028V007	40	28	7	And go quickly, tell his disciples, ‘He has been raised from the dead, and behold, he is going ahead of you into Galilee. You will see him there.’ Behold, I have told you.”
B040C028V008	40	28	8	And they departed quickly from the tomb with fear and great joy, and ran to tell his disciples.
B040C028V009	40	28	9	And behold, Jesus met them, saying, “Greetings!” And they came up and took hold of his feet and worshiped him.
B040C028V010	40	28	10	Then Jesus said to them, “Do not be afraid! Go tell my brothers that they should go to Galilee, and there they will see me.”
B040C028V011	40	28	11	And while they were going, behold, some of the guard of soldiers went into the city and reported to the chief priests everything that had happened.
B040C028V012	40	28	12	And after they had assembled with the elders and had taken counsel, they gave a rather large sum of money to the soldiers,
B040C028V013	40	28	13	telling them, “Say ‘His disciples came during the night and stole him while we were sleeping.’
B040C028V014	40	28	14	And if this matter is heard before the governor, we will satisfy him and ˻keep you out of trouble˼.”
B040C028V015	40	28	15	So they took the money and did as they were told, and spread abroad this report among the Jews until this very day.
B040C028V016	40	28	16	So the eleven disciples proceeded to Galilee, to the mountain which Jesus had designated for them.
B040C028V017	40	28	17	And when they saw him, they worshiped him, but some doubted.
B040C028V018	40	28	18	And Jesus approached and spoke to them, saying, “All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.
B040C028V019	40	28	19	Therefore, go and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,
B040C028V020	40	28	20	teaching them to observe everything I have commanded you, and behold, I am with you all the days until the end of the age.”
B041C001V001	41	1	1	The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God.
B041C001V002	41	1	2	Just as it is written in the prophet Isaiah,“Behold, I am sending my messenger before your face,who will prepare your way,
B041C001V003	41	1	3	the voice of one shouting in the wilderness,‘Prepare the way of the Lord,make straight his paths!’ ”
B041C001V004	41	1	4	John was there baptizing in the wilderness and proclaiming a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.
B041C001V005	41	1	5	And all the Judean region and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem went out to him and were being baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	And John was dressed in camel’s hair and a belt made of leather around his waist, and he ate locusts and wild honey.
B041C001V007	41	1	7	And he was preaching, saying, “One who is more powerful than I is coming after me, of whom I am not worthy to bend down and untie the strap of his sandals.
B041C001V008	41	1	8	I baptized you with water, but he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit.”
B041C001V009	41	1	9	And it happened that in those days Jesus came from Nazareth in Galilee and was baptized in the Jordan by John.
B041C001V010	41	1	10	And immediately as he was coming up out of the water, he saw the heavens being split apart and the Spirit descending like a dove on him.
B041C001V011	41	1	11	And a voice came from heaven, “You are my beloved Son; with you I am well pleased.”
B041C001V012	41	1	12	And immediately the Spirit drove him out into the wilderness.
B041C001V013	41	1	13	And he was in the wilderness forty days being tempted by Satan. And he was with the wild animals, and the angels were ministering to him.
B041C001V014	41	1	14	Now after John ˻had been taken into custody˼, Jesus went into Galilee proclaiming the gospel of God
B041C001V015	41	1	15	and saying, “The time is fulfilled and the kingdom of God has come near. Repent and believe in the gospel!”
B041C001V016	41	1	16	And as he was passing by along the Sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew, Simon’s brother, casting a net into the sea (for they were fishermen).
B041C001V017	41	1	17	And Jesus said to them, “˻Follow˼ me and I will make you become fishers of people.”
B041C001V018	41	1	18	And immediately they left their nets and followed him.
B041C001V019	41	1	19	And going on a little farther, he saw James the son of Zebedee and his brother John, and they were in the boat mending the nets.
B041C001V020	41	1	20	And immediately he called them, and they left their father Zebedee in the boat with the hired men and went away after him.
B041C001V021	41	1	21	And they went into Capernaum and immediately on the Sabbath he went into the synagogue and began to teach.
B041C001V022	41	1	22	And they were amazed at his teaching, because he was teaching them like one who had authority, and not like the scribes.
B041C001V023	41	1	23	And so then there was a man in their synagogue with an unclean spirit, and he cried out,
B041C001V024	41	1	24	saying, “˻Leave us alone˼, Jesus the Nazarene! Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are—the Holy One of God!”
B041C001V025	41	1	25	And Jesus rebuked him, saying, “Be silent, and come out of him!”
B041C001V026	41	1	26	And after convulsing him and crying out with a loud voice, the unclean spirit came out of him.
B041C001V027	41	1	27	And they were all amazed, so that they began to discuss with one another, saying, “What is this? A new teaching with authority! He even commands the unclean spirits and they obey him.”
B041C001V028	41	1	28	And the report about him then went out everywhere in the whole surrounding region of Galilee.
B041C001V029	41	1	29	And so then he departed from the synagogue and came into the house of Simon and Andrew with James and John.
B041C001V030	41	1	30	Now Simon’s mother-in-law was lying down, suffering with a fever, and at once they told him about her.
B041C001V031	41	1	31	And he came and raised her up by taking hold of her hand, and the fever left her, and she began to serve them.
B041C001V032	41	1	32	Now when it was evening, when the sun had set, they began bringing to him all those ˻who were sick˼ and those who were demon-possessed.
B041C001V033	41	1	33	And the whole town was gathered together at the door.
B041C001V034	41	1	34	And he healed many ˻who were sick˼ with various diseases and expelled many demons. And he did not permit the demons to speak, because they knew him.
B041C001V035	41	1	35	And getting up early in the morning while it was very dark, he departed and went to a deserted place, and there he was praying.
B041C001V036	41	1	36	And Simon and those who were with him searched diligently for him.
B041C001V037	41	1	37	And they found him and said to him, “Everyone is looking for you!”
B041C001V038	41	1	38	And he said to them, “Let us go elsewhere, into the neighboring rural towns, so that I can preach there also, because I have come out for this very reason.”
B041C001V039	41	1	39	And he went into all Galilee preaching in their synagogues and expelling demons.
B041C001V040	41	1	40	And a leper came to him, entreating him and kneeling down and saying to him, “If you are willing, you are able to make me clean.”
B041C001V041	41	1	41	And having compassion, he stretched out his hand and touched him, and said to him, “I am willing; be made clean.”
B041C001V042	41	1	42	And immediately the leprosy went away from him and he was made clean.
B041C001V043	41	1	43	And warning him sternly, he sent him away at once.
B041C001V044	41	1	44	And he said to him, “See to it that you say nothing to anyone, but go, show yourself to the priest and bring for your cleansing the things which Moses commanded, for a testimony to them.
B041C001V045	41	1	45	But he went out and began to proclaim it freely and to spread abroad the account, so that he was no longer able to enter publicly into a town. But he was staying outside in deserted places, and they were coming to him from all directions.
B041C002V001	41	2	1	And when he entered again into Capernaum after some days, it became known that he was at home.
B041C002V002	41	2	2	And many had gathered, so that there was no longer room, not even at the door, and he was speaking the word to them.
B041C002V003	41	2	3	And they came bringing to him a paralytic, carried by four of them.
B041C002V004	41	2	4	And when they were not able to bring him to him because of the crowd, they removed the roof where he was. And after digging through, they lowered the stretcher on which the paralytic was lying.
B041C002V005	41	2	5	And when Jesus saw their faith, he said to the paralytic, “Child, your sins are forgiven.”
B041C002V006	41	2	6	Now some of the scribes were sitting there and reasoning in their hearts,
B041C002V007	41	2	7	“Why does this man speak like this? He is blaspheming! Who is able to forgive sins except God alone?”
B041C002V008	41	2	8	And immediately Jesus, perceiving in his spirit that they were reasoning like this within themselves, said to them, “Why are you considering these things in your hearts?
B041C002V009	41	2	9	Which is easier to say to the paralytic, ‘Your sins are forgiven,’ or to say ‘Get up and pick up your stretcher and walk’?
B041C002V010	41	2	10	But so that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins,”—he said to the paralytic—
B041C002V011	41	2	11	“I say to you, get up, pick up your stretcher, and go to your home.”
B041C002V012	41	2	12	And he got up and immediately picked up his stretcher and went out in front of them all, so that they were all amazed and glorified God, saying, “We have never seen anything like this!”
