B041C007V013	41	7	13	thus making void the word of God by your tradition that you have handed down, and you do many similar things such as this.”
B041C007V014	41	7	14	And summoning the crowd again, he said to them, “Listen to me, all of you, and understand:
B041C007V015	41	7	15	There is nothing outside of a person that is able to defile him by going into him. But the things that go out of a person are the things that defile a person.”
B041C007V017	41	7	17	And when he entered into the house away from the crowd, his disciples asked him about the parable.
B041C007V018	41	7	18	And he said to them, “So are you also without understanding? Do you not understand that everything that is outside that goes into a person is not able to defile him?
