B041C015V007	41	15	7	And the one named Barabbas was imprisoned with the rebels who had committed murder in the rebellion.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	And the crowd came up and began to ask him to do as he customarily did for them.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	So Pilate answered them, saying, “Do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?”
B041C015V010	41	15	10	(For he realized that the chief priests had handed him over because of envy.)
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests incited the crowd so that he would release for them Barabbas instead.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	So Pilate answered and said to them again, “Then what do you want me to do with the one whom you call the king of the Jews?”
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And they shouted again, “Crucify him!”
B041C015V014	41	15	14	And Pilate said to them, “Why? What evil has he done?” But they shouted even louder, “Crucify him!”
B041C015V015	41	15	15	So Pilate, because he wanted ˻to satisfy˼ the crowd, released for them Barabbas. And after he had Jesus flogged, he handed him over so that he could be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	So the soldiers led him away into the palace (that is, the governor’s residence) and called together the whole cohort.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	And they put a purple cloak on him, and after weaving a crown of thorns they placed it on him.
B041C015V018	41	15	18	And they began to greet him, “Hail, king of the Jews!”
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they repeatedly struck him on the head with a reed, and were spitting on him, and ˻they knelt down˼and did obeisance to him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked him, they stripped him of the purple cloak and put his own clothes on him, and they led him out so that they could crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	And they forced a certain man who was passing by, Simon of Cyrene (the father of Alexander and Rufus), who was coming from the country, to carry his cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they brought him to the place Golgotha (which is translated “Place of a Skull”).
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they attempted to give him wine mixed with myrrh, but he did not take it.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And they crucified him and divided his clothes among themselves by casting lots for them to see who should take what.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	Now it was the third hour when they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And the inscription of the charge against him was written, “The king of the Jews.”
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And with him they crucified two robbers, one on his right and one on his left.
B041C015V029	41	15	29	And those who passed by reviled him, shaking their heads and saying, “Aha! The one who would destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days,
B041C015V030	41	15	30	save yourself by coming down from the cross!”
B041C015V031	41	15	31	In the same way also the chief priests, along with the scribes, were mocking him to one another, saying, “He saved others; he is not able to save himself!
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let the Christ, the king of Israel, come down now from the cross, so that we may see and believe! Even those who were crucified with him were reviling him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	And when the sixth hour came, darkness came over the whole land until the ninth hour.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	And at the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, “Eloi, Eloi, lema sabachthani?” (which is translated, “My God, my God, ˻why˼ have you forsaken me?”)
B041C015V035	41	15	35	And some of the bystanders, when they heard it, said, “Behold, he is summoning Elijah!”
B041C015V036	41	15	36	And someone ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, put it on a reed, and gave it to him to drink, saying, “Leave him alone! Let us see if Elijah is coming to take him down.”
B041C015V037	41	15	37	But Jesus uttered a loud cry and expired.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	And the curtain of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	And when the centurion who was standing opposite him saw that he expired like this, he said, “Truly this man was God’s Son!”
B041C015V040	41	15	40	And there were also women observing from a distance, among whom were Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the younger and Joses, and Salome,
B041C015V041	41	15	41	who used to follow him and serve him when he was in Galilee, and many other women who went up with him to Jerusalem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	And when it was already evening, since it was the day of preparation (that is, the day before the Sabbath),
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathea, a prominent member of the council who was also himself looking forward to the kingdom of God, came acting courageously and went in to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	And Pilate was surprised that he was already dead, and summoning the centurion, asked him whether he had died already.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	And when he learned of it from the centurion, he granted the corpse to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	And after purchasing a linen cloth and taking him down, he wrapped him in the linen cloth and placed him in a tomb that had been cut from the rock. And he rolled a stone over the entrance of the tomb.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	Now Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses saw where he was placed.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	And when the Sabbath was over, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James, and Salome purchased fragrant spices so that they could go and anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And very early in the morning on the first day of the week they came to the tomb after the sun had risen.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	And they were saying to one another, “Who will roll away the stone for us from the entrance of the tomb?”
B041C016V004	41	16	4	And when they looked up, they saw that the stone had been rolled away (for it was very large).
B041C016V005	41	16	5	And as they were going into the tomb, they saw a young man dressed in a white robe sitting on the right side, and they were alarmed.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	But he said to them, “Do not be alarmed. You are looking for Jesus the Nazarene who was crucified. He has been raised, he is not here! See the place where they laid him!
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go, tell his disciples and Peter that he is going ahead of you to Galilee. You will see him there, just as he told you.”
B041C016V008	41	16	8	And they went out and fled from the tomb, because trembling and amazement had seized them. And they said nothing to anyone, because they were afraid.〚So they promptly reported all the things they had been commanded to those around Peter. And after these things, Jesus himself also sent out through them from the east even as far as the west the holy and imperishable proclamation of eternal salvation. Amen.〛〚
B041C016V009	41	16	9	Now early on the first day of the week, after he rose, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, from whom he had expelled seven demons.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	She went out and announced it to those who were with him while they were mourning and weeping.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	And those, when they heard that he was alive and had been seen by her, refused to believe it.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	And after these things, he appeared in a different form to two of them as they were walking, while they were going out into the countryside.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	And these went and reported it to the others, and they did not believe them.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	And later, while they were reclining at table, he appeared to the eleven. And he reprimanded their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they did not believe those who had seen him after he had been raised.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And he said to them, “Go into all the world and preach the gospel to all creation.
B041C016V016	41	16	16	The one who believes and is baptized will be saved, but the one who refuses to believe will be condemned.
B041C016V017	41	16	17	And these signs will accompany those who believe: in my name they will expel demons, they will speak in new tongues,
B041C016V018	41	16	18	and they will pick up snakes with their hands. And if they drink any deadly poison it will never hurt them; they will lay hands on the sick and ˻they will get˼ well.”
B041C016V019	41	16	19	Then the Lord Jesus, after he had spoken to them, was taken up into heaven and sat down at the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	And they went out and proclaimed everywhere, while the Lord was working together with them and confirming the message through the accompanying signs.〛
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Since many have attempted to compile an account concerning the events that have been fulfilled among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as those who were eyewitnesses and servants of the word from the beginning passed on to us,
B042C001V003	42	1	3	it seemed best to me also—because I have followed all things carefully from the beginning—to write them down in orderly sequence for you, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	so that you may know the certainty concerning the things about which you were taught.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	It happened that in the days of Herod, king of Judea, there was a certain priest, Zechariah by name, of the division of Abijah. And ˻he had a wife˼ from the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	And they were both righteous in the sight of God, living blamelessly in all the commandments and regulations of the Lord.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	And ˻they did not have˼ a child, because Elizabeth was barren. And they were both advanced ˻in years˼.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	And it happened that while he was serving as priest before God in the order of his division,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	according to the custom of the priesthood he was chosen by lot to enter into the temple of the Lord to burn incense.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And the whole crowd of the people were praying outside at the hour of the incense offering.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	And an angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing at the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And Zechariah was terrified when he saw the angel, and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him,“Do not be afraid, Zechariah,because your prayer has been heard,and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son,and you will call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	And ˻you will experience joy and exultation˼,and many will rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he will be great in the sight of the Lord,and he must never drink wine or beer,and he will be filled with the Holy Spiritwhile he is still in his mother’s womb.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And he will turn many of the sons of Israelto the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	And he will go on before himin the spirit and power of Elijah,to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children,and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous,to prepare for the Lord a people made ready.”
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zechariah said to the angel, “By what will I know this? For I am an old man, and my wife is advanced ˻in years˼!”
B042C001V019	42	1	19	And the angel answered and said to him, “I am Gabriel, who stands in the presence of God, and I was sent to speak to you and to announce to you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	And behold, you will be silent and not able to speak until the day these things take place, ˻because˼ you did not believe my words, which will be fulfilled in their time.”
B042C001V021	42	1	21	And the people were waiting for Zechariah, and began to wonder when he was delayed in the temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	And when he came out he was not able to speak to them, and they realized that he had seen a vision in the temple. And he kept making signs to them, and remained unable to speak.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And it happened that when the days of his service came to an end, he went away to his home.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	Now after these days, his wife Elizabeth conceived, and she kept herself in seclusion for five months, saying,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	“Thus the Lord has done for me in the days in which he has concerned himself with me, to take away my disgrace among people.”
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Now in the sixth month, the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a town of Galilee ˻named˼ Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a virgin legally promised in marriage to a man ˻named˼ Joseph of the house of David. And the name of the virgin was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	And he came to her and said, “Greetings, favored one! The Lord is with you.”
B042C001V029	42	1	29	But she was greatly perplexed at the statement, and was pondering what sort of greeting this might be.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	And the angel said to her,“Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And behold, you will conceive in the womb and will give birth to a son,and you will call his name Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	This one will be great, and he will be called the Son of the Most High,and the Lord God will give him the throne of his father David.
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And he will reign over the house of Jacob ˻forever˼,and of his kingdom there will be no end.
B042C001V034	42	1	34	And Mary said to the angel, “How will this be, since I have not had sexual relations with a man?”
B042C001V035	42	1	35	And the angel answered and said to her,“The Holy Spirit will come upon you,and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.Therefore also the one to be born will be called holy, the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And behold, your relative Elizabeth—she also has conceived a son in her old age, and this is the sixth month for her who was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For ˻nothing will be impossible with God˼.”
B042C001V038	42	1	38	So Mary said, “Behold, the Lord’s female slave! May it happen to me according to your word.” And the angel departed from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	Now in those days Mary set out and traveled with haste into the hill country, to a town of Judah,
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and entered into the house of Zechariah, and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And it happened that when Elizabeth heard the greeting of Mary, the baby in her womb leaped and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.
B042C001V042	42	1	42	And she cried out with a loud shout and said,“Blessed are you among women,and blessed is the fruit of your womb!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	And why is this granted to me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For behold, when the sound of your greeting came to my ears, the baby in my womb leaped for joy!
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And blessed is she who believed that there will be a fulfillment to what was spoken to her from the Lord!”
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said,“My soul exalts the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	and my spirit has rejoiced greatly in God my Savior,
B042C001V048	42	1	48	because he has looked upon the humble state of his female slave,for behold, from now on all generations will consider me blessed,
B042C001V049	42	1	49	because the Mighty One has done great things for me,and holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And his mercy is for generation after generationto those who fear him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He has done a mighty deed with his arm;he has dispersed the proud in the thoughts of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He has brought down rulers from their thrones,and has exalted the lowly.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	He has filled those who are hungry with good things,and those who are rich he has sent away empty-handed.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He has helped Israel his servant,remembering his mercy,
B042C001V055	42	1	55	just as he spoke to our fathers,to Abraham and to his descendants ˻forever˼.”
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mary stayed with her about three months, and returned to her home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now the time came for Elizabeth that she should give birth, and she gave birth to a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	And her neighbors and relatives heard that ˻the Lord had shown his great mercy to her˼, and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And it happened that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and they were wanting to name him ˻after˼ his father Zechariah.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	And his mother answered and said, “No, but he will be named John.”
B042C001V061	42	1	61	And they said to her, “There is no one of your relatives who is called by this name.”
B042C001V062	42	1	62	So they made signs to his father asking what he wanted him to be named,
B042C001V063	42	1	63	and he asked for a writing tablet and wrote, saying, “John is his name.” And they were all astonished.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	And his mouth and his tongue were opened immediately, and he began to speak, praising God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And fear came on all those who lived near them, and in all the hill country of Judea all these events were discussed.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all those who heard kept these things in their hearts, saying, “What then will this child be? For indeed the hand of the Lord was with him!”
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied, saying,
B042C001V068	42	1	68	“Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,because he has visited to help and ˻has redeemed˼ his people,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	and has raised up a horn of salvation for usin the house of his servant David,
B042C001V070	42	1	70	just as he spoke through the mouth of his holy prophets from earliest times—
B042C001V071	42	1	71	salvation from our enemies and from the hand of all those who hate us,
B042C001V072	42	1	72	to show mercy to our fathersand to remember his holy covenant,
B042C001V073	42	1	73	the oath that he swore to Abraham our father,to grant us
B042C001V074	42	1	74	that we, being rescued from the hand of our enemies,could serve him without fear
B042C001V075	42	1	75	in holiness and righteousnessbefore him all our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And so you, child, will be called the prophet of the Most High,for you will go on before the Lord to prepare his ways,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	to give knowledge of salvation to his peopleby the forgiveness of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	because of the merciful compassion of our Godby which the dawn will visit to help us from on high,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	to give light to those who sit in darkness and in the shadow of death,to direct our feet into the way of peace.”
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child kept growing and becoming strong in spirit, and was in the wilderness until the day of his public appearance to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	Now it happened that in those days a decree went out from Caesar Augustus to register all the empire.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	(This first registration took place when Quirinius was governor of Syria.)
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And everyone went to be registered, each one to his own town.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	So Joseph also went up from Galilee, from the town of Nazareth, to Judea, to the city of David which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and family line of David,
B042C002V005	42	2	5	to be registered together with Mary, who was legally promised in marriage to him and was pregnant.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	And it happened that while they were there, ˻the time came˼ for her to give birth.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she gave birth to her firstborn son, and wrapped him in strips of cloth and laid him in a manger, because there was no place for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	And there were shepherds in the same region, living out of doors and keeping watch, guarding over their flock by night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	And an angel of the Lord stood near them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and ˻they were terribly frightened˼.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	And the angel said to them, “Do not be afraid, for behold, I bring good news to you of great joy which will be for all the people:
B042C002V011	42	2	11	that today a Savior, who is Christ the Lord, was born for you in the city of David.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this will be the sign for you: you will find the baby wrapped in strips of cloth and lying in a manger.”
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly army, praising God and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	“Glory to God in the highest,and on earth peaceamong people ˻with whom he is pleased˼!”
B042C002V015	42	2	15	And it happened that when the angels had departed from them into heaven, the shepherds began to say to one another, “Let us go now to Bethlehem and see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has revealed to us!”
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And they went hurrying and found both Mary and Joseph, and the baby who was lying in the manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	And when they saw it, they made known the statement that had been told to them about this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all who heard it were astonished concerning what had been said to them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary treasured up all these words, pondering them in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all that they had heard and seen, just as it had been told to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	And when eight days were completed ˻so that he could be circumcised˼, he was named Jesus, his name thathe was called by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when the days of their purification were completed according to the law of Moses, they brought him up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord
B042C002V023	42	2	23	(just as it is written in the law of the Lord, “Every male that opens the womb will be called holy to the Lord”)
B042C002V024	42	2	24	and to offer a sacrifice according to what was stated in the law of the Lord, “a pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons.”
B042C002V025	42	2	25	And behold, there was a man in Jerusalem ˻whose name was˼ Simeon, and this man was righteous and devout, looking forward to the consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	And it had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he would not see death before he would see the Lord’s Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	And he came in the Spirit into the temple, and when the parents brought in the child Jesus so that they could do for him according to what was customary under the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	he took him in his arms and praised God and said,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	“Now dismiss your slave in peace, Lord,according to your word.
B042C002V030	42	2	30	For my eyes have seen your salvation
B042C002V031	42	2	31	that you have prepared in the presence of all the peoples,
B042C002V032	42	2	32	a light for revelation to the Gentiles,and glory to your people Israel.”
B042C002V033	42	2	33	And his father and mother were astonished at what was said about him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	And Simeon blessed them and said to his mother Mary, “Behold, this child is appointed for the fall and rise of many in Israel, and for a sign that is opposed—
B042C002V035	42	2	35	and a sword will pierce your own soul also, so that the thoughts of many hearts will be revealed!”
B042C002V036	42	2	36	And there was a prophetess, Anna the daughter of Phanuel of the tribe of Asher (she was advanced ˻in years˼, having lived with her husband seven years ˻after her marriage˼,
B042C002V037	42	2	37	and herself as a widow up to eighty-four years) who did not depart from the temple with fastings and prayers, serving night and day.
B042C002V038	42	2	38	And at that same hour she approached and began to give thanks to God, and to speak about him to all those who were waiting for the redemption of Jerusalem.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	And when they had completed everything according to the law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee, to their own town of Nazareth.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	And the child was growing and becoming strong, filled with wisdom, and the favor of God was upon him.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	And his parents went every year to Jerusalem for the feast of the Passover.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	And when he was twelve years old, they went up according to the custom of the feast.
B042C002V043	42	2	43	And after the days were completed, while they were returning, the boy Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem. And his parents did not know it,
B042C002V044	42	2	44	but believing him to be in the group of travelers, they went a day’s journey. And they began searching for him among their relatives and their acquantances,
B042C002V045	42	2	45	and when they did not find him, they returned to Jerusalem to search for him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	And it happened that after three days they found him in the temple courts, sitting in the midst of the teachers and listening to them and asking them questions.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	And all who heard him were amazed at his insight and his answers.
B042C002V048	42	2	48	And when they saw him, they were astounded and his mother said to him, “Child, why have you done this to us? Look, your father and I have been searching for you anxiously!”
B042C002V049	42	2	49	And he said to them, “˻Why˼ were you searching for me? Did you not know that it was necessary for me to be in the house of my Father?”
B042C002V050	42	2	50	And they did not understand the statement that he spoke to them.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	And he went down with them and came to Nazareth, and was submitting to them. And his mother treasured all these things in her heart.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	And Jesus was advancing in wisdom and stature and in favor with God and with people.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, when Pontius Pilate was governor of Judea, and Herod was tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip was tetrarch of the region of Iturea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias was tetrarch of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	in the time of the high priest Annas and Caiaphas, the word of God came to John the son of Zechariah in the wilderness.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	And he went into all the surrounding region of the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins,
B042C003V004	42	3	4	as it is written in the book of the words of the prophet Isaiah,“The voice of one crying out in the wilderness,‘Prepare the way of the Lord,make his paths straight!
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Every valley will be filled,and every mountain and hill will be leveled,and the crooked will become straight,and the rough road will become smooth,
B042C003V006	42	3	6	and all flesh will see the salvation of God.’ ”
