B042C023V008	42	23	8	And when Herod saw Jesus, he was very glad, for he had been wanting to see him for a long time, because he had heard about him and was hoping to see some miracle performed by him.
B042C023V009	42	23	9	So he questioned him ˻at considerable length˼, but he answered nothing to him.
B042C023V010	42	23	10	And the chief priests and the scribes were standing there vehemently accusing him.
B042C023V011	42	23	11	And Herod with his soldiers also treated him with contempt, and after mocking himand dressing himin glistening clothing, he sent him back to Pilate.
B042C023V012	42	23	12	And both Herod and Pilate became friends with one another on that same day, ˻for they had previously been enemies of one another˼.
B042C023V013	42	23	13	So Pilate called together the chief priests and the rulers and the people
B042C023V014	42	23	14	and said to them, “You brought me this man as one who was misleading the people, and behold, when I examined him before you, I found nothing in this man as basis for the accusation which ˻you are making˼ against him.
B042C023V015	42	23	15	But neither did Herod, because he sent him back to us. And behold, nothing deserving death ˻has been done˼ by him.
B042C023V016	42	23	16	Therefore I will punish him and release him.”
B042C023V018	42	23	18	But they all cried out in unison, saying, “Take this man away, and release for us Barabbas!”
B042C023V019	42	23	19	(who had been thrown in prison because of a certain insurrection that had taken place in the city, and for murder).
B042C023V020	42	23	20	And Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, addressed them again,
B042C023V021	42	23	21	but they kept crying out, saying, “Crucify! Crucify him!”
B042C023V022	42	23	22	So he said to them a third time, “Why? What wrong has this man done? I found no basis for an accusation ˻deserving death˼ in him. Therefore I will punish him and release him.”
B042C023V023	42	23	23	But they were urgent, demanding with loud cries that he be crucified. And their cries prevailed.
B042C023V024	42	23	24	And Pilate decided that their demand should be granted.
B042C023V025	42	23	25	And he released the one who had been thrown into prison because of insurrection and murder, whom they were asking for, but Jesus he handed over to their will.
B042C023V026	42	23	26	And as they led him away, they seized Simon, a certain man of Cyrene, who was coming from the country, and placed the cross on him, to carry it behind Jesus.
B042C023V027	42	23	27	And a great crowd of the people were following him, and of women who were mourning and lamenting him.
B042C023V028	42	23	28	But turning to them, Jesus said, “Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children!
B042C023V029	42	23	29	For behold, days are coming in which they will say, ‘Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that did not give birth, and the breasts that did not nurse!’
B042C023V030	42	23	30	Then they will begin to say to the mountains, ‘Fall on us!’ and to the hills, ‘Cover us!’
B042C023V031	42	23	31	For if they do these things˻when the wood is green˼, what will happen ˻when it is dry˼?”
B042C023V032	42	23	32	And two other criminals were also led away to be executed with him.
B042C023V033	42	23	33	And when they came to the place that is called “The Skull,” there they crucified him, and the criminals, the one on his right and the other on his left.
B042C023V034	42	23	34	〚But Jesus said, “Father, forgive them, for they do not know what they are doing.”〛 And they cast lots to divide his clothes.
B042C023V035	42	23	35	And the people stood there watching, but the rulers also ridiculed him, saying, “He saved others; let him save himself, if this man is the Christ of God, the Chosen One!”
B042C023V036	42	23	36	And the soldiers also mocked him, coming up and offering him sour wine
B042C023V037	42	23	37	and saying, “If you are the king of the Jews, save yourself!”
B042C023V038	42	23	38	And there was also an inscription over him, “This is the king of the Jews.”
B042C023V039	42	23	39	And one of the criminals who were hanged there reviled him, saying, “Are you not the Christ? Save yourself—and us!”
B042C023V040	42	23	40	But the other answered and rebuked him, saying, “Do you not even fear God, because you are undergoing the same condemnation?
B042C023V041	42	23	41	And we indeed justly, for we are receiving ˻what we deserve˼for what we have done. But this man has done nothing wrong!”
B042C023V042	42	23	42	And he said, “Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom!”
B042C023V043	42	23	43	And he said to him, “Truly I say to you, today you will be with me in paradise.”
B042C023V044	42	23	44	And by this time it was about the sixth hour, and darkness came over the whole land until the ninth hour
B042C023V045	42	23	45	becausethe light of the sun failed. And the curtain of the temple was torn apart down the middle.
B042C023V046	42	23	46	And Jesus, calling out with a loud voice, said, “Father, into your hands I entrust my spirit!” And after he said this, he expired.
B042C023V047	42	23	47	Now when the centurion saw what had happened, he began to praise God, saying, “Certainly this man was righteous!”
B042C023V048	42	23	48	And all the crowds that had come together for this spectacle, when they saw the things that had happened, returned home beating their breasts.
B042C023V049	42	23	49	And all his acquaintances, and the women who had followed him from Galilee who saw these things, stood at a distance.
B042C023V050	42	23	50	And behold, a man ˻named˼ Joseph, who was a member of the council and a good and righteous man
B042C023V051	42	23	51	(this man was not consenting to their plan and deed), from Arimathea, ˻a Judean town˼, who was looking forward to the kingdom of God.
B042C023V052	42	23	52	This man approached Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
B042C023V053	42	23	53	And he took it down and wrapped it in a linen cloth and placed him in a tomb cut into the rock where no one had ever been placed.
B042C023V054	42	23	54	And it was the day of preparation, and the Sabbath was drawing near.
B042C023V055	42	23	55	And the women who had been accompanying him from Galilee followed and saw the tomb and how his body was placed.
B042C023V056	42	23	56	And they returned and prepared fragrant spices and perfumes, and on the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment.
B042C024V001	42	24	1	Now on the first day of the week, at very early dawn, they came back to the tomb bringing the fragrant spices which they had prepared.
B042C024V002	42	24	2	And they found the stone had been rolled away from the tomb,
B042C024V003	42	24	3	but when they went in, they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	And it happened that while they were perplexed about this, behold, two men in gleaming clothing stood near them.
B042C024V005	42	24	5	And as they were terrified and bowed their faces to the ground, they said to them, “Why are you looking for the living among the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	He is not here, but has been raised! Remember how he spoke to you while he was still in Galilee,
B042C024V007	42	24	7	saying that the Son of Man must be delivered into the hands of men who are sinners, and be crucified, and on the third day rise?”
B042C024V008	42	24	8	And they remembered his words,
B042C024V009	42	24	9	and when they returned from the tomb, they reported all these things to the eleven and to all the rest.
B042C024V010	42	24	10	Now Mary Magdalene and Joanna and Mary the mother of James and the others with them were telling these things to the apostles.
B042C024V011	42	24	11	And these words appeared to them as nonsense, and they refused to believe them.
B042C024V012	42	24	12	But Peter got up and ran to the tomb, and bending over to look, he saw only the strips of linen cloth, and he went away to his home wondering what had happened.
B042C024V013	42	24	13	And behold, on that same day, two of them were traveling to a village ˻named˼ Emmaus that was sixty stadia distant from Jerusalem,
B042C024V014	42	24	14	and they were conversing with one another about all these things that had happened.
B042C024V015	42	24	15	And it happened that while they were conversing, and discussing, Jesus himself also approached and began to go along with them,
B042C024V016	42	24	16	but their eyes were prevented from recognizing him.
B042C024V017	42	24	17	And he said to them, “What are these matters that you are discussing with one another as you are walking along?” And they stood still, looking sad.
B042C024V018	42	24	18	And one of them, ˻named˼ Cleopas, answered and said to him, “Are you the only one living near Jerusalem and not knowing the things that have happened in it in these days?”
B042C024V019	42	24	19	And he said to them, “What things?” So they said to him, “The things concerning Jesus the Nazarene, a man who was a prophet, powerful in deed and word before God and all the people,
B042C024V020	42	24	20	and how our chief priests and rulers handed him over to a sentence of death, and crucified him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	But we were hoping that he was the one who was going to redeem Israel. But in addition to all these things, this is the third day ˻since˼ these things took place.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	But also some women from among us astonished us, who were at the tomb early in the morning,
B042C024V023	42	24	23	and when they did not find his body, they came back saying they had seen even a vision of angels, who said that he was alive!
B042C024V024	42	24	24	And some of those with us went out to the tomb and found it like this, just as the women had also said, but him they did not see.”
B042C024V025	42	24	25	And he said to them, “O foolish and slow in heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken!
B042C024V026	42	24	26	Was it not necessary that the Christ suffer these things and enter into his glory?”
B042C024V027	42	24	27	And beginning from Moses and from all the prophets, he interpreted to them the things concerning himself in all the scriptures.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	And they drew near to the village where they were going, and he acted as though he was going farther.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	And they urged him strongly, saying, “Stay with us, because it is getting toward evening, and by this time the day is far spent.” And he went in to stay with them.
B042C024V030	42	24	30	And it happened that when he reclined at the table with them, he took the bread and gave thanks, and after breaking it, he gave it to them.
B042C024V031	42	24	31	And their eyes were opened, and they recognized him, and he became invisible to them.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	And they said to one another, “Were not our hearts burning within us while he was speaking with us on the road, while he was explaining the scriptures to us?”
B042C024V033	42	24	33	And they got up that same hour and returned to Jerusalem and found the eleven and those with them assembled,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	saying, “The Lord has really been raised, and has appeared to Simon!”
B042C024V035	42	24	35	And they began describing ˻what happened˼ on the road, and how he was recognized by them in the breaking of the bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	And while they were saying these things, he himself stood there among them and said to them, “Peace to you!”
B042C024V037	42	24	37	But they were startled and became terrified, and thought they had seen a ghost.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	And he said to them, “Why are you frightened? And for what reason do doubts arise in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	Look at my hands and my feet, that I am I myself! Touch me and see, because a ghost does not have flesh and bones, as ˻you see that I have˼.”
B042C024V040	42	24	40	And when he had said this, he showed them his hands and his feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	And while they were still disbelieving because of joy and were marveling, he said to them, “Do you have anything ˻to eat˼ here?”
B042C024V042	42	24	42	So they gave him a piece of broiled fish,
B042C024V043	42	24	43	and he took itand ate it in front of them.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	And he said to them, “These are my words that I spoke to you while I was still with you, that everything that is written about me in the law of Moses and the prophets and psalms must be fulfilled.”
B042C024V045	42	24	45	Then he opened their minds to understand the scriptures,
B042C024V046	42	24	46	and said to them, “Thus it is written that the Christ would suffer and would rise from the dead on the third day,
B042C024V047	42	24	47	and repentance for the forgiveness of sins would be proclaimed in his name to all the nations, beginning from Jerusalem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	You are witnesses of these things.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	And behold, I am sending what was promised by my Father upon you, but you stay in the city until you are clothed with power from on high.”
B042C024V050	42	24	50	And he led them out as far as Bethany, and lifting up his hands, he blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	And it happened that while he was blessing them, he parted from them and was taken up into heaven.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	And they worshiped him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy.
B042C024V053	42	24	53	And they were ˻continually˼ in the temple courts praising God.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	This one was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things came into being through him, and apart from him not one thing came into being that has come into being.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life, and the life was the light of humanity.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shines in the darkness, and the darkness did not overcome it.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	A man came, sent from God, ˻whose name was˼ John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	This one came for a witness, in order that he could testify about the light, so that all would believe through him.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	That one was not the light, but came in order that he could testify about the light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	The true light, who gives light to every person, was coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world came into being through him, and the world did not recognize him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own things, and his own people did not receive him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But as many as received him—to those who believe in his name—he gave to them authority to become children of God,
B043C001V013	43	1	13	who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of a husband, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word became flesh and took up residence among us, and we saw his glory, glory as of the one and only from the Father, full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John testified about him and cried out, saying, “This one was he about whom I said, ‘The one who comes after me is ahead of me, because he existed before me.’ ”
B043C001V016	43	1	16	For from his fullness we have all received, and grace after grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the law was given through Moses; grace and truth came about through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one has seen God at any time; the one and only, God, the one who is in the bosom of the Father—that one has made him known.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	And this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent to him priests and Levites from Jerusalem so that they could ask him, “Who are you?”
B043C001V020	43	1	20	And he confessed—and he did not deny, and confessed—“I am not the Christ!”
B043C001V021	43	1	21	And they asked him, “Then who are you? Are you Elijah?” And he said, “I am not!” “Are you the Prophet?” And he answered, “No!”
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then they said to him, “Who are you, so that we can give an answer to those who sent us? What do you say about yourself?”
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said,“I am ‘the voice of one crying out in the wilderness,“Make straight the way of the Lord,” ’just as Isaiah the prophet said.”
B043C001V024	43	1	24	(And they had been sent from the Pharisees.)
B043C001V025	43	1	25	And they asked him and said to him, “Why then are you baptizing, if you are not the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?”
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John answered them, saying, “I baptize with water. In your midst stands one whom you do not know—
B043C001V027	43	1	27	the one who comes after me, of whom I am not worthy ˻to untie˼ the strap of his sandal!”
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things took place in Bethany on the other side of the Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	On the next day he saw Jesus coming to him and said, “Look! The Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world!
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This one is the one about whom I said, ‘After me is coming a man who is ahead of me, because he existed before me.’
B043C001V031	43	1	31	And I did not know him, but in order that he could be revealed to Israel, because of this I came baptizing with water.”
B043C001V032	43	1	32	And John testified, saying, “I have seen the Spirit descending like a dove from heaven and remaining upon him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	And I did not know him, but the one who sent me to baptize with water, that one said to me, ‘The one upon whom you see the Spirit descending and remaining upon him—this one is the one who baptizes with the Holy Spirit.’
B043C001V034	43	1	34	And I have seen and testify that this one is the Son of God.
B043C001V035	43	1	35	On the next day again John was standing there, and two of his disciples,
B043C001V036	43	1	36	and looking at Jesus as he was walking by, he said, “Look! The Lamb of God!”
B043C001V037	43	1	37	And the two disciples heard him speaking, and they followed Jesus.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	And Jesus, turning around and seeing them following him, said to them, “What do you seek?” And they said to him, “Rabbi” (which means when translated “Teacher”), “where are you staying?”
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He said to them, “Come and you will see!” So they came and saw where he was staying, and they stayed with him that day (it was about the tenth hour).
B043C001V040	43	1	40	Andrew, the brother of Simon Peter, was one of the two who heard John and followed him.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	This one first found his own brother Simon and said to him, “We have found the Messiah!” (which is translated “Christ”).
B043C001V042	43	1	42	He brought him to Jesus. Looking at him, Jesus said, “You are Simon the son of John. You will be called Cephas” (which is interpreted “Peter”).
B043C001V043	43	1	43	On the next day he wanted to depart for Galilee, and he found Philip. And Jesus said to him, “Follow me!”
B043C001V044	43	1	44	(Now Philip was from Bethsaida, the town of Andrew and Peter.)
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Philip found Nathanael and said to him, “We have found the one whom Moses wrote about in the law, and the prophets wrote about—Jesus son of Joseph from Nazareth!”
B043C001V046	43	1	46	And Nathanael said to him, “Can anything good come out of Nazareth?” Philip said to him, “Come and see!”
B043C001V047	43	1	47	Jesus saw Nathanael coming toward him and said about him, “Look! ˻A true Israelite˼ in whom is no deceit!”
B043C001V048	43	1	48	Nathanael said to him, “From where do you know me?” Jesus answered and said to him, “Before Philip called you, when you were under the fig tree, I saw you.”
B043C001V049	43	1	49	Nathanael answered him, “Rabbi, you are the Son of God! You are the king of Israel!”
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jesus answered and said to him, “Because I said to you that I saw you under the fig tree, do you believe? You will see greater things than these!”
B043C001V051	43	1	51	And he said to him, “Truly, truly I say to all of you, you will see heaven opened and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the Son of Man.”
B043C002V001	43	2	1	And on the third day, there was a wedding at Cana in Galilee, and the mother of Jesus was there.
B043C002V002	43	2	2	And both Jesus and his disciples were invited to the wedding.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	And when the wine ran out, the mother of Jesus said to him, “They have no wine!”
B043C002V004	43	2	4	And Jesus said to her, “What ˻does your concern have to do with me˼, woman? My hour has not yet come.”
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother said to the servants, “Whatever he says to you, do it!”
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now six stone water jars were set there, in accordance with the ceremonial cleansing of the Jews, each holding two or three measures.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jesus said to them, “Fill the water jars with water.” And they filled them to the brim.
B043C002V008	43	2	8	And he said to them, “Now draw some out and take it to the head steward. So they took it.
B043C002V009	43	2	9	Now when the head steward tasted the water which had become wine and did not know where it was from—but the servants who had drawn the water knew—the head steward summoned the bridegroom
B043C002V010	43	2	10	and said to him, “˻Everyone˼ serves the good wine first, and whenever they are drunk, the inferior. You have kept the good wine until now!”
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This beginning of signs Jesus performed at Cana in Galilee, and revealed his glory, and his disciples believed in him.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	After this he went down to Capernaum, and his mother and his brothers and his disciples, and they stayed there ˻a few˼ days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	And the Passover of the Jews was near, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C002V014	43	2	14	And he found in the temple courts those who were selling oxen and sheep and doves, and the money changers seated.
B043C002V015	43	2	15	And he made a whip of cords and drove them all out of the temple courts, both the sheep and the oxen, and he poured out the coins of the money changers and overturned their tables.
B043C002V016	43	2	16	And to the ones selling the doves he said, “Take these things away from here! Do not make my Father’s house ˻a marketplace˼!”
B043C002V017	43	2	17	His disciples remembered that it is written, “Zeal for your house will consume me.”
B043C002V018	43	2	18	So the Jews answered and said to him, “What sign do you show to us, because you are doing these things?”
B043C002V019	43	2	19	Jesus answered and said to them, “Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up!”
B043C002V020	43	2	20	Then the Jews said, “This temple has been under construction forty-six years, and will you raise it up in three days?”
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But he was speaking about the temple of his body.
B043C002V022	43	2	22	So when he was raised from the dead, his disciples remembered that he had said this, and they believed the scripture and the saying that Jesus had spoken.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	Now while he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, during the feast, many believed in his name because they saw his signs which he was doing.
B043C002V024	43	2	24	But Jesus himself did not entrust himself to them, because he knew all people,
B043C002V025	43	2	25	and because he did not ˻need˼ anyone ˻to testify˼ about man, for he himself knew what was in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	Now there was a man of the Pharisees ˻whose name was˼ Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.
B043C003V002	43	3	2	This man came to him at night and said to him, “Rabbi, we know that you are a teacher who has come from God, for no one is able to perform these signs that you are performing unless God were with him.”
B043C003V003	43	3	3	Jesus answered and said to him, “Truly, truly I say to you, unless someone is born from above, he is not able to see the kingdom of God.”
B043C003V004	43	3	4	Nicodemus said to him, “How can a man be born when he is an old man? He is not able to enter into his mother’s womb for the second time and be born, can he?”
B043C003V005	43	3	5	Jesus answered, “Truly, truly I say to you, unless someone is born of water and spirit, he is not able to enter into the kingdom of God.
B043C003V006	43	3	6	What is born of the flesh is flesh, and what is born of the Spirit is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Do not be astonished that I said to you, ‘It is necessary for you to be born from above.’
B043C003V008	43	3	8	The wind blows wherever it wishes, and you hear the sound of it, but you do not know where it comes from and where it is going. So is everyone who is born of the Spirit.”
B043C003V009	43	3	9	Nicodemus answered and said to him, “How can these things be?”
B043C003V010	43	3	10	Jesus answered and said to him, “Are you the teacher of Israel, and you do not understand these things?
B043C003V011	43	3	11	Truly, truly I say to you, we speak what we know, and we testify about what we have seen, and you do not accept our testimony!
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If I tell you earthly things and you do not believe, how will you believe if I tell you heavenly things?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	And no one has ascended into heaven except the one who descended from heaven—the Son of Man.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	And just as Moses lifted up the snake in the wilderness, thus it is necessary that the Son of Man be lifted up,
B043C003V015	43	3	15	so that everyone who believes in him will have eternal life.”
B043C003V016	43	3	16	For in this way God loved the world, so that he gave his one and only Son, in order that everyone who believes in him will not perish, but will have eternal life.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For God did not send his Son into the world in order that he should judge the world, but in order that the world should be saved through him.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	The one who believes in him is not judged, but the one who does not believe has already been judged, because he has not believed in the name of the one and only Son of God.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	And this is the judgment: that the light has come into the world, and people loved the darkness rather than the light, because their deeds were evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For everyone who practices evil hates the light and does not come to the light, lest his deeds be exposed.
B043C003V021	43	3	21	But the one who practices the truth comes to the light, in order that his deeds may be revealed, that they are done in God.
B043C003V022	43	3	22	After these things Jesus and his disciples came into Judean territory, and there he spent time with them and was baptizing.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	Now John was also baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because water was plentiful there, and they were coming and were being baptized.
B043C003V024	43	3	24	(For John had not yet been thrown into prison.)
B043C003V025	43	3	25	So a dispute occurred on the part of John’s disciples with a Jew concerning purification.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	And they came to John and said to him, “Rabbi, he who was with you on the other side of the Jordan, about whom you testified—look, this one is baptizing, and all are coming to him!”
B043C003V027	43	3	27	John answered and said, “A man can receive not one thing unless it is granted to him from heaven!
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You yourselves testify about me that I said, ‘I am not the Christ, but I am sent before that one.’
B043C003V029	43	3	29	The one who has the bride is the bridegroom. But the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices ˻greatly˼ because of the bridegroom’s voice. So this joy of mine is complete.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	It is necessary for that one to increase, but for me to decrease.”
B043C003V031	43	3	31	The one who comes from above is over all. The one who is from the earth is from the earth and speaks from the earth; the one who comes from heaven is over all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	What he has seen and heard, this he testifies, and no one accepts his testimony.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	The one who accepts his testimony has attested that God is true.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For the one whom God sent speaks the words of God, for he does not give the Spirit by measure.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	The Father loves the Son and has given all things into his hand.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	The one who believes in the Son has eternal life, but the one who disobeys the Son will not see life—but the wrath of God remains on him.
B043C004V001	43	4	1	Now when Jesus knew that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus was making and baptizing more disciples than John
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(although Jesus himself was not baptizing, but his disciples),
B043C004V003	43	4	3	he left Judea and departed again for Galilee.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	And it was necessary for him to go through Samaria.
B043C004V005	43	4	5	Now he came to a town of Samaria called Sychar, near the piece of land that Jacob had given to his son Joseph.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	And Jacob’s well was there, so Jesus, because he had become tired from the journey, simply sat down at the well. It was about the sixth hour.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	A woman of Samaria came to draw water. Jesus said to her, “Give me water to drink.”
B043C004V008	43	4	8	(For his disciples had gone away into the town so that they could buy food.)
B043C004V009	43	4	9	So the Samaritan woman said to him, “How do you, being a Jew, ask from me water to drink, since I am a Samaritan woman?” (For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.)
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Jesus answered and said to her, “If you had known the gift of God and who it is who says to you, ‘Give me water to drink,’ you would have asked him, and he would have given you living water.”
B043C004V011	43	4	11	The woman said to him, “Sir, you have no bucket and the well is deep! From where then do you get this living water?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	You are not greater than our father Jacob, are you, who gave us the well and drank from it himself, and his sons and his livestock?”
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Jesus answered and said to her, “Everyone who drinks of this water will be thirsty again.
B043C004V014	43	4	14	But whoever drinks of this water which I will give to him will never be thirsty for eternity, but the water which I will give to him will become in him a well of water springing up to eternal life.”
B043C004V015	43	4	15	The woman said to him, “Sir, give me this water, so that I will not be thirsty or come here to draw water!”
B043C004V016	43	4	16	He said to her, “Go, call your husband and come here.”
B043C004V017	43	4	17	The woman answered and said to him, “I do not have a husband.” Jesus said to her, “You have said rightly, ‘I do not have a husband,’
B043C004V018	43	4	18	for you have had five husbands, and the one whom you have now is not your husband; this you have said truthfully!”
B043C004V019	43	4	19	The woman said to him, “Sir, I see that you are a prophet.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	Our fathers worshiped on this mountain, and you people say that in Jerusalem is the place where it is necessary to worship.”
B043C004V021	43	4	21	Jesus said to her, “Believe me, woman, that an hour is coming when neither on this mountain nor in Jerusalem will you worship the Father.
B043C004V022	43	4	22	You worship what you do not know. We worship what we know, because salvation is from the Jews.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But an hour is coming—and now is here—when the true worshipers will worship the Father in spirit and truth, for indeed the Father seeks such peopleto be his worshipers.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	God is spirit, and the ones who worship him must worship in spirit and truth.”
B043C004V025	43	4	25	The woman said to him, “I know that Messiah is coming” (the one called Christ); “whenever that one comes, he will proclaim all things to us.”
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jesus said to her, “I, the one speaking to you, am he.
B043C004V027	43	4	27	And at this point his disciples came, and they were astonished that he was speaking with a woman. However, no one said, “What do you seek?” or “Why are you speaking with her?”
B043C004V028	43	4	28	So the woman left her water jar and went away into the town and said to the people,
B043C004V029	43	4	29	“Come, see a man who told me everything I have ever done! Perhaps this one is the Christ?”
B043C004V030	43	4	30	They went out from the town and were coming to him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	In the meanwhile the disciples were asking him, saying, “Rabbi, eat something!”
B043C004V032	43	4	32	But he said to them, “I have food to eat that you do not know about.”
B043C004V033	43	4	33	So the disciples began to say to one another, “No one brought him anything to eat, did they?”
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jesus said to them, “My food is that I do the will of the one who sent me and complete his work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Do you not say, ‘There are yet four months and the harvest comes’? Behold, I say to you, lift up your eyes and look at the fields, that they are white for harvest already.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	The one who reaps receives wages and gathers fruit for eternal life, in order that the one who sows and the one who reaps can rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	For in this instance the saying is true, ‘It is one who sows and another who reaps.’
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap what you did not work for; others have worked, and you have entered into their work.”
B043C004V039	43	4	39	Now from that town many of the Samaritans believed in him because of the word of the woman who testified, “He told me everything that I have done.”
B043C004V040	43	4	40	So when the Samaritans came to him, they began asking him to stay with them. And he stayed there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	And many more believed because of his word,
B043C004V042	43	4	42	And they were saying to the woman, “No longer because of ˻what you said˼ do we believe, for we ourselves have heard, and we know that this one is truly the Savior of the world!”
B043C004V043	43	4	43	And after the two days he departed from there into Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	For Jesus himself testified that a prophet has no honor in his own homeland.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	So when he came to Galilee, the Galileans welcomed him, because they had seen all the things he had done in Jerusalem at the feast (for they themselves had also come to the feast).
B043C004V046	43	4	46	Now he came again to Cana in Galilee, where he had made the water wine. And there was at Capernaum a certain royal official whose son was sick.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	This man, when he heard that Jesus had come from Judea into Galilee, went to him and asked that he come down and heal his son, for he was about to die.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	So Jesus said to him, “Unless you people see signs and wonders, you will never believe!”
B043C004V049	43	4	49	The royal official said to him, “Sir, come down before my child dies!”
B043C004V050	43	4	50	Jesus said to him, “Go, your son will live.” The man believed the word that Jesus spoke to him, and he departed.
B043C004V051	43	4	51	Now as he was going down, his slaves met him, saying that his child was alive.
B043C004V052	43	4	52	So he inquired from them the hour at which he had gotten better. Then they said to him, “Yesterday at the seventh hour the fever left him.”
B043C004V053	43	4	53	So the father knew that it was at that same hour at which Jesus said to him, “Your son will live,” and he himself believed, and his whole household.
B043C004V054	43	4	54	Now this is again a second sign Jesus performed when he came from Judea into Galilee.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	After these thingsthere was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now there is in Jerusalem near the Sheep Gate a pool called in Aramaic Bethzatha, which has five porticoes.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	In these were lying a large number of those who were sick, blind, lame, paralyzed.
B043C005V005	43	5	5	And a certain man was there who had been thirty-eight years in his sickness.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	Jesus, when he saw this one lying there and knew that he had been sick a long time already, said to him, “Do you want to become well?”
B043C005V007	43	5	7	The one who was sick answered him, “Sir, I do not have anyone that, whenever the water is stirred up, could put me into the pool. But ˻while˼ I am coming, another goes down before me.”
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Jesus said to him, “Get up! Pick up your mat and walk!”
B043C005V009	43	5	9	And immediately the man became well and picked up his mat and began to walk. (Now it was the Sabbath on that day.)
B043C005V010	43	5	10	So the Jews were saying to the one who had been healed, “It is the Sabbath, and it is not permitted for you to pick up your mat!”
B043C005V011	43	5	11	But he answered them, “The one who made me well—that one said to me, ‘Pick up your mat and walk!’ ”
B043C005V012	43	5	12	They asked him, “Who is the man who said to you, ‘Pick up your mat and walk?’ ”
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But the one who was healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had withdrawn while a crowd was in the place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	After these things Jesus found him at the temple and said to him, “Look, you have become well! Sin no longer, lest something worse happen to you.”
B043C005V015	43	5	15	The man went and reported to the Jews that Jesus was the one who made him well.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	And on account of this the Jews began to persecute Jesus, because he was doing these things on the Sabbath.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But Jesus answered them, “My Father is working until now, and I am working.”
B043C005V018	43	5	18	So on account of this the Jews were seeking even more to kill him, because he not only was breaking the Sabbath, but also was calling God his own Father, thus making himself equal with God.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	So Jesus answered and said to them, “Truly, truly I say to you, the Son can do nothing from himself except what he sees the Father doing. For whatever that one does, these things also the Son does likewise.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	For the Father loves the Son and shows him everything that he himself is doing. And greater works than these he will show him, so that you will be astonished.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	For just as the Father raises the dead and makes them alive, thus also the Son makes alive whomever he wishes.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	For the Father does not judge anyone, but he has given all judgment to the Son,
B043C005V023	43	5	23	in order that all people will honor the Son, just as they honor the Father. The one who does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	Truly, truly I say to you that the one who hears my word and who believes the one who sent me has eternal life, and does not come into judgment, but has passed from death into life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	“Truly, truly I say to you, that an hour is coming—and now is here—when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God, and the ones who hear will live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	For just as the Father has life in himself, thus also he has granted to the Son to have life in himself.
B043C005V027	43	5	27	And he has granted him authority to carry out judgment, because he is the Son of Man.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	“Do not be astonished at this, because an hour is coming in which all those in the tombs will hear his voice
B043C005V029	43	5	29	and they will come out—those who have done good things to a resurrection of life, but those who have practiced evil things to a resurrection of judgment.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	I am able to do nothing from myself. Just as I hear, I judge, and my judgment is just, because I do not seek my own will, but the will of the one who sent me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	“If I testify about myself, my testimony is not true.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	There is another who testifies about me, and I know that the testimony which he testifies about me is true.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You have sent to John and he has testified to the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	(And I do not receive testimony from people, but I say these things in order that you may be saved.)
B043C005V035	43	5	35	That one was the lamp which was burning and shining, and you wanted to rejoice for an hour in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	“But I have a testimony greater than John’s, for the works which the Father has given to me that I should complete them—the very works which I am doing—these testify about me, that the Father has sent me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	And the Father who sent me, that one has testified about me. You have neither heard his voice at any time nor seen his form.
B043C005V038	43	5	38	And you do not have his word residing in yourselves, because the one whom that one sent, in this one you do not believe.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	You search the scriptures because you think that you have eternal life in them, and it is these that testify about me.
B043C005V040	43	5	40	And you are not willing to come to me so that you may have life.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	“I do not accept glory from people,
B043C005V042	43	5	42	but I know you, that you do not have the love of God in yourselves.
B043C005V043	43	5	43	I have come in my Father’s name, and you do not accept me. If another should come in his own name, you would accept that one!
B043C005V044	43	5	44	How are you able to believe, if you accept glory from one another, and do not seek the glory which is from the only God?
B043C005V045	43	5	45	Do not think that I will accuse you before the Father! The one who accuses you is Moses, in whom you have put your hope!
B043C005V046	43	5	46	For if you had believed Moses, you would believe me, for that one wrote about me.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	But if you do not believe that one’s writings, how will you believe my words?”
B043C006V001	43	6	1	After these things Jesus went away to the other side of the sea of Galilee (that is, Tiberias).
B043C006V002	43	6	2	And a large crowd was following him because they were observing the signs that he was doing on those who were sick.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	So Jesus went up on the mountain and sat down there with his disciples.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	(Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was near.)
B043C006V005	43	6	5	˻Then Jesus, when he looked up˼  and saw that a large crowd was coming to him, said to Philip, “Where can we buy bread so that these people can eat?”
B043C006V006	43	6	6	(Now he said this to test him, because he knew what he was going to do.)
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Philip replied to him, “Two hundred denarii worth of bread would not be enough for them, in order that each one could receive a little.”
B043C006V008	43	6	8	One of his disciples, Andrew the brother of Simon Peter, said to him,
B043C006V009	43	6	9	“Here is a boy who has five barley loaves and two fish, but what are these for so many people?”
B043C006V010	43	6	10	Jesus said, “Make the people recline.” (Now there was a lot of grass in the place.) So the men reclined, approximately five thousand in number.
B043C006V011	43	6	11	Then Jesus took the bread, and after he had given thanks, he distributed it to those who were reclining—likewise also of the fish, as much as they wanted.
B043C006V012	43	6	12	And when they were satisified, he said to his disciples, “Gather the remaining fragments so that nothing is lost.”
B043C006V013	43	6	13	So they gathered them, and filled twelve baskets with fragments from the five barley loaves which were left over by those who had eaten.
B043C006V014	43	6	14	Now when the people saw the sign that he performed, they began to say, “This one is truly the Prophet who is to come into the world!”
B043C006V015	43	6	15	Then Jesus, because he knew that they were about to come and seize him in order to make him king, withdrew again up the mountain by himself alone.
B043C006V016	43	6	16	Now when evening came, his disciples went down to the sea.
B043C006V017	43	6	17	And getting into a boat, they began to go to the other side of the sea, to Capernaum. And it had already become dark, and Jesus had not yet come to them.
B043C006V018	43	6	18	And the sea began to be stirred up because a strong wind was blowing.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	Then when they had rowed about twenty-five or thirty stadia, they saw Jesus walking on the sea and coming near the boat, and they were afraid.
B043C006V020	43	6	20	But he said to them, “It is I! Do not be afraid!”
B043C006V021	43	6	21	So they were wanting to take him into the boat, and immediately the boat came to the land to which they were going.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	On the next day, the crowd that was on the other side of the sea saw that other boats were not there (except one), and that Jesus had not entered with his disciples into the boat, but his disciples had departed alone.
B043C006V023	43	6	23	Other boats from Tiberias came near the place where they had eaten the bread after the Lord had given thanks.
B043C006V024	43	6	24	So when the crowd saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples, they themselves got into the boats and came to Capernaum seeking Jesus.
B043C006V025	43	6	25	And when they found him on the other side of the sea, they said to him, “Rabbi, when did you get here?”
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jesus replied to them and said, “Truly, truly I say to you, you seek me not because you saw signs, but because you ate of the loaves and were satisfied!
B043C006V027	43	6	27	Do not work for the food that perishes, but the food that remains to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give to you. For God the Father has set his seal on this one.”
B043C006V028	43	6	28	So they said to him, “What shall we do that we can accomplish the works of God?”
B043C006V029	43	6	29	Jesus answered and said to them, “This is the work of God: that you believe in the one whom that one sent.”
B043C006V030	43	6	30	So they said to him, “Then what sign will you perform, so that we can see it and believe you? What will you do?
B043C006V031	43	6	31	Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, just as it is written, ‘He gave them bread from heaven to eat.’
B043C006V032	43	6	32	Then Jesus said to them, “Truly, truly I say to you, Moses did not give you bread from heaven, but my Father is giving you the true bread from heaven!
B043C006V033	43	6	33	For the bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven and gives life to the world.”
B043C006V034	43	6	34	So they said to him, “Sir, always give us this bread!”
B043C006V035	43	6	35	Jesus said to them, “I am the bread of life. The one who comes to me will never be hungry, and the one who believes in me will never be thirsty again.
B043C006V036	43	6	36	But I said to you that you have seen me and do not believe.
B043C006V037	43	6	37	Everyone whom the Father gives to me will come to me, and the one who comes to me I will never throw out,
B043C006V038	43	6	38	because I have come down from heaven not that I should do my will, but the will of the one who sent me.
B043C006V039	43	6	39	Now this is the will of the one who sent me: that everyone whom he has given me, I would not lose any of them, but raise them up on the last day.
B043C006V040	43	6	40	For this is the will of my Father, that everyone who looks at the Son and believes in him would have eternal life, and I will raise him up on the last day.”
B043C006V041	43	6	41	Now the Jews began to grumble about him because he said, “I am the bread that came down from heaven,”
B043C006V042	43	6	42	and they were saying, “Is this one not Jesus the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How does he now say, ‘I have come down from heaven’?”
B043C006V043	43	6	43	Jesus answered and said to them, “Do not grumble ˻among yourselves˼!
B043C006V044	43	6	44	No one is able to come to me unless the Father who sent me draws him, and I will raise him up on the last day.
B043C006V045	43	6	45	It is written in the prophets, ‘And they will all be taught by God.’ Everyone who hears from the Father and learns comes to me.
B043C006V046	43	6	46	(Not that anyone has seen the Father except the one who is from God—this one has seen the Father.)
B043C006V047	43	6	47	Truly, truly I say to you, the one who believes has eternal life.
B043C006V048	43	6	48	I am the bread of life.
B043C006V049	43	6	49	Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness and they died.
B043C006V050	43	6	50	This is the bread that comes down from heaven so that someone may eat from it and not die.
B043C006V051	43	6	51	I am the living bread that came down from heaven. If anyone eats from this bread, he will live ˻forever˼. And the bread that I will give for the life of the world is my flesh.”
B043C006V052	43	6	52	So the Jews began to quarrel ˻among themselves˼, saying, “How can this man give us his flesh to eat?”
B043C006V053	43	6	53	Then Jesus said to them, “Truly, truly I say to you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you do not have life in yourselves!
B043C006V054	43	6	54	The one who eats my flesh and drinks my blood has eternal life, and I will raise him up on the last day.
B043C006V055	43	6	55	For my flesh is true food, and my blood is true drink.
B043C006V056	43	6	56	The one who eats my flesh and drinks my blood resides in me and I in him.
B043C006V057	43	6	57	Just as the living Father sent me, and I live because of the Father, so also the one who eats me—that one will live because of me.
B043C006V058	43	6	58	This is the bread that came down from heaven, not as the fathers ate and died. The one who eats this bread will live ˻forever˼.”
B043C006V059	43	6	59	He said these thingswhile teaching in the synagogue in Capernaum.
B043C006V060	43	6	60	Thus many of his disciples, when they heard it, said, “This saying is hard! Who can understand it?”
B043C006V061	43	6	61	But Jesus, because he knew within himself that his disciples were grumbling about this, said to them, “Does this cause you to be offended?
B043C006V062	43	6	62	Then what if you see the Son of Man ascending where he was before?
B043C006V063	43	6	63	The Spirit is the one who gives life; the flesh profits nothing. The words that I have spoken to you are spirit and are life.
B043C006V064	43	6	64	But there are some of you who do not believe.” (For Jesus knew from the beginning who they were who did not believe, and who it was who would betray him.)
B043C006V065	43	6	65	And he said, “Because of this I said to you that no one can come to me unless it has been granted to him by the Father.”
B043C006V066	43	6	66	For this reason many of his disciples ˻drew back˼ and were not walking with him any longer.
B043C006V067	43	6	67	So Jesus said to the twelve, “You do not want to go away also, do you?”
B043C006V068	43	6	68	Simon Peter answered him, “Lord, to whom would we go? You have the words of eternal life.
B043C006V069	43	6	69	And we have believed, and have come to know, that you are the Holy One of God.”
B043C006V070	43	6	70	Jesus replied to them, “Did I not choose you, the twelve, and one of you is the devil?”
B043C006V071	43	6	71	(Now he was speaking about Judas son of Simon Iscariot, because this one—one of the twelve—was going to betray him.)
B043C007V001	43	7	1	And after these things Jesus was going about in Galilee. For he did not want to go about in Judea, because the Jews were seeking to kill him.
B043C007V002	43	7	2	Now the feast of the Jews—the feast of Tabernacles—was near.
B043C007V003	43	7	3	So his brothers said to him, “Depart from here and go to Judea, so that your disciples also can see your works that you are doing.
B043C007V004	43	7	4	For no one does anything in secret and yet he himself desires to be ˻publicly recognized˼. If you are doing these things, reveal yourself to the world!”
B043C007V005	43	7	5	(For not even his brothers believed in him.)
B043C007V006	43	7	6	So Jesus said to them, “My time has not yet come, but your time is always ready.
B043C007V007	43	7	7	The world cannot hate you, but it hates me, because I am testifying about it, that its deeds are evil.
B043C007V008	43	7	8	You go up to the feast. I am not going up to this feast, because my time is not yet completed.
B043C007V009	43	7	9	And when he had said these things, he remained in Galilee.
