B043C015V018	43	15	18	If the world hates you, you know that it has hated me before it hated you.
B043C015V019	43	15	19	If you were of the world, the world would love its own. But because you are not of the world, but I chose you out of the world, for this reason the world hates you.
B043C015V020	43	15	20	Remember the word that I said to you: ‘A slave is not greater than his master.’ If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you. If they kept my word, they will keep yours also.
B043C015V021	43	15	21	But they will do all these things to you on account of my name, because they do not know the one who sent me.
B043C015V022	43	15	22	If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin. But now they do not have a valid excuse for their sin.
B043C015V023	43	15	23	The one who hates me hates my Father also.
B043C015V024	43	15	24	If I had not done among them the works that no one else did, they would not have sin. But now they have both seen and hated both me and my Father.
B043C015V025	43	15	25	But this happened so that the word that is written in their law would be fulfilled, ‘They hated me without a reason.’
B043C015V026	43	15	26	“When the Advocate comes, whom I will send to you from the Father—the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father—that one will testify about me.
B043C015V027	43	15	27	And you also will testify, because you have been with me from the beginning.
B043C016V001	43	16	1	“I have said these things to you so that you will not fall away.
B043C016V002	43	16	2	˻They will expel you from the synagogue˼, but an hour is coming that everyone who kills you will think they are offering service to God.
B043C016V003	43	16	3	And they will do these things because they do not know the Father or me.
B043C016V004	43	16	4	But I have said these things to you so that when their hour comes, you may remember that I told you about them.“And I have not said these things to you from the beginning, because I was with you.
B043C016V005	43	16	5	But now I am going away to the one who sent me, and none of you is asking me, ‘Where are you going?’
B043C016V006	43	16	6	But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled your hearts.
B043C016V007	43	16	7	But I tell you the truth, it is better for you that I go away. For if I do not go away, the Advocate will not come to you; but if I go, I will send him to you.
B043C016V008	43	16	8	And when he comes, he will convict the world concerning sin and concerning righteousness and concerning judgment:
B043C016V009	43	16	9	concerning sin, because they do not believe in me,
B043C016V010	43	16	10	and concerning righteousness, because I am going away to the Father and you will see me no more,
B043C016V011	43	16	11	and concerning judgment, because the ruler of this world has been condemned.
B043C016V012	43	16	12	I still have many things to say to you, but you are not able to bear them now.
B043C016V013	43	16	13	But when he—the Spirit of truth—comes, he will guide you into all the truth. For he will not speak from himself, but whatever he hears he will speak, and he will proclaim to you the things to come.
B043C016V014	43	16	14	He will glorify me, because he will take from what is mine and will proclaim it to you.
B043C016V015	43	16	15	Everything that the Father has is mine. For this reason I said that he takes from what is mine and will proclaim it to you.
B043C016V016	43	16	16	“A little while and you will see me no more, and again a little while and you will see me.
B043C016V017	43	16	17	So some of his disciples said to one another, “What is this that he is saying to us, ‘A little while and you will not see me, and again a little while and you will see me,’ and ‘Because I am going away to the Father’?”
B043C016V018	43	16	18	So they kept on saying, “What is this that he is saying, ‘A little while’? We do not understand what he is speaking about!”
B043C016V019	43	16	19	Jesus knew that they were wanting to ask him, and he said to them, “Are you deliberating with one another about this—that I said, ‘A little while, and you will not see me, and again a little while and you will see me’?
B043C016V020	43	16	20	Truly, truly I say to you, that you will weep and lament, but the world will rejoice; you will become sorrowful, but your sorrow will change to joy.
B043C016V021	43	16	21	A woman, when she gives birth, experiences pain because her hour has come. But when her child is born, she no longer remembers the affliction, on account of the joy that a human being has been born into the world.
B043C016V022	43	16	22	So you also are experiencing sorrow now, but I will see you again, and your hearts will rejoice, and no one will take away your joy from you.
B043C016V023	43	16	23	And on that day you will ask me nothing. Truly, truly I say to you, whatever you ask the Father in my name, he will give you.
B043C016V024	43	16	24	Until now you have asked nothing in my name. Ask and you will receive, so that your joy may be complete.
B043C016V025	43	16	25	“I have said these things to you in figurative sayings. An hour is coming when I will speak to you in figurative sayings no longer, but I will tell you plainly about the Father.
B043C016V026	43	16	26	On that day you will ask in my name, and I do not say to you that I will ask the Father on your behalf.
B043C016V027	43	16	27	For the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me and have believed that I came from God.
B043C016V028	43	16	28	I have gone out from the Father and have come into the world; again, I am leaving the world and am going to the Father.”
B043C016V029	43	16	29	His disciples said, “Behold, now you are speaking ˻plainly˼ and are telling us no figurative saying!
B043C016V030	43	16	30	Now we know that you know everything and do not ˻need for˼ anyone to ask you questions. By this we believe that you have come from God.”
B043C016V031	43	16	31	Jesus replied to them, “Now do you believe?
B043C016V032	43	16	32	Behold, an hour is coming—and has come—that you will be scattered each one to his own home, and you will leave me alone. And I am not alone, because the Father is with me.
B043C016V033	43	16	33	I have said these things to you so that in me you may have peace. In the world you have affliction, but have courage! I have conquered the world.”
B043C017V001	43	17	1	Jesus said these things, and lifting up his eyes to heaven he said, “Father, the hour has come! Glorify your Son, in order that your Son may glorify you—
B043C017V002	43	17	2	just as you have given him authority over all flesh, in order that he would give eternal life to them—everyone whom you have given him.
B043C017V003	43	17	3	Now this is eternal life: that they know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent.
B043C017V004	43	17	4	I have glorified you on earth by completing the work that you have given me ˻to do˼.
B043C017V005	43	17	5	And now, Father, you glorify me ˻at your side˼ with the glory that I had ˻at your side˼ before the world existed.
B043C017V006	43	17	6	“I have revealed your name to the men whom you gave me out of the world. They were yours, and you have given them to me, and they have kept your word.
B043C017V007	43	17	7	Now they understand that all the things that you have given me are from you,
B043C017V008	43	17	8	because the words that you gave to me I have given to them, and they received them and know truly that I have come from you, and they have believed that you have sent me.
B043C017V009	43	17	9	I am asking on behalf of them. I am not asking on behalf of the world, but on behalf of those whom you have given me, because they are yours,
B043C017V010	43	17	10	and all my things are yours, and your thingsare mine, and I have been glorified in them.
B043C017V011	43	17	11	And I am no longer in the world, and they are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, keep them in your name, which you have given to me, so that they may be one, just as we are.
B043C017V012	43	17	12	When I was with them, I kept them in your name, which you have given to me, and guarded them, and none of them has perished except the son of destruction, in order that the scripture would be fulfilled.
B043C017V013	43	17	13	And now I am coming to you, and I am saying these things in the world so that they may have my joy completed in themselves.
B043C017V014	43	17	14	I have given them your word, and the world has hated them, because they are not of the world just as I am not of the world.
B043C017V015	43	17	15	I do not ask that you take them out of the world, but that you protect them from the evil one.
B043C017V016	43	17	16	They are not of the world, just as I am not of the world.
B043C017V017	43	17	17	Sanctify them in the truth—your word is truth.
B043C017V018	43	17	18	Just as you sent me into the world, I also have sent them into the world.
B043C017V019	43	17	19	And for them I sanctify myself, so that they themselves also may be sanctified in the truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	“And I do not ask on behalf of these only, but also on behalf of those who believe in me through their word,
B043C017V021	43	17	21	that they all may be one, just as you, Father, are in me and I am in you, that they also may be in us, in order that the world may believe that you sent me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	And the glory that you have given to me, I have given to them, in order that they may be one, just as we are one—
B043C017V023	43	17	23	I in them, and you in me, in order that they may be completed in one, so that the world may know that you sent me, and you have loved them just as you have loved me.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	“Father, those whom you have given to me—I want that those also may be with me where I am, in order that they may see my glory that you have given me because you loved me before the foundation of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	Righteous Father, although the world does not know you, yet I have known you, and these men have come to know that you sent me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	And I made known to them your name, and will make it known, in order that the love with which you loved me may be in them, and I may be in them.”
B043C018V001	43	18	1	When Jesus had said these things, he went out with his disciples to the other side of the ravine of the Kidron, where there was a garden into which he and his disciples entered.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	(Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, also knew about the place, because Jesus often gathered there with his disciples.)
B043C018V003	43	18	3	So Judas, taking the cohort and officers from the chief priests and from the Pharisees, came there with lanterns and torches and weapons.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	Then Jesus, because he knew all the things that were coming upon him, went out and said to them, “Who are you looking for?”
B043C018V005	43	18	5	They replied to him, “Jesus the Nazarene.” He said to them, “I am he.” (Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, was also standing with them.)
B043C018V006	43	18	6	So when he said to them, “I am he,” ˻they drew back˼ and fell to the ground.
B043C018V007	43	18	7	Then he asked them again, “Who are you looking for?” And they said, “Jesus the Nazarene.”
B043C018V008	43	18	8	Jesus replied, “I said to you that I am he! So if you are looking for me, let these men go,”
B043C018V009	43	18	9	in order that the word that he had spoken would be fulfilled: “Those whom you have given to me—I have not lost anyone of them.”
B043C018V010	43	18	10	Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it and struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear. (Now the name of the slave was Malchus.)
B043C018V011	43	18	11	So Jesus said to Peter, “Put the sword into its sheath! The cup that the Father has given me—shall I not drink it?”
B043C018V012	43	18	12	Then the cohort and the military tribune and the officers of the Jews seized Jesus and tied him up,
B043C018V013	43	18	13	and brought him to Annas first, for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year.
B043C018V014	43	18	14	(Now it was Caiaphas who had advised the Jews that it was better that one man die for the people.)
B043C018V015	43	18	15	So Simon Peter and another disciple followed Jesus. (Now that disciple was known to the high priest, and entered with Jesus into the courtyard of the high priest.)
B043C018V016	43	18	16	But Peter was standing by the door outside. So the other disciple who was known to the high priest went out and spoke to the doorkeeper and brought Peter in.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	Then the female slave who was the doorkeeper said to Peter, “You are not also one of the disciples of this man, are you?” He said, “I am not!”
B043C018V018	43	18	18	(Now the slaves and the officers were standing there, having made a charcoal fire because it was cold, and they were warming themselves. And Peter was also standing there with them and warming himself.)
B043C018V019	43	18	19	So the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	Jesus replied to him, “I have spoken openly to the world. I always taught in the synagogue and in the temple courts where all the Jews assemble, and I have said nothing in secret.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	Why are you asking me? Ask those who heard what I have said to them! Behold, these people know what I said.”
B043C018V022	43	18	22	Now when he had said these things, one of the officers who was standing by gave a slap in the face to Jesus, saying, “Do you reply to the high priest in this way?”
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus replied to him, “If I have spoken wrongly, testify about what is wrong! But if I have spoken correctly, why do you strike me?”
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Then Annas sent him, tied up, to Caiaphas the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	Now Simon Peter was standing there and warming himself. So they said to him, “You are not also one of his disciples, are you?” He denied it and said, “I am not!”
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the slaves of the high priest, who was related to the one whose ear Peter had cut off, said, “Did I not see you in the garden with him?”
B043C018V027	43	18	27	So Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	Then they brought Jesus from Caiaphas to the governor’s residence. Now it was early, and they did not enter into the governor’s residence so that they would not be defiled, but could eat the Passover.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	So Pilate came outside to them and said, “What accusation do you bring against this man?”
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered and said to him, “If this man were not doing evil, we would not have handed him over to you!”
B043C018V031	43	18	31	So Pilate said to them, “You take him and judge him according to your law!” The Jews said to him, “It is not permitted for us to kill anyone,”
B043C018V032	43	18	32	in order that the word of Jesus would be fulfilled that he had spoken, indicating by what sort of death he was going to die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	Then Pilate entered again into the governor’s residence and summoned Jesus and said to him, “Are you the king of the Jews?”
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus replied, “Do you say this from yourself, or have others said this to you about me?”
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilate replied, “I am not a Jew, am I? Your people and the chief priests handed you over to me! What have you done?”
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus replied, “My kingdom is not of this world. If my kingdom were of this world, my servants would be fighting so that I would not be handed over to the Jews. But now my kingdom is not from here.”
B043C018V037	43	18	37	Then Pilate said to him, “So then you are a king!” Jesus replied, “You say that I am a king. For this reason I was born, and for this reason I have come into the world: in order that I can testify to the truth. Everyone who is of the truth hears my voice.”
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to him, “What is truth?”And when he had said this, he went out again to the Jews and said to them, “I find no basis for an accusation against him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	But it is your custom that I release for you one prisoner at the Passover. So do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?”
B043C018V040	43	18	40	Then they shouted again, saying, “Not this man, but Barabbas!” (Now Barabbas was a revolutionary.)
B043C019V001	43	19	1	So then Pilate took Jesus and had him flogged.
B043C019V002	43	19	2	And the soldiers wove a crown of thorns and placed it on his head, and put a purple robe on him,
B043C019V003	43	19	3	and were coming up to him and saying, “Hail, king of the Jews!” and were giving him slaps in the face.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	And Pilate came outside again and said to them, “Behold, I am bringing him outside to you, so that you will know that I find no basis for an accusation against him.”
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Then Jesus came outside wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe, and he said to them, “Behold the man!”
B043C019V006	43	19	6	So when they saw him, the chief priests and the officers shouted, saying, “Crucify! Crucify!” Pilate said to them, “You take him and crucify him! For I do not find a basis for an accusation against him.”
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jews replied to him, “We have a law, and according to the law he ought to die, because he made himself out to be the Son of God!”
B043C019V008	43	19	8	So when Pilate heard this statement, he was even more afraid,
B043C019V009	43	19	9	and he entered into the governor’s residence again and said to Jesus, “Where are you from?” But Jesus did not give him an answer.
B043C019V010	43	19	10	So Pilate said to him, “Will you not speak to me? Do you not know that I have authority to release you, and I have authority to crucify you?”
B043C019V011	43	19	11	Jesus replied to him, “You would not have any authority over me unless it was given to you from above. For this reason the one who handed me over to you has greater sin.”
B043C019V012	43	19	12	From this point on Pilate was seeking to release him, but the Jews shouted, saying, “If you release this man, you are not a friend of Caesar! Everyone who makes himself out to be a king opposes Caesar!”
B043C019V013	43	19	13	So Pilate, when he heard these words, brought Jesus outside and sat down on the judgment seat, in the place called The Stone Pavement (but Gabbatha in Aramaic).
B043C019V014	43	19	14	(Now it was the day of preparation of the Passover; it was about the sixth hour.) And he said to the Jews, “Behold your king!”
B043C019V015	43	19	15	Then those shouted, “Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!” Pilate said to them, “Shall I crucify your king?” The chief priests replied, “We do not have a king except Caesar!”
B043C019V016	43	19	16	So then he handed him over to them in order that he could be crucified.So they took Jesus,
B043C019V017	43	19	17	and carrying for himself the cross, he went out to the place called The Place of a Skull (which is called Golgotha in Aramaic),
B043C019V018	43	19	18	where they crucified him, and with him two others, ˻one on each side˼, and Jesus in the middle.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	And Pilate also wrote a notice and placed it on the cross, and it was written: “Jesus the Nazarene, the king of the Jews.”
B043C019V020	43	19	20	So many of the Jews read this notice, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city. And it was written in Aramaic, in Latin, and in Greek.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, “Do not write ‘The king of the Jews,’ but, ‘He said, I am king of the Jews.’ ”
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilate replied, “What I have written, I have written.”
B043C019V023	43	19	23	Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his clothing and made four shares—for each soldier a share—and the tunic. (Now the tunic was seamless, woven from the top ˻in a single piece˼.)
B043C019V024	43	19	24	So they said to one another, “Let us not tear it apart, but cast lots for it, to see whose it will be,” so that the scripture would be fulfilled that says,“They divided my garments among themselves,and for my clothing they cast lots.”Thus the soldiers did these things.
B043C019V025	43	19	25	Now his mother and the sister of his mother, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene were standing near the cross of Jesus.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	So Jesus, seeing his mother and the disciple whom he loved standing there, said to his mother, “Woman, behold your son!”
B043C019V027	43	19	27	Then he said to the disciple, “Behold your mother!” And from that hour the disciple took her into his own home.
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After this, Jesus, knowing that now at last everything was completed, in order that the scripture would be fulfilled, said, “I am thirsty.”
B043C019V029	43	19	29	A jar full of sour wine was standing there, so they put a sponge full of the sour wine on a branch of hyssop and brought it to his mouth.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	Then when he had received the sour wine, Jesus said, “It is completed,” and bowing his head, he gave up his spirit.
B043C019V031	43	19	31	Then the Jews, because it was the day of preparation, so that the bodies would not remain on the cross on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath was an important day), asked Pilate that their legs could be broken and they could be taken away.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the first and of the other who had been crucified with him.
B043C019V033	43	19	33	But when they came to Jesus, after they saw he was already dead, they did not break his legs.
B043C019V034	43	19	34	But one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and blood and water came out immediately.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	And the one who has seen it has testified, and his testimony is true, and that person knows that he is telling the truth, so that you also may believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For these things happened in order that the scripture would be fulfilled: “Not a bone of his will be broken.”
B043C019V037	43	19	37	And again another scripture says, “They will look on the one whom they have pierced.”
B043C019V038	43	19	38	And after these things, Joseph who was from Arimathea, who was a disciple of Jesus (but a secret one for fear of the Jews), asked Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus. And Pilate allowed it, so he came and took away his body.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	And Nicodemus—the one who had come to him formerly at night—also came, bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes weighing about a hundred pounds.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	So they took the body of Jesus and wrapped it in strips of linen cloth with the fragrant spices, as is the Jews’ custom to prepare for burial.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	Now there was a garden at the place where he was crucified, and in the garden a new tomb in which no one was yet buried.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	So there, on account of the day of preparation of the Jews, because the tomb was close by, they buried Jesus.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	Now on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb early, while it was still dark, and saw the stone had been taken away from the tomb.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	So she ran and came to Simon Peter and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved and said to them, “They have taken away the Lord from the tomb and we do not know where they have put him!”
B043C020V003	43	20	3	Then Peter and the other disciple went out and were going to the tomb.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	And the two were running together, and the other disciple ran ahead, faster than Peter, and came to the tomb first.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	And bending over to look, he saw the strips of linen cloth lying there, though he did not go in.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	Then Simon Peter also came following him, and he went into the tomb and saw the strips of linen cloth lying there,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	and the facecloth that was on his head—not lying with the strips of linen cloth, but folded up separately in one place.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	So then the other disciple who had come to the tomb first also went in, and he saw and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	(For they did not yet know the scripture that it was necessary for him to rise from the dead.)
B043C020V010	43	20	10	Then the disciples went away again to their own homes.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	But Mary stood outside at the tomb, weeping. Then, while she was weeping, she bent over to look into the tomb,
B043C020V012	43	20	12	and she saw two angels in white, seated one at the head and one at the feet where the body of Jesus had been lying.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	And they said to her, “Woman, why are you weeping?” She said to them, “They have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have put him!”
B043C020V014	43	20	14	When she had said these things, she turned ˻around˼ and saw Jesus standing there, and she did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her, “Woman, why are you weeping? Who are you looking for?” She thought that it was the gardener, and said to him, “Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will take him.”
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jesus said to her, “Mary.” She turned around and said to him in Aramaic, “Rabboni” (which means “Teacher”).
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jesus said to her, “Do not touch me, for I have not yet ascended to the Father. But go to my brothers and tell them, ‘I am ascending to my Father and your Father, and my God and your God.’ ”
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Mary Magdalene came and announced to the disciples, “I have seen the Lord,” and he had said these things to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	Now when it was evening on that day—the first day of the week—and the doors had been shut where the disciples were because of fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood in their midst and said to them, “Peace to you.”
