B043C020V025	43	20	25	So the other disciples said to him, “We have seen the Lord!” But he said to them, “Unless I see in his hands the mark of the nails, and put my finger into the mark of the nails, and put my hand into his side, I will never believe!”
B043C020V026	43	20	26	And after eight days his disciples were again inside, and Thomas with them. Although the doors had been shut, Jesus came and stood in their midst and said, “Peace to you.”
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then he said to Thomas, “Place your finger here and see my hands, and place your hand and put it into my side. And do not be unbelieving, but believing!”
B043C020V028	43	20	28	Thomas answered and said to him, “My Lord and my God!”
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jesus said to him, “Because you have seen me, have you believed? Blessed are those who have not seen and have believed.”
B043C020V030	43	20	30	Now Jesus also performed many other signs in the presence of his disciples which are not recorded in this book,
B043C020V031	43	20	31	but these things are recorded in order that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life in his name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	After these things Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples by the Sea of Tiberias. Now he revealed himself in this way:
B043C021V002	43	21	2	Simon Peter and Thomas (who was called Didymus) and Nathanael from Cana in Galilee and the sons of Zebedee and two others of his disciples were together.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, “I am going fishing!” They said to him, “We also are coming with you.” They went out and got into the boat, and during that night they caught nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	Now when it was already early morning, Jesus stood on the beach. However, the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	So Jesus said to them, “Children, you do not have any fish to eat, do you? They answered him, “No.”
B043C021V006	43	21	6	And he said to them, “Throw the net on the right side of the boat, and you will find some.” So they threw it, and were no longer able to haul it in from the large number of the fish.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	Then that disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, “It is the Lord!” So Simon Peter, when he heard that it was the Lord, tied around himself his outer garment (for he was naked) and threw himself into the sea.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	But the other disciples came in the boat, dragging the net of fish, because they were not far from the land, but about two hundred cubits away.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	So when they got out on the land, they saw a charcoal fire laid there, and a fish lying on it, and bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	Jesus said to them, “Bring some of the fish that you have just now caught.”
B043C021V011	43	21	11	So Simon Peter got into the boat and hauled the net to the land, full of large fish—one hundred fifty-three—and although there were so many, the net was not torn.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	Jesus said to them, “Come, eat breakfast!” But none of the disciples dared to ask him, “Who are you?” because they knew that it was the Lord.
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them, and the fish likewise.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This was now the third time Jesus was revealed to the disciples after he had been raised from the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	Now when they had eaten breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, “Simon son of John, do you love me more than these?” He said to him, “Yes, Lord, you know that I love you.” He said to him, “Feed my lambs!”
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He said to him again a second time, “Simon son of John, do you love me?” He said to him, “Yes, Lord, you know that I love you.” He said to him, “Shepherd my sheep!”
B043C021V017	43	21	17	He said to him a third time, “Simon son of John, do you love me?” Peter was distressed because he said to him a third time, “Do you love me?” and he said to him, “Lord, you know everything! You know that I love you!” Jesus said to him, “Feed my sheep!
B043C021V018	43	21	18	Truly, truly I say to you, when you were young, you tied your clothes around yourself and walked wherever you wanted. But when you grow old, you will stretch out your hands, and someone else will tie you up and carry you where you do not want to go.
B043C021V019	43	21	19	(Now he said this to indicate by what kind of death he would glorify God.) And after he had said this, he said to him, “Follow me!”
B043C021V020	43	21	20	Peter turned and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following them (who also leaned back on his chest at the dinner and said, “Lord, who is the one betraying you?”)
B043C021V021	43	21	21	So when he saw this one, Peter said to Jesus, “Lord, but what about this one?”
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said to him, “If I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you? You follow me!”
B043C021V023	43	21	23	So this saying went out to the brothers that that disciple would not die. But Jesus did not say to him that he would not die, but “If I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you?”
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who is testifying about these things, and who has written down these things. And we know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	Now there are also many other things that Jesus did, which—if they were written down one after the other—I suppose not even the world itself could contain the books that would be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	I produced the former account, O Theophilus, about all ˻that˼ Jesus began to do and to teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	until the day he was taken up, after he had given orders through the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen,
B044C001V003	44	1	3	to whom he also presented himself alive after he suffered, with many convincing proofs, appearing to them over a period of forty days and speaking the things about the kingdom of God.
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And while he was with them, he commanded them, “Do not depart from Jerusalem, but wait for what was promised by the Father, which you heard about from me.
B044C001V005	44	1	5	For John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit ˻not many days from now˼.”
B044C001V006	44	1	6	So when they had come together, they began asking him, saying, “Lord, is it at this time you are restoring the kingdom to Israel?”
B044C001V007	44	1	7	But he said to them, “It is not for you to know the times or seasons that the Father has set by his own authority.
B044C001V008	44	1	8	But you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you, and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and Samaria, and to the farthest part of the earth.”
B044C001V009	44	1	9	And after he had said these things, while they were watching, he was taken up, and a cloud received him from their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	And as they were staring into the sky while he was departing, behold, two men in white clothing stood by them
B044C001V011	44	1	11	who also said, “Men ˻of Galilee˼, why do you stand there gazing into the sky? This Jesus who was taken up from you into heaven like this will come back in the same way you saw him departing into heaven!”
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mountain that is called Olive Grove which is near Jerusalem, ˻a Sabbath day’s journey away˼.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	And when they had entered, they went up to the upstairs room where they were staying—Peter and John and James and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot and Judas son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	All these were busily engaged with one mind in prayer, together with the women and Mary the mother of Jesus and his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the brothers (and it was a crowd of persons of about one hundred twenty at the same place) and said,
B044C001V016	44	1	16	“Men and brothers, it was necessary that the scripture be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit proclaimed beforehand through the mouth of David concerning Judas, who became a guide to those who arrested Jesus,
B044C001V017	44	1	17	because he was counted among us and received a share in this ministry.”
B044C001V018	44	1	18	(Now this man acquired a field for the wages of his wickedness, and falling headlong, he burst open in the middle and all his intestines spilled out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	And it became known to all who live in Jerusalem, so that that field was called in their own language “Akeldama,” that is, “Field of Blood.”)
B044C001V020	44	1	20	“For it is written in the book of Psalms,‘Let his residence become deserted,and let there be no one to live in it,’and,‘Let another person take his position.’
B044C001V021	44	1	21	Therefore it is necessary for one of the men who have accompanied us during all the time in which the Lord Jesus went in and went out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	beginning from the baptism of John until the day on which he was taken up from us—one of these men must become a witness of his resurrection together with us.”
B044C001V023	44	1	23	And they proposed two men, Joseph called Barsabbas (who was called Justus) and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	And they prayed and said, “You, Lord, who know the hearts of all, show clearly which one of these two you have chosen
B044C001V025	44	1	25	to take the place in this ministry and apostleship from which Judas turned aside to depart to his own place.”
B044C001V026	44	1	26	And they cast lots for them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he was added to serve with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	And when the day of Pentecost had come, they were all together in the same place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	And suddenly a sound like a violent rushing wind came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	And divided tongues like fire appeared to them and rested on each one of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other languages as the Spirit gave them ability to speak out.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	Now there were Jews residing in Jerusalem, devout men from every nation under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	And when this sound occurred, the crowd gathered and was in confusion, because each one was hearing them speaking in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	And they were astounded and astonished, saying, “Behold, are not all these who are speaking Galileans?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	And how do we hear, each one of us, in ˻our own native language˼?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians and Medes and Elamites and those residing in Mesopotamia, Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya toward Cyrene, and the Romans who were in town,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	both Jews and proselytes, Cretans and Arabs—we hear them speaking in our own languages the great deeds of God!”
B044C002V012	44	2	12	And all were amazed and greatly perplexed, saying ˻to one another˼, “˻What can this mean?˼”
B044C002V013	44	2	13	But others jeered and said, “They are full of sweet new wine!”
B044C002V014	44	2	14	But Peter, standing with the eleven, raised his voice and declared to them, “Judean men, and all those who live in Jerusalem, let this be known to you, and pay attention to my words!
B044C002V015	44	2	15	For these men are not drunk, as you assume, because it is the third hour of the day.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	But this is what was spoken through the prophet Joel:
B044C002V017	44	2	17	‘And it will be in the last days,’ God says,‘I will pour out my Spirit on all flesh,and your sons and your daughters will prophesy,and your young men will see visions,and your old men will dream dreams.
B044C002V018	44	2	18	And even on my male slaves and on my female slavesI will pour out my Spirit in those days, and they will prophesy.
B044C002V019	44	2	19	And I will cause wonders in the heaven aboveand signs on the earth below,blood and fire and vapor of smoke.
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun will be changed to darknessand the moon to blood,before the great and glorious day of the Lord comes.
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And it will be that everyone who calls upon the name of the Lord will be saved.’
B044C002V022	44	2	22	“Israelite men, listen to these words! Jesus the Nazarene, a man attested to you by God with deeds of power and wonders and signs that God did through him in your midst, just as you yourselves know—
B044C002V023	44	2	23	this man, delivered up by the determined plan and foreknowledge of God, you executed by nailing to a cross through the hand of lawless men.
B044C002V024	44	2	24	God raised ˻him˼ up, having brought to an end the pains of death, because it was not possible for him to be held by it.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David says with reference to him,‘I saw the Lord before me ˻continually˼,for he is at my right hand so that I will not be shaken.
B044C002V026	44	2	26	For this reason my heart was gladand my tongue rejoiced greatly,furthermore also my flesh will live in hope,
B044C002V027	44	2	27	because you will not abandon my soul in Hades,nor will you permit your Holy One to experience decay.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	You have made known to me the paths of life;you will fill me with gladness with your presence.’
B044C002V029	44	2	29	“Men and brothers, it is possible to speak with confidence to you about the patriarch David, that he both died and was buried, and his tomb is with us until this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	Therefore, because he was a prophet and knew that God had sworn to him with an oath to seat ˻one of his descendants˼ on his throne,
B044C002V031	44	2	31	by having foreseen this, he spoke about the resurrection of the Christ, that neither was he abandoned in Hades nor did his flesh experience decay.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jesus God raised up, of which we all are witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	Therefore, having been exalted to the right hand of God and having received the promise of the Holy Spirit from the Father, he has poured out this that you both see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David did not ascend into heaven, but he himself says,‘The Lord said to my Lord,“Sit at my right hand,
B044C002V035	44	2	35	until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.” ’
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Therefore let all the house of Israel know beyond a doubt, that God has made him both Lord and Christ—this Jesus whom you crucified!”
B044C002V037	44	2	37	Now when they heard this, they were pierced to the heart and said to Peter and the other apostles, “What should we do, men and brothers?”
B044C002V038	44	2	38	And Peter said to them, “Repent and be baptized, each one of you, in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins, and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For the promise is for you and for your children, and for all those who are far away, as many as the Lord our God calls to himself.”
B044C002V040	44	2	40	And with many other words he solemnly urged and exhorted them, saying, “Be saved from this crooked generation!”
B044C002V041	44	2	41	So those who accepted his message were baptized, and on that day about three thousand souls were added.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	And they were devoting themselves to the teaching of the apostles and to fellowship, to the breaking of bread and to prayers.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	And fear came on every soul, and many wonders and signs were being performed by the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	And all who believed were in the same place, and had everything in common.
B044C002V045	44	2	45	And they began selling their possessions and property, and distributing these things to all, to the degree that anyone had need.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	And every day, devoting themselves to meeting with one purpose in the temple courts and breaking bread from house to house, they were eating their food with joy and simplicity of heart,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	praising God and having favor with all the people. And the Lord was adding every day to the total of those who were being saved.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	Now Peter and John were going up to the temple at the hour of prayer, the ninth hour.
B044C003V002	44	3	2	And a certain man was being carried who was lame ˻from birth˼. ˻He˼ was placed every day at the gate of the temple called “Beautiful,” so that he could ask for charitable gifts from those who were going into the temple courts.
B044C003V003	44	3	3	When he saw Peter and John about to go into the temple courts, he began asking to receive alms.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	And Peter looked intently at him, together with John, and said, “Look at us!”
B044C003V005	44	3	5	So he fixed his attention on them, expecting to receive something from them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	But Peter said, “Silver and gold ˻I do not possess˼, but what I have, this I give to you—in the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, get up and walk!”
B044C003V007	44	3	7	And taking hold of him by the right hand, he raised him up, and immediately his feet and ankles were made strong.
B044C003V008	44	3	8	And leaping up, he stood and began walking around and entered into the temple courts with them, walking and leaping and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	And all the people saw him walking and praising God,
B044C003V010	44	3	10	And they recognized him, that he himself was the one who used to sit asking for alms at the Beautiful Gate of the temple, and they were filled with awe and astonishment at what had happened to him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	And while he was holding fast to Peter and John, all the people ran together to them in the portico called Solomon’s, utterly astonished.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	And when he saw it, Peter replied to the people, “Men and Israelites, why are you astonished at this? Or why are you staring at us, as if by our own power or godliness we have made him walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob, the God of our fathers, has glorified his servant Jesus, whom you handed over and denied in the presence of Pilate, after he had decided to release him.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	But you denied the Holy and Righteous One and demanded that a man—a murderer—be granted to you.
B044C003V015	44	3	15	And you killed the originator of life, whom God raised from the dead, of which we are witnesses!
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And on the basis of faith in his name, his name has made this man strong, whom you see and know, and the faith that is through him has given him this perfect health in the presence of you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	And now, brothers, I know that you acted in ignorance, just as your rulers did also.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	But the things which God foretold through the mouth of all the prophets, that his Christ would suffer, he has fulfilled in this way.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Therefore repent and turn back, so that your sins may be blotted out,
B044C003V020	44	3	20	so that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord, and he may send the Christ appointed for you—Jesus,
B044C003V021	44	3	21	whom heaven must receive until the times of the restoration of all things, about which God spoke through the mouth of his holy prophets from earliest times.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	Moses said, ‘The Lord your God will raise up for you a prophet like me from your brothers. You will listen to him in everything that he says to you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	And it will be that every soul who—if he does not listen to that prophet—will be destroyed utterly from the people.’
B044C003V024	44	3	24	And indeed, all the prophets from Samuel and all those who followed him have spoken about and proclaimed these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the sons of the prophets and of the covenant that God ordained with your fathers, saying to Abraham, ‘And in your offspring all the nations of the earth will be blessed.’
B044C003V026	44	3	26	God, after he had raised up his servant, sent him to you first, to bless you by turning each of you back from your wickedness!”
B044C004V001	44	4	1	And while they were speaking to the people, the priests and the captain of the temple and the Sadducees approached them,
B044C004V002	44	4	2	greatly annoyed because they were teaching the people and proclaiming in Jesus the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid hands on them and put them in custody until the next day, because it was already evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	But many of those who listened to the message believed, and the number of the men was approximately five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	And it happened that on the next day, their rulers and elders and scribes came together in Jerusalem,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	and Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas and John and Alexander, and all those who were from the high priest’s family.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And they made them stand in their midst and began to ask, “By what power or by what name did you do this?”
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, “Rulers of the people and elders,
B044C004V009	44	4	9	if we are being examined today concerning a good deed done to a sick man—by what means this man was healed—
B044C004V010	44	4	10	let it be known to all of you and to all the people of Israel that by the name of Jesus Christ the Nazarene, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead—by him this man stands before you healthy!
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This one is the stone that was rejected by you, the builders, that has become ˻the cornerstone˼.
B044C004V012	44	4	12	And there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven that is given among people by which we must be saved.”
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and understood that they were uneducated and untrained men, they were astonished, and recognized them, that they had been with Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	And because they saw the man who had been healed standing there with them, they had nothing to say in return.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	But after they had ordered them to go outside the Sanhedrin, they began to confer with one another,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	saying, “What should we do with these men? For that a remarkable sign has taken place through them is evident to all those who live in Jerusalem, and we are not able to deny it!
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But in order that it may not spread much further among the people, let us warn them to speak no more in this name ˻to anyone at all˼.”
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And they called them backand commanded them not to speak or to teach at all in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John answered and said to them, “Whether it is right in the sight of God to listen to you rather than God, you decide!
B044C004V020	44	4	20	For we are not able to refrain from speaking about the things that we have seen and heard.”
B044C004V021	44	4	21	So after threatening them further, they released them, finding no way to punish them on account of the people, because they were all praising God for what had happened.
B044C004V022	44	4	22	For the man on whom this sign of healing had been performed was more than forty years old.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And when they were released, they went to their own people and reported all that the chief priests and the elders had said to them.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	And when they heard it, they lifted their voices with one mind to God and said, “Master, you are the one who made the heaven and the earth and the sea and all the things in them,
B044C004V025	44	4	25	the one who said by the Holy Spirit through the mouth of our father David, your servant,‘Why do the nations rage,and the peoples conspire in vain?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings of the earth stood opposed,and the rulers assembled together at the same place,against the Lord and against his Christ.’
B044C004V027	44	4	27	For in truth both Herod and Pontius Pilate, together with the Gentiles and the peoples of Israel, assembled together in this city against your holy servant Jesus whom you anointed,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	to do all that your hand and your plan had predestined to take place.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	And now, Lord, concern yourself with their threats and grant your slaves to speak your message with all boldness,
B044C004V030	44	4	30	as you extend your hand to heal and signs and wonders are performed through the name of your holy servant Jesus.”
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And when they had prayed, the place in which they were gathered was shaken, and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak the word of God with boldness.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	Now the group of those who believed were one heart and soul, and no one said anything of what belonged to him was his own, but all things were theirs in common.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power the apostles were giving testimony to the resurrection of the Lord Jesus, and great grace was on them all.
