B044C005V001	44	5	1	Now a certain man ˻named˼ Ananias, together with his wife Sapphira, sold a piece of property,
B044C005V002	44	5	2	and he kept back for himself some of the proceeds, and his wife was aware of it. And he brought a certain part and placed it at the feet of the apostles.
B044C005V003	44	5	3	But Peter said, “Ananias, for what reason has Satan filled your heart, that you lied to the Holy Spirit and kept back for yourself some of the proceeds of the piece of land?
B044C005V004	44	5	4	When it remained to you, did it not remain yours? And when it was sold, was it at your disposal? How is it that you have contrived this deed in your heart? You have not lied to people, but to God!”
B044C005V005	44	5	5	And when Ananias heard these words, he fell down and died. And great fear came on all those who heard about it.
B044C005V006	44	5	6	So the young men stood up, wrapped him up, and carried him out and buried him.
B044C005V007	44	5	7	And it happened that there was an interval of about three hours, and his wife came in, not knowing what had happened.
B044C005V008	44	5	8	And Peter said to her, “Tell me whether you both were paid this much for the piece of land.” And she said, “Yes, this much.”
B044C005V009	44	5	9	So Peter said to her, “How is it that it was agreed by you two to test the Spirit of the Lord? Behold, the feet of those who buried your husband are at the door, and they will carry you out!”
