B044C024V010	44	24	10	And when the governor gestured for him to speak, Paul replied, “Because I know you have been a judge over this nation for many years, I defend myself cheerfully with respect to the things concerning myself.
B044C024V011	44	24	11	You can ascertain that ˻it has not been more than˼ twelve days ˻since˼ I went up to Jerusalem to worship.
B044C024V012	44	24	12	And neither did they find me arguing with anyone or making a crowd develop in the temple courts nor in the synagogues nor throughout the city.
B044C024V013	44	24	13	Nor can they prove the things to you concerning which they are now accusing me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	But I do confess this to you, that according to the Way (which they call a sect), so I worship the God of our fathers, believing all things that are in accordance with the law and that are written in the prophets,
B044C024V015	44	24	15	having a hope in God which these men also themselves await: that there is going to be a resurrection of both the righteous and the unrighteous.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	˻For this reason˼ also I myself ˻always˼ do my best to have a clear conscience toward God and people.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	So after many years, I came to practice charitable giving and offerings to my people,
B044C024V018	44	24	18	in which they found me purified in the temple courts, not with a crowd or with a disturbance.
B044C024V019	44	24	19	But there are some Jews from Asia who ought to be present before you and bring charges against me, if they have anything against me,
B044C024V020	44	24	20	or these men themselves should say what crime they found when I stood before the Sanhedrin,
B044C024V021	44	24	21	other than concerning this one declaration that I shouted while standing there before them: ‘I am being judged before you today concerning the resurrection of the dead!’ ”
B044C024V022	44	24	22	But Felix, because he understood the facts concerning the Way more accurately, put them off, saying, “When Lysias the military tribune comes down, I will decide ˻your case˼.”
B044C024V023	44	24	23	He ordered the centurion for him to be guarded and to have some freedom, and in no way to prevent any of his own peoplefrom serving him.
B044C024V024	44	24	24	And after some days, when Felix arrived with his wife Drusilla, who was Jewish, he sent for Paul and listened to him concerning faith in Christ Jesus.
B044C024V025	44	24	25	And while he was discussing about righteousness and self control and the judgment that is to come, Felix became afraid and replied, “Go away for the present, and when I have an opportunity, I will summon you.”
B044C024V026	44	24	26	At the same time he was also hoping that money would be given to him by Paul. For this reason also he sent for him as often as possible and talked with him.
B044C024V027	44	24	27	And when two years had passed, Felix received as successor Porcius Festus. And because he wanted to do a favor for the Jews, Felix left Paul behind ˻as a prisoner˼.
B044C025V001	44	25	1	Now when Festus set foot in the province, after three days he went up to Jerusalem from Caesarea.
B044C025V002	44	25	2	And the chief priests and the most prominent men of the Jews brought charges against Paul to him, and were urging him,
B044C025V003	44	25	3	asking for a favor against him, that he summon him to Jerusalem, because they were preparing an ambush to do away with him along the way.
B044C025V004	44	25	4	Then Festus replied that Paul was being kept at Caesarea, and he himself was about to go there in a short time.
B044C025V005	44	25	5	So he said, “Let those among you who are prominent go down with me, and if there is any wrong in the man, let them bring charges against him.”
B044C025V006	44	25	6	And after he had stayed among them not more than eight or ten days, he went down to Caesarea. On the next day he sat down on the judgment seat and gave orders for Paul to be brought.
B044C025V007	44	25	7	And when he arrived, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood around him, bringing many and serious charges that they were not able to prove,
B044C025V008	44	25	8	while Paul said in his defense, “Neither against the law of the Jews nor against the temple nor against Caesar have I sinned with reference to anything!”
B044C025V009	44	25	9	But Festus, because he wanted to do a favor for the Jews, answered and said to Paul, “Are you willing to go up to Jerusalem to be tried before me there concerning these things?”
B044C025V010	44	25	10	But Paul said, “I am standing before the judgment seat of Caesar, where it is necessary for me to be judged. I have done no wrong to the Jews, as you also know very well.
B044C025V011	44	25	11	If then I am doing wrong and have done anything deserving death, I am not trying to avoid dying. But if there is nothing true of the things which these people are accusing me, no one can give me up to them. I appeal to Caesar!”
B044C025V012	44	25	12	Then Festus, after discussing this with his council, replied, “You have appealed to Caesar—to Caesar you will go!”
B044C025V013	44	25	13	Now after some days had passed, King Agrippa and Bernice arrived at Caesarea to welcome Festus.
B044C025V014	44	25	14	And while they were staying there many days, Festus laid out the case against Paul to the king, saying, “There is a certain man left behind by Felix as a prisoner,
B044C025V015	44	25	15	concerning whom when I was in Jerusalem the chief priests and the elders of the Jews presented evidence, asking for a sentence of condemnation against him.
B044C025V016	44	25	16	To ˻them˼ I replied that it was not the custom of the Romans to give up any man before the one who had been accused met his accusers face to face and received an opportunity for a defense concerning the accusation.
B044C025V017	44	25	17	Therefore, when they had assembled here, I made no delay; on the next day I sat down on the judgment seat and gave orders for the man to be brought.
B044C025V018	44	25	18	When they stood up, his accusers began bringing no charge concerning ˻him˼ of the evil deeds that I was suspecting,
B044C025V019	44	25	19	but they had some issues with him concerning their own religion, and concerning a certain Jesus, who was dead, whom Paul claimed to be alive.
B044C025V020	44	25	20	And because I was at a loss with regard to the investigation concerning these things, I asked if he was willing to go to Jerusalem and to be judged there concerning these things.
B044C025V021	44	25	21	But when Paul appealed that he be kept under guard for the decision of His Majesty the Emperor, I gave orders for him to be kept under guard until I could send him to Caesar.”
B044C025V022	44	25	22	So Agrippa said to Festus, “I want to hear the man myself also.” “Tomorrow,” he said, “you will hear him.”
B044C025V023	44	25	23	So on the next day, Agrippa and Bernice came with great pageantry and entered into the audience hall, along with military tribunes and the most prominent men of the city. And when Festus gave the order, Paul was brought in.
B044C025V024	44	25	24	And Festus said, “King Agrippa and all who are present with us, you see this man about whom the whole population of the Jews appealed to me, both in Jerusalem and here, shouting that he must not live any longer.
B044C025V025	44	25	25	But I understood that he had done nothing deserving death himself, and when this man appealed to His Majesty the Emperor, I decided to send him.
B044C025V026	44	25	26	I do not have anything definite to write to my lord about ˻him˼. Therefore I have brought him before you all—and especially before you, King Agrippa—so that after this preliminary hearing has taken place, I may have something to write.
B044C025V027	44	25	27	For it seems unreasonable to me to send a prisoner and not to indicate the charges against him.”
B044C026V001	44	26	1	So Agrippa said to Paul, “It is permitted for you to speak for yourself.” Then Paul extended his hand and began to defend himself:
B044C026V002	44	26	2	“Concerning all the things of which I am accused by the Jews, King Agrippa, I consider myself fortunate that before you I am about to defend myself today,
B044C026V003	44	26	3	because you are especially acquainted with both all the customs and controversial questions with respect to the Jews. Therefore I beg you to listen to me with patience.
B044C026V004	44	26	4	“Now all the Jews know my manner of life from my youth, that had taken place from the beginning among my own people and in Jerusalem,
B044C026V005	44	26	5	having known me for a long time, if they are willing to testify, that in accordance with the strictest party of our religion I lived as a Pharisee.
B044C026V006	44	26	6	And now I stand here on trial on the basis of hope in the promise made by God to our fathers,
B044C026V007	44	26	7	to which our twelve tribes hope to attain as they earnestly serve him night and day. Concerning this hope I am being accused by the Jews, O king!
B044C026V008	44	26	8	Why is it thought incredible by you people that God raises the dead?
B044C026V009	44	26	9	Indeed, I myself thought it was necessary to do many things opposed to the name of Jesus the Nazarene,
B044C026V010	44	26	10	which I also did in Jerusalem, and not only did I lock up many of the saints in prison, having received authority from the chief priests, but also when they were being executed, I cast my vote against them.
B044C026V011	44	26	11	And throughout all the synagogues I punished them often and tried to force them to blaspheme, and because I was enraged at them beyond measure, I was pursuing them even as far as to foreign cities.
B044C026V012	44	26	12	In ˻this activity˼ I was traveling to Damascus with the authority and full power of the chief priests.
B044C026V013	44	26	13	In the middle of the day along the road, O king, I saw a light from heaven, more than the brightness of the sun, shining around me and those who were traveling with me.
B044C026V014	44	26	14	And when we had all fallen to the ground, I heard a voice saying to me in the Aramaic language, ‘Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me? It is hard for you to kick against the goads!’
B044C026V015	44	26	15	So I said, ‘Who are you, Lord?’ And the Lord said, ‘I am Jesus whom you are persecuting.
B044C026V016	44	26	16	But get up and stand on your feet, because for this reason I have appeared to you, to appoint you a servant and witness both to the things in which you saw me and to the things in which I will appear to you,
B044C026V017	44	26	17	rescuing you from the people and from the Gentiles to whom I am sending you,
B044C026V018	44	26	18	to open their eyes so that they may turn from darkness to light and from the power of Satan to God, so that they may receive forgiveness of sins and a share among those who are sanctified by faith in me.’
B044C026V019	44	26	19	“Therefore, O King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision,
B044C026V020	44	26	20	but to those in Damascus first, and in Jerusalem and all the region of Judea and to the Gentiles, I proclaimed that they should repent and turn to God, doing deeds worthy of repentance.
B044C026V021	44	26	21	On account of these things the Jews seized me while I was in the temple courtsand were attempting to kill me.
B044C026V022	44	26	22	Therefore I have experienced help from God until this day, and I stand here testifying to both small and great, saying nothing except what both the prophets and Moses have said were going to happen,
B044C026V023	44	26	23	that the Christ was to suffer and that as the first of the resurrection from the dead, he was going to proclaim light both to the people and to the Gentiles.”
B044C026V024	44	26	24	And as he was saying these things in his defense, Festus said with a loud voice, “You are out of your mind, Paul! Your great learning ˻is driving˼ you ˻insane˼!”
B044C026V025	44	26	25	But Paul said, “I am not out of my mind, most excellent Festus, but am speaking words of truth and rationality.
B044C026V026	44	26	26	For the king knows about these things, to whom also I am speaking freely, for I am not convinced that any of these things in any way has escaped his notice, because this ˻was˼ not ˻done˼ in a corner.
B044C026V027	44	26	27	Do you believe the prophets, King Agrippa? I know that you believe.”
B044C026V028	44	26	28	But Agrippa said to Paul, “In a short time are you persuading me to become a Christian?”
B044C026V029	44	26	29	And Paul replied, “I pray to God, whether in a short time or in a long time, not only you but also all those who are listening to me today may become such people as I also am, except for these bonds!”
B044C026V030	44	26	30	Both the king and the governor got up, and Bernice and those who were sitting with them.
B044C026V031	44	26	31	And as they were going out, they were talking to one another, saying, “This man is not doing anything deserving death or imprisonment.”
B044C026V032	44	26	32	And Agrippa said to Festus, “This man could have been released if he had not appealed to Caesar.”
B044C027V001	44	27	1	And when it was decided that we would sail away to Italy, they handed over Paul and some other prisoners to a centurion ˻named˼ Julius of the Augustan Cohort.
B044C027V002	44	27	2	And we went aboard a ship from Adramyttium that was about to sail to the places along the coast of Asia and put out to sea. Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica, was with us.
B044C027V003	44	27	3	And on the next day, we put in at Sidon. And Julius, treating Paul kindly, allowed him to go to his friends ˻to be cared for˼.
B044C027V004	44	27	4	And from there we put out to sea and sailed under the lee of Cyprus, because the winds were against us.
B044C027V005	44	27	5	And after we had sailed across the open sea along Cilicia and Pamphylia, we put in at Myra in Lycia.
B044C027V006	44	27	6	And there the centurion found an Alexandrian ship sailing for Italy and put us ˻on board˼ it.
B044C027V007	44	27	7	And sailing slowly, in many days and with difficulty we came to Cnidus. Because the wind did not permit us to go further, we sailed under the lee of Crete off Salmone.
B044C027V008	44	27	8	And sailing along its coast with difficulty, we came to a certain place called Fair Havens, near which was the town of Lasea.
B044C027V009	44	27	9	And because considerable time had passed and the voyage was now dangerous because even the Fast was already over, Paul strongly recommended,
B044C027V010	44	27	10	saying to them, “Men, I perceive that the voyage is going ˻to end˼ with disaster and great loss, not only of the cargo and the ship, but also of our lives!”
B044C027V011	44	27	11	But the centurion was convinced even more by the shipmaster and the shipowner than by what was said by Paul.
B044C027V012	44	27	12	And because the harbor was unsuitable for spending the winter in, the majority decided on a plan to put out to sea from there, if somehow they could arrive at Phoenix, a harbor of Crete facing toward the southwest and toward the northwest, to spend the winter there.
B044C027V013	44	27	13	And when a southwest wind began to blow gently, because they thought they could accomplish their purpose, they weighed anchor and sailed close along Crete.
B044C027V014	44	27	14	But not long afterward a wind like a hurricane, called the northeaster, rushed down from it.
B044C027V015	44	27	15	And when the ship was caught and was not able to head into the wind, we gave way and were driven along.
B044C027V016	44	27	16	And running under the lee of a certain small island called Cauda, we were able with difficulty to get the ship’s boat under control.
B044C027V017	44	27	17	After hoisting ˻it up˼, they made use of supports to undergird the ship. And because they were afraid lest they run aground on the Syrtis, they lowered the sea anchor and thus were driven along.
B044C027V018	44	27	18	And because we were violently battered by the storm, on the next day˻they began˼ jettisoning the cargo,
B044C027V019	44	27	19	and on the third day they threw overboard the gear of the ship with their own hands.
B044C027V020	44	27	20	But when neither sun nor stars appeared for many days, and with not a little bad weather confronting us, finally all hope was abandoned that we would be saved.
B044C027V021	44	27	21	And because many were experiencing lack of appetite, at that time Paul stood up in their midst and said, “Men, you ought to have followed my advice not to put out to sea from Crete, and thus avoided this damage and loss!
B044C027V022	44	27	22	And now I urge you to cheer up, for there will be no loss of life from among you, but only of the ship.
B044C027V023	44	27	23	For this night an angel of the God whose I am and whom I serve came to me,
B044C027V024	44	27	24	saying, ‘Do not be afraid, Paul! It is necessary for you to stand before Caesar, and behold, God has graciously granted you all who are sailing with you.’
B044C027V025	44	27	25	Therefore keep up your courage, men, for I believe God that it will be like this—according to ˻the˼ way it was told to me.
B044C027V026	44	27	26	But it is necessary that we run aground on some island.”
B044C027V027	44	27	27	And when the fourteenth night had come, as we were being driven in the Adriatic Sea about the middle of the night, the sailors suspected ˻they were approaching some land˼.
B044C027V028	44	27	28	And taking soundings, they found twenty fathoms. So going on a little further and taking soundings again, they found fifteen fathoms.
B044C027V029	44	27	29	And because they were afraid lest somewhere we run aground against rough places, they threw down four anchors from the stern and prayed for day to come.
B044C027V030	44	27	30	And when the sailors were seeking to escape from the ship and were lowering the ship’s boat into the sea, pretending as if they were going to lay out anchors from the bow,
B044C027V031	44	27	31	Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, “Unless these men remain with the ship, you cannot be saved!”
B044C027V032	44	27	32	Then the soldiers cut away the ropes of the ship’s boat and let it fall away.
B044C027V033	44	27	33	And until the day was about to come, Paul was urging them all to take some food, saying, “Today is the fourteenth day you have waited anxiously, and you have continued without eating, having taken nothing.
B044C027V034	44	27	34	Therefore I urge you to take some food, for this is necessary for your preservation. For not a hair from your head will be lost.”
B044C027V035	44	27	35	And after he said these things and took bread, he gave thanks to God in front of them all, and after breaking it, he began to eat.
B044C027V036	44	27	36	So they all were encouraged and partook of food themselves.
B044C027V037	44	27	37	(Now we were in all two hundred seventy six persons on the ship.)
B044C027V038	44	27	38	And when they had eaten their fill of food, they lightened the ship by throwing the wheat into the sea.
B044C027V039	44	27	39	Now when day came, they did not recognize the land, but they noticed a certain bay having a beach, onto which they decided to run the ship ashore if they could.
B044C027V040	44	27	40	And slipping the anchors, they left them in the sea, at the same time loosening the ropes of the steering oars. And hoisting the foresail to the wind that was blowing, they held course for the beach.
B044C027V041	44	27	41	But falling into a place of crosscurrents, they ran the ship aground. And the bow stuck fast and stayed immovable, but the stern was being broken up by the force of the waves.
B044C027V042	44	27	42	Now the plan of the soldiers was that they would kill the prisoners lest any escape by swimming away,
B044C027V043	44	27	43	but the centurion, because he wanted to save Paul, prevented them ˻from doing what they intended˼, and gave orders that those who were able to swim should jump in first to get to the land,
B044C027V044	44	27	44	and then the rest, some of whom floated on planks and some of whom on anything that was from the ship. And in this way all were brought safely to the land.
B044C028V001	44	28	1	And after we were brought safely through, then we found out that the island was called Malta.
B044C028V002	44	28	2	And the local inhabitants showed ˻extraordinary˼ kindness to us, for they lit a fire and welcomed us all, because of the rain that had begun and because of the cold.
B044C028V003	44	28	3	And when Paul had gathered a large number of sticks and was placing them on the fire, a viper came out because of the heat and fastened itself on his hand.
B044C028V004	44	28	4	And when the local people saw the creature hanging from his hand, they began saying to one another, “Doubtless this man is a murderer whom, although he was rescued from the sea, Justice has not permitted to live!”
B044C028V005	44	28	5	He, in turn, shook off the creature into the fire and suffered no harm.
B044C028V006	44	28	6	But they were expecting that he was going to swell up or suddenly to fall down dead. So after they had waited for a long time and saw nothing unusual happen to him, they changed their minds and began saying that he was a god.
B044C028V007	44	28	7	Now in the regions around that place were fields belonging to the chief official of the island, ˻named˼ Publius, who welcomed us and entertained us hospitably for three days.
B044C028V008	44	28	8	And it happened that the father of Publius was lying down, afflicted with fever and dysentery. Paul went to ˻him˼ and after praying, he placed his hands on him and healed him.
B044C028V009	44	28	9	And after this had taken place, the rest of those on the island who had diseases were coming and being healed also.
B044C028V010	44	28	10	They also honored us with many honors, and when we were putting out to sea, they gave us the things˻we needed˼.
B044C028V011	44	28	11	Now after three months we put out to sea in a ship that had wintered at the island, an Alexandrian one˻with the twin gods Castor and Pollux as its insignia˼.
B044C028V012	44	28	12	And putting in at Syracuse, we stayed there three days.
B044C028V013	44	28	13	From there we got underway and arrived at Rhegium, and after one day a south wind came up and on the second day we came to Puteoli,
B044C028V014	44	28	14	where we found brothers, and were implored to stay with them seven days. And in this way we came to Rome.
B044C028V015	44	28	15	And from there the brothers, when they heard the news about us, came to meet us as far as the Forum of Appius and Three Taverns. When he saw them, Paul gave thanks to God and took courage.
B044C028V016	44	28	16	And when we entered into Rome, Paul was allowed to stay by himself with the soldier who was guarding him.
B044C028V017	44	28	17	Now it happened that after three days, he called together those who were the most prominent of the Jews. And when they had assembled, he said to them, “Men and brothers, although I had done nothing against our people or the customs of our fathers, from Jerusalem I was delivered as a prisoner into the hands of the Romans,
B044C028V018	44	28	18	who, when they had examined me, were wanting to release me, because there was no basis for an accusation worthy of death with me.
B044C028V019	44	28	19	But because the Jews objected, I was forced to appeal to Caesar (not as if I had any charge to bring against my own people).
B044C028V020	44	28	20	Therefore for this reason I have requested to see you and to speak with you, for because of the hope of Israel I am wearing this chain!”
B044C028V021	44	28	21	And they said to him, “We have received no letters about you from Judea, nor has any of the brothers come and reported or spoken anything evil about you.
B044C028V022	44	28	22	But we would like to hear from you what you think, for concerning this sect it is known to us that it is spoken against everywhere.”
B044C028V023	44	28	23	And when they had set a day with him, many more came to him at his lodging place, to whom he was explaining from early in the morning until evening, testifying about the kingdom of God and attempting to convince them about Jesus from both the law of Moses and the prophets.
B044C028V024	44	28	24	And some were convinced by what was said, but others refused to believe.
B044C028V025	44	28	25	So being in disagreement with one another, they began to leave after Paul made one statement: “The Holy Spirit spoke rightly through the prophet Isaiah to your fathers,
B044C028V026	44	28	26	saying,‘Go to this people and say,“˻You will keep on hearing˼ and will never understand,and ˻you will keep on seeing˼ and will never perceive.
B044C028V027	44	28	27	For the heart of this people has become dull,and with their ears they hear with difficulty,and they have shut their eyes,lest they see with their eyes,and hear with their ears,and understand with their heart,and turn, and I would heal them.” ’
B044C028V028	44	28	28	Therefore let it be known to you that this salvation of God has been sent to the Gentiles. They also will listen!”
B044C028V030	44	28	30	So he stayed two whole years in his own rented house, and welcomed all who came to him,
B044C028V031	44	28	31	proclaiming the kingdom of God and teaching the things concerning the Lord Jesus Christ with all boldness, without hindrance.
B045C001V001	45	1	1	Paul, a slave of Christ Jesus, called to be an apostle, set apart for the gospel of God,
B045C001V002	45	1	2	which he promised previously through his prophets in the holy scriptures,
B045C001V003	45	1	3	concerning his Son, who was born ˻a descendant˼ of David according to the flesh,
B045C001V004	45	1	4	who was declared Son of God in power according to ˻the Holy Spirit˼ by the resurrection from the dead of Jesus Christ our Lord,
B045C001V005	45	1	5	through whom we have received grace and apostleship for the obedience of faith among all the Gentiles on behalf of his name,
B045C001V006	45	1	6	among whom you also are the called of Jesus Christ.
B045C001V007	45	1	7	To all those in Rome who are loved by God, called to be saints. Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C001V008	45	1	8	First, I give thanks to my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because your faith is being proclaimed in the whole world.
B045C001V009	45	1	9	For God, whom I serve with my spirit in the gospel of his Son, is my witness, how constantly I make mention of you,
B045C001V010	45	1	10	always asking in my prayers if somehow now at last I may succeed to come to you in the will of God.
B045C001V011	45	1	11	For I desire to see you, in order that I may impart some spiritual gift to you, in order to strengthen you,
B045C001V012	45	1	12	that is, to be encouraged together with you through ˻our mutual faith˼, both yours and mine.
B045C001V013	45	1	13	Now I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, that often I intended to come to you, and was prevented until now, in order that I might have some fruit among you also, just as also among the rest of the Gentiles.
B045C001V014	45	1	14	I am under obligation both to Greeks and to barbarians, both to the wise and to the foolish.
B045C001V015	45	1	15	Thus ˻I am eager˼ to proclaim the gospel also to you who are in Rome.
B045C001V016	45	1	16	For I am not ashamed of the gospel, for it is the power of God for salvation to everyone who believes, to the Jew first and also to the Greek.
B045C001V017	45	1	17	For the righteousness of God is revealed in it from faith to faith, just as it is written, “But the one who is righteous by faith will live.”
B045C001V018	45	1	18	For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all impiety and unrighteousness of people, who suppress the truth in unrighteousness,
B045C001V019	45	1	19	because what can be known about God is evident among them, for God made it clear to them.
B045C001V020	45	1	20	For from the creation of the world, his invisible attributes, both his eternal power and deity, are discerned clearly, being understood in the things created, so that they are without excuse.
B045C001V021	45	1	21	For although they knew God, they did not honor him as God or give thanks, but they became futile in their reasoning, and their senseless hearts were darkened.
B045C001V022	45	1	22	Claiming to be wise, they became fools,
B045C001V023	45	1	23	and exchanged the glory of the immortal God with the likeness of an image of mortal human beings and birds and quadrupeds and reptiles.
B045C001V024	45	1	24	Therefore God gave them over in the desires of their hearts to immorality, that their bodies would be dishonored among themselves,
B045C001V025	45	1	25	who exchanged the truth of God with a lie, and worshiped and served the creation rather than the Creator, who is blessed for eternity. Amen.
B045C001V026	45	1	26	Because of this, God gave them over to degrading passions, for their females exchanged the natural relations for those contrary to nature,
B045C001V027	45	1	27	and likewise also the males, abandoning the natural relations with the female, were inflamed in their desire toward one another, males with males committing the shameless deed, and receiving in themselves the penalty that was necessary for their error.
B045C001V028	45	1	28	And just as they did not see fit ˻to recognize God˼, God gave them over to a debased mind, to do the things that are not proper,
B045C001V029	45	1	29	being filled with all unrighteousness, wickedness, greediness, malice, full of envy, murder, strife, deceit, malevolence. They are gossipers,
B045C001V030	45	1	30	slanderers, haters of God, insolent, arrogant, boasters, contrivers of evil, disobedient to parents,
B045C001V031	45	1	31	senseless, faithless, unfeeling, unmerciful,
B045C001V032	45	1	32	who, although they know the requirements of God, that those who do such things are worthy of death, not only do they do the same things, but also they approve of those who do them.
B045C002V001	45	2	1	Therefore you are without excuse, O man, every one of you who passes judgment. For in that which you pass judgment on someone else, you condemn yourself, for you who are passing judgment are doing the same things.
B045C002V002	45	2	2	Now we know that the judgment of God is according to truth against those who do such things.
B045C002V003	45	2	3	But do you think this, O man who passes judgment on those who do such things, and who does the same things, that you will escape the judgment of God?
B045C002V004	45	2	4	Or do you despise the wealth of his kindness and forbearance and patience, not knowing that the kindness of God leads you to repentence?
B045C002V005	45	2	5	But because of your stubbornness and unrepentant heart, you are storing up for yourself wrath in the day of wrath and of the revelation of the righteous judgment of God,
B045C002V006	45	2	6	who will reward each one according to his works:
B045C002V007	45	2	7	to those who, by perseverance in good work, seek glory and honor and immortality, eternal life,
B045C002V008	45	2	8	but to those who act from selfish ambition and who disobey the truth, but who obey unrighteousness, wrath and anger.
B045C002V009	45	2	9	There will be affliction and distress for every ˻human being˼ who does evil, of the Jew first and of the Greek,
B045C002V010	45	2	10	but glory and honor and peace to everyone who does good, to the Jew first and to the Greek.
B045C002V011	45	2	11	For there is no partiality with God.
B045C002V012	45	2	12	For as many as have sinned without law will also perish without law, and as many as have sinned under the law will be judged by the law.
B045C002V013	45	2	13	For it is not the hearers of the law who are righteous in the sight of God, but the doers of the law will be declared righteous.
B045C002V014	45	2	14	For whenever the Gentiles, who do not have the law, do by nature the things of the law, these, although they do not have the law, are a law to themselves,
B045C002V015	45	2	15	who show the work of the law written on their hearts, their conscience bearing witness and their thoughts one after another accusing or even defending them
B045C002V016	45	2	16	on the day when God judges the secret things of people, according to my gospel, through Christ Jesus.
B045C002V017	45	2	17	But if you call yourself a Jew and rely on the law and boast in God
B045C002V018	45	2	18	and know his will and approve the things that are superior, because you are instructed by the law,
B045C002V019	45	2	19	and are confident that you yourself are a guide of the blind, a light of those in darkness,
B045C002V020	45	2	20	an instructor of the foolish, a teacher of the immature, having the embodiment of knowledge and of the truth in the law.
B045C002V021	45	2	21	Therefore, the one who teaches someone else, do you not teach yourself? The one who preaches not to steal, do you steal?
B045C002V022	45	2	22	The one who says not to commit adultery, do you commit adultery? The one who abhors idols, do you rob temples?
B045C002V023	45	2	23	Who boast in the law, by the transgression of the law you dishonor God!
B045C002V024	45	2	24	For just as it is written, “The name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles because of you.”
B045C002V025	45	2	25	For circumcision is of value if you do the law, but if you should be a transgressor of the law, your circumcision has become uncircumcision.
B045C002V026	45	2	26	Therefore, if the uncircumcised person follows the requirements of the law, will not his uncircumcision be credited for circumcision?
B045C002V027	45	2	27	And the uncircumcised person by nature who carries out the law will judge you who, though provided with ˻the precise written code˼ and circumcision are a transgressor of the law.
B045C002V028	45	2	28	For the Jew is not ˻one outwardly˼, nor is circumcision ˻outwardly˼, in the flesh.
B045C002V029	45	2	29	But the Jew ˻is one inwardly˼, and circumcision is of the heart, by the Spirit, not by the letter, whose praise is not from people but from God.
B045C003V001	45	3	1	Therefore, what is the advantage of the Jew, or what is the use of circumcision?
B045C003V002	45	3	2	Much in every way. For first, that they were entrusted with the oracles of God.
B045C003V003	45	3	3	˻What is the result˼ if some refused to believe? Their unbelief will not nullify the faithfulness of God, will it?
B045C003V004	45	3	4	May it never be! But let God be true but every human being a liar, just as it is written,“In order that you may be justified in your words,and may prevail when you are judged.”
B045C003V005	45	3	5	But if our unrighteousness demonstrates the righteousness of God, what shall we say? God, who inflicts wrath, is not unjust, is he? (I am speaking according to a human perspective.)
B045C003V006	45	3	6	May it never be! For otherwise, how will God judge the world?
B045C003V007	45	3	7	But if by my lying, the truth of God abounded to his glory, why am I also still condemned as a sinner?
B045C003V008	45	3	8	And why not (as we are slandered, and as some affirm that we say), “Let us do evil, in order that good may come of it? Their condemnation is just!
B045C003V009	45	3	9	What then? Do we have an advantage? Not at all. For we have already charged both Jews and Greeks are all under sin,
B045C003V010	45	3	10	just as it is written,“There is no one righteous, not even one;
B045C003V011	45	3	11	there is no one who understands;there is no one who seeks God.
B045C003V012	45	3	12	All have turned aside together; they have become worthless;There is no one who practices kindness;there is not even one.
B045C003V013	45	3	13	Their throat is an opened grave;they deceive with their tongues;the venom of asps is under their lips,
B045C003V014	45	3	14	whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness.
B045C003V015	45	3	15	Their feet are swift to shed blood;
B045C003V016	45	3	16	destruction and distress are in their paths,
B045C003V017	45	3	17	and they have not known the way of peace.
B045C003V018	45	3	18	The fear of God is not before their eyes.”
B045C003V019	45	3	19	Now we know that whatever the law says, it speaks to those under the law, in order that every mouth may be closed and the whole world may become accountable to God.
B045C003V020	45	3	20	For by the works of the law ˻no person will be declared righteous˼ before him, for through the law comes knowledge of sin.
B045C003V021	45	3	21	But now, apart from the law, the righteousness of God has been revealed, being testified about by the law and the prophets—
B045C003V022	45	3	22	that is, the righteousness of God through faith in Jesus Christ to all who believe. For there is no distinction,
B045C003V023	45	3	23	for all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God,
B045C003V024	45	3	24	being justified as a gift by his grace, through the redemption which is in Christ Jesus,
B045C003V025	45	3	25	whom God made publicly available as the mercy seat through faith in his blood, for a demonstration of his righteousness, because of the passing over of previously committed sins,
B045C003V026	45	3	26	in the forbearance of God, for the demonstration of his righteousness in the present time, so that he should be just and the one who justifies the person by faith in Jesus.
B045C003V027	45	3	27	Therefore, where is boasting? It has been excluded. By what kind of law? Of works? No, but by a law of faith.
B045C003V028	45	3	28	For we consider a person to be justified by faith apart from the works of the law.
B045C003V029	45	3	29	Or is God the God of the Jews only? Is he not also the God of the Gentiles? Yes, also of the Gentiles,
B045C003V030	45	3	30	since God is one, who will justify ˻those who are circumcised˼ by faith and ˻those who are uncircumcised˼ through faith.
B045C003V031	45	3	31	Therefore, do we nullify the law through faith? May it never be! But we uphold the law.
B045C004V001	45	4	1	What then shall we say that Abraham, our ancestor according to the flesh, has found?
B045C004V002	45	4	2	For if Abraham was justified by works, he has something to boast about, but not before God.
B045C004V003	45	4	3	For what does the scripture say? “And Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him for righteousness.”
B045C004V004	45	4	4	Now to the one who works, his pay is not credited according to grace, but according to his due.
B045C004V005	45	4	5	But to the one who does not work, but who believes in the one who justifies the ungodly, his faith is credited for righteousness,
B045C004V006	45	4	6	just as David also speaks about the blessing of the person to whom God credits righteousness apart from works:
B045C004V007	45	4	7	“Blessed are they whose lawless deeds have been forgiven,and whose sins are covered over.
B045C004V008	45	4	8	Blessed is the person against whom the Lord will never count sin.”
B045C004V009	45	4	9	Therefore, is this blessing for ˻those who are circumcised˼, or also for ˻those who are uncircumcised˼? For we say, “Faith was credited to Abraham for righteousness.”
B045C004V010	45	4	10	How then was it credited? While he was ˻circumcised˼ or ˻uncircumcised˼? Not ˻while circumcised˼ but ˻while uncircumcised˼!
B045C004V011	45	4	11	And he received the sign of circumcision as a seal of the righteousness by faith which he had˻while uncircumcised˼, so that he could be the father of all who believe ˻although they are uncircumcised˼, so that righteousness could be credited to them also,
B045C004V012	45	4	12	and the father ˻of those who are circumcised˼ to those who are not only from the circumcision, but who also follow in the footsteps of the faith of our father Abraham ˻which he had while uncircumcised˼.
B045C004V013	45	4	13	For the promise to Abraham or to his descendants, that he would be heir of the world, was not through the law, but through the righteousness by faith.
B045C004V014	45	4	14	For if those of the law are heirs, faith is rendered void and the promise is nullified.
B045C004V015	45	4	15	For the law produces wrath, but where there is no law, neither is there transgression.
B045C004V016	45	4	16	Because of this, it is by faith, in order that it may be according to grace, so that the promise may be secure to all the descendants, not only to those of the law, but also to those of the faith of Abraham, who is the father of us all
B045C004V017	45	4	17	(just as it is written, “I have made you the father of many nations”) before God, in whom he believed, the one who makes the dead alive and who calls the things that are not as though they are,
B045C004V018	45	4	18	who against hope believed in hope, so that he became the father of many nations, according to what was said, “so will your descendants be.”
B045C004V019	45	4	19	And not being weak in faith, he considered his own body already as good as dead, because he was approximately a hundred years old, and the deadness of Sarah’s womb.
B045C004V020	45	4	20	And he did not waver in unbelief at the promise of God, but was strengthened in faith, giving glory to God
B045C004V021	45	4	21	and being fully convinced that what he had promised, he was also able to do.
B045C004V022	45	4	22	Therefore, indeed, it was credited to him for righteousness.
B045C004V023	45	4	23	But it was not written for the sake of him alone that it was credited to him,
B045C004V024	45	4	24	but also for the sake of us to whom it is going to be credited, to those who believe in the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead,
B045C004V025	45	4	25	who was handed over on account of our trespasses, and was raised up in the interest of our justification.
B045C005V001	45	5	1	Therefore, because we have been declared righteous by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B045C005V002	45	5	2	through whom also we have obtained access by faith into this grace in which we stand, and we boast in the hope of the glory of God.
B045C005V003	45	5	3	And not only this, but we also boast in our afflictions, because we know that affliction produces patient endurance,
B045C005V004	45	5	4	and patient endurance, proven character, and proven character, hope,
B045C005V005	45	5	5	and hope does not disappoint, because the love of God has been poured out in our hearts through the Holy Spirit who was given to us.
B045C005V006	45	5	6	For while we were still helpless, yet at the proper time Christ died for the ungodly.
B045C005V007	45	5	7	For only rarely will someone die on behalf of a righteous person (for on behalf of a good person possibly someone might even dare to die),
B045C005V008	45	5	8	but God demonstrates his own love for us, in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.
B045C005V009	45	5	9	Therefore, by much more, because we have been declared righteous now by his blood, we will be saved through him from the wrath.
B045C005V010	45	5	10	For if, while we were enemies, we were reconciled to God through the death of his Son, by much more, having been reconciled, we will be saved by his life.
B045C005V011	45	5	11	And not only this, but also we are boasting in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have now received the reconciliation.
B045C005V012	45	5	12	Because of this, just as sin entered into the world through one man, and death through sin, so also death spread to all people because all sinned.
B045C005V013	45	5	13	For until the law, sin was in the world, but sin is not charged to one’s account when there is no law.
B045C005V014	45	5	14	But death reigned from Adam until Moses even over those who did not sin in the likeness of the transgression of Adam, who is a type of the one who is to come.
B045C005V015	45	5	15	˻But the gift is not like the trespass˼, for if by the trespass of the one, the many died, by much more did the grace of God and the gift by the grace of the one man, Jesus Christ, multiply to the many.
B045C005V016	45	5	16	And the gift is not as through the one who sinned, for on the one hand, judgment from the one sinled to condemnation, but the gift, from many trespasses, led to justification.
B045C005V017	45	5	17	For if by the trespass of the one man, death reigned through the one man, much more will those who receive the abundance of grace and of the gift of righteousness reign in life through the one, Jesus Christ.
B045C005V018	45	5	18	Consequently therefore, as through one trespass came condemnation to all people, so also through one righteous deed came justification of life to all people.
B045C005V019	45	5	19	For just as through the disobedience of the one man, the many were made sinners, so also through the obedience of the one, the many will be made righteous.
B045C005V020	45	5	20	Now the law came in as a side issue, in order that the trespass could increase, but where sin increased, grace was present in greater abundance,
B045C005V021	45	5	21	so that just as sin reigned in death, so also grace would reign through righteousness to eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
B045C006V001	45	6	1	What therefore shall we say? Shall we continue in sin, in order that grace may increase?
B045C006V002	45	6	2	May it never be! How can we who died to sin still live in it?
B045C006V003	45	6	3	Or do you not know that as many as were baptized into Christ Jesus were baptized into his death?
B045C006V004	45	6	4	Therefore we have been buried with him through baptism into death, in order that just as Christ was raised from the dead through the glory of the Father, so also we may live ˻a new way of life˼.
B045C006V005	45	6	5	For if we have become identified with him in the likeness of his death, certainly also we will be identified with him in the likeness of his resurrection,
B045C006V006	45	6	6	knowing this, that our old man was crucified together with him, in order that the body of sin may be done away with, that we may no longer be enslaved to sin.
B045C006V007	45	6	7	For the one who has died has been freed from sin.
B045C006V008	45	6	8	Now if we died with Christ, we believe that we will also live with him,
B045C006V009	45	6	9	knowing that Christ, because he has been raised from the dead, is going to die no more, death no longer being master over him.
B045C006V010	45	6	10	For that death he died, he died to sin once and never again, but that life he lives, he lives to God.
B045C006V011	45	6	11	So also you, consider yourselves to be dead to sin, but alive to God in Christ Jesus.
B045C006V012	45	6	12	Therefore do not let sin reign in your mortal body, so that you obey its desires,
B045C006V013	45	6	13	and do not present your members to sin as instruments of unrighteousness, but present yourselves to God as those who are alive from the dead, and your members to God as instruments of righteousness.
B045C006V014	45	6	14	For sin will not be master over you, because you are not under law, but under grace.
B045C006V015	45	6	15	What then? Shall we sin because we are not under law but under grace? May it never be!
B045C006V016	45	6	16	Do you not know that to whomever you present yourselves as slaves for obedience, you are slaves to whomever you obey, whether sin, leading to death, or obedience, leading to righteousness?
B045C006V017	45	6	17	But thanks be to God that you were slaves of sin, but you have obeyed from the heart the pattern of teaching to which you were entrusted,
B045C006V018	45	6	18	and having been set free from sin, you became enslaved to righteousness.
B045C006V019	45	6	19	(I am speaking in human terms because of the weakness of your flesh.) For just as you presented your members as slaves to immorality and lawlessness, leading to lawlessness, so now present your members as slaves to righteousness, leading to sanctification.
B045C006V020	45	6	20	For when you were slaves of sin, you were free with respect to righteousness.
B045C006V021	45	6	21	Therefore what sort of fruit did you have then, about which you are now ashamed? For the end of those thingsis death.
B045C006V022	45	6	22	But now, having been set free from sin and having been enslaved to God, you have your fruit leading to sanctification, and its end is eternal life.
B045C006V023	45	6	23	For the compensation due sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C007V001	45	7	1	Or do you not know, brothers (for I am speaking to those who know the law), that the law is master of a person for as long a time as he lives?
B045C007V002	45	7	2	For the married woman is bound by law to her husband while he lives, but if her husband dies, she is released from the law of the husband.
B045C007V003	45	7	3	Therefore as a result, if she belongs to another man while her husband is living, she will be called an adulteress. But if her husband dies, she is free from the law, so that she is not an adulteress if she belongs to another man.
B045C007V004	45	7	4	So then, my brothers, you also were brought to death with respect to the law through the body of Christ, so that you may belong to another, to the one who was raised from the dead, in order that we may bear fruit for God.
B045C007V005	45	7	5	For when we were in the flesh, sinful desires were working through the law in our members, to bear fruit for death.
B045C007V006	45	7	6	But now we have been released from the law, because we have died to that by which we were bound, so that we may serve in newness of the Spirit and not in oldness of the letter of the law.
B045C007V007	45	7	7	What then shall we say? Is the law sin? May it never be! But I would not have known sin except through the law, for I would not have known covetousness if the law had not said, “Do not covet.”
B045C007V008	45	7	8	But sin, seizing an opportunity through the commandment, produced in me all kinds of covetousness. For apart from the law, sin is dead.
B045C007V009	45	7	9	And I was alive once, apart from the law, but when the commandment came, sin sprang to life
B045C007V010	45	7	10	and I died, and this commandment which was to lead to life was found with respect to me to lead to death.
B045C007V011	45	7	11	For sin, seizing the opportunity through the commandment, deceived me and through it killed me.
B045C007V012	45	7	12	So then, the law is holy, and the commandment is holy and righteous and good.
B045C007V013	45	7	13	Therefore, did that which is good become death to me? May it never be! Rather it was sin, in order that it might be recognized as sin, producing death through what is good for me, in order that sin might become sinful to an extraordinary degree through the commandment.
B045C007V014	45	7	14	For we know that the law is spiritual, but I am fleshly, ˻sold into slavery to sin˼.
B045C007V015	45	7	15	For what I am doing I do not understand, because what I want to do, this I do not practice, but what I hate, this I do.
B045C007V016	45	7	16	But if what I do not want to do, this I do, I agree with the law that it is good.
B045C007V017	45	7	17	But now I am no longer the one doing it, but sin that lives in me.
B045C007V018	45	7	18	For I know that good does not live in me, that is, in my flesh. For the willing is present in me, but the doing of the good is not.
B045C007V019	45	7	19	For the good that I want to do, I do not do, but the evil that I do not want to do, this I do.
B045C007V020	45	7	20	But if what I do not want to do, this I am doing, I am no longer the one doing it, but sin that lives in me.
B045C007V021	45	7	21	Consequently, I find the principle with me, the one who wants to do good, that evil is present with me.
B045C007V022	45	7	22	For I joyfully agree with the law of God in my inner person,
B045C007V023	45	7	23	but I observe another law in my members, at war with the law of my mind and making me captive to the law of sin that exists in my members.
B045C007V024	45	7	24	Wretched man that I am! Who will rescue me from this body of death?
B045C007V025	45	7	25	But thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, I myself with my mind am enslaved to the law of God, but with my flesh I am enslaved to the law of sin.
B045C008V001	45	8	1	Consequently, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.
B045C008V002	45	8	2	For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus has set you free from the law of sin and death.
B045C008V003	45	8	3	For what was impossible for the law, in that it was weak through the flesh, God did. By sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh and concerning sin, he condemned sin in the flesh,
B045C008V004	45	8	4	in order that the requirement of the law would be fulfilled in us, who do not live according to the flesh but according to the Spirit.
B045C008V005	45	8	5	For those who are living according to the flesh are intent on the things of the flesh, but those who are living according to the Spirit are intent on the things of the Spirit.
B045C008V006	45	8	6	For the mindset of the flesh is death, but the mindset of the Spirit is life and peace,
B045C008V007	45	8	7	because the mindset of the flesh is enmity toward God, for it is not subjected to the law of God, for it is not able to do so,
B045C008V008	45	8	8	and those who are in the flesh are not able to please God.
B045C008V009	45	8	9	But you are not in the flesh but in the Spirit, if indeed the Spirit of God lives in you. But if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, this person ˻does not belong to him˼.
B045C008V010	45	8	10	But if Christ is in you, the body is dead because of sin, but the Spirit is life because of righteousness.
B045C008V011	45	8	11	And if the Spirit of the one who raised Jesus from the dead lives in you, the one who raised Christ from the dead will also make alive your mortal bodies through his Spirit who lives in you.
B045C008V012	45	8	12	So then, brothers, we are obligated not to the flesh, to live according to the flesh.
B045C008V013	45	8	13	For if you live according to the flesh, you are going to die, but if by the Spirit you put to death the deeds of the body, you will live.
B045C008V014	45	8	14	For all those who are led by the Spirit of God, these are sons of God.
B045C008V015	45	8	15	For you have not received a spirit of slavery leading to fear again, but you have received the Spirit of adoption, by whom we cry out, “Abba! Father!”
B045C008V016	45	8	16	The Spirit himself confirms to our spirit that we are children of God,
B045C008V017	45	8	17	and if children, also heirs—heirs of God and fellow heirs with Christ, if indeed we suffer together with him so that we may also be glorified together with him.
B045C008V018	45	8	18	For I consider that the sufferings of the present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory that is about to be revealed to us.
B045C008V019	45	8	19	For the eagerly expecting creation awaits eagerly the revelation of the sons of God.
B045C008V020	45	8	20	For the creation has been subjected to futility, not willingly, but because of the one who subjected it, in hope
B045C008V021	45	8	21	that the creation itself also will be set free from its servility to decay, into the glorious freedom of the children of God.
B045C008V022	45	8	22	For we know that the whole creation groans together and suffers agony together until now.
B045C008V023	45	8	23	Not only this, but we ourselves also, having the first fruits of the Spirit, even we ourselves groan within ourselves while we await eagerly our adoption, the redemption of our body.
B045C008V024	45	8	24	For in hope we were saved, but hope that is seen is not hope, for who hopes for what he sees?
B045C008V025	45	8	25	But if we hope for what we do not see, we await it eagerly with patient endurance.
B045C008V026	45	8	26	And likewise also, the Spirit helps us in our weakness, for we do not know how to pray as one ought, but the Spirit himself intercedes for uswith unexpressed groanings.
B045C008V027	45	8	27	And the one who searches our hearts knows what the mindset of the Spirit is, because he intercedes on behalf of the saints according to the will of God.
B045C008V028	45	8	28	And we know that all things work together for good for those who love God, for those who are called according to his purpose,
B045C008V029	45	8	29	because those whom he foreknew, he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his Son, so that he should be the firstborn among many brothers.
B045C008V030	45	8	30	And those whom he predestined, these he also called, and those whom he called, these he also justified, and those whom he justified, these he also glorified.
B045C008V031	45	8	31	What then shall we say about these things? If God is for us, who can be against us?
B045C008V032	45	8	32	Indeed, he who did not spare his own Son, but gave him up for us all, how will he not also, together with him, freely give us all things?
B045C008V033	45	8	33	Who will bring charges against God’s elect? God is the one who justifies.
B045C008V034	45	8	34	Who is the one who condemns? Christ Jesus is the one who died, and more than that, who was raised, who is also at the right hand of God, who also intercedes for us.
B045C008V035	45	8	35	Who will separate us from the love of Christ? Will affliction or distress or persecution or hunger or lack of sufficient clothing or danger or the sword?
B045C008V036	45	8	36	Just as it is written,“On account of you we are being put to death the whole day long;we are considered as sheep for slaughter.”
B045C008V037	45	8	37	No, but in all these things we prevail completely through the one who loved us.
B045C008V038	45	8	38	For I am convinced that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor rulers, nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,
B045C008V039	45	8	39	nor height, nor depth, nor any other created thing, will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C009V001	45	9	1	I am telling the truth in Christ—I am not lying; my conscience bears witness to me in the Holy Spirit—
B045C009V002	45	9	2	that my grief is great and there is constant distress in my heart.
B045C009V003	45	9	3	For I could wish myself to be accursed from Christ for the sake of my brothers, my fellow countrymen according to the flesh,
B045C009V004	45	9	4	who are Israelites, to whom belong the adoption, and the glory, and the covenants, and the giving of the law, and the temple service, and the promises,
B045C009V005	45	9	5	to whom belong the patriarchs, and from whom is the Christ according to human descent, who is God over all, blessed ˻forever˼! Amen.
B045C009V006	45	9	6	But it is not as if the word of God had failed. For not all those who are descended from Israel are truly Israel,
B045C009V007	45	9	7	nor are they all children because they are descendants of Abraham, but “In Isaac will your descendants be named.”
B045C009V008	45	9	8	That is, it is not the children ˻by human descent˼who are children of God, but the children of the promise are counted as descendants.
B045C009V009	45	9	9	For the statement of the promise is this: “At this time I will return and ˻Sarah will have˼ a son.”
B045C009V010	45	9	10	And not only this, but also when Rebecca conceived children by one man, Isaac our father—
B045C009V011	45	9	11	for although they had not yet been born, or done anything good or evil, in order that the purpose of God according to election might remain,
B045C009V012	45	9	12	not by works but by the one who calls—it was said to her, “The older will serve the younger,”
B045C009V013	45	9	13	just as it is written, “Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated.”
B045C009V014	45	9	14	What then shall we say? There is no injustice with God, is there? May it never be!
B045C009V015	45	9	15	For to Moses he says, “I will have mercy on whomever I have mercy, and I will have compassion on whomever I have compassion.”
B045C009V016	45	9	16	Consequently therefore, ˻it does not depend on the˼ one who wills or on the one who runs, but on God who shows mercy.
B045C009V017	45	9	17	For the scripture says to Pharaoh, “For this very reason I have raised you up, so that I may demonstrate my power in you, and so that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth.”
B045C009V018	45	9	18	Consequently therefore, he has mercy on whomever he wishes, and he hardens whomever he wishes.
B045C009V019	45	9	19	Therefore you will say to me, “Why then does he still find fault? For who has resisted his will?
B045C009V020	45	9	20	On the contrary, O man, who are you who answers back to God? Will what is molded say to the one who molded it, “Why did you make me like this”?
B045C009V021	45	9	21	Or does the potter not have authority over the clay, to make from the same lump a vessel that is for ˻honorable use˼ and one that is for ˻ordinary use˼?
B045C009V022	45	9	22	And what if God, wanting to demonstrate his wrath and to make known his power, endured with much patience vessels of wrath prepared for destruction?
B045C009V023	45	9	23	And he did so in order that he could make known the riches of his glory upon vessels of mercy that he prepared beforehand for glory,
B045C009V024	45	9	24	us whom he also called, not only from the Jews but also from the Gentiles?
B045C009V025	45	9	25	As he also says in Hosea,“I will call those who were not my people, ‘My people,’and those who were not loved, ‘Loved.’
B045C009V026	45	9	26	And it will be in the place where it was said to them, ‘You are not my people,’there they will be called ‘sons of the living God.’ ”
B045C009V027	45	9	27	And Isaiah cries out concerning Israel,“Even if the number of the sons of Israel is like the sand of the sea,the remnant will be saved,
B045C009V028	45	9	28	˻for the Lord will execute his sentence thoroughly and decisively˼ upon the earth.”
B045C009V029	45	9	29	And just as Isaiah foretold,“If the Lord of hosts had not left us descendants,we would have become like Sodomand would have resembled Gomorrah.”
B045C009V030	45	9	30	What then shall we say? That the Gentiles, who did not pursue righteousness, attained righteousness—even the righteousness that is by faith.
B045C009V031	45	9	31	But Israel, pursuing the law of righteousness, did not attain to the law.
B045C009V032	45	9	32	Why that? Because they did not pursue it by faith, but as if by works. They stumbled over the ˻stone that causes people to stumble˼,
B045C009V033	45	9	33	just as it is written,“Behold, I am laying in Zion ˻a stone that causes people to stumble˼,and ˻a rock that causes them to fall˼,and the one who believes in him will not be put to shame.”
B045C010V001	45	10	1	Brothers, the desire of my heart and my prayer to God on behalf of them is for their salvation.
B045C010V002	45	10	2	For I testify about them that they have a zeal for God, but not according to knowledge.
B045C010V003	45	10	3	For ignoring the righteousness of God, and seeking to establish their own righteousness, they did not subject themselves to the righteousness of God.
B045C010V004	45	10	4	For Christ is the end of the law for righteousness to everyone who believes.
B045C010V005	45	10	5	For Moses writes about the righteousness that is from the law: “The person who does these things will live by them.”
B045C010V006	45	10	6	But the righteousness from faith speaks like this: “Do not say in your heart, ‘Who will ascend into heaven?’ ” (that is, to bring Christ down),
B045C010V007	45	10	7	or “Who will descend into the abyss?” (that is, to bring Christ up from the dead).
B045C010V008	45	10	8	But what does it say? “The word is near to you, in your mouth and in your heart” (that is, the word of faith that we proclaim),
B045C010V009	45	10	9	that if you confess with your mouth “Jesus is Lord” and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.
B045C010V010	45	10	10	For with the heart one believes, resulting in righteousness, and with the mouth one confesses, resulting in salvation.
B045C010V011	45	10	11	For the scripture says, “Everyone who believes in him will not be put to shame.”
B045C010V012	45	10	12	For there is no distinction between Jew and Greek, for the same Lordis Lord of all, who is rich to all who call upon him.
B045C010V013	45	10	13	For “everyone who calls upon the name of the Lord will be saved.”
B045C010V014	45	10	14	How then will they call upon him in whom they have not believed? And how will they believe in him about whom they have not heard? And how will they hear about him without one who preaches to them?
B045C010V015	45	10	15	And how will they preach, unless they are sent? Just as it is written, “How timely are the feet of those who bring good news of good things.”
B045C010V016	45	10	16	But not all have obeyed the good news, for Isaiah says, “Lord, who has believed our report?”
B045C010V017	45	10	17	Consequently, faith comes by hearing, and hearing through the word about Christ.
B045C010V018	45	10	18	But I say, they have not heard, have they? On the contrary,“Their voice has gone out to all the earth,and their words to the ends of the inhabited world.”
B045C010V019	45	10	19	But I say, Israel did not know, did they? First, Moses says,“I will provoke you to jealousy by those who are not a nation;by a senseless nation I will provoke you to anger.”
B045C010V020	45	10	20	And Isaiah is very bold and says,“I was found by those who did not seek me;I became known to those who did not ask for me.”
B045C010V021	45	10	21	But about Israel he says,“The whole day long I held out my handsto a disobedient and resistant people.”
B045C011V001	45	11	1	Therefore I say, God has not rejected his people, has he? May it never be! For I also am an Israelite, from the descendants of Abraham, of the tribe of Benjamin.
B045C011V002	45	11	2	God has not rejected his people, whom he foreknew! Or do you not know, in the passage about Elijah, what the scripture says—how he appeals to God against Israel?
B045C011V003	45	11	3	“Lord, they have killed your prophets, they have torn down your altars, and I alone am left, and they are seeking my life!”
B045C011V004	45	11	4	But what does the divine response say to him? “I have left for myself seven thousand people who have not bent the knee to Baal.”
B045C011V005	45	11	5	So in this way also at the present time, there is a remnant ˻selected by grace˼.
B045C011V006	45	11	6	But if by grace, it is no longer by works, for otherwise grace would no longer be grace.
B045C011V007	45	11	7	What then? What Israel was searching for, this it did not obtain. But the elect obtained it, and the rest were hardened,
B045C011V008	45	11	8	just as it is written,“God gave them a spirit of stupor,eyes that do not see and ears that do not hear,until this very day.”
B045C011V009	45	11	9	And David says,“Let their table become a snare and a trap,and a cause for stumbling and a retribution to them;
B045C011V010	45	11	10	let their eyes be darkened so that they do not see,and cause their backs to bend ˻continually˼.”
B045C011V011	45	11	11	I say then, they did not stumble so that they fell, did they? May it never be! But by their trespass, salvation has come to the Gentiles, in order to provoke them to jealousy.
B045C011V012	45	11	12	And if their trespass means riches for the world and their loss means riches for the Gentiles, how much more will their fullness mean?
B045C011V013	45	11	13	Now I am speaking to you Gentiles. Therefore, inasmuch as I am apostle to the Gentiles, I promote my ministry,
B045C011V014	45	11	14	if somehow I may provoke my people to jealousy and save some of them.
B045C011V015	45	11	15	For if their rejection means the reconciliation of the world, what will their acceptance mean except life from the dead?
B045C011V016	45	11	16	Now if the first fruits are holy, so also is the whole batch of dough, and if the root is holy, so also are the branches.
B045C011V017	45	11	17	Now if some of the branches were broken off, and you, although you were a wild olive tree, were grafted in among them and became a sharer of the root of the olive tree’s richness,
B045C011V018	45	11	18	do not boast against the branches. But if you boast against them, you do not support the root, but the root supports you.
B045C011V019	45	11	19	Then you will say, “Branches were broken off in order that I could be grafted in.”
B045C011V020	45	11	20	Well said! They were broken off because of unbelief, but you stand firm because of faith. Do not think arrogant thoughts, but be afraid.
B045C011V021	45	11	21	For if God did not spare the ˻natural˼ branches, perhaps he will not spare you either.
B045C011V022	45	11	22	See, then, the kindness and severity of God: severity upon those who have fallen, but upon you the kindness of God—if you continue in his kindness, for otherwise you also will be cut off.
B045C011V023	45	11	23	And those also, if they do not persist in unbelief, will be grafted in, because God is able to graft them in again.
B045C011V024	45	11	24	For if you were cut off from what is by nature a wild olive tree, and contrary to nature were grafted into a cultivated olive tree, how much more will these who are ˻natural branches˼ be grafted into their own olive tree?
B045C011V025	45	11	25	For I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, of this mystery, so that you will not be wise in your own sight, that a partial hardening has happened to Israel, until the full number of the Gentiles has come in,
B045C011V026	45	11	26	and so all Israel will be saved, just as it is written,“The deliverer will come out of Zion;he will turn away ungodliness from Jacob.
B045C011V027	45	11	27	And this is the covenant from me with themwhen I take away their sins.”
B045C011V028	45	11	28	With respect to the gospel, they are enemies for your sake, but with respect to election, they are dearly loved for the sake of the fathers.
B045C011V029	45	11	29	For the gifts and the calling of God are irrevocable.
B045C011V030	45	11	30	For just as you formerly were disobedient to God, but now have been shown mercy because of the disobedience of these,
B045C011V031	45	11	31	so also these have now been disobedient for your mercy, in order that they also may now be shown mercy.
B045C011V032	45	11	32	For God confined them all in disobedience, in order that he could have mercy on them all.
B045C011V033	45	11	33	Oh, the depth of the richesand the wisdom and the knowledge of God!How unsearchable are his judgmentsand how incomprehensible are his ways!
B045C011V034	45	11	34	“For who has known the mind of the Lord,or who has been his counselor?
B045C011V035	45	11	35	Or who has given in advance to him,and it will be paid back to him?”
B045C011V036	45	11	36	For from him and through him and to him are all things.To him be glory for eternity! Amen.
B045C012V001	45	12	1	Therefore I exhort you, brothers, through the mercies of God, to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and pleasing to God, which is your reasonable service.
B045C012V002	45	12	2	And do not be conformed to this age, but be transformed by the renewal of your mind, so that you may approve what is the good and well-pleasing and perfect will of God.
B045C012V003	45	12	3	For by the grace given to me I say to everyone who is among you not to think more highly of yourself than what one ought to think, but to think ˻sensibly˼, as God has apportioned a measure of faith to each one.
B045C012V004	45	12	4	For just as in one body we have many members, but all the members do not have the same function,
B045C012V005	45	12	5	in the same way we who are many are one body in Christ, and ˻individually˼ members of one another,
B045C012V006	45	12	6	but having different gifts according to the grace given to us: if it is prophecy, according to the proportion of his faith;
B045C012V007	45	12	7	if it is service, by service; if it is one who teaches, by teaching;
B045C012V008	45	12	8	if it is one who exhorts, by exhortation; one who gives, with sincerity; one who leads, with diligence; one who shows mercy, with cheerfulness.
B045C012V009	45	12	9	Love must be without hypocrisy. Abhor what is evil; be attached to what is good,
B045C012V010	45	12	10	being devoted to one another in brotherly love, esteeming one another more highly in honor,
B045C012V011	45	12	11	not lagging in diligence, being enthusiastic in spirit, serving the Lord,
B045C012V012	45	12	12	rejoicing in hope, enduring in affliction, being devoted to prayer,
B045C012V013	45	12	13	contributing to the needs of the saints, pursuing hospitality.
B045C012V014	45	12	14	Bless those who persecute you, bless and do not curse them.
B045C012V015	45	12	15	Rejoice with those who rejoice; weep with those who weep.
B045C012V016	45	12	16	Think the same thing toward one another; ˻do not think arrogantly˼, but associate with the lowly. Do not be wise ˻in your own sight˼.
B045C012V017	45	12	17	Pay back no one evil for evil. Take thought for what is good in the sight of all people.
B045C012V018	45	12	18	If it is possible on your part, be at peace with all people.
B045C012V019	45	12	19	Do not take revenge yourselves, dear friends, but give place to God’s wrath, for it is written, “Vengeance is mine, I will repay,” says the Lord.
B045C012V020	45	12	20	But “if your enemy is hungry, feed him; if he is thirsty, give him something to drink; for by doing this, you will heap up coals of fire upon his head.”
B045C012V021	45	12	21	Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.
B045C013V001	45	13	1	Let every person be subject to the governing authorities, for there is no authority except by God, and those that exist are put in place by God.
B045C013V002	45	13	2	So then, the one who resists authority resists the ordinance which is from God, and those who resist will receive condemnation on themselves.
B045C013V003	45	13	3	For rulers are not a cause of terror for a good deed, but for bad conduct. So do you want not to be afraid of authority? Do what is good, and you will have praise from it,
B045C013V004	45	13	4	for it is God’s servant to you for what is good. But if you do what is bad, be afraid, because it does not bear the sword to no purpose. For it is God’s servant, the one who avenges for punishment on the one who does what is bad.
B045C013V005	45	13	5	Therefore it is necessary to be in subjection, not only because of wrath but also because of conscience.
B045C013V006	45	13	6	For because of this you also pay taxes, for the authorities are servants of God, busily engaged in this very thing.
B045C013V007	45	13	7	Pay to everyone what is owed: pay taxes to whom taxes are due; pay customs duties to whom customs duties are due; pay respect to whom respect is due; pay honor to whom honor is due.
B045C013V008	45	13	8	Owe nothing to anyone, except to love one another, for the one who loves someone else has fulfilled the law.
B045C013V009	45	13	9	For the commandments, “You shall not commit adultery, you shall not commit murder, you shall not steal, you shall not covet,” and if there is any other commandment, are summed up in this statement: “You shall love your neighbor as yourself.”
B045C013V010	45	13	10	Love does not commit evil against a neighbor. Therefore love is the fulfillment of the law.
B045C013V011	45	13	11	And do this because you know the time, that it is already the hour for you to wake up from sleep. For our salvation is nearer now than when we believed.
B045C013V012	45	13	12	The night is far gone, and the day has drawn near. Therefore let us lay aside the deeds of darkness and put on the weapons of light.
B045C013V013	45	13	13	Let us live decently, as in the day, not in carousing and drunkenness, not in sexual immorality and licentiousness, not in strife and jealousy.
B045C013V014	45	13	14	But put on the Lord Jesus Christ and do not make provision for the desires of the flesh.
B045C014V001	45	14	1	Now receive the one who is weak in faith, but not for quarrels about opinions.
B045C014V002	45	14	2	One believes he may eat all things, but the one who is weak eats only vegetables.
B045C014V003	45	14	3	The one who eats must not despise the one who does not eat, and the one who does not eat must not judge the one who eats, because God has accepted him.
B045C014V004	45	14	4	Who are you, who passes judgment on the domestic slave belonging to someone else? To his own master he stands or falls, and he will stand, for the Lord is able to make him stand.
B045C014V005	45	14	5	For one person prefers one day over another day, and another person regards every day alike. Each one must be fully convinced in his own mind.
B045C014V006	45	14	6	The one who is intent on the day is intent on it for the Lord, and the one who eats eats for the Lord, because he is thankful to God, and the one who does not eat does not eat for the Lord, and he is thankful to God.
B045C014V007	45	14	7	For none of us lives for himself and none dies for himself.
B045C014V008	45	14	8	For if we live, we live for the Lord, and if we die, we die for the Lord. Therefore whether we live or whether we die, we are the Lord’s.
B045C014V009	45	14	9	For Christ died and became alive again for this reason, in order that he might be Lord of both the dead and the living.
B045C014V010	45	14	10	But why do you judge your brother? Or also, why do you despise your brother? For we will all stand before the judgment seat of God.
B045C014V011	45	14	11	For it is written,“As I live, says the Lord, every knee will bow to me,and every tongue will praise God.”
B045C014V012	45	14	12	So then, each one of us will give an account concerning himself to God.
B045C014V013	45	14	13	Therefore, let us no longer pass judgment on one another, but rather decide this: not to place a cause for stumbling or a temptation before a brother.
B045C014V014	45	14	14	I know and am convinced in the Lord Jesus that nothing is unclean of itself, except to the one who considers something to be unclean; to that person it is unclean.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	For if because of food, your brother is grieved, you are no longer living according to love. Do not destroy by your food that person for whom Christ died.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Therefore do not let your good be slandered.
B045C014V017	45	14	17	For the kingdom of God is not eating and drinking, but righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For the one who serves Christ in this wayis well-pleasing to God and approved by people.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	So then, let us pursue ˻what promotes peace˼ and ˻what edifies one another˼.
B045C014V020	45	14	20	Do not destroy the work of God on account of food. All thingsare clean, but it is wrong for the person ˻who eats and stumbles in the process˼.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	It is good not to eat meat or to drink wine or to do anything by which your brother stumbles.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	The faith that you have, have with respect to yourself before God. Blessed is the one who does not pass judgment on himself by what he approves.
B045C014V023	45	14	23	But the one who doubts is condemned if he eats, because he does not do so from faith, and everything that is not from faith is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	But we who are strong ought to bear the weaknesses of the weak, and not to please ourselves.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	Let each one of us please his neighbor for his good, for the purpose of edification.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	For even Christ did not please himself, but just as it is written, “The insults of those who insult you have fallen on me.”
B045C015V004	45	15	4	For whatever was written beforehand was written for our instruction, in order that through patient endurance and through the encouragement of the scriptures we may have hope.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	Now may the God of patient endurance and of encouragement grant you ˻to be in agreement˼ with one another, in accordance with Christ Jesus,
B045C015V006	45	15	6	so that with one mind you may glorify with one mouth the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore accept one another, just as Christ also has accepted you, to the glory of God.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	For I say, Christ has become a servant of the circumcision on behalf of the truth of God, in order to confirm the promises to the fathers,
B045C015V009	45	15	9	and that the Gentiles may glorify God for his mercy, just as it is written,“Because of this, I will praise you among the Gentiles,and I will sing praise to your name.”
B045C015V010	45	15	10	And again it says,“Rejoice, Gentiles, with his people.”
B045C015V011	45	15	11	And again,“Praise the Lord, all the Gentiles,and let all the peoples praise him.”
B045C015V012	45	15	12	And again Isaiah says,“The root of Jesse will come,even the one who rises to rule over the Gentiles;in him the Gentiles will put their hope.”
B045C015V013	45	15	13	Now may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, so that you may abound in hope by the power of the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V014	45	15	14	Now I myself also am convinced about you, my brothers, that you yourselves also are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, able also to instruct one another.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	But I have written to you more boldly on some points, so as to remind you again because of the grace that has been given to me by God,
B045C015V016	45	15	16	with the result that I am a servant of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles, serving the gospel of God as a priest, in order that the offering of the Gentiles may become acceptable, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	Therefore I have a reason for boasting in Christ Jesus regarding the things concerning God.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I will not dare to speak about anything except that which Christ has accomplished through me, resulting in the obedience of the Gentiles by word and deed,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	by the power of signs and wonders, by the power of the Spirit of God, so that from Jerusalem and traveling around as far as Illyricum I have fully proclaimed the gospel of Christ.
B045C015V020	45	15	20	And so, having as my ambition to proclaim the gospel where Christ has not been named, in order that I will not build on the foundation belonging to someone else,
B045C015V021	45	15	21	but just as it is written,“Those to whom it was not announced concerning him will see,and those who have not heard will understand.”
B045C015V022	45	15	22	For this reason also I was hindered many times from coming to you,
B045C015V023	45	15	23	and now, no longer having a place in these regions, but having a desire for many years to come to you
B045C015V024	45	15	24	whenever I travel to Spain. For I hope while I am passing through to see you and to be sent on my way by you, whenever I have first enjoyed your company for a while.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now I am traveling to Jerusalem, serving the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For Macedonia and Achaia were pleased to make some contribution for the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	For they were pleased to do so, and they are obligated to them. For if the Gentiles have shared in their spiritual things, they ought also to serve them in material things.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	Therefore, after I have accomplished this and sealed this fruit for delivery to them, I will depart by way of you for Spain,
B045C015V029	45	15	29	and I know that when I come to you, I will come in the fullness of the blessing of Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I exhort you, brothers, through our Lord Jesus Christ and through the love of the Spirit, to contend along with me in your prayers on my behalf to God,
B045C015V031	45	15	31	that I may be rescued from those who are disobedient in Judea, and my ministry in Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints,
B045C015V032	45	15	32	so that, coming to you with joy by the will of God, I may rest with you.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	Now may the God of peace be with all of you. Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	Now I commend to you Phoebe our sister, who is also a servant of the church in Cenchrea,
B045C016V002	45	16	2	in order that you may welcome her in the Lord in a manner worthy of the saints, and help her in whatever task she may have need from you, for she herself also has been a helper of many, even me myself.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus,
B045C016V004	45	16	4	who risked their own necks for my life, for which not only I am thankful, but also all the churches of the Gentiles;
B045C016V005	45	16	5	also greet the church in their house. Greet Epenetus my dear friend, who is ˻the first convert˼ of Asia for Christ.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Greet Mary, who ˻has worked hard˼ for you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Greet Andronicus and Junia, my compatriots and my fellow prisoners, who are well known to the apostles, who were also in Christ before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Greet Ampliatus, my dear friend in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Greet Urbanus, our fellow worker in Christ, and my dear friend Stachys.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Greet Apelles, who is approved in Christ. Greet those of the household of Aristobulus.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Greet Herodion my compatriot. Greet those of the household of Narcissus who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Greet Tryphena and Tryphosa, the laborers in the Lord. Greet Persis, the dear friend who ˻has worked hard˼ in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Greet Rufus, the chosen one in the Lord, and his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Greet Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	Now I exhort you, brothers, to look out for those who cause dissensions and temptations contrary to the teaching which you learned, and stay away from them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For such people do not serve our Lord Christ, but their own stomach, and by smooth speech and flattery they deceive the hearts of the unsuspecting.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For the report of your obedience has reached to all; therefore I am rejoicing over you, and I want you to be wise toward what is good, but innocent toward what is evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	And in a short time the God of peace will crush Satan under your feet. The grace of our Lord Jesus be with you.
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, greets you, and Lucius and Jason and Sosipater, my compatriots.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I, Tertius, the one who wrote this letter, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, my host and the host of the whole church, greets you. Erastus the city treasurer greets you, and Quartus the brother.
B045C016V025	45	16	25	Now to the one who is able to strengthen you according to my gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery that had been kept secret for eternal ages,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	but now has been revealed, and through the prophetic scriptures has been made known according to the command of the eternal God, resulting in obedience of faith to all the Gentiles,
B045C016V027	45	16	27	to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory for eternity. Amen.
B046C001V001	46	1	1	Paul, called to be an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	to the church of God that is in Corinth, sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, together with all those who call upon the name of our Lord Jesus Christ in every place, their Lord and ours.
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I give thanks to my God always concerning you, because of the grace of God which was given to you in Christ Jesus,
B046C001V005	46	1	5	that in everything you were made rich in him, in all speech and all knowledge,
B046C001V006	46	1	6	just as the testimony about Christ has been confirmed in you,
B046C001V007	46	1	7	so that you do not lack in any spiritual gift as you eagerly await the revelation of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B046C001V008	46	1	8	who will also confirm you until the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	God is faithful, by whom you were called to fellowship with his Son Jesus Christ our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	Now I exhort you, brothers, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you all say the same thing and there not be divisions among you, and that you be made complete in the same mind and with the same purpose.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For it has been made clear to me concerning you, my brothers, by ˻Chloe’s people˼, that there are quarrels among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	But I say this, that each of you is saying, “I am with Paul,” and “I am with Apollos,” and “I am with Cephas,” and “I am with Christ.”
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Has Christ been divided? Paul was not crucified for you, was he? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I give thanks to God that I baptized none of you except Crispus and Gaius,
B046C001V015	46	1	15	lest anyone should say that you were baptized in my name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	(Now I also baptized the household of Stephanus. Beyond that I do not know if I baptized anyone else.)
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to proclaim the gospel, not with ˻clever speech˼, lest the cross of Christ be emptied.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the message about the cross is foolishness to those who are perishing, but to us who are being saved it is the power of God.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written,“I will destroy the wisdom of the wise,and the intelligence of the intelligent I will confound.”
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise person? Where is the scribe? Where is the debater of this age? Has not God made foolish the wisdom of the world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For since, in the wisdom of God, the world through its wisdom did not know God, God was pleased through the foolishness of preaching to save those who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	For indeed, Jews ask for sign miracles and Greeks seek wisdom,
B046C001V023	46	1	23	but we preach Christ crucified, to the Jews a cause for stumbling, but to the Gentiles foolishness,
B046C001V024	46	1	24	but to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ is the power of God and the wisdom of God.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	For the foolishness of God is wiser than human wisdom, and the weakness of God is stronger than human strength.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	For consider your calling, brothers, that not many were wise according to human standards, not many were powerful, not many were well born.
B046C001V027	46	1	27	But the foolish things of the world God chose in order that he might put to shame the wise, and the weak things of the world God chose in order that he might put to shame the strong,
B046C001V028	46	1	28	and the insignificant of the world, and the despised, God chose, the things that are not, in order that he might abolish the things that are,
B046C001V029	46	1	29	so that all flesh may not boast before God.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	But from him you are in Christ Jesus, who became wisdom to us from God, and righteousness and sanctification and redemption,
B046C001V031	46	1	31	so that, just as it is written, “The one who boasts, let him boast in the Lord.”
B046C002V001	46	2	1	And I, when I came to you, brothers, did not come with superiority of speech or of wisdom, proclaiming to you the mystery of God.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For I decided not to know anything among you except Jesus Christ and him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	And I came to you in weakness and in fear and with much trembling,
B046C002V004	46	2	4	and my speech and my preaching were not with persuasive words of wisdom, but with a demonstration of the Spirit and power,
B046C002V005	46	2	5	in order that your faith would not be in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	Now we do speak wisdom among the mature, but wisdom not of this age or of the rulers of this age, who are perishing,
B046C002V007	46	2	7	but we speak the hidden wisdom of God in a mystery, which God predestined before the ages for our glory,
B046C002V008	46	2	8	which none of the rulers of this age knew. For if they had known it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But just as it is written,“Things which eye has not seen and ear has not heard,and have not entered into the heart of man,are the things which God has prepared for those who love him.”
B046C002V010	46	2	10	But to us God has revealed them through the Spirit. For the Spirit searches all things, even the depths of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For who among men knows the things of a man, except the spirit of the man that is in him? Thus also no one knows the things of God except the Spirit of God.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	Now we have received not the spirit of the world, but the Spirit who is from God, in order that we may know the things freely given to us by God,
B046C002V013	46	2	13	things which we also speak, not in words taught by human wisdom, but in words taught by the Spirit, explaining spiritual things to spiritual people.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	But the natural man does not accept the things of the Spirit of God, for they are foolishness to him, and he is not able to understand them, because they are spiritually discerned.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	Now the spiritual person discerns all things, but he himself is judged by no one.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	“For who has known the mind of the Lord; who has advised him?” But we have the mind of Christ.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	And I, brothers, was not able to speak to you as to spiritual people, but as to fleshly people, as to infants in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I gave you milk to drink, not solid food, for you were not yet able to eat it. But now you are still not able,
B046C003V003	46	3	3	for you are still fleshly. For where there is jealousy and strife among you, are you not fleshly, and do you not live like unregenerate people?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For whenever anyone says, “I am with Paul,” and another, “I am with Apollos,” are you not merely human?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	Therefore, what is Apollos and what is Paul? Servants through whom you believed, and to each as the Lord gave.
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I planted, Apollos watered, but God was causing it to grow.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So then, neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but God who is causing it to grow.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	Now the one who plants and the one who waters are one, but each one will receive his own reward according to his own labor.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For we are God’s fellow workers; you are God’s field, God’s building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	According to the grace of God given to me, like a skilled master builder I laid a foundation, and another is building upon it. But each one must direct his attention to how he is building upon it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	For no one is able to lay another foundation than the one which is laid, which is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	Now if anyone builds upon the foundation with gold, silver, precious stones, wood, grass, straw,
B046C003V013	46	3	13	the work of each one will become evident. For the day will reveal it, because it will be revealed with fire, and the fire itself will test the work of each one, of what sort it is.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If anyone’s work that he has built upon it remains, he will receive a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If anyone’s work is burned up, he will suffer loss, but he himself will be saved, but so as through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	Do you not know that you are God’s temple and the Spirit of God dwells in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If anyone destroys God’s temple, God will destroy this one. For God’s temple is holy, which you are.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no one deceive himself. If anyone thinks himself to be wise among you in this age, let him become a fool, in order that he may become wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God, for it is written, “The one who catches the wise in their craftiness,”
B046C003V020	46	3	20	and again, “The Lord knows the thoughts of the wise, that they are futile.”
B046C003V021	46	3	21	So then, let no one boast in people. For all things are yours,
B046C003V022	46	3	22	whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or things present or things to come, all thingsare yours,
B046C003V023	46	3	23	and you are Christ’s, and Christ is God’s.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	Thus let a person consider us as servants of Christ and stewards of God’s mysteries.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	In this case, moreover, it is sought in stewards that one be found faithful.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But to me it is a very little matter that I be judged by you or by a human court, but I do not even judge myself.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For I am conscious of nothing against myself, but not by this am I vindicated. But the one who judges me is the Lord.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	Therefore do not judge anything before the time, until the Lord should come, who will both enlighten the hidden things of darkness and will reveal the counsels of hearts, and then praise will come to each one from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	Now I have applied these things, brothers, to myself and Apollos for your sake, in order that in us you may learn not to go beyond what is written, lest someone be inflated with pride on behalf of one person against the other.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who concedes you superiority? And what do you have that you did not receive? But if indeed you received it, why do you boast as if you did not receive it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	Already you are satiated! Already you are rich! Apart from us you reign as kings! And would that indeed you reigned as kings, in order that we also might reign as kings with you!
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For, I think, God has exhibited us apostles last of all, as condemned to death, because we have become a spectacle to the world and to angels and to people.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for the sake of Christ, but you are prudent in Christ! We are weak, but you are strong! You are honored, but we are dishonored!
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Until the present hour we are both hungry and thirsty and poorly clothed and roughly treated and homeless,
B046C004V012	46	4	12	and we toil, working with our own hands. When we are reviled, we bless; when we are persecuted, we endure;
B046C004V013	46	4	13	when we are slandered, we encourage. We have become like the refuse of the world, the offscouring of all things, until now.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I am not writing these things to shame you, but admonishing you as my dear children.
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For if you have ten thousand guardians in Christ, yet you do not have many fathers, for in Christ Jesus I fathered you through the gospel.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	Therefore I exhort you, become imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	Because of this, I have sent to you Timothy, who is my dear and faithful child in the Lord, who will remind you of my ways in Christ Jesus, just as I teach everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	But some have become arrogant, as if I were not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I am coming to you soon, if the Lord wills, and I will know not the talk of the ones who have become arrogant, but the power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the kingdom of God is not with talk, but with power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	What do you want? Shall I come to you with a rod, or with love and a spirit of gentleness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	It is reported everywhere that there is sexual immorality among you, and sexual immorality of such a kind which does not even exist among the Gentiles, so that someone has the wife of his father.
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you are inflated with pride, and should you not rather have mourned, so that the one who has done this deed would be removed from your midst?
B046C005V003	46	5	3	For although I am absent in body but present in spirit, I have already passed judgment on the one who has done this in this way, as if I were present.
B046C005V004	46	5	4	In the name of our Lord Jesus, when you are assembled, and my spirit, together with the power of our Lord Jesus,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	I have decided to hand over such a person to Satan for the destruction of the flesh, in order that his spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is not good. Do you not know that a little leaven leavens the whole batch of dough?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Clean out the old leaven in order that you may be a new batch of dough, just as you are unleavened. For Christ our Passover has been sacrificed.
B046C005V008	46	5	8	So then, let us celebrate the feast, not with the old leaven or with the leaven of wickedness and sinfulness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in the letter not to associate with sexually immoral people.
B046C005V010	46	5	10	By no means did I mean the sexually immoral people of this world or the greedy people and swindlers or idolaters, since then you would have to depart out of the world.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But now I have written to you not to associate with any so-called brother, if he is a sexually immoral person or a greedy person or an idolater or an abusive person or a drunkard or a swindler—with such a person not even to eat.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what is it to me to judge those outside? Should you not judge those inside?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	But those outside God will judge. Remove the evil person ˻from among yourselves˼.
B046C006V001	46	6	1	Does anyone among you, if he has a matter against someone else, dare to go to court before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Or do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And if by you the world is judged, are you unworthy of the most insignificant courts?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Do you not know that we will judge angels, not to mention ordinary matters?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	Therefore, if you have courts with regard to ordinary matters, do you seat these despised people in the church?
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I say this to your shame. So is there not anyone wise among you who will be able to render a decision between his brothers?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	But brother goes to court with brother, and this before unbelievers!
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Therefore it is already completely a loss for you that you have lawsuits with one another. Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be defrauded?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	But you wrong and defraud, and do this to brothers!
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Or do you not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be deceived! Neither sexually immoral people, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor passive homosexual partners, nor dominant homosexual partners,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	nor thieves, nor greedy persons, not drunkards, not abusive persons, not swindlers will inherit the kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	And some of you were these things, but you were washed, but you were sanctified, but you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and by the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	All things are permitted for me, but not all things are profitable. All things are permitted for me, but I will not be controlled by anything.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Food is for the stomach, and the stomach for food, but God will abolish ˻both of them˼. Now the body is not for sexual immorality, but for the Lord, and the Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	And God both raised up the Lord and will raise us up by his power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Do you not know that your bodies are members of Christ? Therefore, shall I take away the members of Christ and make them members of a prostitute? May it never be!
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Or do you not know that the one who joins himself to a prostitute is one body with her? For it says, “The two will become one flesh.”
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But the one who joins himself to the Lord is one spirit with him.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Flee sexual immorality. Every sin that a person commits is outside his body, but the one who commits sexual immorality sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Or do you not know that your body is the temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have from God, and you are not your own?
B046C006V020	46	6	20	For you were bought at a price; therefore glorify God with your body.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	Now concerning the things about which you wrote: “It is good for a man not to touch a woman.”
B046C007V002	46	7	2	But because of sexual immorality, let each man have his own wife and let each woman have her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	The husband must fulfill his obligation to his wife, and likewise also the wife to her husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	The wife does not have authority over her own body, but her husband does. And likewise also the husband does not have authority over his own body, but his wife does.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not defraud one another, except perhaps by agreement, for a time, in order that you may devote yourselves to prayer, and then you should be ˻together˼ again, lest Satan tempt you because of your lack of self control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But I say this as a concession, not as a command.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	I wish all people could be like myself, but each one has his own gift from God, one in this way and another in that way.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	Now I say to the unmarried and to the widows: It is good for them if they remain as I am.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	But if they cannot control themselves, they should marry, for it is better to marry than to burn with sexual desire.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	To the married I command—not I, but the Lord—a wife must not separate from her husband.
B046C007V011	46	7	11	But if indeed she does separate, she must remain unmarried or be reconciled to her husband. And a husband must not divorce his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	Now to the rest I say—not the Lord—if any brother has an unbelieving wife and she consents to live with him, he must not divorce her.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And if any wife has an unbelieving husband and he consents to live with her, she must not divorce her husband.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by his wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the brother, since otherwise your children are unclean, but now they are holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if the unbeliever leaves, let him leave. The brother or the sister is not bound in such cases. But God has called you in peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how do you know, wife, whether you will save your husband? Or how do you know, husband, whether you will save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	But to each one as the Lord has apportioned. As God has called each one, thus let him live—and thus I order in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was anyone called after being circumcised? He must not undo his circumcision. Was anyone called in uncircumcision? He must not become circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of the commandments of God.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Each one in the calling in which he was called—in this he should remain.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you called while a slave? Do not let it be a concern to you. But if indeed you are able to become free, rather make use of it.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For the one who is called in the Lord while a slave is the Lord’s freedperson. Likewise the one who is called while free is a slave of Christ.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought at a price; do not become slaves of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Each one in the situation in which he was called, brothers—in this he should remain with God.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	Now concerning virgins I do not have a command from the Lord, but I am giving an opinion as one shown mercy by the Lord to be trustworthy.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	Therefore, I consider this to be good because of the impending distress, that it is good for a man to be thus.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek release. Are you free from a wife? Do not seek a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But if you marry, you have not sinned, and if the virgin marries, she has not sinned. But such people will have affliction in the flesh, and I would spare you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	But I say this, brothers: the time is shortened, that from now on even those who have wives should be as if they do not have wives,
B046C007V030	46	7	30	and those who weep as if they do not weep, and those who rejoice as if they do not rejoice, and those who buy as if they do not possess,
B046C007V031	46	7	31	and those who make use of the world as if they do not make full use of it. For the present form of this world is passing away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	But I want you to be free from care. The unmarried person cares for the things of the Lord, how he may please the Lord.
B046C007V033	46	7	33	But the one who is married cares for the things of the world, how he may please his wife,
B046C007V034	46	7	34	and he is divided. And the unmarried woman or the virgin cares for the things of the Lord, in order that she may be holy both in body and in spirit. But the married woman cares for the things of the world, how she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	Now I am saying this for your own benefit, not that I may put a restriction on you, but to promote appropriate and devoted service to the Lord without distraction.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	But if anyone thinks he is behaving dishonorably concerning his virgin, if she is past her prime and it ought to be thus, let him do what he wishes. He does not sin. Let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	But he who stands firm in his heart, not having necessity, but has authority concerning his own will, and has decided this in his own heart, to keep his own virgin, he will do well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So then, the one who marries his own virgin does well, and the one who does not marry her will do better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	A wife is bound for as long a time as her husband lives. But if her husband ˻dies˼, she is free to marry whomever she wishes, only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But she is happier if she remains thus, according to my opinion—and I think I have the Spirit of God.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	Now concerning food sacrificed to idols, we know that “we all have knowledge.” Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	If anyone thinks he knows anything, he has not yet known as it is necessary to know.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	But if anyone loves God, this one is known by him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Therefore, concerning the eating of food sacrificed to idols, we know that “an idol is nothing in the world” and that “there is no God except one.”
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For even if after all there are so-called gods, whether in heaven or on earth, just as there are many gods and many lords,
B046C008V006	46	8	6	yet to us there is one God, the Father,from whom are all things, and we are for him,and there is one Lord, Jesus Christ,through whom are all things, and we are through him.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	But this knowledge is not in everyone. But some, being accustomed until now to the idol, eat this food as food sacrificed to idols, and their conscience, because it is weak, is defiled.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But food does not bring us close to God. Neither if we do not eat do we lack, nor if we do eat do we have more.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But watch out lest somehow this right of yours becomes a cause for stumbling to the weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if someone should see you who has knowledge reclining for a meal in an idol’s temple, will not his conscience, because it is weak, be strengthened so that he eats the food sacrificed to idols?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	For the one who is weak—the brother for whom Christ died—is destroyed by your knowledge.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	Now if you sin in this way against the brothers and wound their conscience, which is weak, you sin against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Therefore, if food causes my brother to sin, I will never eat meat ˻forever˼, in order that I may not cause my brother to sin.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen Jesus our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If to others I am not an apostle, yet indeed I am to you, for you are my seal of apostleship in the Lord.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My defense to those who examine me is this:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Do we not have the right to eat and drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	Do we not have the right to take along a sister as wife, like the rest of the apostles and the brothers of the Lord and Cephas?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or do only I and Barnabas not have the right ˻to refrain from working˼?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who ever serves as a soldier at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat the fruit of it? Or who shepherds a flock and does not drink from the milk of the flock?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	I am not saying these things according to a human perspective. Or does the law not also say these things?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For in the law of Moses it is written, “You must not muzzle an ox while it is threshing.” It is not about oxen God is concerned, is it?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	Or doubtless does he speak ˻for our sake˼? For it is written ˻for our sake˼, because the one who plows ought to plow in hope and the one who threshes ought to do so in hope of a share.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we have sown spiritual things among you, is it too great a thing if we reap material things from you?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others share this right over you, do we not do so even more? Yet we have not made use of this right, but we endure all things, in order that we may not cause any hindrance to the gospel of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	Do you not know that those performing the holy services eat the things from the temple, and those attending to the altar have a share with the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	In the same way also the Lord ordered those who proclaim the gospel to live from the gospel.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I have not made use of any of these rights. And I am not writing these things in order that it may be thus with me. For it would be better to me rather to die than for anyone to deprive me of my reason for boasting.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For if I proclaim the gospel, it is not to me a reason for boasting, for necessity is imposed on me. For woe is to me if I do not proclaim the gospel.
B046C009V017	46	9	17	For if I do this voluntarily, I have a reward, but if I do so unwillingly, I have been entrusted with a stewardship.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What then is my reward? That when I proclaim the gospel, I may offer the gospel free of charge, in order not to make full use of my right in the gospel.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For although I am free from all people, I have enslaved myself to all, in order that I may gain more.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	I have become like a Jew to the Jews, in order that I may gain the Jews. To those under the law I became as under the law (although I myself am not under the law) in order that I may gain those under the law.
B046C009V021	46	9	21	To those outside the law I became as outside the law (although I am not outside the law of God, but subject to the law of Christ) in order that I may gain those outside the law.
B046C009V022	46	9	22	To the weak I became weak, in order that I may gain the weak. I have become all things to all people, in order that by all means I may save some.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	I do all this for the sake of the gospel, in order that I may become a participant with it.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Do you not know that those who run in the stadium all run, but one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may win.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	And everyone who competes exercises self-control in all things. Thus those do so in order that they may receive a perishable crown, but we an imperishable one.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	Therefore I run in this way, not as running aimlessly; I box in this way, not as beating the air.
B046C009V027	46	9	27	But I discipline my body and subjugate it, lest somehow after preaching to others, I myself should become disqualified.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	For I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, that our fathers were all under the cloud and all went through the sea,
B046C010V002	46	10	2	and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea,
B046C010V003	46	10	3	and all ate the same spiritual food,
B046C010V004	46	10	4	and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank from the spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	But God was not pleased with the majority of them, for they were struck down in the desert.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	Now these things happened as examples for us, so that we should not be desirers of evil things, just as those also desired them,
B046C010V007	46	10	7	and not become idolaters, as some of them did, just as it is written, “The people sat down to eat and drink, and stood up to play,”
B046C010V008	46	10	8	nor commit sexual immorality, as some of them committed sexual immorality, and twenty-three thousand fell in one day,
B046C010V009	46	10	9	nor put Christ to the test, as some of them tested him, and were destroyed by snakes,
B046C010V010	46	10	10	nor grumble, just as some of them grumbled, and were destroyed by the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	Now these things happened to those people as an example, but are written for our instruction, on whom the ends of the ages have come.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	Therefore, the one who thinks that he stands must watch out lest he fall.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	Temptation has not come upon you except what is common to humanity. But God is faithful, who will not permit you to be tempted beyond what you are able, but will also make a way out together with the temptation, so that you may be able to endure it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	Therefore, my dear friends, flee from idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I am speaking as to sensible people; you judge what I am saying.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing which we bless, is it not a participation in the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, is it not a participation in the body of Christ?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because there is one bread, we who are many are one body, for we all share from the one bread.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Consider Israel according to the flesh: are not the ones who eat the sacrifices sharers in the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	Therefore, what am I saying? That food sacrificed to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	No, but that the things which they sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons and not to God, and I do not want you to become sharers with demons.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You are not able to drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You are not able to share the table of the Lord and the table of demons.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Or are we attempting to provoke the Lord to jealousy? We are not stronger than he is, are we?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	All things are permitted, but not all things are profitable. All things are permitted, but not all things build up.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no one seek ˻his own good˼ but the good of the other.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Eat everything that is sold in the meat market, ˻asking no questions˼ for the sake of the conscience,
B046C010V026	46	10	26	for “the earth is the Lord’s, and its fullness.”
B046C010V027	46	10	27	If any of the unbelievers invites you, and you want to go, eat everything that is set before you, ˻asking no questions˼ for the sake of the conscience.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But if someone says to you, “This is offered to idols,” do not eat it, for the sake of that one who informed you and the conscience.
B046C010V029	46	10	29	Now I am not speaking about your own conscience, but the conscience of the other person. For why is my freedom judged by another’s conscience?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	If I partake with thankfulness, why am I slandered concerning that for which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Therefore, whether you eat or you drink or whatever you do, do all things for the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	˻Give no offense˼ both to Jews and to Greeks and to the church of God,
B046C010V033	46	10	33	just as I also please all people in all things, not seeking my own benefit, but the benefit of the many, in order that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Become imitators of me, just as I also am of Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	Now I praise you that you remember me in all things, and just as I handed over to you the traditions, you hold fast to them.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	But I want you to know that Christ is the head of every man, and the man is the head of the woman, and the head of Christ is God.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man who prays or prophesies while having something on his head dishonors his head,
B046C011V005	46	11	5	but every woman who prays or prophesies with uncovered head dishonors her head, for she is one and the same with the one whose head is shaved.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if a woman does not cover herself, let her hair be shorn off. But if it is shameful for a woman to have her head shorn or shaved, let her cover her head.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For indeed a man ought not to cover his head, because he is the image and glory of God, but the woman is the glory of the man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For man is not from woman, but woman from man.
B046C011V009	46	11	9	For indeed man was not created for the sake of the woman, but woman for the sake of the man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	Because of this, the woman ought to have a symbol of authority on her head, on account of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Nevertheless, neither is woman anything apart from man, nor is man anything apart from woman in the Lord.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For just as the woman is from the man, thus also the man is through the woman. But all thingsare from God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	You judge ˻for yourselves˼: is it fitting for a woman to pray to God with her head uncovered?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	And does not nature itself teach you that a man, if he wears long hair, it is a dishonor to him?
B046C011V015	46	11	15	But a woman, if she wears long hair, it is her glory, because her hair is given to her for a covering.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if anyone is disposed to be contentious, we have no such custom, nor do the churches of God.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	But in giving this instruction I do not praise you, because you come together not for the better but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For in the first place, when you come together as a church, I hear there are divisions among you, and in part I believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For indeed it is necessary that there be factions among you, in order that those who are approved may become evident among you.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	Therefore, when you come together in the same place, it is not to eat the Lord’s supper.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For when you eat it, each one of you goes ahead to take his own supper, and one is hungry and another is drunk.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	For do you not have houses for eating and drinking? Or do you despise the church of God and humiliate those who do not have anything? What shall I say to you? Shall I praise you? In this I will not praise you!
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I received from the Lord what I also passed on to you, that the Lord Jesus, on the night in which he was betrayed, took bread,
B046C011V024	46	11	24	and after he had given thanks, he broke it and said, “This is my body which is for you. Do this in remembrance of me.”
B046C011V025	46	11	25	Likewise also the cup, after they had eaten, saying, “This cup is the new covenant in my blood. Do this, as often as you drink it, in remembrance of me.”
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord’s death until he comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	So then, whoever eats the bread or drinks the cup of the Lord in an unworthy manner will be guilty of the body and the blood of the Lord.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	But let a person examine himself, and in this way let him eat from the bread and let him drink from the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For the one who eats and drinks, if he does not recognize the body, eats and drinks judgment against himself.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	Because of this, many are weak and sick among you, and quite a few ˻have died˼.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	But if we were evaluating ourselves, we would not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But if we are judged by the Lord, we are being disciplined, in order that we will not be condemned with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	So then, my brothers, when you come together in order to eat the Lord’s supper, wait for one another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	If anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, lest you come together for judgment. And I will give directions about the remaining matters whenever I come.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers, I do not want you to be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	You know that when you were pagans, you were led astray to the speechless idols, however you were led.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore I make known to you that no one speaking by the Spirit of God says, “Jesus is accursed,” and no one is able to say “Jesus is Lord” except by the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit,
B046C012V005	46	12	5	and there are varieties of ministries, and the same Lord,
B046C012V006	46	12	6	and there are varieties of activities, but the same God, who works all things in all people.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for what is beneficial to all.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	For to one is given a word of wisdom through the Spirit, and to another a word of knowledge by the same Spirit,
B046C012V009	46	12	9	to another faith by the same Spirit, and to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit,
B046C012V010	46	12	10	and to another ˻miraculous powers˼, and to another prophecy, and to another distinguishing of spirits, to another kinds of tongues, and to another interpretation of tongues.
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But in all these things one and the same Spirit is at work, distributing to each one individually just as he wishes.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For just as the body is one and has many members, but all the members of the body, although they are many, are one body, thus also Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For by one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether slaves or free persons, and all were made to drink one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body is not one member, but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot should say, “Because I am not a hand, I am not a part of the body,” not because of this is it not a part of the body.
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear should say, “Because I am not an eye, I am not a part of the body, not because of this is it not a part of the body.
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the sense of smell be?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now God has placed the members, each one of them, in the body just as he wanted.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	And if they all were one member, where would the body be?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But now there are many members, but one body.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	Now the eye is not able to say to the hand, “I do not have need of you,” or again, the head to the feet, “I do not have need of you.”
B046C012V022	46	12	22	But by much more the members of the body which are thought to be weaker are necessary,
B046C012V023	46	12	23	and the parts of the body which we think to be less honorable, these we clothe with more abundant honor, and our unpresentable parts come to have more abundant presentability,
B046C012V024	46	12	24	but our presentable parts do not have need of this. Yet God composed the body by giving more abundant honor to the part which lacked it,
B046C012V025	46	12	25	in order that there not be a division in the body, but the members would have the same concern for one another.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	And if one member suffers, all the members suffer together; if one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	Now you are the body of Christ, and members ˻of it individually˼,
B046C012V028	46	12	28	and whom God has appointed in the church: first, apostles, second, prophets, third, teachers, then miracles, then gifts of healing, helps, administrations, kinds of tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Not all are apostles, are they? Not all are prophets, are they? Not all are teachers, are they? Not all are workers of miracles, are they?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Not all have gifts of healing, do they? Not all speak with tongues, do they? Not all interpret, do they?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	But strive for the greater gifts. And I will show you a still more excellent way.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	If I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, but do not have love, I have become a ringing brass gong or a clashing cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	And if I have the gift of prophecy and I know all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith so that I can remove mountains, but do not have love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	And if I parcel out all my possessions, and if I hand over my body in order that I may boast, but do not have love, it benefits me nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is patient, love is kind, love is not jealous, it does not boast, it does not become conceited,
B046C013V005	46	13	5	it does not behave dishonorably, it˻is not selfish˼, it does not become angry, it does not keep a record of wrongs,
B046C013V006	46	13	6	it does not rejoice at unrighteousness, but rejoices with the truth,
B046C013V007	46	13	7	bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never ends. But if there are prophecies, they will pass away. If there are tongues, they will cease. If there is knowledge, it will pass away.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	For we know in part and we prophesy in part,
B046C013V010	46	13	10	but whenever the perfect comes, the partial will pass away.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I spoke like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child. When I became a man, I set aside the things of a child.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	For now we see through a mirror ˻indirectly˼, but then face to face. Now I know in part, but then I will know completely, just as I have also been completely known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	And now these three things remain: faith, hope, and love. But the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Pursue love, and strive for spiritual gifts, but especially that you may prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For the one who speaks in a tongue does not speak to people but to God, because no one understands, but by the Spirit he speaks mysteries.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But the one who prophesies speaks to people edification and encouragement and consolation.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	The one who speaks in a tongue edifies himself, but the one who prophesies edifies the church.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	Now I want you all to speak with tongues, but even more that you may prophesy. The one who prophesies is greater than the one who speaks with tongues, unless he interprets, in order that the church may receive edification.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	But now, brothers, if I come to you speaking with tongues, how do I benefit you, unless I speak to you either with a revelation or with knowledge or with a prophecy or with a teaching?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	Likewise, the inanimate things which produce a sound, whether flute or lyre, if they do not produce a distinction in the tones, how will it be known what is played on the flute or on the lyre?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	For indeed, if the trumpet produces an indistinct sound, who will prepare for battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	And so you through the tongue, unless you produce a clear message, how will it be known what is spoken? For you will be speaking into the air.
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are probably so many kinds of languages in the world, and none without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	Therefore, if I do not know the meaning of the language, I will be a barbarian to the one who is speaking, and the one who is speaking will be a barbarian in my judgment.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	In this way also you, since you are zealous of spiritual gifts, seek for the edification of the church, in order that you may abound.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore the one who speaks in a tongue must pray that he may interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays but my mind is unproductive.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	˻Therefore what should I do˼? I will pray with my spirit, but I will also pray with my mind. I will sing praise with my spirit, but I will also sing praise with my mind.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	For otherwise, if you praise in your spirit, how will the one who fills the place of the outsider say the “amen” at your thanksgiving, because he does not know what you are saying?
B046C014V017	46	14	17	For indeed you are giving thanks well, but the other person is not edified.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I give thanks to God that I speak with tongues more than all of you,
B046C014V019	46	14	19	but in the church I prefer to speak five words with my mind, in order that I may instruct other people, than ten thousand words in a tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brothers, do not become children in your understanding, but with respect to wickedness be as a child, and in your understanding be mature.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written:“By those who speak a foreign languageand by the lips of othersI will speak to this people,and not even in this way will they obey me,”says the Lord.
B046C014V022	46	14	22	So then, tongues are for a sign not to those who believe, but to unbelievers, but prophecy is not for unbelievers, but for those who believe.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	Therefore, if the whole church comes together at the same time and all speak with tongues, and outsiders or unbelievers enter, will they not say that you are out of your minds?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if all prophesy, and some unbeliever or outsider enters, he is convicted by all, he is judged by all,
B046C014V025	46	14	25	the secret things of his heart become evident, and so, falling on his face, he will worship God, proclaiming, “God is truly among you!”
B046C014V026	46	14	26	˻Therefore what should you do˼, brothers? Whenever you come together, each one of you has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has a tongue, has an interpretation. All things must be done for edification.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If anyone speaks in a tongue, it must be on one occasion two or at most three, and ˻one after the other˼, and one must interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	But if there is no interpreter, he must be silent in the church, but let him speak to himself and to God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Let two or three prophets speak, and the others evaluate.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	And if something is revealed to another who is seated, the first must be silent.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For you are all able to prophesy ˻in turn˼, in order that all may learn and all may be encouraged,
B046C014V032	46	14	32	and the spirits of prophets are subject to prophets.
B046C014V033	46	14	33	For God is not a God of disorder but of peace.As in all the churches of the saints,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	the women must be silent in the churches, for it is not permitted for them to speak, but they must be in submission, just as the law also says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	But if they want to learn something, let them ask their own husbands at home, for it is shameful for a woman to speak in church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	Or has the word of God gone out from you, or has it come to you only?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If anyone thinks he is a prophet or spiritual, he should recognize that the things which I am writing to you are a command of the Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if anyone ignores this, he is ignored.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	So then, my brothers, desire to prophesy, and do not prevent speaking with tongues.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	But let all things be done decently and according to proper procedure.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	Now I make known to you, brothers, the gospel which I proclaimed to you, which you have also received, in which you also stand,
B046C015V002	46	15	2	by which you are also being saved, if you hold fast to the message I proclaimed to you, unless you believed to no purpose.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I passed on to you ˻as of first importance˼ what I also received, that Christ died for our sins according to the scriptures,
B046C015V004	46	15	4	and that he was buried, and that he was raised up on the third day according to the scriptures,
B046C015V005	46	15	5	and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve,
B046C015V006	46	15	6	then he appeared to more than five hundred brothers at once, the majority of whom remain until now, but some have fallen asleep.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	Then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles,
B046C015V008	46	15	8	and last of all, as it were to one born at the wrong time, he appeared also to me.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles, not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by the grace of God I am what I am, and his grace to me has not been in vain, but I labored even more than all of them, and not I, but the grace of God with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Therefore whether I or those, in this way we preached, and in this way you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	Now if Christ is preached as raised up from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	But if there is no resurrection of the dead, Christ has not been raised either.
B046C015V014	46	15	14	But if Christ has not been raised, then both our preaching is in vain, and your faith is in vain.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	And also we are found to be false witnesses of God, because we testified against God that he raised Christ, whom he did not raise if after all, then, the dead are not raised.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, Christ has not been raised either.
B046C015V017	46	15	17	But if Christ has not been raised, your faith is empty; you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	And as a further result, those who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If ˻we have put our hope˼ in Christ in this life only, we are of all people most pitiable.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But now Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have fallen asleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since through a man came death, also through a man came the resurrection of the dead.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For just as in Adam all die, so also in Christ all will be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	But each in his own group: Christ the first fruits, then those who are Christ’s at his coming,
B046C015V024	46	15	24	then the end, when he hands over the kingdom to the God and Father, when he has abolished all rule and all authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For it is necessary for him to reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy to be abolished is death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For “he subjected all things under his feet.” But when it says “all things” are subjected, it is clear that the one who subjected all things to him is not included.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	But whenever all things are subjected to him, then the Son himself also will be subjected to the one who subjected all things to him, in order that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Otherwise, why do they do it, those who are being baptized on behalf of the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why indeed are they being baptized on behalf of them?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why are we in danger every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I die every day—yes indeed, by my boasting in you, brothers, which I have in Christ Jesus our Lord!
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If according to a human perspective I fought wild beasts at Ephesus, what benefit is it to me? If the dead are not raised, let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Do not be deceived! “Bad company corrupts good morals.”
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Sober up correctly and ˻stop sinning˼, for some have no knowledge of God—I say this to your shame.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But someone will say, “How are the dead raised? And with what sort of body do they come?”
B046C015V036	46	15	36	Foolish person! What you sow does not come to life unless it dies.
B046C015V037	46	15	37	And what you sow is not the body which it will become, but you sow the bare seed, whether perhaps of wheat or of some of the rest.
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives to it a body just as he wishes, and to each one of the seeds its own body.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	Not all flesh is the same, but there is one flesh of human beings, and another flesh of animals, and another flesh of birds, and another of fish,
B046C015V040	46	15	40	and heavenly bodies and earthly bodies. But the glory of the heavenly bodiesis of one kind, and the glory of the earthly bodiesis of another kind.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars, for star differs from star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	Thus also is the resurrection of the dead. It is sown in corruption, it is raised in incorruptibility.
B046C015V043	46	15	43	It is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness, it is raised in power.
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown a natural body, it is raised a spiritual body. If there is a natural body, there is also a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	Thus also it is written, “The first man, Adam, became a living soul”; the last Adam became a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	But the spiritual is not first, but the natural; then the spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man is from the earth, made of earth; the second man is from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	As the one who is made of earth, so also are those who are made of earth, and as the heavenly, so also are those who are heavenly.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	And just as we have borne the image of the one who is made of earth, we will also bear the image of the heavenly.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	But I say this, brothers, that flesh and blood is not able to inherit the kingdom of God, nor can corruption inherit incorruptibility.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Behold, I tell you a mystery: we will not all fall asleep, but we will all be changed,
B046C015V052	46	15	52	in a moment, in the blink of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised imperishable, and we will be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For it is necessary for this perishable body to put on incorruptibility, and this mortal body to put on immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	But whenever this perishable body puts on incorruptibility and this mortal body puts on immortality, then the saying that is written will take place:“Death is swallowed up in victory.
B046C015V055	46	15	55	Where, O death, is your victory?Where, O death, is your sting?
B046C015V056	46	15	56	Now the sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ!
B046C015V058	46	15	58	So then, my dear brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	Now concerning the collection for the saints: just as I gave directions about it to the churches of Galatia, so you do also.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	On the first day of the week, each one of you ˻put aside˼something, saving up ˻to whatever extent he has prospered˼, in order that whenever I come, at that time collections do not take place.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	And whenever I arrive, whomever you approve by letters, I will send these to take your gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	And if it is worthwhile for me to go also, they will travel with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	But I will come to you whenever I go through Macedonia (for I am going through Macedonia),
B046C016V006	46	16	6	and perhaps I will stay with you, or even spend the winter, so that you may send me on my way wherever I may go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	For I do not want to see you now in passing, for I hope to remain some time with you, if the Lord allows it.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	But I will remain in Ephesus until Pentecost,
B046C016V009	46	16	9	for a great and effective door has opened for me, and there are many opponents.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	But if Timothy comes, see that he is with you without cause to fear, for he is carrying out the Lord’s work, as I also am.
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Therefore do not let anyone disdain him, but send him on his way in peace in order that he may come to me, for I am expecting him with the brothers.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	Now concerning Apollos our brother, I urged him many times that he should come to you with the brothers, and he was not at all willing that he should come now, but he will come whenever he has an opportunity.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Be on the alert, stand firm in the faith, act courageously, be strong.
B046C016V014	46	16	14	All your actions must be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	Now I urge you, brothers—you know about the household of Stephanas, that they are the first fruits of Achaia, and they have devoted themselves to the ministry for the saints—
B046C016V016	46	16	16	that you also be subject to such people, and to all those who work together and labor.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	Now I rejoice over the arrival of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus, because these make up for your absence,
B046C016V018	46	16	18	for they have refreshed my spirit and yours. Therefore recognize such people.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches of the province of Asia greet you. Aquila and Prisca greet you in the Lord many times, together with the church in their house.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brothers greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	The greeting is by my hand—Paul’s.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If anyone does not love the Lord, let him be accursed. O Lord, come!
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love be with all of you in Christ Jesus.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Timothy our brother, to the church of God that is in Corinth, together with all the saints who are in all Achaia.
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed is the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and God of all comfort,
B047C001V004	47	1	4	who comforts us in all our affliction, so that we may be able to comfort those who are in all affliction with the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	For just as the sufferings of Christ overflow to us, thus through Christ our comfort overflows also.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	But if we are afflicted, it is for your comfort and salvation; if we are comforted, it is for your comfort that is at work in the patient endurance of the same sufferings that we also suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	And our hope for you is firm, because we know that as you are sharers in the sufferings, so also you will be sharers in the comfort.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning our affliction that happened in the province of Asia, that we were burdened to an extraordinary degree, beyond our strength, so that we were in despair even of living.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	But we ourselves had the sentence of death in ourselves, so that we would not be putting confidence in ourselves, but in God who raises the dead,
B047C001V010	47	1	10	who delivered us from so great a risk of death, and will deliver us, in whom we have put our hope that he will also deliver us again,
B047C001V011	47	1	11	while you also join in helping ˻on our behalf˼ by prayer, so that thanks may be given ˻on our behalf˼ by many persons for this gracious gift given to us through the help of many.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For our reason for boasting is this: the testimony of our conscience that we conducted ourselves in the world, and especially toward you, in sincerity and purity of motive from God and not in merely human wisdom, but by the grace of God.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we are not writing anything else to you except what you can read or also understand. But I hope that you will understand ˻completely˼,
B047C001V014	47	1	14	just as you have also understood us in part, that we are your reason for boasting, just as you are also ours in the day of our Lord Jesus.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	And with this confidence, I was wanting to come to you previously, in order that you may have a second proof of my goodwill,
B047C001V016	47	1	16	and through you to go to Macedonia, and to come to you again from Macedonia, and to be sent on my way by you to Judea.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	Therefore, when I was wanting to do this, perhaps then was I making use of vacillation? Or was I deciding what I was deciding according to the flesh, in order that with me my “yes” may be “yes” and my “no” may be “no” at the same time?
B047C001V018	47	1	18	But God is faithful, so that our word to you is not “yes” and “no.”
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, the one who was proclaimed among you by us, by me and Silvanus and Timothy, did not become “yes” and “no,” but has become “yes” in him.
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For as many as are the promises of God, in him they are “yes”; therefore also through him is the “amen” to the glory of God through us.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	Now the one who establishes us together with you in Christ and who anoints us is God,
B047C001V022	47	1	22	who also sealed us and gave the down payment of the Spirit in our hearts.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	But I call upon God as witness against my life, that in order to spare you, I did not come again to Corinth.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not that we lord it over your faith, but we are fellow workers for your joy, because by faith you stand firm.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	For I have decided this for myself, not to come to you again in sorrow.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I cause you sorrow, then who will make me glad except the one who is caused to be sad by me?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	And I wrote this very thing in order that when I came, I would not experience sorrow from those who ought to have made me glad, because I have confidence about you all, that my joy ˻belongs to all of you˼.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For out of great distress and anguish of heart I wrote to you through many tears, not so that you may be caused to be sad, but so that you may know the love that I have especially for you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if anyone has caused sorrow, he has not caused me sorrow, but ˻to some degree˼—˻in order not to say too much˼—to all of you.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	This punishment by the majority is sufficient for such a person.
B047C002V007	47	2	7	So then, you should rather forgive and comfort him, lest somehow this person should be overwhelmed by excessive sorrow.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I urge you to confirm your love for him.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	Because for this reason also I wrote, in order that I could know your proven character, whether you are obedient in everything.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	Now to whomever you forgive anything, I also do; for indeed, whatever I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, it is˻for your sake˼ in the presence of Christ,
B047C002V011	47	2	11	in order that we may not be exploited by Satan (for we are not ignorant of his schemes).
B047C002V012	47	2	12	Now when I arrived in Troas for the gospel of Christ and a door was opened for me by the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	I did not experience rest in my spirit, because I did not find Titus my brother, but saying farewell to them, I departed for Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	But thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumphal procession in Christ, and who reveals the fragrance of the knowledge of him through us in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are the aroma of Christ to God among those who are being saved and among those who are perishing,
B047C002V016	47	2	16	to those on the one hand an odor from death to death, and to those on the other hand a fragrance from life to life. And who is qualified for these things?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not like the majority who peddle the word of God, but as from pure motives—but as from God—we speak before God in Christ.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Are we beginning to commend ourselves again? Or do we, like some, need letters of recommendation to you or from you?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, inscribed on our hearts, known and read by all people,
B047C003V003	47	3	3	revealing that you are a letter of Christ, delivered by us, inscribed not with ink but with the Spirit of the living God, not on stone tablets but on tablets of human hearts.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	Now we possess such confidence through Christ toward God.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	Not that we are adequate in ourselves to consider anything as from ourselves, but our adequacy is from God,
B047C003V006	47	3	6	who also makes us adequate as servants of a new covenant, not of the letter, but of the Spirit, for the letter kills, but the Spirit gives life.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	But if the ministry of death in letters carved on stone came with glory, so that the sons of Israel were not able to look intently into the face of Moses because of the glory of his face, which was transitory,
B047C003V008	47	3	8	how will the ministry of the Spirit not be even more with glory?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if there was glory in the ministry of condemnation, by much more will the ministry of righteousness overflow with glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For indeed what had been glorified has not been glorified in this case, on account of the glory that surpasses it.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if what was transitory came with glory, by much more what remains is with glory.
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Therefore, because we have such a hope, we use much boldness,
B047C003V013	47	3	13	and not as Moses used to place a veil over his face, in order that the sons of Israel would not stare at the end of what was transitory.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	But their minds were hardened. For until this very day, the same veil remains upon the reading of the old covenant, not being uncovered, because it is done away with in Christ.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	But until today, whenever Moses is read aloud, a veil lies upon their heart,
B047C003V016	47	3	16	but whenever one turns to the Lord, the veil is removed.
B047C003V017	47	3	17	Now the Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	And we all, with unveiled face, reflecting the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into the same image from glory into glory, just as from the Lord, the Spirit.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	Because of this, since we have this ministry, just as we have been shown mercy, we do not lose heart,
B047C004V002	47	4	2	but we have renounced shameful hidden things, not behaving with craftiness or adulterating the word of God, but with the open proclamation of the truth commending ourselves to every person’s conscience before God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	But if indeed our gospel is veiled, it is veiled among those who are perishing,
B047C004V004	47	4	4	among whom the god of this age has blinded the minds of the unbelievers, so that they would not see the light of the gospel of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we do not proclaim ourselves, but Jesus Christ as Lord, and ourselves as your slaves for the sake of Jesus.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	For God who said, “Light will shine out of darkness,” is the one who has shined in our hearts for the enlightenment of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in earthenware jars, in order that the extraordinary degree of the power may be from God and not from us.
B047C004V008	47	4	8	We are afflicted in every way, but not crushed; perplexed, but not despairing;
B047C004V009	47	4	9	persecuted, but not abandoned; struck down, but not destroyed;
B047C004V010	47	4	10	always carrying around the death of Jesus in our body, in order that the life of Jesus may also be revealed in our body.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For we who are alive are continually being handed over to death because of Jesus, in order that the life of Jesus may also be revealed in our mortal flesh.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	So then, death is at work in us, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	But because we have the same spirit of faith in accordance with what is written, “I believed, therefore I spoke,” we also believe, therefore we also speak,
B047C004V014	47	4	14	because we know that the one who raised the Lord Jesus will also raise us together with Jesus and present us together with you.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For all these things˻are for your sake˼, in order that the grace that is increasing through the many may cause thanksgiving to abound to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	Therefore we do not lose heart, but even if our outer person is being destroyed, yet our inner person is being renewed day after day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For our momentary light affliction is producing in us an eternal weight of glory ˻beyond all measure and proportion˼,
B047C004V018	47	4	18	because we are not looking at what is seen, but what is not seen. For what is seen is temporary, but what is not seen is eternal.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	For we know that if our earthly house, the tent, is destroyed, we have a building from God, a house not made by hands, eternal in the heavens.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For indeed, in this house we groan, because we desire to put on our dwelling from heaven,
B047C005V003	47	5	3	if indeed, even after we have taken it off, we will not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For indeed we who are in this tent groan, being burdened ˻for this reason, that˼ we do not want to be unclothed, but to be clothed, in order that what is mortal may be swallowed up by life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	Now the one who has prepared us for this very thingis God, who has given us the down payment, the Spirit.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	Therefore, although we are always confident and know that while we are at home in the body we are absent from the Lord—
B047C005V007	47	5	7	for we live by faith, not by sight—
B047C005V008	47	5	8	so we are confident and prefer rather to be absent from the body and to be at home with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	Therefore indeed we have as our ambition, whether at home in the body or absent from the body, to be acceptable to him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ, in order that each one may receive back the things through the body according to what he has done, whether good or bad.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Therefore, because we know the fear of the Lord, we are attempting to persuade people, but we are revealed to God, and I hope to be revealed in your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	We are not commending ourselves to you again, but are giving you an opportunity to boast about us, in order that you may have an answer for those who boast in appearance and not in heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we are out of our senses, it is for God; if we are of sound mind, it is for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of Christ controls us, because we have concluded this: that one died for all; as a result all died.
B047C005V015	47	5	15	And he died for all, in order that those who live should no longer live for themselves, but for the one who died for them and was raised.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	So then, from now on we know no one ˻from a human point of view˼, if indeed we have known Christ ˻from a human point of view˼, but now we know him this way no longer.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Therefore if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation; the old things have passed away; behold, new things have come.
B047C005V018	47	5	18	And all these thingsare from God, who has reconciled us to himself through Christ, and who has given us the ministry of reconciliation,
B047C005V019	47	5	19	namely, that God was in Christ reconciling the world to himself, not counting their trespasses against them, and entrusting to us the message of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	Therefore we are ambassadors on behalf of Christ, as if God were imploring you through us. We beg you on behalf of Christ, be reconciled to God.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	He made the one who did not know sin to be sin on our behalf, in order that we could become the righteousness of God in him.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	Now because we are fellow workers, we also urge you not to receive the grace of God in vain.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	For he says,“At the acceptable time I heard you,and in the day of salvation I helped you.”Behold, now is the acceptable time; behold, now is the day of salvation!
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We are giving no one an occasion for taking offense in anything, in order that our ministry will not have fault found with it,
B047C006V004	47	6	4	but commending ourselves as servants of God in every way, in much endurance, in afflictions, in distresses, in difficulties,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	in beatings, in prisons, in disturbances, in troubles, in sleepless nights, in going hungry,
B047C006V006	47	6	6	in purity, in knowledge, in patience, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in love without hypocrisy,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	in the word of truth, in the power of God, with the weapons of righteousness for the right hand and left hand,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	through glory and dishonor, through slander and good repute, regarded as deceivers and yet truthful,
B047C006V009	47	6	9	as unknown and yet known completely, as dying, and behold, we go on living, as disciplined, and yet not put to death,
B047C006V010	47	6	10	as grieving, but always rejoicing, as poor, but making many rich, as having nothing, and possessing everything.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	˻We have spoken freely and openly˼ to you, Corinthians; our heart is open wide.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted in your affections.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	Now the same wayin exchange (I am speaking as to children), you open wide your hearts also.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Do not become unevenly yoked with unbelievers, for what participation is there between righteousness and lawlessness? Or what fellowship does light have with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	And what agreement does Christ have with Beliar? Or what share does a believer have with an unbeliever?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	And what agreement does the temple of God have with idols? For we are the temple of the living God, just as God said,“I will live in them and will walk about among them,and I will be their God and they will be my people.”
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore “come out from their midstand be separate,” says the Lord,“and do not touch what is unclean,and I will welcome you,
B047C006V018	47	6	18	and I will be a father to you,and you will be sons and daughters to me,”says the all-powerful Lord.
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Therefore since we have these promises, dear friends, let us cleanse ourselves from all defilement of body and spirit, accomplishing holiness in the fear of God.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	˻Make room for us in your hearts˼. We have wronged no one, we have ruined no one, we have defrauded no one.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I do not say this˻to condemn you˼, because I have already said that you are in our hearts, so that we die together and we live together.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	Great is my confidence toward you; great is my boasting on your behalf; I am filled with encouragement; I am overflowing with joy in all our affliction.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For even when we arrived in Macedonia, our body had no rest, but we were afflicted in every way—quarrels outside, fears within.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	But God, who comforts the humble, comforted us by the coming of Titus,
B047C007V007	47	7	7	and not only by his coming, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted among you, because he reported to us your longing, your mourning, your zeal for me, so that I rejoiced even more.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	For if indeed I grieved you by my letter, I do not regret it (even if I did regret it), for I see that that letter grieved you, even though for ˻a short time˼.
B047C007V009	47	7	9	Now I do not rejoice that you were grieved, but that you were grieved to repentence. For you were grieved according to the will of God, so that you suffered loss in no way through us.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For grief according to the will of God brings about a repentence leading to salvation, not to be regretted, but worldly grief brings about death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	For behold how much diligence this very thing, being grieved according to the will of God, has brought about in you: what defense of yourselves, what indignation, what fear, what longing, what zeal, what punishment! In everything you have demonstrated yourselves to be innocent in this matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	Consequently, even if I wrote to you, it was not because of the one who did wrong or because of the one who had been wronged, but in order that your diligence ˻on our behalf˼ might be revealed to you before God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	Because of this we have been encouraged, and in addition to our encouragement, we rejoiced much more over the joy of Titus, because his spirit had been refreshed by all of you.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	For if I have boasted anything to him about you, I have not been put to shame, but as I have spoken everything to you in truth, thus also our boasting to Titus ˻has proven to be true˼.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	And his affection for you is all the more when he remembers the obedience of all of you as you welcomed him with fear and trembling.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I rejoice, because in everything I am completely confident in you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	Now we make known to you, brothers, the grace of God that has been given among the churches of Macedonia,
B047C008V002	47	8	2	that with a great ordeal of affliction, the abundance of their joy and the extreme depth of their poverty have overflowed to the wealth of their generosity.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	I testify that they gave according to their ability, and beyond their ability, by their own choice,
B047C008V004	47	8	4	requesting of us with much exhortation the favor and the fellowship of the ministry to the saints,
B047C008V005	47	8	5	and not just as we had hoped, but they gave themselves first to the Lord and then to us, by the will of God.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	So we urged Titus that, just as he had previously begun it, thus he would also complete for you this act of grace.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	But just as you excel in everything—in faith and in speaking and in knowledge and with all diligence and in the love from us that is in you—so may you excel in this grace also.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I am not saying this as a command, but proving the genuineness of your love by means of the diligence of others.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that although he was rich, for your sake he became poor, in order that you, by his poverty, may become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	And I am giving an opinion in this matter, because this is profitable for you who not only began previously, a year ago, to do something, but also to want to do it.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	So now also complete the doing of it, in order that just as you have the eagerness to want to do it, thus also you may complete it from what you have.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if the eagerness is present ˻according to what one has˼, it is acceptable not ˻according to what one does not have˼.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	For this is not that for others there may be relief, and for you difficult circumstances, but as a matter of equality.
B047C008V014	47	8	14	At the present time your abundance will be for their need, in order that their abundance may also be for your need, so that there may be equality,
B047C008V015	47	8	15	just as it is written, “The one who gathered much did not have too much, and the one who gathered little did not have too little.”
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But thanks be to God, who has put in the heart of Titus the same devotion ˻on your behalf˼,
B047C008V017	47	8	17	because he not only welcomed our request, but being very earnest, by his own choice he went out to you.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	And we have sent at the same time with him the brother whose praise in the gospel has become known throughout all the churches.
B047C008V019	47	8	19	And not only this, but he was also chosen by the churches as our traveling companion together with this gift that is being administered by us to the glory of the Lord himself and to show our readiness to help.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	We are trying to avoid this, lest anyone should find fault with us in this abundant gift that is being administered by us.
B047C008V021	47	8	21	For we are taking into consideration what is honorable not only before the Lord, but also before people.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	And we are sending with them our brother whom we have tested many times in many things that he is diligent, but now much more diligent because of his great confidence in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	If there is a question concerning Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker for you. If there is a question concerning our brothers, they are messengers of the churches, the glory of Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Therefore show to them the proof of your love and our boasting about you ˻openly before˼ the churches.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	For it is unnecessary for me to write to you concerning the ministry to the saints,
B047C009V002	47	9	2	because I know your readiness to help, concerning which I keep on boasting to the Macedonians about you, that Achaia has been ready to help since last year, and your zeal has stirred up the majority of them.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	But I am sending the brothers in order that our boasting about you would not prove to be empty in this case, so that you may be prepared just as I was saying,
B047C009V004	47	9	4	lest somehow if Macedonians should come with me and find you unprepared, we—˻not to speak of you˼—would be humiliated in connection with this project.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	Therefore I considered it necessary to urge the brothers that they should go on ahead to you and make arrangements in advance for your generous gift that was promised previously, so this would be prepared as a generous gift and not as grudgingly granted.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	Now the point is this: the one who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly, and the one who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Each one should give as he has decided in his heart, not ˻reluctantly˼ or from compulsion, for God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	And God is able to cause all grace to abound to you, so that in everything at all times, because you have enough of everything, you may overflow in every good work.
B047C009V009	47	9	9	Just as it is written,“He scattered widely, he gave to the poor;his righteousness remains ˻forever˼.”
B047C009V010	47	9	10	Now the one who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food will provide and multiply your seed, and will cause the harvest of your righteousness to grow,
B047C009V011	47	9	11	being made rich in every way for all generosity, which is producing through us thanksgiving to God,
B047C009V012	47	9	12	because the service of this ministry is not only supplying the needs of the saints, but also is overflowing through many expressions of thanksgiving to God.
B047C009V013	47	9	13	Through the proven character of this service they will glorify God because of the submission of your confession to the gospel of Christ and the generosity of your participation toward them and toward everyone,
B047C009V014	47	9	14	and they are longing for you in their prayers for you, because of the surpassing grace of God to you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Thanks be to God for his indescribable gift!
B047C010V001	47	10	1	Now I, Paul, appeal to you myself by the humility and gentleness of Christ, who ˻when I am present in person˼am humble among you, but when I am absent am bold toward you—
B047C010V002	47	10	2	now I ask when I am present that I will not need to be bold with the confidence with which I propose to show boldness toward some who consider us as behaving according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For although we are living in the flesh, we do not wage war according to the flesh,
B047C010V004	47	10	4	for the weapons of our warfare are not merely human, but powerful to God for the tearing down of fortresses, tearing down arguments
B047C010V005	47	10	5	and all pride that is raised up against the knowledge of God, and taking every thought captive to the obedience of Christ.
B047C010V006	47	10	6	And ˻we are ready˼ to punish all disobedience, whenever your obedience is completed.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	You are looking at things according to appearance. If anyone is convinced he himself is Christ’s, he should consider this concerning himself again: that just as Christ himself is, so also are we.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For even if I boast somewhat more about our authority that the Lord gave us˻for building you up and not for tearing you down˼, I will not be put to shame,
B047C010V009	47	10	9	so that I do not want to appear as if I were terrifying you by my letters,
B047C010V010	47	10	10	because it is said, “His letters are severe and powerful, but his bodily presence is weak and his speech is of no account.”
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Let such a person consider this: that what we are in word by letters when we are absent, we will also be in ˻actions˼when we are present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	For we do not dare to classify or to compare ourselves with some who commend themselves, but they themselves, when they measure themselves by themselves and compare themselves with themselves, do not understand.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	But we will not boast ˻beyond limits˼, but according to the measure of the assignment that God has assigned to us as a measure to reach even as far as you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For we are not overextending ourselves, as if we had not reached you, because we have reached even as far as you with the gospel of Christ,
B047C010V015	47	10	15	not boasting ˻beyond limits˼ in the labors of others, but having hope that as your faith is growing to be enlarged greatly by you according to our assignment,
B047C010V016	47	10	16	so that we may proclaim the gospel in the regions that lie beyond you, and not boast in the things accomplished in the area assigned to someone else.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	But “the one who boasts, let him boast in the Lord.”
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For it is not the one commending himself who is approved, but the one whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	I wish that you would put up with me ˻in something a little foolish˼—but indeed you are putting up with me.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	For I am jealous for you with a godly jealousy, because I promised you in marriage to one husband, to present youas a pure virgin to Christ.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I am afraid lest somehow, as the serpent deceived Eve by his craftiness, your minds may be led astray from the sincerity and the purity of devotion to Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if the one who comes proclaims another Jesus whom we have not proclaimed, or you receive a different spirit which you did not receive, or a different gospel which you did not accept, you put up with it well enough!
B047C011V005	47	11	5	For I consider myself in no way to be inferior to the preeminent apostles.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	But even if I am unskilled in speech, yet I am not in knowledge; certainly in everything we have made this clear to you in every way.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Or did I commit a sin by humbling myself in order that you may be exalted, because I proclaimed the gospel of God to you without payment?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches by accepting support from them for the ministry to you.
B047C011V009	47	11	9	And when I was present with you and was in need, I did not burden anyone, for the brothers who came from Macedonia supplied my need, and in everything I kept myself from being a burden to you, and will keep myself from being a burden.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As the truth of Christ is in me, this boasting ˻of mine˼ will not be stopped in the regions of Achaia.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	˻Why˼? Because I do not love you? God knows I do!
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But what I am doing, I will also do, in order that I may remove the opportunity of those who want an opportunity, that they may be found just as also we are in what they are boasting about.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For such people are false apostles, deceitful workers, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder, for Satan himself disguises himself as an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	Therefore it is not a great thing if his servants also disguise themselves as servants of righteousness, whose end will be according to their deeds.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	Again I say, do not let anyone think I am foolish. But indeed, if you do, accept me even as foolish, in order that I also may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	What I am saying in this project of boasting, I am not saying as the Lord would say, but as in foolishness.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Since many are boasting according to human standards, I also will boast.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	For because you are wise, you put up with foolish people gladly!
B047C011V020	47	11	20	For you put up with it if someone enslaves you, if someone devours you, if someone takes advantage of you, if someone is presumptious toward you, if someone strikes you in the face.
B047C011V021	47	11	21	I say this to my shame, namely, that we have been weak.But in whatever anyone dares to boast—I am speaking in foolishness—I also dare to boast.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? I am also! Are they Israelites? I am also! Are they descendants of Abraham? I am also!
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they servants of Christ?—I am speaking as though I were beside myself—I am more so, with far greater labors, with far more imprisonments, with beatings to a much greater degree, in danger of death many times.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	Five times I received at the hands of the Jews forty lashes less one.
B047C011V025	47	11	25	Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I received a stoning. Three times I was shipwrecked. A day and a night I have spent in the deep water.
B047C011V026	47	11	26	I have been on journeys many times, in dangers from rivers, in dangers from robbers, in dangers from my own people, in dangers from the Gentiles, in dangers in the city, in dangers in the wilderness, in dangers at sea, in dangers because of false brothers,
B047C011V027	47	11	27	with toil and hardship, often in sleepless nights, with hunger and thirst, often going hungry, in cold and poorly clothed.
B047C011V028	47	11	28	Apart from these external things, there is the pressure on me every day of the anxiety about all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is caused to sin, and I do not burn with indignation?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If it is necessary to boast, I will boast about˻the things related to my weakness˼.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of the Lord Jesus, who is blessed ˻forever˼, knows that I am not lying.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus, the governor under King Aretas was guarding the city of the Damascenes in order to take me into custody,
B047C011V033	47	11	33	and I was lowered through a window through the wall in a rope-basket, and I escaped his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	It is necessary to boast; it is not profitable, but I will proceed to visions and revelations of the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I know a man in Christ fourteen years ago—whether in the body I do not know, or outside the body I do not know, God knows—such a man was caught up to the third heaven,
B047C012V003	47	12	3	and I know this man—whether in the body or apart from the body I do not know, God knows—
B047C012V004	47	12	4	that he was caught up to paradise and heard words not to be spoken, which it is not permitted for a person to speak.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	On behalf of such a person I will boast, but on behalf of myself I will not boast, except in my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	For if I want to boast, I will not be foolish, because I will be telling the truth, but I am refraining, so that no one can credit to me more than what he sees in me or hears anything from me,
B047C012V007	47	12	7	even because of the extraordinary degree of the revelations. Therefore, so that I would not exalt myself, a thorn in the flesh was given to me, a messenger of Satan, in order that it would torment me so that I would not exalt myself.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	Three times I appealed to the Lord about this, that it would depart from me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	And he said to me, “My grace is sufficient for you, because the power is perfected in weakness.” Therefore rather I will boast most gladly in my weaknesses, in order that the power of Christ may reside in me.
B047C012V010	47	12	10	Therefore I delight in weaknesses, in insults, in calamities, in persecutions and difficulties for the sake of Christ, for whenever I am weak, then I am strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have become a fool! You compelled me, for I ought to have been commended by you, for I am in no way inferior to the preeminent apostles, even if I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	Indeed, the signs of an apostle have been done among you with all patient endurance, both signs and wonders and deeds of power.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	˻For in what respect are you made worse off˼ more than the rest of the churches, except that I myself was not a burden to you? Forgive me this wrong!
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Behold, this third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not be a burden to you. For I am not seeking your possessions, but you. For children are not obligated to save up for their parents, but parents for their children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	But I will spend and be expended most gladly for your lives. If I love you much more, am I to be loved less?
B047C012V016	47	12	16	But let it be. I have not been a burden to you, but because I was crafty, I took you by cunning.
B047C012V017	47	12	17	I have not taken advantage of you ˻through anyone whom I sent to you˼, have I?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I urged Titus to go, and I sent the brother with him. Titus did not take advantage of you, did he? Did we not conduct ourselves in the same spirit? Did we not walk in the same footsteps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	Have you been thinking all this time that we are defending ourselves to you? We are speaking in Christ before God, and all these things, dear friends, are for your edification.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I am afraid lest somehow when I arrive, I will not find you as I want, and I may be found by you as you do not want. I am afraid lest somehow there will be strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, selfish ambition, slander, gossip, pride, disorder.
B047C012V021	47	12	21	I am afraid lest when I come again my God will humiliate me ˻in your presence˼, and I will grieve over many of those who sinned previously and have not repented because of their impurity and sexual immorality and licentiousness that they have practiced.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This is the third time I am coming to you. ˻By the testimony˼ of two or three witnesses every word will be established.
B047C013V002	47	13	2	I have already said when I was present the second time, and although I am absent now I also say in advance to those who sinned previously and to all the rest, that if I come again I will not spare anyone,
B047C013V003	47	13	3	since you are demanding proof that Christ, who is not weak toward you, but is powerful among you, is speaking in me.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	For indeed, he was crucified because of weakness, but he lives because of the power of God. For we also are weak in him, but we will live together with him because of the power of God toward you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Test yourselves to see if you are in the faith. Examine yourselves! Or do you not recognize regarding yourselves that Jesus Christ is in you, unless you are unqualified?
B047C013V006	47	13	6	And I hope that you will recognize that we are not unqualified!
B047C013V007	47	13	7	Now we pray to God that you not do wrong in any way, not that we are seen as approved, but that you do what is good, even though we are seen as though unqualified.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we are not able to do anything against the truth, but rather only for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	For we rejoice whenever we are weak, but you are strong, and we pray for this: your maturity.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	Because of this, I am writing these thingsalthough I am absent, in order that when I am present I may not have to act severely according to the authority that the Lord has given me for building up and not for tearing down.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Finally, brothers, rejoice, be restored, be encouraged, ˻be in agreement˼, be at peace, and the God of love and peace will be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the saints greet you.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ and the love of God and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with all of you.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	Paul, an apostle not from men nor by men but through Jesus Christ and God the Father who raised him from the dead,
B048C001V002	48	1	2	and all the brothers with me, to the churches of Galatia.
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	who gave himself for our sins in order to rescue us from the present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father,
B048C001V005	48	1	5	to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I am astonished that you are turning away so quickly from the one who called you by the grace of Christ to a different gospel,
B048C001V007	48	1	7	not that there is a different gospel, except there are some who are disturbing you and wanting to distort the gospel of Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even if we or an angel from heaven should proclaim a gospel to you contrary to what we proclaimed to you, let him be accursed!
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As we said before, and now I say again, if anyone is proclaiming a gospel to you contrary to what you have received, let him be accursed!
B048C001V010	48	1	10	For am I now making an appeal to people or to God? Or am I seeking to please people? If I were still trying to please people, I would not be a slave of Christ.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	For I make known to you, brothers, the gospel that has been proclaimed by me, that it is not ˻of human origin˼.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For neither did I receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but I received it through a revelation of Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard about my former way of life in Judaism, that to an extraordinary degree I was persecuting the church of God, and trying to destroy it,
B048C001V014	48	1	14	and was progressing in Judaism beyond many contemporaries in my nation, because I was a far more zealous adherent of the traditions handed down by my forefathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when God, who set me apart from my mother’s womb and called me by his grace, was pleased
B048C001V016	48	1	16	to reveal his Son in me, in order that I would proclaim the gospel about him among the Gentiles, immediately I did not consult with flesh and blood,
B048C001V017	48	1	17	nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away to Arabia and I returned again to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to become acquainted with Cephas, and I stayed with him fifteen days,
B048C001V019	48	1	19	but I did not see any others of the apostles except James, the brother of the Lord.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	(Now the things which I am writing to you, behold, I assure you before God that I am not lying.)
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Then I came to the regions of Syria and of Cilicia,
B048C001V022	48	1	22	but I was unknown ˻in person˼ to the churches of Judea that are in Christ,
B048C001V023	48	1	23	and they were only hearing, “The one formerly persecuting us is now proclaiming the faith that formerly he was attempting to destroy,”
B048C001V024	48	1	24	and they were glorifying God because of me.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Then after fourteen years I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, taking along Titus also.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	Now I went up there because of a revelation and laid out to them the gospel that I preach among the Gentiles, but in private to the influential people, lest somehow I was running, or had run, in vain.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But not even Titus who was with me, although he was a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised.
B048C002V004	48	2	4	Now this was because of the false brothers secretly brought in, who slipped in to spy out our freedom that we have in Christ Jesus, in order that they might enslave us,
B048C002V005	48	2	5	to whom not even for an hour did we yield in subjection, in order that the truth of the gospel might remain continually with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But from those ˻who were influential˼ (whatever they were, it makes no difference to me, ˻God does not show partiality˼)—for those who were influential added nothing to me.
B048C002V007	48	2	7	But these, when they saw that I had been entrusted with the gospel to the uncircumcision, just as Peter to the circumcision
B048C002V008	48	2	8	(for the one who was at work through Peter for his apostleship to the circumcision was at work also through me for the Gentiles),
B048C002V009	48	2	9	and when James and Cephas and John—those thought to be pillars—acknowledged the grace given to me, they gave to me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, in order that we should go to the Gentiles and they to the circumcision.
B048C002V010	48	2	10	They asked only that we should remember the poor, the very thing I was also eager to do.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Cephas came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he was condemned.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For before certain people came from James, he used to eat with the Gentiles, but when they came, he withdrew and separated himself, because he was afraid of those who were of the circumcision,
B048C002V013	48	2	13	and the rest of the Jews also joined in this hypocrisy with him, so that even Barnabas was carried away with them in their hypocrisy.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they were not being straightforward with the truth of the gospel, I said to Cephas in the presence of them all, “If you, although you are a Jew, live like a Gentile and not like a Jew, how can you try to compel the Gentiles to live like Jews?”
B048C002V015	48	2	15	We are Jews by nature and not sinners from among the Gentiles,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	but knowing that a person is not justified by the works of the law, if not by faith in Jesus Christ, and we have believed in Christ Jesus so that we may be justified by faith in Christ and not by the works of the law, because by the works of the law ˻no human being will be justified˼.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	But if while seeking to be justified by Christ, we ourselves also have been found to be sinners, then is Christ an agent of sin? May it never be!
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I build up again these things which I destroyed, I show myself to be a transgressor.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For through the law I died to the law, in order that I might live to God. I have been crucified with Christ,
B048C002V020	48	2	20	and I no longer live, but Christ lives in me, and that life I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me and gave himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not declare invalid the grace of God, for if righteousness is through the law, then Christ died to no purpose.
B048C003V001	48	3	1	O foolish Galatians, who has bewitched you, before whose eyes Jesus Christ was publicly portrayed as having been crucified?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	I want only to learn this from you: Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish? Having begun by the Spirit, are you now trying to be made complete by the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Have you suffered so many things for nothing—if indeed also it was for nothing?
B048C003V005	48	3	5	Therefore does the one who gives you the Spirit and who works miracles among you do so by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?
B048C003V006	48	3	6	Just as Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him for righteousness,
B048C003V007	48	3	7	then understand that the ones ˻who have faith˼, these are sons of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	And the scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles by faith, proclaimed the good news in advance to Abraham: “In you all the nations will be blessed.”
B048C003V009	48	3	9	So then, the ones who have faith are blessed together with Abraham who believed.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse, for it is written, “Cursed is everyone who does not abide by all the things that are written in the book of the law to do them.”
B048C003V011	48	3	11	Now it is clear that no one is justified in the sight of God by the law, because “the one who is righteous will live by faith.”
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the law is not from faith, but “the one who does these things will live by them.”
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ redeemed us from the curse of the law by becoming a curse for us, because it is written, “Cursed is everyone who hangs on a tree,”
B048C003V014	48	3	14	in order that the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles in Christ Jesus, so that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brothers, I am speaking according to a human perspective. Nevertheless, when the covenant of a man has been ratified, no one declares it invalid or adds additional provisions to it.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	Now to Abraham and to his descendant the promises were spoken. It does not say, “and to descendants,” as concerning many, but as concerning one, “and to your descendant,” who is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	Now I am saying this: the law, that came after four hundred and thirty years, does not revoke a covenant previously ratified by God, in order to nullify the promise.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance is from the law, it is no longer from the promise, but God graciously gave it to Abraham through the promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Why then the law? It was added on account of transgressions, until the descendant should come to whom it had been promised, having been ordered through angels by the hand of a mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	Now the mediator is not for one, but God is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Therefore is the law opposed to the promises of God? May it never be! For if a law had been given that was able to give life, certainly righteousness would have been from the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the scripture imprisoned all under sin, in order that the promise could be given by faith in Jesus Christ to those who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	But before faith came, we were detained under the law, imprisoned until the coming faith was revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	So then, the law became our guardian until Christ, in order that we could be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But after faith has come, we are no longer under a guardian.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For you are all sons of God through faith in Christ Jesus,
B048C003V027	48	3	27	for as many of you as were baptized into Christ have put on Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free, there is neither male and female, for you are all one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	And if you are Christ’s, then you are descendants of Abraham, heirs according to the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	Now I say, for as long a time as the heir is a child, he is no different from a slave, although he is master of everything,
B048C004V002	48	4	2	but he is under guardians and managers until the time set by his father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	So also we, when we were children, we were enslaved under the elemental spirits of the world.
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fullness of time came, God sent out his Son, born of a woman, born under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	in order that he might redeem those under the law, in order that we might receive the adoption.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because you are sons, God sent out the Spirit of his Son into our hearts, crying out, “Abba! (Father!),”
B048C004V007	48	4	7	so that you are no longer a slave but a son, and if a son, also an heir through God.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	But at that time when you did not know God, you were enslaved to the things which by nature are not gods.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now, because you have come to know God, or rather have come to be known by God, how can you turn back again to the weak and miserable elemental spirits? Do you want to be enslaved to them all over again?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You carefully observe days and months and seasons and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid for you, lest perhaps I have labored for you in vain!
B048C004V012	48	4	12	I ask you, brothers, become like me, because I also have become like you. You have done me no wrong!
B048C004V013	48	4	13	But you know that because of an illness of the flesh I proclaimed the gospel to you the first time.
B048C004V014	48	4	14	And you did not despise or disdain what was a trial for you in my flesh, but you welcomed me like an angel of God, like Christ Jesus.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	So where is your blessing? For I testify to you that, if possible, you would have torn out your eyes and given them to me!
B048C004V016	48	4	16	So then, have I become your enemy by being truthful to you?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They zealously seek you, not commendably, but they want to exclude you, in order that you may seek them zealously.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	But it is good to be sought zealously in good at all times, and not only when I am present with you.
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My children, for whom I am having birth pains again, until Christ is formed in you!
B048C004V020	48	4	20	But I could wish to be present with you now, and to change my tone because I am perplexed about you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who are wanting to be under the law, do you not understand the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by the female slave and one by the free woman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	But the one by the female slave was born according to human descent, and the one by the free woman through the promise,
B048C004V024	48	4	24	which things are spoken allegorically, for these women are two covenants, one from Mount Sinai, bearing children for slavery, who is Hagar.
B048C004V025	48	4	25	Now Hagar is Mount Sinai in Arabia, and corresponds to the present Jerusalem, for she is a slave with her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But the Jerusalem above is free, which is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written,“Rejoice, O barren woman, who does not give birth to children;burst out and shout, you who do not have birth pains,because many are the children of the desolate woman,even more than those of the one who has a husband.”
B048C004V028	48	4	28	But you, brothers, are children of the promise, just as Isaac.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But just as at that time the child born according to human descent persecuted the child born according to the Spirit, so also now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	But what does the scripture say? “Drive out the female slave and her son, for the son of the female slave will never inherit with the son” of the free woman.
B048C004V031	48	4	31	Therefore, brothers, we are not children of the female slave but of the free woman.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	For freedom Christ has set us free. Stand firm, therefore, and do not be subject again to a yoke of slavery.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Look! I, Paul, tell you that if you become circumcised, Christ will profit you nothing!
B048C005V003	48	5	3	And again I testify to every man who becomes circumcised, that he is under obligation to keep the whole law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You are estranged from Christ, you who are attempting to be justified by the law; you have fallen from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For through the Spirit by faith we eagerly await the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision counts for anything nor uncircumcision, but faith working through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running well. Who hindered you from obeying the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	This persuasion is not from the one who calls you!
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little leaven leavens the whole batch of dough.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I have confidence in you in the Lord that you will think nothing different, but the one who is confusing you ˻will pay the penalty˼, whoever he may be.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	Now, brothers, if I am still preaching circumcision, why am I still being persecuted? In that case the stumbling block of the cross has been abolished.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	I wish that the ones who are disturbing you would also ˻castrate themselves˼!
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you were called to freedom, brothers. Only do not let your freedom become an opportunity for the flesh, but through love serve one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For the whole law is fulfilled in one statement, namely, “You shall love your neighbor as yourself.”
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, watch out that you are not consumed by one another.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	But I say, live by the Spirit, and you will never carry out the desire of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the flesh desires against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh, for these are in opposition to one another, so that whatever you want, you may not do these things.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the deeds of the flesh are evident, which are sexual immorality, impurity, licentiousness,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, sorcery, enmity, strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, selfish ambition, dissension, factions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	envy, drunkenness, carousing, and things like these, things which I am telling you in advance, just as I said before, that the ones who practice such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, self control. Against such things there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	Now those ˻who belong to Christ Jesus˼ have crucified the flesh together with its feelings and its desires.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, we must also follow the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	We must not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brothers, even if a person is caught in some trespass, you who are spiritual restore such a person in a spirit of humility, looking out for yourself, lest you also be tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Carry the burdens of one another, and so fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if anyone thinks he is something although he is nothing, he is deceiving himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let each one examine his own work, and then he will have a reason for boasting in himself alone, and not in someone else.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For each one will carry his own burden.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	Now the one who is taught the word must share in all good things with the one who teaches.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not be deceived: God is not to be mocked, for whatever a person sows, this he will also reap,
B048C006V008	48	6	8	because the one who sows to his own flesh will reap corruption from the flesh, but the one who sows to the Spirit will reap eternal life from the Spirit.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	And let us not grow weary in doing good, for at the proper time we will reap, if we do not give up.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	So then, as we have opportunity, let us do good to all people, and especially to those who belong to the household of faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See with what large letters I am writing to you with my own hand.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	As many as are wanting to make a good showing in the flesh, these are attempting to compel you to be circumcised, only so that they will not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For not even those who are circumcised observe the law themselves, but they want you to be circumcised in order that they may boast in your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But as for me, may it never be that I boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For neither is circumcision anything nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	And all those who follow this rule, peace and mercy be on them and on the Israel of God.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	Finally, let no one cause me trouble, for I carry on my body the marks of Jesus.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brothers. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, to the saints who are in Ephesus and faithful in Christ Jesus:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed is the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places in Christ,
B049C001V004	49	1	4	just as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and blameless before him in love,
B049C001V005	49	1	5	having predestined us to adoption through Jesus Christ to himself according to the good pleasure of his will,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	to the praise of the glory of his grace that he bestowed on us in the beloved,
B049C001V007	49	1	7	in whom we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of his grace,
B049C001V008	49	1	8	that he caused to abound to us in all wisdom and insight,
B049C001V009	49	1	9	making known to us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure that he purposed in him,
B049C001V010	49	1	10	for the administration of the fullness of times, to bring together all things in Christ, the things in the heavens and the things on the earth, in him
B049C001V011	49	1	11	in whom also we were chosen, having been predestined according to the purpose of the One who works all things according to the counsel of his will,
B049C001V012	49	1	12	that we who hoped beforehand in Christ should be for the praise of his glory,
B049C001V013	49	1	13	in whom also you, when you heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation, in whom also when you believed you were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	who is the down payment of our inheritance, until the redemption of the possession, to the praise of his glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	Because of this I also, hearing of ˻your faith˼ in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	do not cease giving thanks for you, making mention in my prayers,
B049C001V017	49	1	17	that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, ˻the glorious Father˼, may give you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him
B049C001V018	49	1	18	(the eyes of your hearts having been enlightened), so that you may know what is the hope of his calling, what are the riches of the glory of his inheritance among the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	and what is the surpassing greatness of his power toward us who believe, according to the working of his mighty strength
B049C001V020	49	1	20	which he worked in Christ, raising him from the dead and seating him at his right hand in the heavenly places,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	above all rule and authority and power and lordship and every name named, not only in this age but also in the coming one,
B049C001V022	49	1	22	and he subjected all things under his feet and gave him as head over all things to the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	which is his body, the fullness of the one who fills all things in every way.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	And you, ˻although you were dead˼ in your trespasses and sins,
B049C002V002	49	2	2	in which you formerly walked according to the course of this world, according to the ruler of the authority of the air, the spirit now working in the sons of disobedience,
B049C002V003	49	2	3	among whom also we all formerly lived in the desires of our flesh, doing the will of the flesh and of the mind, and we were children of wrath by nature, as also the rest of them were.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, being rich in mercy, because of his great love with which he loved us,
B049C002V005	49	2	5	and we being dead in trespasses, he made us alive together with Christ (by grace you are saved),
B049C002V006	49	2	6	and raised us together and seated us together in the heavenly places in Christ Jesus,
B049C002V007	49	2	7	in order that he might show in the coming ages the surpassing riches of his grace in kindness upon us in Christ Jesus.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by grace you are saved through faith, and this is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God;
B049C002V009	49	2	9	it is not from works, so that no one can boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his creation, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand, so that we may walk in them.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Therefore remember that formerly you, the Gentiles in the flesh, the so-called uncircumcision by the so-called circumcision in the flesh, made by hands,
B049C002V012	49	2	12	that you were at that time apart from Christ, alienated from the citizenship of Israel, and strangers to the covenants of promise, not having hope, and without God in the world.
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now in Christ Jesus you, the ones who once were far away, have become near by the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For he himself is our peace, who made both one and broke down the dividing wall of the partition, the enmity, in his flesh,
B049C002V015	49	2	15	invalidating the law of commandments in ordinances, in order that he might create the two in himself into one new man, thus making peace,
B049C002V016	49	2	16	and might reconcile both in one body to God through the cross, killing the enmity in himself.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	And coming, he proclaimed the good news of peace to you who were far away and peace to the ones who were near,
B049C002V018	49	2	18	because through him we both have access in one Spirit to the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	Consequently, therefore, you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but you are fellow citizens of the saints and members of the household of God,
B049C002V020	49	2	20	built on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Christ Jesus himself being the cornerstone,
B049C002V021	49	2	21	in whom the whole building, joined together, grows into a holy temple in the Lord,
B049C002V022	49	2	22	in whom you also are built up together into a dwelling place of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	On account of this I, Paul, the prisoner of Christ Jesus for the sake of you Gentiles
B049C003V002	49	3	2	—if indeed you have heard about the stewardship of God’s grace given to me for you,
B049C003V003	49	3	3	that according to revelation the mystery was made known to me, just as I wrote beforehand in brief,
B049C003V004	49	3	4	so that you may be able when you read to understand my insight into the mystery of Christ
B049C003V005	49	3	5	(which in other generations was not made known to the sons of men as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit):
B049C003V006	49	3	6	that the Gentiles are fellow heirs, and fellow members of the body, and fellow sharers of the promise in Christ Jesus through the gospel,
B049C003V007	49	3	7	of which I became a servant, according to the gift of God’s grace given to me, according to the working of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, the least of all the saints, was given this grace: to proclaim the good news of the fathomless riches of Christ to the Gentiles,
B049C003V009	49	3	9	and to enlighten everyone as to what is the administration of the mystery hidden from the ages by God, who created all things,
B049C003V010	49	3	10	in order that the many-sided wisdom of God might be made known now to the rulers and the authorities in the heavenly places through the church,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	according to the purpose of the ages which he carried out in Christ Jesus our Lord,
B049C003V012	49	3	12	in whom we have boldness and access in confidence through faith in him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	Therefore I ask you not to be discouraged at my afflictions on behalf of you, which are your glory.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	On account of this, I bend my knees before the Father,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	from whom every family in heaven and on earth is named,
B049C003V016	49	3	16	that he may grant you according to the riches of his glory to be strengthened with power through his Spirit in the inner person,
B049C003V017	49	3	17	that Christ may dwell in your hearts through faith (you having been firmly rooted and established in love),
B049C003V018	49	3	18	in order that you may be strong enough to grasp together with all the saints what is the breadth, and length, and height, and depth,
B049C003V019	49	3	19	and to know the love of Christ that surpasses knowledge, in order that you may be filled up to all the fullness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	Now to the one who is able to do beyond all measure more than all that we ask or think, according to the power that is at work in us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	to him be the glory in the church and in Christ Jesus to all generations forever and ever. Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	Therefore I, the prisoner in the Lord, exhort you to live in a manner worthy of the calling with which you were called:
B049C004V002	49	4	2	with all humility and gentleness, with patience, putting up with one another in love,
B049C004V003	49	4	3	being eager to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace;
B049C004V004	49	4	4	one body and one Spirit (just as also you were called with one hope of your calling),
B049C004V005	49	4	5	one Lord, one faith, one baptism,
B049C004V006	49	4	6	one God and Father of all, who is over all, and through all, and in all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	Now to each one of us was given this grace, according to the measure of Christ’s gift.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Therefore it says,“Ascending on high he led captivity captive;he gave gifts to men.”
B049C004V009	49	4	9	Now “he ascended,” what is it, except that he also descended to the lower regions of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	The one who descended himself is also the one who ascended above all the heavens, in order that he might fill all things.
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And he himself gave some as apostles and some as prophets and some as evangelists and some as pastors and teachers
B049C004V012	49	4	12	for the equipping of the saints, for the work of the ministry, for building up the body of Christ,
B049C004V013	49	4	13	until we all reach the unity of the faith and the knowledge of the Son of God, to a mature man, to a measure of the maturity of the fullness of Christ,
B049C004V014	49	4	14	so that we may no longer be infants, tossed about by waves and carried about by every wind of teaching, by the trickery of people, by craftiness with reference to the scheming of deceit.
B049C004V015	49	4	15	But speaking the truth in love, we are to grow into him with reference to all things, who is the head, Christ,
B049C004V016	49	4	16	from whom the whole body, joined together and held together by every supporting ligament, according to the working by measure of each single part, the growth of the body makes for the building up of itself in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	This therefore I say and testify in the Lord, that you no longer walk as the Gentiles walk: in the futility of their mind,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	being darkened in understanding, alienated from the life of God, because of the ignorance that is in them, because of the hardness of their heart,
B049C004V019	49	4	19	who, becoming callous, gave themselves over to licentiousness, for the pursuit of all uncleanness in greediness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you did not learn Christ in this way,
B049C004V021	49	4	21	if indeed you have heard about him, and you were taught by him (just as truth is in Jesus),
B049C004V022	49	4	22	that you take off, according to your former way of life, the old man, who is being destroyed according to deceitful desires,
B049C004V023	49	4	23	be renewed in the spirit of your mind,
B049C004V024	49	4	24	and put on the new man (in accordance with God), who is created in righteousness and holiness from the truth.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore, putting aside the lie, speak truth each one of you with his neighbor, because we are members of one another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	Be angry and do not sin; do not let the sun set on your anger,
B049C004V027	49	4	27	nor give place to the devil.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	The one who steals must steal no longer, but instead must labor, working with his own hands what is good, so that he may have something to share with the one who has need.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	˻No rotten word must proceed˼ from your mouth, but only something good for the building up of the need, in order that it may give grace to those who hear,
B049C004V030	49	4	30	and do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, by whom you were sealed for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	All bitterness, and rage, and wrath, and clamor, and abusive speech, must be removed from you, together with all wickedness.
B049C004V032	49	4	32	But become kind toward one another, compassionate, forgiving one another, just as also God in Christ has forgiven you.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	Therefore become imitators of God, as beloved children,
B049C005V002	49	5	2	and live in love, just as also Christ loved us, and gave himself for us an offering and sacrifice to God for a fragrant smell.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness, or greediness, must not even be named among you (as is fitting for saints),
B049C005V004	49	5	4	and obscenity, and foolish talk, or coarse jesting (which are not proper), but rather thanksgiving.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	For this you know ˻for certain˼, that every sexually immoral person, or unclean person, or greedy person (who is an idolater), does not have an inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of these things the wrath of God is coming on the sons of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Therefore do not be sharers with them,
B049C005V008	49	5	8	for you were formerly darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Live like children of light
B049C005V009	49	5	9	(for the fruit of the light is in all goodness and righteousness and truth),
B049C005V010	49	5	10	trying to learn what is well-pleasing to the Lord.
B049C005V011	49	5	11	And do not participate in the unfruitful deeds of darkness, but rather even expose them.
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For it is shameful even to speak about the things being done by them in secret,
B049C005V013	49	5	13	but all things exposed by the light are made visible,
B049C005V014	49	5	14	for everything made visible is light. Therefore it says,Wake up, sleeper,and rise from the dead,and Christ will shine on you.
B049C005V015	49	5	15	Therefore, consider carefully how you live, not as unwise but as wise,
B049C005V016	49	5	16	making the most of the time because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Because of this do not become foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	And do not be drunk with wine (in which is dissipation), but be filled by the Spirit,
B049C005V019	49	5	19	speaking to one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and singing praise in your heart to the Lord,
B049C005V020	49	5	20	giving thanks always for all things in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to the God and Father,
B049C005V021	49	5	21	being subject to one another ˻out of reverence for˼ Christ
B049C005V022	49	5	22	—wives to their own husbands as to the Lord,
B049C005V023	49	5	23	because the husband is the head of the wife, as also Christ is the head of the church (he himself being the Savior of the body).
B049C005V024	49	5	24	But as the church is subject to Christ, thus also wives should be subject to their husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ also loved the church, and gave himself for her;
B049C005V026	49	5	26	in order that he might sanctify her by cleansing her with the washing of water by the word;
B049C005V027	49	5	27	in order that he might present to himself the church glorious, not having a spot or wrinkle or any such thing, but that she may be holy and blameless.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	Thus also husbands ought to love their own wives as their own bodies. The one who loves his own wife loves himself.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no one ever hated his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, just as also Christ does the church,
B049C005V030	49	5	30	because we are members of his body.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	“For this reason a man will leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and the two will become one flesh.”
B049C005V032	49	5	32	(This mystery is great, but I am speaking with reference to Christ and the church.)
B049C005V033	49	5	33	Only you also, each one of you, must thus love his own wife as himself, and the wife ˻must respect˼ her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in the Lord, for this is right.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	“Honor your father and mother” (which is the first commandment with a promise),
B049C006V003	49	6	3	“in order that it may be well with you, and you may ˻live a long time˼ on the earth.”
B049C006V004	49	6	4	And fathers, do not make your children angry, but bring them up in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Slaves, obey your earthly masters with fear and trembling, in the sincerity of your heart, as to Christ,
B049C006V006	49	6	6	not ˻while being watched˼, as people pleasers, but as slaves of Christ doing the will of God from the heart,
B049C006V007	49	6	7	serving with goodwill as to the Lord and not to people,
B049C006V008	49	6	8	knowing that each one of you, if he should do anything good, this he will receive back from the Lord, whether slave or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	And masters, do the same things to them, giving up threats, knowing that both their Lord and yours is in heaven, and there is no partiality with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	Finally, become strong in the Lord and in the might of his strength.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the full armor of God, so that you may be able to stand against the strategems of the devil,
B049C006V012	49	6	12	because our struggle is not against blood and flesh, but against the rulers, against the authorities, against the world rulers of this darkness, against the spiritual forces of wickedness in the heavenly places.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Because of this, take up the full armor of God, in order that you may be able to resist in the evil day, and having done everything, to stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand therefore, girding your waist with truth, and putting on the breastplate of righteousness,
B049C006V015	49	6	15	and binding shoes under your feet with the preparation of the good news of peace,
B049C006V016	49	6	16	in everything taking up the shield of faith, with which you are able to quench all the flaming arrows of the evil one,
B049C006V017	49	6	17	and receive the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God,
B049C006V018	49	6	18	with all prayer and supplication praying at all times in the Spirit, and to this end being alert with all perseverance and supplication for all the saints,
B049C006V019	49	6	19	and for me, that a word may be given to me at the opening of my mouth, to make known with boldness the mystery of the gospel,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	for the sake of which I am an ambassador in chains, that ˻in them˼ I may speak freely, as it is necessary for me to speak.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	Now, so that you also may know ˻my circumstances˼, what I am doing, Tychicus, my dear brother and faithful servant in the Lord, will make known to you all things,
B049C006V022	49	6	22	whom I have sent to you for this very reason, that you may know ˻our circumstances˼, and he may encourage your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace to the brothers and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be with all who love our Lord Jesus Christ in incorruptibility.
B050C001V001	50	1	1	Paul and Timothy, slaves of Christ Jesus, to all the saints in Christ Jesus who are in Philippi, together with the overseers and deacons.
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I give thanks to my God upon my every remembrance of you,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	always in my every prayer for all of you, making the prayer with joy,
B050C001V005	50	1	5	because of your participation in the gospel from the first day until now,
B050C001V006	50	1	6	convinced of this same thing, that the one who began a good work in you will finish it until the day of Christ Jesus,
B050C001V007	50	1	7	just as it is right for me to think this about all of you, because I have you in my heart, since both in my imprisonment and in the defense and confirmation of the gospel all of you are sharers of grace with me.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness, that I long for all of you with the affection of Christ Jesus.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this I pray: that your love may abound still more and more in knowledge and all discernment,
B050C001V010	50	1	10	so that you may approve what is superior, in order that you may be sincere and blameless in the day of Christ,
B050C001V011	50	1	11	having been filled with the fruit of righteousness which comes through Jesus Christ to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	Now I want you to know, brothers, that ˻my circumstances˼ have happened instead for the progress of the gospel,
B050C001V013	50	1	13	so that my imprisonment in Christ has become known in the whole praetorium and to all the rest,
B050C001V014	50	1	14	and most of the brothers, trusting in the Lord because of my imprisonment, dare even more to speak the word without fear.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some even because of envy and strife preach Christ, but some also because of good will.
B050C001V016	50	1	16	The latter do so from love, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the gospel.
B050C001V017	50	1	17	The former proclaim Christ from selfish ambition, not sincerely, thinking to raise up affliction in my imprisonment.
B050C001V018	50	1	18	˻What is the result?˼ Only that in every way, whether in pretense or in truth, Christ is proclaimed, and in this I rejoice. But also I will rejoice,
B050C001V019	50	1	19	for I know that this will turn out to me for deliverance through your prayer and the support of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,
B050C001V020	50	1	20	according to my eager expectation and hope, that I will be put to shame in nothing, but with all boldness, even now as always Christ will be exalted in my body, whether through life or through death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me to live is Christ and to die is gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	But if it is to live in the flesh, this is fruitful work for me, and which I will prefer I do not know.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	But I am hard pressed ˻between the two options˼, having the desire to depart and to be with Christ, ˻for this is very much better˼.
B050C001V024	50	1	24	But to stay on in the flesh is more necessary for your sake.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	And because I am convinced of this, I know that I will remain and continue with all of you for your progress and joy in the faith,
B050C001V026	50	1	26	so that what you can be proud of may increase in Christ Jesus because of me through my return again to you.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	Only lead your lives in a manner worthy of the gospel of Christ, so that whether I come and see you or am absent I hear ˻your circumstances˼, that you are standing firm in one spirit, with one soul contending side by side for the faith of the gospel,
B050C001V028	50	1	28	and not letting yourselves be intimidated in anything by your opponents, which is a sign of destruction to them, but of your salvation, and this from God,
B050C001V029	50	1	29	because to you has been graciously granted on behalf of Christ not only to believe in him, but also to suffer on behalf of him,
B050C001V030	50	1	30	having the same struggle which you saw in me and now hear about in me.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	Therefore, if there is any encouragement in Christ, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any affection and compassion,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	complete my joy, so that ˻you are in agreement˼, having the same love, united in spirit, ˻having one purpose˼.
B050C002V003	50	2	3	Do nothing according to selfish ambition or according to empty conceit, but in humility considering one another better than yourselves,
B050C002V004	50	2	4	each one of you not looking out for ˻his own interests˼, but also each of you looking out for˻the interests˼ of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Think this in yourselves which was also in Christ Jesus,
B050C002V006	50	2	6	who, existing in the form of God,did not consider being equal with God something to be grasped,
B050C002V007	50	2	7	but emptied himselfby taking the form of a slave,by becoming in the likeness of people.And being found in appearance like a man,
B050C002V008	50	2	8	he humbled himselfby becoming obedient to the point of death,that is, death on a cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Therefore also God exalted himand graciously granted him the name above every name,
B050C002V010	50	2	10	so that at the name of Jesusevery knee should bow,of those in heaven and of those on earth and of those under the earth,
B050C002V011	50	2	11	and every tongue confessthat Jesus Christ is Lord,to the glory of God the Father.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	Therefore my dear friends, just as you have always obeyed, not as in my presence only but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.
B050C002V013	50	2	13	For the one at work in you, both to will and to work for his good pleasure, is God.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do all things without grumbling and disputing,
B050C002V015	50	2	15	in order that you may become blameless and innocent, children of God without fault in the midst of a crooked and perverted generation, among whom you shine as stars in the world,
B050C002V016	50	2	16	holding fast to the word of life, for a source of pride to me in the day of Christ, that I did not run in vain or labor in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	But even if I am being poured out as a drink offering on the sacrifice and service of your faith, I rejoice and rejoice with all of you.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	And in the same way also you rejoice and rejoice with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	But I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon, so that I also may be encouraged when I know ˻your circumstances˼.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no one like-minded who will sincerely be concerned about ˻your circumstances˼.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For they all seek ˻their own interests˼, not those of Jesus Christ.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But you know his proven character, that like a child with a father he served with me for the gospel.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Therefore I hope to send him at once, as soon as I see ˻my circumstances˼.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	And I am convinced in the Lord that I myself will arrive shortly also.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	But I considered it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother and fellow worker and fellow soldier, but your messenger and servant of my need,
B050C002V026	50	2	26	because he was longing for all of you and was distressed because you had heard that he was sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	For indeed he was sick, coming near to death, but God had mercy on him and not on him only, but also on me, so that I would not have grief upon grief.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	Therefore I am sending him with special urgency, in order that when you see him again you may rejoice, and I may be less anxious.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Therefore welcome him in the Lord with all joy, and consider such people highly honored,
B050C002V030	50	2	30	because on account of the work of Christ he came near to the point of death, risking his life in order that ˻he might make up for your inability to serve me˼.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord. To write the same things to you is not troublesome to me, but is a safeguard for you.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs, beware of the evil workers, beware of the mutilation.
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For we are the circumcision, the ones who worship by the Spirit of God and boast in Christ Jesus and do not put confidence in the flesh,
B050C003V004	50	3	4	although I could have confidence even in the flesh.If anyone else thinks to put confidence in the flesh, I can do so more:
B050C003V005	50	3	5	˻circumcised on the eighth day˼, from the nation of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew born from Hebrews, according to the law a Pharisee,
B050C003V006	50	3	6	according to zeal persecuting the church, according to the righteousness in the law being blameless.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But whatever things were gain to me, these things I have considered loss because of Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	˻More than that˼, I even consider all things to be loss because of the surpassing greatness of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord, for the sake of whom I have suffered the loss of all things, and consider them dung, in order that I may gain Christ
B050C003V009	50	3	9	and may be found in him, not having my righteousness which is from the law, but which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness from God on the basis of faith,
B050C003V010	50	3	10	so that I may know him and the power of his resurrection and the fellowship of his sufferings, being conformed to his death,
B050C003V011	50	3	11	if somehow I may attain to the resurrection from the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	Not that I have already received this, or have already been made perfect, but I press on if indeed I may lay hold of that for which also I was laid hold of by Christ Jesus.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brothers, I do not consider myself to have laid hold of it. But I do one thing, forgetting the things behind and straining toward the things ahead,
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I press on toward the goal for the prize of the upward call of God in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Therefore as many as are perfect, ˻let us hold this opinion˼, and if you think anything differently, God will reveal this also to you.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	Only to what we have attained, to the same hold on.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Become fellow imitators of me, brothers, and observe those who walk in this way, just as you have us as an example.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For many live, of whom I spoke about to you many times, but now speak about even weeping, as the enemies of the cross of Christ,
B050C003V019	50	3	19	whose end is destruction, whose God is the stomach, and whose glory is in their shame, the ones who think on earthly things.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	For our commonwealth exists in heaven, from which also we eagerly await a savior, the Lord Jesus Christ,
B050C003V021	50	3	21	who will transform our humble body to be conformed to his glorious body, in accordance with the power that enables him even to subject all things to himself.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	So then, my beloved and greatly desired brothers, my joy and crown, thus stand firm in the Lord, dear friends.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I appeal to Euodia and I appeal to Syntyche ˻to be in agreement˼ in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	Yes, I ask also you, true yokefellow, help them, who struggled along with me in the gospel with both Clement and the rest of my fellow workers whose names are in the book of life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in the Lord always; again I say, rejoice.
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your gentleness be made known to all people. The Lord is near.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	Be anxious for nothing, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God.
B050C004V007	50	4	7	And the peace of God that surpasses all understanding will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are honorable, whatever things are right, whatever things are pure, whatever things are pleasing, whatever things are commendable, if there is any excellence of character and if anything praiseworthy, think about these things.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	And the things which you have learned and received and heard about and seen in me, practice these things, and the God of peace will be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	But I rejoiced in the Lord greatly that now at last ˻you have renewed your concern for me˼, for whom also you were thinking, but you had no opportunity to express it.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	Not that I speak from need, for I have learned to be content in whatever circumstances I am.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how both ˻to make do with little˼ and I know how˻to have an abundance˼. In everything and in all things I have learned the secret both to be filled and to be hungry, both ˻to have an abundance˼ and to go without.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I am able to do all things by the one who strengthens me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Nevertheless you have done well by sharing with me in my affliction.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	Now you also know, Philippians, that at the beginning of the gospel, when I departed from Macedonia, no church shared with me in the matter of giving and receiving except you alone,
B050C004V016	50	4	16	because even in Thessalonica ˻on more than one occasion˼ you sent for my need.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not that I seek the gift, but I seek for the profit that increases to your account.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	But I have received everything in full and have an abundance; ˻I am well supplied˼because I received from Epaphroditus ˻what you had sent˼, a fragrant offering, an acceptable sacrifice, well-pleasing to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	And my God will fulfill your every need according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	Now to our God and Father be the glory ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every saint in Christ Jesus. The brothers with me greet you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints greet you, and especially those of Caesar’s household.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	to the saints and faithful brothers in Christ in Colossae. Grace to you and peace from God our Father.
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks always to God the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ when we pray for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	since we heard about your faith in Christ Jesus and the love that you have for all the saints,
B051C001V005	51	1	5	because of the hope reserved for you in heaven, which you have heard about beforehand in the word of truth, the gospel,
B051C001V006	51	1	6	that has come to you, just as also in all the world it is bearing fruit and increasing, just as also among you from the day you heard about and understood the grace of God in truth,
B051C001V007	51	1	7	just as you learned it from Epaphras, our dear fellow slave who is a faithful minister of Christ on your behalf,
B051C001V008	51	1	8	who also made clear to us your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	Because of this also we, from the day we heard about it, did not cease praying for you, and asking that you may be filled with the knowledge of his will in all wisdom and spiritual insight,
B051C001V010	51	1	10	so that you may live in a manner worthy of the Lord, ˻to please him in all respects˼, bearing fruit in every good deed and increasing in the knowledge of God,
B051C001V011	51	1	11	enabled with all power, according to his glorious might, for all steadfastness and patience with joy,
B051C001V012	51	1	12	giving thanks to the Father who has qualified you for a share of the inheritance of the saints in light,
B051C001V013	51	1	13	who has rescued us from the domain of darkness and transferred us to the kingdom of the Son ˻he loves˼,
B051C001V014	51	1	14	in whom we have the redemption, the forgiveness of sins,
B051C001V015	51	1	15	who is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn over all creation,
B051C001V016	51	1	16	because all things in the heavens and on the earth were created by him, things visible and things invisible, whether thrones or dominions or rulers or powers, all things were created through him and for him,
B051C001V017	51	1	17	and he himself is before all things, and in him all things are held together,
B051C001V018	51	1	18	and he himself is the head of the body, the church, who is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, so that he himself may become first in everything,
B051C001V019	51	1	19	because he was well pleased for all the fullness to dwell in him,
B051C001V020	51	1	20	and through him to reconcile all things to himself, by making peace through the blood of his cross, through him, whether things on earth or things in heaven.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	And ˻although you were formerly alienated˼ and enemies in attitude, because of your evil deeds,
B051C001V022	51	1	22	but now he has reconciled you by ˻his physical body˼ through death, to present you holy and blameless and above reproach before him,
B051C001V023	51	1	23	if indeed you remain in the faith, established and steadfast and not shifted away from the hope of the gospel that you heard, which was proclaimed in all creation under heaven, of which I, Paul, became a minister.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	Now I rejoice in my sufferings on behalf of you, and I fill up in my flesh what is lacking of the afflictions of Christ, on behalf of his body which is the church,
B051C001V025	51	1	25	of which I became a minister, according to God’s stewardship which was given to me for you, to complete the word of God,
B051C001V026	51	1	26	the mystery which has been hidden from the ages and from the generations, but has now been revealed to his saints,
B051C001V027	51	1	27	to whom God wanted to make known what is the glorious wealth of this mystery among the Gentiles, which is Christ in you, the hope of glory,
B051C001V028	51	1	28	whom we proclaim, by admonishing every person and teaching every person with all wisdom, in order that we may present every person mature in Christ,
B051C001V029	51	1	29	for which purpose also I labor, striving according to his working which is at work powerfully in me.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	For I want you to know how great a struggle I have on behalf of you, and those in Laodicea, and all those who have not seen my face ˻in person˼,
B051C002V002	51	2	2	so that their hearts may be encouraged, united in love and into all the wealth of the full assurance of insight into the knowledge of the mystery of God, Christ,
B051C002V003	51	2	3	in whom all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge are hidden.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	I say this in order that no one will deceive you with persuasive speech,
B051C002V005	51	2	5	for even if I am absent in the flesh, yet I am with you in spirit, rejoicing and seeing your good order and the steadfastness of your faith in Christ.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	Therefore as you have received Christ Jesus the Lord, live in him,
B051C002V007	51	2	7	firmly rooted and built up in him and established in the faith, just as you were taught, abounding with thankfulness.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Beware lest ˻anyone take you captive˼ through philosophy and empty deceit, according to ˻human tradition˼, according to the elemental spirits of the world and not according to Christ,
B051C002V009	51	2	9	because in him all the fullness of deity dwells bodily,
B051C002V010	51	2	10	and you are filled in him, who is the head over every ruler and authority,
B051C002V011	51	2	11	in whom also you were circumcised with a circumcision not made by hands, by the removal of the body of the flesh, by the circumcision of Christ,
B051C002V012	51	2	12	having been buried with him in baptism, in which also you were raised together with him through faith in the working of God, who raised him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	And ˻although you were dead˼ in the trespasses and the uncircumcision of your flesh, he made you alive together with him, having forgiven us all our trespasses,
B051C002V014	51	2	14	having destroyed the certificate of indebtedness in ordinances against us, which was hostile to us, and removed it out of the way by nailing it to the cross.
B051C002V015	51	2	15	When he had disarmed the rulers and the authorities, he made a display of them in public, triumphing over them by it.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Therefore do not let anyone judge you with reference to eating and drinking or participation in a feast or a new moon or a sabbath,
B051C002V017	51	2	17	which are a shadow of what is to come, but the reality is Christ.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no one condemn you, taking pleasure in humility and the worship of angels, going into detail aboutthe things which he has seen, inflated without cause by his fleshly mind,
B051C002V019	51	2	19	and not holding fast to the head, from whom the whole body, supported and held together by the ligaments and sinews, grows with the growth of God.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	If you have died with Christ to the elemental spirits of the world, why do you submit to them as if living in the world?
B051C002V021	51	2	21	“Do not handle, do not taste, do not touch,”
B051C002V022	51	2	22	which things are all meant for destruction by consuming according to human commandments and teachings,
B051C002V023	51	2	23	which things˻although they have˼, to be sure, an appearance of wisdom in self-made religion and humility and unsparing treatment of the body, ˻do not have any value˼ against the indulgence of the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	Therefore, if you have been raised together with Christ, seek the things above, where Christ is, seated at the right hand of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Set your mind on the things above, not on the things on earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you have died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	When Christ, who is your life, is revealed, then you also will be revealed with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Therefore put to death ˻what is earthly in you˼: sexual immorality, uncleanness, lustful passion, evil desire, and greediness, which is idolatry,
B051C003V006	51	3	6	because of which the wrath of God is coming upon the sons of disobedience,
B051C003V007	51	3	7	in which also you once lived, when you used to live in them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now you also lay aside all these things: anger, rage, wickedness, slander, abusive language from your mouth.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another, because you have taken off the old man together with his deeds,
B051C003V010	51	3	10	and have put on the new man that is being renewed in knowledge according to the image of the one who created him,
B051C003V011	51	3	11	where there is neither Greek nor Jew, circumcision nor uncircumcision, barbarian, Scythian, slave, or free, but Christ is all, and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Therefore, as the chosen of God, holy and dearly loved, put on affection, compassion, kindness, humility, gentleness, patience,
B051C003V013	51	3	13	putting up with one another and forgiving one another. If anyone should have a complaint against anyone, just as also the Lord forgave you, thus also you do the same.
B051C003V014	51	3	14	And to all these thingsadd love, which is the bond of perfection.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	And the peace of Christ must rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body, and be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly, teaching and admonishing one another with all wisdom, with psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, singing with thankfulness in your hearts to God,
B051C003V017	51	3	17	and everything ˻whatever˼ you do in word or in deed, giving thanks for all things in the name of the Lord Jesus to God the Father through him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, be subject to your husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives and do not be embittered against them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in everything, for this is pleasing in the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, do not provoke your children, so that they will not become discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Slaves, obey your ˻human˼ masters in everything, not ˻while being watched˼, as people pleasers, but with sincerity of heart, fearing the Lord.
B051C003V023	51	3	23	Whatever you do, accomplish it from the soul, as to the Lord, and not to people,
B051C003V024	51	3	24	because you know that from the Lord you will receive the reward of the inheritance. Serve the Lord Christ.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	For the one who does wrong will receive back whatever wrong he has done, and there is no partiality.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, grant your slaves justice and fairness, knowing that you also have a master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Be devoted to prayer, keeping alert in it with thanksgiving,
B051C004V003	51	4	3	praying at the same time for us also, that God may open for us a door of the message, to speak the mystery of Christ, for which also ˻I am a prisoner˼,
B051C004V004	51	4	4	so that I may reveal it, as it is necessary for me to speak.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Live with wisdom toward those outside, making the most of the time.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let your speech always be with grace, seasoned with salt, so that you may know how it is necessary for you to answer each one.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	Tychicus, my dear brother and faithful servant and fellow slave in the Lord, will make known to you all ˻my circumstances˼,
B051C004V008	51	4	8	whom I have sent to you for this very reason, in order that you may know ˻our circumstances˼ and he may encourage your hearts,
B051C004V009	51	4	9	together with Onesimus, my faithful and dear brother, who is one of you. They will make known to you all ˻the circumstances˼ here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets you, and Mark, the cousin of Barnabas (about whom you received instructions—if he should come to you, welcome him),
B051C004V011	51	4	11	and Jesus who is called Justus. These are the only ones who are fellow workers for the kingdom of God from the circumcision, who have been a comfort to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras, who is one of you, greets you, a slave of Christ Jesus always struggling on behalf of you in his prayers, that you may stand mature and fully assured in all the will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I testify to him that ˻he is working hard˼ on behalf of you and those in Laodicea and those in Hierapolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke the physician, our dear friend, greets you, as does Demas.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Greet the brothers in Laodicea, and Nympha and the church in her house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	And whenever this letter is read among you, ˻see to it˼ that it is read also among the Laodicean church, and that you also read the letter from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	And tell Archippus, “Direct your attention to the ministry that you received in the Lord, in order that you may complete it.”
B051C004V018	51	4	18	The greeting is by my hand, Paul’s. Remember my ˻imprisonment˼. Grace be with you.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	Paul and Silvanus and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. Grace to you and peace.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We give thanks to God always concerning all of you, making mention constantly in our prayers,
B052C001V003	52	1	3	because we remember your work of faith and labor of love and steadfastness of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ in the presence of our God and Father,
B052C001V004	52	1	4	knowing, brothers dearly loved by God, ˻that he has chosen you˼,
B052C001V005	52	1	5	because our gospel did not come to you with word only, but also with power and with the Holy Spirit and with much certainty, just as you know what sort of people we became among you for your sake.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	And you became imitators of us and of the Lord, receiving the word in much affliction, with the joy of the Holy Spirit,
B052C001V007	52	1	7	so that you became an example to all those who believe in Macedonia and in Achaia,
B052C001V008	52	1	8	for from you the word of the Lord has sounded forth, not only in Macedonia and in Achaia, but in every place your faith toward God has gone out, so that we have no need to say anything.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For they themselves report about us, what sort of welcome we had with you, and how you turned to God from idols to serve the living and true God,
B052C001V010	52	1	10	and to await his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead, Jesus, the one who delivers us from the coming wrath.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	For you yourselves know, brothers, our reception with you, that it was not in vain,
B052C002V002	52	2	2	but after we had already suffered and been mistreated in Philippi, just as you know, we had the courage in our God to speak to you the gospel of God amid much opposition.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our exhortation is not from error or from impurity or with deceit,
B052C002V004	52	2	4	but just as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the gospel, thus we speak, not as pleasing people but God, who examines our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	˻For never˼ did we come with a word of flattery, just as you know, nor with a pretext of greediness (God is witness),
B052C002V006	52	2	6	nor seeking glory from people, neither from you nor from others.
B052C002V007	52	2	7	˻Although we could have insisted on our own importance˼ as apostles of Christ, yet we became infants in your midst, like a nursing mother cherishes her own children.
B052C002V008	52	2	8	Longing for you in this way, we determined to share with you not only the gospel of God but also our own souls, because you had become dear to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	For you remember, brothers, our labor and hardship: working by night and day in order not to be a burden to any of you, we proclaimed to you the gospel of God.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You are witnesses, and so is God, how devoutly and righteously and blamelessly we became to you who believe,
B052C002V011	52	2	11	just as you know how we treated each one of you, like a father his own children,
B052C002V012	52	2	12	exhorting and consoling you and insisting that you live in a manner worthy of God, who calls you to his own kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	And because of this we also give thanks to God constantly, that when you received God’s word ˻that you heard˼ from us, you accepted it not as the word of men, but as it truly is, the word of God, which also is at work in you who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you became imitators, brothers, of the churches of God which are in Judea in Christ Jesus, because you also suffered the same things at the hands of your own people, just as they themselves did also at the hands of the Jews,
B052C002V015	52	2	15	who killed both the Lord Jesus and the prophets, and who persecuted us, and who are not pleasing to God and are opposed to all people,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	hindering us from speaking to the Gentiles in order that they may be saved, so that they always fill up their sins. But wrath has come upon them to the end.
B052C002V017	52	2	17	But when we were made orphans by separation from you, brothers, for ˻a short time˼ (in face, not in heart), we were even more eager with great desire to see your face,
B052C002V018	52	2	18	because we wanted to come to you—I, Paul, ˻on more than one occasion˼—and Satan hindered us.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For who is our hope or joy or crown of boasting? Is it not even you, in the presence of our Lord Jesus at his coming?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	For you are our glory and joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore when we could bear it no longer, we determined to be left behind in Athens alone,
B052C003V002	52	3	2	and we sent Timothy, our brother and fellow worker for God in the gospel of Christ, in order to strengthen and to encourage you about your faith,
B052C003V003	52	3	3	so that no one would be shaken by these afflictions. For you yourselves know that we are appointed for this,
B052C003V004	52	3	4	for indeed when we were with you we told you beforehand that we were about to be afflicted, just as indeed it happened, and you know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	Because of this, I also, when I could endure it no longer, sent in order to know your faith, lest somehow the tempter tempted you and our labor should be in vain.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But now, because Timothy has come to us from you and has brought good news to us of your faith and love, and that ˻you always think kindly of us˼, desiring to see us just as also we desire to see you,
B052C003V007	52	3	7	because of this, brothers, we have been comforted because of you in all our distress and affliction through your faith,
B052C003V008	52	3	8	because now we live, if you stand firm in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For what thanks can we repay to God concerning you, because of all the joy with which we rejoice because of you before our God,
B052C003V010	52	3	10	night and day praying beyond all measure that we may see your face and complete what is lacking in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now may our God and Father himself and our Lord Jesus direct our way to you,
B052C003V012	52	3	12	and may the Lord cause you to increase and to abound in love for one another and for all, just as also we do for you,
B052C003V013	52	3	13	so that your hearts may be established blameless in holiness before our God and Father at the coming of our Lord Jesus with all his saints. Amen.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	Finally therefore, brothers, we ask you and appeal to you in the Lord Jesus that, just as you have received from us how it is necessary for you to live and to please God, just as indeed you are living, that you progress even more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know what commands we gave to you through the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is the will of God, your sanctification: that you abstain from sexual immorality;
B052C004V004	52	4	4	that each of you know how to possess his own vessel in sanctification and honor,
B052C004V005	52	4	5	not in lustful passion, just as also the Gentiles who do not know God;
B052C004V006	52	4	6	not to transgress and to exploit his brother in the matter, because the Lord is the one who avenges concerning all these things, just as also we told you beforehand and testified solemnly.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For God did not call us to impurity, but in holiness.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore the one who rejects thisis not rejecting man, but God, who also gives his Holy Spirit to you.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	But concerning brotherly love, I do not have need to write to you, for you yourselves are taught by God to love one another,
B052C004V010	52	4	10	for indeed you are practicing it toward all the brothers in all of Macedonia. But we urge you, brothers, to progress even more,
B052C004V011	52	4	11	and to aspire to live a quiet life, and to attend to ˻your own business˼, and to work with your own hands, just as we commanded you,
B052C004V012	52	4	12	so that you may live decently toward those outside, and may have need of nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	Now we do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning those who have fallen asleep, so that you will not grieve as also the rest, who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again, thus also God will bring those who have fallen asleep through Jesus together with him.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	For this we say to you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive, who remain until the Lord’s coming, will not possibly precede those who have fallen asleep.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	For the Lord himself will descend from heaven with a shout of command, with the voice of the archangel and with the trumpet of God, and the dead in Christ will rise first.
B052C004V017	52	4	17	Then we who are alive, who remain, will be snatched away at the same time together with them in the clouds for a meeting with the Lord in the air, and thus we will be together with the Lord always.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	Therefore comfort one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	Now concerning the times and the seasons, brothers, you have no need of anything to be written to you,
B052C005V002	52	5	2	for you yourselves well know that the day of the Lord is coming in the same way as a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	Whenever they say “Peace and security,” then sudden destruction will overtake them like the birth pains of ˻a pregnant woman˼, and they will not possibly escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, brothers, are not in the darkness, so that the day should catch you like a thief,
B052C005V005	52	5	5	for you are all sons of light and sons of day. We are not of the night nor of darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	So then, we must not sleep like the rest, but must be on the alert and be self-controlled.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For those who sleep, sleep at night, and those who get drunk, are drunk at night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But because we are of the day, we must be sober, by putting on the breastplate of faith and love and as a helmet the hope of salvation,
B052C005V009	52	5	9	because God did not appoint us for wrath, but for the obtaining of salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	who died for us, so that whether we are awake or asleep, we will live at the same time with him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Therefore encourage one another and build up ˻each other˼, just as indeed you are doing.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	Now we ask you, brothers, to respect those who labor among you and rule over you in the Lord and admonish you,
B052C005V013	52	5	13	and to esteem them beyond all measure in love, because of their work. Be at peace among yourselves.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	And we urge you, brothers, admonish the disorderly, console the discouraged, help the sick, be patient toward all people.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	See to it that no one pays back evil for evil to anyone, but always pursue good, both toward one another and toward all people.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Rejoice always,
B052C005V017	52	5	17	pray constantly,
B052C005V018	52	5	18	give thanks in everything; for this is the will of God for you in Christ Jesus.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not quench the Spirit.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophecies,
B052C005V021	52	5	21	but examine all things; hold fast to what is good.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	Abstain from every form of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	Now may the God of peace himself sanctify you completely, and may your spirit and soul and body be kept complete, blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	The one who calls you is faithful, who also will do this.
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brothers, pray for us also.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I adjure you by the Lord, have this letter read aloud to all the brothers.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	Paul and Silvanus and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	We ought to give thanks to God always concerning you, brothers, just as it is fitting, because your faith is flourishing and the love of each one of you all toward one another is increasing
B053C001V004	53	1	4	so that we ourselves boast in you in the churches of God about your patient endurance and faith in all your persecutions and the afflictions that you are enduring,
B053C001V005	53	1	5	a proof of the righteous judgment of God, so that you may be considered worthy of the kingdom of God, on behalf of which also you are suffering,
B053C001V006	53	1	6	since it is righteous in the sight of God to pay back those who are afflicting you with affliction,
B053C001V007	53	1	7	and to you who are being afflicted, rest with us at the revelation of the Lord Jesus from heaven with his powerful angels,
B053C001V008	53	1	8	with flaming fire giving punishment to those who do not know God and who do not obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus,
B053C001V009	53	1	9	who will pay the penalty of eternal destruction, away from the presence of the Lord and from the glory of his strength,
B053C001V010	53	1	10	whenever he should come to be glorified on that day by his saints and to be marveled at by all who believe, because our testimony was believed among you,
B053C001V011	53	1	11	for which purpose we also pray always for you, that you may be considered worthy of the calling of our God, and he might fulfill every desire for goodness and work of faith with power,
B053C001V012	53	1	12	in order that the name of our Lord Jesus may be glorified in you, and you in him, according to the grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	Now we ask you, brothers, concerning the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ and our assembling to him,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	that you not be easily shaken from your composure, nor be troubled either by a spirit or by a message or by a letter ˻alleged to be from us˼, to the effect that the day of the Lord has arrived.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Do not let anyone deceive you in any way, for that day will not come unless the rebellion comes first, and the man of lawlessness is revealed, the son of destruction,
B053C002V004	53	2	4	who opposes and who exalts himself over every so-called god or object of worship, so that he sits down in the temple of God, proclaiming that he himself is God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember that while we were still with you, we were saying these things to you?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	And you know that which restrains him now, so that he will be revealed in his own time.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of lawlessness is at work already; only the one who now restrains will do so until he is out of the way,
B053C002V008	53	2	8	and then the lawless one will be revealed, whom the Lord Jesus will slay with the breath of his mouth, and wipe out by the appearance of his coming,
B053C002V009	53	2	9	whose coming is in accordance with the working of Satan, with all power and signs and lying wonders,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	and with every unrighteous deception against those who are perishing, in place of which they did not accept the love of the truth, so that they would be saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	And because of this, God sends them ˻a powerful delusion˼ so that they will believe the lie,
B053C002V012	53	2	12	in order that all may be condemned who did not believe the truth, but delighted in unrighteousness.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	But we ought to give thanks to God always concerning you, brothers dearly loved by the Lord, because God has chosen you as first fruits for salvation by the sanctification of the Spirit and faith in the truth,
B053C002V014	53	2	14	for which purpose also he called you through our gospel for the obtaining of the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	So then, brothers, stand firm and hold fast to the traditions which you were taught, whether by spoken word or by letter from us.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	Now may our Lord Jesus Christ himself and God our Father, who has loved us and given us eternal encouragement and good hope by grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	encourage your hearts and strengthen you in every good work and word.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Finally, brothers, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may progress and be honored, just as also it was with you,
B053C003V002	53	3	2	and that we may be delivered from evil and wicked people, ˻for not all have the faith˼.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful, who will strengthen you and guard you from the evil one.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	And we have confidence in the Lord about you, that you are both doing and you will do the things that we are commanding.
B053C003V005	53	3	5	Now may the Lord direct your hearts toward the love of God and toward the patient endurance of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	But we command you, brothers, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you keep away from every brother who lives irresponsibly and not according to the tradition that they received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you yourselves know how it is necessary to imitate us, that we did not behave irresponsibly among you,
B053C003V008	53	3	8	nor did we eat bread from anyone without paying, but with toil and labor, we were working night and day in order not to be a burden to any of you,
B053C003V009	53	3	9	not that we do not have the right, but so that we may give ourselves as an example to you, so that you may imitate us.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For even when we were with you, we used to command this to you: that if anyone does not want to work, neither should he eat.
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear that some among you are living irresponsibly, working at nothing, but being busybodies.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	Now we command and we exhort such people in the Lord Jesus Christ that, working with quietness, they eat their own bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But as for you, brothers, do not be discouraged while doing what is right.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	But if anyone does not obey our message through this letter, take note not to associate with him, in order that he may be put to shame.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	And do not consider him as an enemy, but admonish him as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	Now may the Lord of peace himself grant you peace through everything in every way. May the Lord be with all of you.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	The greeting is by my hand, Paul’s, which is ˻a sign of genuineness˼ in every letter: ˻this is how I write˼.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus according to the command of God our Savior and of Christ Jesus our hope,
B054C001V002	54	1	2	to Timothy, my true child in the faith. Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	Just as I urged you when I traveled to Macedonia, remain in Ephesus, so that you may instruct certain people not to teach other doctrine,
B054C001V004	54	1	4	and not to pay attention to myths and endless genealogies, which cause useless speculations rather than God’s plan that is by faith.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	But the goal of our instruction is love from a pure heart and a good conscience and a faith without hypocrisy,
B054C001V006	54	1	6	from which some have deviated, and have turned away into fruitless discussion,
B054C001V007	54	1	7	wanting to be teachers of the law, although they do not understand either the things which they are saying or the things concerning which they are speaking confidently.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	But we know that the law is good, if anyone makes use of it lawfully,
B054C001V009	54	1	9	knowing this, that the law is not given for a righteous person but for the lawless and rebellious, for the ungodly and sinners, for the unholy and totally worldly, for the one who kills his father and the one who kills his mother, for murderers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	sexually immoral people, homosexuals, kidnappers, liars, perjurers, and ˻whatever˼ else is opposed to sound teaching,
B054C001V011	54	1	11	according to the glorious gospel of the blessed God that I was entrusted with.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	˻I give thanks˼ to the one who strengthens me, Christ Jesus our Lord, because he considered me faithful, placing me into ministry,
B054C001V013	54	1	13	although I was formerly a blasphemer and a persecutor and a violent man, but I was shown mercy because I acted ignorantly in unbelief,
B054C001V014	54	1	14	and the grace of our Lord abounded with the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	The saying is trustworthy and worthy of all acceptance: Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am the foremost.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	But because of this I was shown mercy, in order that in me foremost, Christ Jesus might demonstrate his total patience, for an example for those who are going to believe in him for eternal life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	Now to the King of the ages, immortal, invisible, to the only God, be honor and glory ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	I am setting before you this instruction, Timothy my child, in accordance with the prophecies spoken long ago about you, in order that by them you may fight the good fight,
B054C001V019	54	1	19	having faith and a good conscience, which some, because they have rejected these, have suffered shipwreck concerning their faith,
B054C001V020	54	1	20	among whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I have handed over to Satan, in order that they may be taught not to blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	Therefore, I urge first of all that petitions, prayers, requests, and thanksgiving be made on behalf of all people,
B054C002V002	54	2	2	on behalf of kings and all those who are in authority, in order that we may live a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and dignity.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	This is good and acceptable before God our Savior,
B054C002V004	54	2	4	who wants all people to be saved and to come to a knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For there is one God and one mediator between God and human beings, the man Christ Jesus,
B054C002V006	54	2	6	who gave himself a ransom for all, the testimony at the proper time,
B054C002V007	54	2	7	for which I was appointed a herald and an apostle—I am speaking the truth, I am not lying—a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	Therefore I want the men in every place to pray, lifting up holy hands without anger and dispute.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	Likewise also the women should adorn themselves in appropriate clothing, with modesty and self-control, not with braided hair and gold jewelry or pearls or expensive clothing,
B054C002V010	54	2	10	but with good deeds which are fitting for women who profess godliness.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	A woman must learn in quietness with all submission.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	But I do not permit a woman to teach or to exercise authority over a man, but ˻to remain quiet˼.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam was formed first, then Eve,
B054C002V014	54	2	14	and Adam was not deceived, but the woman, because she was deceived, came into transgression.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	But she will be saved through the bearing of children, if she continues in faith and love and holiness with self-control.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	The saying is trustworthy: if anyone aspires to supervision, he desires a good work.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	Therefore the overseer must be irreproachable, the husband of one wife, temperate, self-controlled, respectable, hospitable, skillful in teaching,
B054C003V003	54	3	3	not addicted to wine, not a violent person, but gentle, peaceable, not loving money,
B054C003V004	54	3	4	managing his own household well, having children in submission with all dignity
B054C003V005	54	3	5	(but if someone does not know how to manage his own household, how will he take care of the church of God?),
B054C003V006	54	3	6	not newly converted, lest he become conceited and fall into the condemnation of the devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	But he must also have a good testimony from those outside, in order that he may not fall into disgrace and the trap of the devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Deacons likewise must be dignified, not insincere, not devoted to much wine, not fond of dishonest gain,
B054C003V009	54	3	9	holding the mystery of the faith with a clear conscience,
B054C003V010	54	3	10	and these also must be tested first; then let them serve if they are above reproach.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	The wives likewise must be dignified, not slanderous, temperate, faithful in all things.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	Deacons must be husbands of one wife, managing their children and their own households well.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	For those who have served well acquire a good standing for themselves, and great boldness in the faith that is in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	I am writing these things to you, hoping to come to you in a short time.
B054C003V015	54	3	15	But if I am delayed, I am writing in order that you may know how one must conduct oneself in the household of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and mainstay of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	And most certainly, great is the mystery of godliness:Who was revealed in the flesh,was vindicated by the Spirit,was seen by angels,was proclaimed among the Gentiles,was believed on in the world,was taken up in glory.
B054C004V001	54	4	1	Now the Spirit explicitly says that in the last times some will depart from the faith, paying attention to deceitful spirits and teachings of demons,
B054C004V002	54	4	2	by the hypocrisy of liars, who are seared in their own conscience,
B054C004V003	54	4	3	who forbid marrying and insist on abstaining from foods that God created for sharing in with thankfulness by those who believe and who know the truth,
B054C004V004	54	4	4	because everything created by God is good and nothing is to be rejected if it is received with thankfulness,
B054C004V005	54	4	5	for it is made holy by the word of God and prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	By teaching these things to the brothers, you will be a good servant of Christ Jesus, trained in the words of the faith and of the good teaching that you have followed faithfully.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But reject those ˻worthless myths told by elderly women˼, and train yourself for godliness.
B054C004V008	54	4	8	For the training of the body is ˻somewhat˼ profitable, but godliness is profitable for everything, because it holds promise for the present life and for the life to come.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	The statement is trustworthy and deserving of complete acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	For to this end we labor and strive, because we have put our hope in the living God, who is the Savior of all people, especially of believers.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	Command these things and teach them.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Let no one look down on your youth, but be an example for the believers in word, in conduct, in love, in faith, in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I come, pay attention to the public reading, to exhortation, to teaching.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, that was granted to you through prophecy with the laying on of hands by the council of elders.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Practice these things. Be diligent in these things, in order that your progress may be evident to everyone.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Fix your attention on yourself and on your teaching. Continue in them, for by doing this you will save both yourself and those who hear you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Do not rebuke an older man, but appeal to him as a father, younger men as brothers,
B054C005V002	54	5	2	older women as mothers, younger women as sisters, with all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honor widows who are truly widows.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	But if any widow has children or grandchildren, they must learn to show profound respect for their own household first, and to pay back recompense to their parents, for this is pleasing in the sight of God.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	But the widow who is one truly, and is left alone, has put her hope in God and continues in her petitions and prayers night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But the one who lives for sensual pleasure is dead even though she lives.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	And command these things, in order that they may be irreproachable.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	But if someone does not provide for his own relatives, and especially the members of his household, he has denied the faith and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	Let a widow be put on the list if she is not less than sixty years old, the wife of one husband,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	being well-attested by good works, if she has brought up children, if she has shown hospitality, if she has washed the feet of the saints, if she has helped those who are oppressed, if she has devoted herself to every good work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But refuse younger widows, for whenever their physical desires lead them away from Christ, they want to marry,
B054C005V012	54	5	12	thus incurring condemnation because they have broken their former pledge.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	And at the same time also, going around from house to house, they learn to be idle, and not only idle, but also gossipy and busybodies, saying the things that are not necessary.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	Therefore I want younger widows to marry, to bear children, to manage a household, to give the adversary no opportunity for reproach.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For already some have turned away and followed after Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any believing woman has widows, she must help them, and the church must not be burdened, in order that it may help those who are truly widows.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	The elders who lead well must be considered worthy of double honor, especially those who labor by speaking and teaching.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the scripture says, “You must not muzzle an ox while it is threshing,” and “The worker is worthy of his wages.”
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Do not accept an accusation against an elder except on the evidence of two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Reprove those who sin in the presence of all, in order that the rest also may experience fear.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I testify solemnly before God and Christ Jesus and the elect angels that you observe these things without prejudice, doing nothing according to partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Lay hands on no one hastily, and do not participate in the sins of others. Keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	(No longer drink only water, but use a little wine for your stomach and your frequent illnesses.)
B054C005V024	54	5	24	The sins of some people are evident, preceding them to judgment, but for some also they follow after them.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	Likewise also good works are evident, and those considered otherwise are not able to be hidden.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	All those who are under the yoke as slaves must regard their own masters as worthy of all honor, lest the name of God and the teaching be slandered.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	And those who have believing masters must not look down on them because they are brothers, but rather they must serve, because those who benefit by their service are believers and dearly loved.Teach and encourage these things.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If anyone teaches other doctrine and does not devote himself to the sound words of our Lord Jesus Christ and the teaching that is in accordance with godliness,
B054C006V004	54	6	4	he is conceited, understanding nothing, but having a morbid interest concerning controversies and disputes about words, from which come envy, strife, slanders, evil suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	constant wrangling by people of depraved mind and deprived of the truth, who consider godliness to be a means of gain.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	But godliness with contentment is a great means of gain.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we have brought nothing into the world, so that neither can we bring anything out.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	But if we have food and clothing, with these things we will be content.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But those who want to be rich fall into temptation and a trap and many foolish and harmful desires, which plunge those people into ruin and destruction.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is a root of all evil, by which some, because they desire it, have gone astray from the faith and have pierced themselves with many pains.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But you, O man of God, flee from these things, and pursue righteousness, godliness, faith, love, patient endurance, gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Fight the good fight of the faith; take hold of the eternal life to which you were called, and confessed the good confession in the presence of many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I command you, in the sight of God who gives life to all things and Christ Jesus who testified the good confession before Pontius Pilate,
B054C006V014	54	6	14	that you observe the commandment without fault, irreproachable until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B054C006V015	54	6	15	which he will make known in his own time, the blessed and only Sovereign, the King of those who reign as kings and Lord of those who rule as lords,
B054C006V016	54	6	16	the one who alone possesses immortality, who lives in unapproachable light, whom no human being has seen nor is able to see, to whom be honor and eternal power. Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Command those who are rich in this present age not to be proud and not to put their hope in the uncertainty of riches, but in God, who provides us all things richly for enjoyment,
B054C006V018	54	6	18	to do good, to be rich in good works, to be generous, sharing freely,
B054C006V019	54	6	19	storing up for themselves a good foundation for the future, in order that they may take hold of what is truly life.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	O Timothy, guard what has been entrusted to you. Turn away from pointless empty talk and contradictions of what is falsely called knowledge,
B054C006V021	54	6	21	which some, by professing it, have deviated concerning the faith. Grace be with you all.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus through the will of God, according to the promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	to Timothy, my dear child. Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	˻I am thankful˼ to God, whom I have served with a clear conscience ˻as my ancestors did˼, when ˻I remember you constantly˼ in my prayers night and day,
B055C001V004	55	1	4	longing to see you as I remember your tears, so that I may be filled with joy,
B055C001V005	55	1	5	˻remembering the˼ sincere faith in you, which lived first in your grandmother Lois and your mother Eunice, and I am convinced that is in you also,
B055C001V006	55	1	6	for which reason I remind you to rekindle the gift of God that is in you through the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God has not given us a spirit of cowardice, but of power and love and self-discipline.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Therefore, do not be ashamed of the testimony about our Lord, nor me his prisoner, but suffer along with me for the gospel, according to the power of God,
B055C001V009	55	1	9	who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our works but according to his own purpose and grace that was given to us in Christ Jesus ˻before time began˼,
B055C001V010	55	1	10	but has now been disclosed by the appearing of our Savior Christ Jesus, who has abolished death and brought to light life and immortality through the gospel,
B055C001V011	55	1	11	for which I was appointed a proclaimer and an apostle and a teacher,
B055C001V012	55	1	12	for which reason also I suffer these things. But I am not ashamed, because I know in whom I have believed, and I am convinced that he is able to guard what I have entrusted until that day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold fast to the pattern of sound words which you heard from me, in the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	Guard the good deposit through the Holy Spirit who lives in us.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	You know this, that all those in Asia turned away from me, among whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	May the Lord grant mercy to the household of Onesiphorus, because he refreshed me many times, and was not ashamed of my imprisonment,
B055C001V017	55	1	17	but when he was in Rome, he diligently sought me and found me.
B055C001V018	55	1	18	May the Lord grant him to find mercy from the Lord in that day! And how much he served me in Ephesus you know very well.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	You, therefore, my child, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus,
B055C002V002	55	2	2	and the things which you have heard from me in the presence of many witnesses, entrust these things to faithful people who will be competent to teach others also.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	Suffer together with me as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No one who serves as a soldier is entangled in the activities of everyday life, so that he may please the one who enlisted him.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	And also if anyone competes he is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	The farmer who works hard must be the first to receive a share of the crops.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Consider what I am saying, for the Lord will grant you understanding in all these things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, a descendant of David according to my gospel,
B055C002V009	55	2	9	in connection with which I suffer misfortune to the point of ˻imprisonment˼ as a criminal, but the word of God is not bound.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	Because of this, I endure all things for the sake of the chosen, in order that they also may obtain salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	The saying is trustworthy:For if we died with him, we will also live with him;
B055C002V012	55	2	12	if we endure, we will also reign with him;if we deny him, he also will deny us;
B055C002V013	55	2	13	if we are unfaithful, he remains faithful, ˻because he cannot deny himself˼.
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind people of these things, solemnly urging them before God not to dispute about words. This is in no way beneficial and leads to the ruin of the hearers.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Make every effort to present yourself approved to God, a worker having no need to be ashamed, guiding the word of truth along a straight path.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	But avoid pointless chatter, for it will progress to greater ungodliness,
B055C002V017	55	2	17	and their message ˻will spread˼ like gangrene, among whom are Hymenaeus and Philetus,
B055C002V018	55	2	18	who have deviated concerning the truth by saying the resurrection has already taken place, and they are upsetting the faith of some.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	However, the solid foundation of God stands firm, having this seal: “The Lord knows those who are his,” and “Everyone who names the name of the Lord must abstain from unrighteousness.”
B055C002V020	55	2	20	Now in a great house there are not only gold and silver vessels, but also wooden and earthenware ones, some of which are for honorable use, and some of which are for ordinary use.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	Therefore, if someone cleanses himself from these things, he will be a vessel for honorable use, set apart, useful to the Master, prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	But flee from youthful desires, and pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace, in company with those who call upon the Lord from a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	But avoid foolish and uninformed controversies, because you know that they produce quarrels.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	And the slave of the Lord must not quarrel, but be kind toward everyone, skillful in teaching, tolerant,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	correcting those who are opposed with gentleness, seeing whether perhaps God may grant them repentence to a knowledge of the truth,
B055C002V026	55	2	26	and they will come to their senses again and escape from the trap of the devil, being held captive by him to do his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	But know this, that in the last days difficult times will come,
B055C003V002	55	3	2	for people will be lovers of themselves, lovers of money, boasters, arrogant, slanderers, disobedient to parents, ungrateful, unholy,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	hardhearted, irreconcilable, slanderous, without self-control, savage, with no interest for what is good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	traitors, reckless, conceited, loving pleasure rather than loving God,
B055C003V005	55	3	5	maintaining a form of godliness, but denying its power. Avoid these people.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For from these are those who slip into houses and captivate foolish women loaded down with sins, led by various kinds of desires,
B055C003V007	55	3	7	always learning and never able to come to a knowledge of the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	And ˻just as˼ Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so also these oppose the truth, people corrupted in mind, disqualified concerning the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they will not progress to a greater extent, for their folly will be quite evident to everyone, as also the folly of those two was.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	But you have faithfully followed my teaching, way of life, purpose, faith, patience, love, endurance,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	persecutions, and sufferings that happened to me in Antioch, in Iconium, and in Lystra, what sort of persecutions I endured, and the Lord delivered me from all of them.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	And indeed, all those who want to live in a godly manner in Christ Jesus will be persecuted.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But evil people and imposters will progress to the worse, deceiving and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But you continue in the things which you have learned and are convinced of, because you know from whom you learned them,
B055C003V015	55	3	15	and that from childhood you have known the holy writings that are able to make you wise for salvation through faith in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	All scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for training in righteousness,
B055C003V017	55	3	17	in order that the person of God may be competent, equipped for every good work.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I solemnly charge you before God and Christ Jesus, who is going to judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his kingdom,
B055C004V002	55	4	2	preach the word, be ready in season and out of season, reprove, rebuke, exhort, with all patience and instruction.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For there will be a time when they will not put up with sound teaching, but in accordance with their own desires, they will accumulate for themselves teachers, ˻because they have an insatiable curiosity˼,
B055C004V004	55	4	4	and they will turn away from the hearing of the truth, but will turn to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But you, be self-controlled in all things, bear hardship patiently, do the work of an evangelist, fulfill your ministry.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being poured out as a drink offering, and the time of my departure is imminent.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have fought the good fight, I have completed the race, I have kept the faith.
B055C004V008	55	4	8	Finally, the crown of righteousness is reserved for me, that the Lord, the righteous Judge, will award to me on that day, and not only to me, but also to all who have loved his appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Make haste to come to me quickly.
B055C004V010	55	4	10	For Demas deserted me, because he loved the present age, and went to Thessalonica. Crescens went to Galatia; Titus went to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Luke alone is with me. Take along Mark and bring him with you, because he is useful to me for ministry.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	But I have sent Tychicus to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	When you come, bring the cloak that I left behind in Troas with Carpus, and the scrolls, especially the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the metalworker did me much harm; may the Lord pay back to him according to his deeds,
B055C004V015	55	4	15	against whom you also be on guard, because he vehemently opposed our words.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first defense, no one came to my aid, but they all deserted me; may it not be counted against them.
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But the Lord helped me and strengthened me, so that through me the proclamation might be fulfilled and all the Gentiles might hear, and he rescued me from the lion’s mouth.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	The Lord will rescue me from every evil deed, and will save me for his heavenly kingdom, to whom be the glory ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Greet Prisca and Aquila and the household of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus remained in Corinth, but Trophimus I left behind in Miletus because he was sick.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Make haste to come before winter. Eubulus and Pudens and Linus and Claudia and all the brothers greet you.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	Paul, a slave of God and an apostle of Jesus Christ for the faith of the chosen of God and the knowledge of the truth that is according to godliness,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	in the hope of eternal life which God, who does not lie, promised before eternal ages,
B056C001V003	56	1	3	but at the proper time has disclosed his message in the proclamation with which I was entrusted according to the command of God our Savior,
B056C001V004	56	1	4	to Titus, my true child according to a common faith. Grace and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Savior.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	On account of this, I left you behind in Crete, in order that what remains may be set in order and you may appoint elders in every town, as I ordered you.
B056C001V006	56	1	6	If anyone is blameless, the husband of one wife, having faithful children, not ˻accused of dissipation˼ or rebellious.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For it is necessary for the overseer to be blameless as God’s steward, not self-willed, not quick-tempered, not addicted to wine, not violent, not greedy for dishonest gain,
B056C001V008	56	1	8	but hospitable, loving what is good, prudent, just, devout, self-controlled,
B056C001V009	56	1	9	holding fast to the faithful message according to the teaching, in order that he may be able both to exhort with sound instruction and to reprove those who speak against it.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are many rebellious people, idle talkers and deceivers, especially those of the circumcision,
B056C001V011	56	1	11	whom it is necessary to silence, whoever are ruining whole families by teaching things which must not be taught for the sake of dishonest gain.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	A certain one of them, one of their own prophets, has said, “Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, lazy gluttons.”
B056C001V013	56	1	13	This testimony is true, for which reason reprove them severely, in order that they may be sound in the faith,
B056C001V014	56	1	14	not paying attention to Jewish myths and commandments of people who turn away from the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	To the pure all thingsare pure, but to those who are defiled and unbelieving nothing is pure, but both their mind and conscience are defiled.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They profess to know God, but by their deeds they deny him, because they are detestable and disobedient, and unfit for every good deed.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But you, speak the things which are fitting for sound instruction.
B056C002V002	56	2	2	Older men are to be temperate, worthy of respect, self-controlled, sound in faith, in love, and in endurance.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	Older women likewise are to be reverent in their behavior, not slanderous, not enslaved to much wine, teaching what is good,
B056C002V004	56	2	4	in order that they may encourage the young women to love their husbands and to love their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	to be self-controlled, pure, busy at home, good, being subject to their own husbands, in order that the word of God may not be slandered.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Likewise, exhort the young men to be self-controlled,
B056C002V007	56	2	7	concerning everything showing yourself to be an example of good deeds, in your teaching demonstrating soundness, dignity,
B056C002V008	56	2	8	a sound message beyond reproach, in order that ˻an opponent˼ may be put to shame, because he has nothing bad to say concerning us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Slaves must be subject to their own masters in everything, to be well-pleasing, not to talk back,
B056C002V010	56	2	10	not stealing, but demonstrating all good faith, in order that they may do credit to the teaching of God our Savior in everything.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the grace of God has appeared, bringing salvation to all people,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	training us in order that, denying impiety and worldly desires, we may live self-controlled and righteously and godly in the present age,
B056C002V013	56	2	13	looking forward to the blessed hope and the glorious appearing of our great God and Savior Jesus Christ,
B056C002V014	56	2	14	who gave himself for us, in order that he might redeem us from all lawlessness and purify for himself a people for his own possession, zealous for good deeds.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	Speak these things and exhort and reprove with all authority. Let no one disregard you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Remind them to be subject to the rulers and to the authorities, to obey, to be prepared for every good work,
B056C003V002	56	3	2	to speak evil of no one, to be peaceable, gentle, showing all courtesy to all people.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we also were once foolish, disobedient, led astray, enslaved to various desires and pleasures, spending our lives in wickedness and envy, despicable, hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when the kindness and love for mankind of God our Savior appeared,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	he saved us, not by deeds of righteousness that we have done, but because of his mercy, through the washing of regeneration and renewal by the Holy Spirit,
B056C003V006	56	3	6	whom he poured out on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Savior,
B056C003V007	56	3	7	so that, having been justified by his grace, we may become heirs according to the hope of eternal life.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	The saying is trustworthy, and I want you to insist concerning these things, so that those who have believed in God may be careful to engage in good deeds. These things are good and beneficial for people.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But avoid foolish controversies and genealogies and contentions and quarrels about the law, for they are useless and fruitless.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	Reject a divisive person after a first and second admonition,
B056C003V011	56	3	11	knowing that such a person is perverted and is sinning, being self-condemned.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	When I send Artemas or Tychicus to you, make haste to come to me in Nicopolis, for I have decided to spend the winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Diligently send on their way Zenas the lawyer and Apollos, so that ˻they may lack nothing˼.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	But also our people must learn to engage in good deeds for necessary needs, so that they will not be unfruitful.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All those with me greet you. Greet those who love us in the faith. Grace be with all of you.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our dear friend and fellow worker,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	and to Apphia our sister, and to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house.
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I thank my God, always making mention of you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	because I hear about your love and faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and for all the saints.
B057C001V006	57	1	6	I pray that the fellowship of your faith may become effective in the knowledge of every good thing that is in us for Christ.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For I have great joy and encouragement from your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Therefore, although I have great confidence in Christ to order you to do what is proper,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	instead I appeal to you because of love, since I am such a one as Paul, now an old man and also a prisoner of Christ Jesus.
B057C001V010	57	1	10	I am appealing to you concerning my child whom I became the father of during my imprisonment, Onesimus.
B057C001V011	57	1	11	Once he was useless to you, but now he is useful both to you and to me,
B057C001V012	57	1	12	whom I have sent back to you himself, that is, my heart,
B057C001V013	57	1	13	whom I wanted to keep with me, in order that he might serve me on behalf of you during my imprisonment for the gospel.
B057C001V014	57	1	14	But apart from your consent, I wanted to do nothing, in order that your good deed might be not as according to necessity, but according to your own free will.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	For perhaps because of this, he was separated from you for a time, in order that you might have him back forever,
B057C001V016	57	1	16	no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a beloved brother, especially to me, but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.
B057C001V017	57	1	17	If therefore you consider me a partner, receive him as you would me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	But if in anything he has caused you loss or owes you anything, ˻charge this to my account˼.
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will pay it back, lest I mention to you that ˻you owe me even your very self besides˼.
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, I ought to have some benefit of you in the Lord; refresh my heart in Christ.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Confident of your obedience, I am writing to you because I know that you will do even beyond what I say.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	At the same time also, prepare a guest room for me, for I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you,
B057C001V024	57	1	24	and so do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	Although God spoke long ago in many parts and in many ways to the fathers by the prophets,
B058C001V002	58	1	2	in these last days he has spoken to us by a Son, whom he appointed heir of all things, through whom also he made the world,
B058C001V003	58	1	3	who is the radiance of his glory and the representation of his essence, sustaining all things by the word of his power. When he had made purification for sins, he sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high,
B058C001V004	58	1	4	having become by so much better than the angels, by as much as he has inherited a more excellent name than theirs.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels did he ever say,“You are my son,today I have fathered you,”and again,“I will be ˻his father˼,and he will be ˻my son˼”?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	And again, when he brings the firstborn into the world, he says,“And let all the angels of God worship him.”
B058C001V007	58	1	7	And concerning the angels he says,“The one who makes his angels winds,and his servants a flame of fire,”
B058C001V008	58	1	8	but concerning the Son,“Your throne, O God, is˻forever and ever˼,and the scepter of righteous is the scepter of your kingdom.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	You have loved righteousness and hated lawlessness;because of this God, your God, has anointed youwith the olive oil of joy more than your companions.
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And,“You, Lord, laid the foundation of the earth in the beginning,and the heavens are the works of your hands;
B058C001V011	58	1	11	they will perish, but you continue,and they will all become old like a garment,
B058C001V012	58	1	12	and like a robe you will roll them up,and like a garment they will be changed;but you are the same, and your years will not run out.”
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But to which of the angels has he ever said,“Sit down at my right hand,until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.”
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are they not all spirits engaged in special service, sent on assignment for the sake of those who are going to inherit salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	Because of this, it is all the more necessary that we pay attention to the things we have heard, lest we drift away.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the word spoken through angels was binding and every transgression and act of disobedience received a just penalty,
B058C002V003	58	2	3	how will we escape if we neglect so great a salvation which had its beginning when it was spoken through the Lord and was confirmed to us by those who heard,
B058C002V004	58	2	4	while God was testifying at the same time by signs and wonders and various miracles and distributions of the Holy Spirit according to his will.
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For he did not subject to angels the world to come, about which we are speaking.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But someone testified somewhere, saying,“What is man, that you remember him,or the son of man, that you care for him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	You made him for a short time lower than the angels;you crowned him with glory and honor;
B058C002V008	58	2	8	you subjected all things under his feet.For in subjecting all things to him, he left nothing that was not subject to him. But now we do not yet see all things subjected to him,
B058C002V009	58	2	9	but we see Jesus, for a short time made lower than the angels, because of the suffering of death crowned with glory and honor, so that by the grace of God he might taste death on behalf of everyone.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it was fitting for him for whom are all things and through whom are all things in bringing many sons to glory to perfect the originator of their salvation through sufferings.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For both the one who sanctifies and the ones who are sanctified are all from one, for which reason he is not ashamed to call them brothers,
B058C002V012	58	2	12	saying,“I will proclaim your name to my brothers;in the midst of the assembly I will sing in praise of you.”
B058C002V013	58	2	13	And again,“I will trust in him.”And again,“Behold, I and the children God has given me.”
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Therefore, since the children share in blood and flesh, he also in like manner shared in these same things, in order that through death he could destroy the one who has the power of death, that is, the devil,
B058C002V015	58	2	15	and could set free these who through fear of death were subject to slavery throughout all their lives.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For surely he is not concerned with angels, but he is concerned with the descendants of Abraham.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Therefore he was obligated to be made like his brothers in all respects, in order that he could become a merciful and faithful high priest in the things relating to God, in order to make atonement for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For in that which he himself suffered when he was tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Therefore, holy brothers, sharers in a heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession,
B058C003V002	58	3	2	who was faithful to the one who appointed him, as Moses also was in all his household.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For this one is considered worthy of greater glory than Moses, inasmuch as the one who builds it has greater honor than the house.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house is built by someone, but the one who built all thingsis God.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	And Moses was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony to the things that would be spoken,
B058C003V006	58	3	6	but Christ was faithful as a son over his house, whose house we are, if indeed we hold fast to our confidence and the hope we can be proud of.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore, just as the Holy Spirit says,“Today, if you hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion,in the day of testing in the wilderness,
B058C003V009	58	3	9	where your fathers tested me by trialand saw my works
B058C003V010	58	3	10	for forty years.Therefore I was angry with this generation,and I said, ‘They always go astray in their heart,and they do not know my ways.’
B058C003V011	58	3	11	As I swore in my anger,‘˻They will never enter˼ into my rest.’ ”
B058C003V012	58	3	12	Watch out, brothers, lest there be in some of you an evil, unbelieving heart, with the result that you fall away from the living God.
B058C003V013	58	3	13	But encourage one another ˻day by day˼, as long as it is called “today,” so that ˻none of you become hardened˼ by the deception of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we have become partners of Christ, if indeed we hold fast the beginning of our commitment steadfast until the end,
B058C003V015	58	3	15	˻while it is said˼,“Today, if you hear his voice,do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion.”
B058C003V016	58	3	16	For who, when they heard it, were disobedient? Surely it was not all who went out from Egypt through Moses?
B058C003V017	58	3	17	And with whom was he angry for forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, whose dead bodies fell in the wilderness?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	And to whom did he swear they would not enter into his rest, except those who were disobedient?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	And so we see that they were not able to enter because of unbelief.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Therefore let us fear, while there remains a promise of entering into his rest, that none of you appear to fall short of it.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	˻For we also have had the good news proclaimed to us˼, just as those also did, but the message ˻they heard˼ did not benefit them, because they were not united with those who heard it in faith.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have believed enter into that rest, just as he has said,“As I swore in my anger,‘˻They will never enter˼ into my rest.’ ”And yet these works have been accomplished from the foundation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For he has spoken somewhere about the seventh day in this way: “And God rested on the seventh day from all his works,”
B058C004V005	58	4	5	and in this passage again, ‘˻They will never enter˼ into my rest.’ ”
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Since therefore it remains for some to enter into it, and the ones to whom the good news was proclaimed previously did not enter because of disobedience,
B058C004V007	58	4	7	again he ordains a certain day, today, speaking by David after so long a time, just as had been said before,“Today, if you hear his voice,do not harden your hearts.”
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had caused them to rest, he would not have spoken about another day after these things.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	Consequently a sabbath rest remains for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For the one who has entered into his rest has also himself rested from his works, just as God did from his own works.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Therefore, let us make every effort to enter into that rest, in order that no one may fall in the same pattern of disobedience.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is living and active and sharper than any double-edged sword, and piercing as far as the division of soul and spirit, both joints and marrow, and able to judge the reflections and thoughts of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	And no creature is hidden in the sight of him, but all things are naked and laid bare to the eyes of him to whom ˻we must give our account˼.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Therefore, because we have a great high priest who has gone through the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast to our confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we do not have a high priest who is not able to sympathize with our weaknesses, but who has been tempted in all things in the same way, without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Therefore let us approach with confidence to the throne of grace, in order that we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest taken from among men is appointed on behalf of people in the things relating to God, in order that he can offer both gifts and sacrifices on behalf of sins,
B058C005V002	58	5	2	being able to deal gently with those who are ignorant and led astray, since he himself also is surrounded by weakness,
B058C005V003	58	5	3	and because of it he is obligated to offer sacrifices for sins ˻for himself also, as well as for the people˼.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	And someone does not take for himself the honor, but is called by God, just as Aaron also was.
B058C005V005	58	5	5	Thus also Christ did not glorify himself to become high priest, but the one who said to him,“You are my Son, today I have fathered you,”
B058C005V006	58	5	6	just as also in another place he says,“You are a priest ˻forever˼ according to the order of Melchizedek,”
B058C005V007	58	5	7	who in the days of his flesh offered up both prayers and supplications, with loud crying and tears, to the one who was able to save him from death, and he was heard as a result of his reverence.
B058C005V008	58	5	8	Although he was a son, he learned obedience from what he suffered,
B058C005V009	58	5	9	and being perfected, he became the source of eternal salvation to all those who obey him,
B058C005V010	58	5	10	being designated by God a high priest according to the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	Concerning this ˻we have much to say and it is difficult to explain˼, since you have become sluggish in hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For indeed, although you ought to be teachers ˻by this time˼, you have need of someone to teach you again the beginning elements of the oracles of God, and ˻you have need of˼ milk and not solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For everyone who partakes of milk is unacquainted with the message of righteousness, because he is an infant.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food is for the mature, who because of practice have trained their faculties for the distinguishing of both good and evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore, leaving behind the elementary message about Christ, let us move on to maturity, not laying again a foundation of repentance from dead works and faith in God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	teaching about baptisms and laying on of hands, and resurrection of the dead and eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	And this we will do, if God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For it is impossible concerning those who have once been enlightened, and have tasted the heavenly gift, and become sharers of the Holy Spirit,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	and have tasted the good word of God and the powers of the coming age,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	and having fallen away, to renew them again to repentence, because they have crucified again for themselves the Son of God and held him up to contempt.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For ground that drinks the rain that comes often upon it, and brings forth vegetation usable to those people˻for whose sake˼it is also cultivated, shares a blessing from God.
B058C006V008	58	6	8	But if it produces thorns and thistles, it is worthless and near to a curse, whose end is for burning.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But even if we are speaking in this way, dear friends, we are convinced of better things concerning you, and belonging to salvation.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not unjust, so as to forget your work and the love which you demonstrated for his name by having served the saints, and continuing to serve them.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	And we desire each one of you to demonstrate the same diligence for the full assurance of your hope until the end,
B058C006V012	58	6	12	in order that you may not be sluggish, but imitators of those who inherit the promises through faith and patience.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when God made a promise to Abraham, since he had no one greater to swear by, he swore by himself,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	saying,“Surely ˻I will greatly bless˼ you, and ˻I will greatly multiply˼ you.”
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so, by persevering, he obtained the promise.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For people swear by what is greater than themselves, and the oath for confirmation is the end of all dispute for them.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	In the same way God, because he wanted to show even more to the heirs of the promise the unchangeableness of his resolve, guaranteed it with an oath,
B058C006V018	58	6	18	in order that through two unchangeable things, in which it is impossible for God to lie, we who have taken refuge may have powerful encouragement to hold fast to the hope set before us,
B058C006V019	58	6	19	which we have like an anchor of the soul, both firm and steadfast, and entering into the inside of the curtain,
B058C006V020	58	6	20	where Jesus, the forerunner for us, entered, because he became a high priest ˻forever˼ according to the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, who met Abraham as he was returning from the slaughter of the kings and blessed him,
B058C007V002	58	7	2	to whom also Abraham apportioned a tenth of everything—in the first place, his name is translated “king of righteousness,” and then also “king of Salem,” that is, “king of peace”;
B058C007V003	58	7	3	without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither beginning of days nor end of life, but resembling the Son of God—he remains a priest for all time.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	But see how great this man was, to whom even Abraham the patriarch gave a tenth from the spoils!
B058C007V005	58	7	5	And indeed those of the sons of Levi who receive the priesthood have a commandment to collect a tenth from the people according to the law, that is, from their brothers, although ˻they are descended from Abraham˼.
B058C007V006	58	7	6	But the one who did not trace his descent from them collected tithes from Abraham and blessed the one who had the promises.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	Now without any dispute the inferior is blessed by the more prominent.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	And in this case mortal men receive tithes, but in that case it is testified that he lives.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	And, ˻so to speak˼, even Levi, the one who receives tithes, has paid tithes through Abraham.
B058C007V010	58	7	10	For he was still in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met him.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	Thus if perfection was through the Levitical priesthood, for on the basis of it the people received the law, what further need is there for another priest to arise according to the order of Melchizedek and not said to be according to the order of Aaron?
B058C007V012	58	7	12	For when the priesthood changes, of necessity there is a change of the law also.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For the one about whom these things are spoken belongs to another tribe from which no one has officiated at the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is evident that our Lord is a descendant of Judah, a tribe with reference to which Moses said nothing concerning priests.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	And it is still more clear, if another priest according to the likeness of Melchizedek arises,
B058C007V016	58	7	16	who has become a priest not according to a law of physical requirement, but according to the power of an indestructible life.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For it is testified,“You are a priest ˻forever˼ according to the order of Melchizedek.”
B058C007V018	58	7	18	For on the one hand a preceding commandment is set aside because of its weakness and uselessness
B058C007V019	58	7	19	(for the law made nothing perfect), but on the other hand there is the introduction of a better hope through which we draw near to God.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	And by as much as this was not without an oath (for these on the one hand ˻have become priests˼ without an oath,
B058C007V021	58	7	21	but he with an oath by the one who said to him,“The Lord has sworn and will not change his mind,‘You are a priest ˻forever˼’ ”),
B058C007V022	58	7	22	by so much more also Jesus has become the guarantee of a better covenant.
B058C007V023	58	7	23	And indeed many ˻have become˼ priests, because they were prevented by death from continuing in office,
B058C007V024	58	7	24	but he, because he continues ˻forever˼, holds the priesthood permanently.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	Therefore also he is able to save completely those who draw near to God through him, because he always lives in order to intercede on their behalf.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	For a high priest such as this indeed is fitting for us, holy, innocent, undefiled, separated from sinners, and having become exalted above the heavens,
B058C007V027	58	7	27	who does not ˻need every day˼ like the former high priests to offer up sacrifices for his own sins and then for the sins of the people, because he did this once for all when he offered up himself.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the law appoints men as high priests who have weakness, but the statement of the oath, after the law, appoints a Son, who is made perfect ˻forever˼.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	Now this is the main point in what has been said: we have a high priest such as this, who sat down at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven,
B058C008V002	58	8	2	a minister of the sanctuary and of the true tabernacle which the Lord set up, not man.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	For every high priest is appointed in order to offer both gifts and sacrifices; therefore it was necessary for this one also to have something that he offers.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	Now if he were on earth, he would not even be a priest, because there are those who offer the gifts according to the law,
B058C008V005	58	8	5	who serve a sketch and shadow of the heavenly things, just as Moses was warned when he was about to complete the tabernacle, for he says, “See to it that you make everything according to the pattern which was shown to you on the mountain.”
B058C008V006	58	8	6	But now he has attained a more excellent ministry, by as much as he is also mediator of a better covenant which has been enacted upon better promises.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if that first covenant had been faultless, occasion would not have been sought for a second.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	For in finding fault with them he says,“Behold, days are coming, says the Lord,when I will complete a new covenant with the house of Israeland with the house of Judah,
B058C008V009	58	8	9	not like the covenant which I made with their fatherson the day I took hold of them by my handto lead them out of the land of Egypt,because they did not continue in my covenantand I disregarded them, says the Lord.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	For this is the covenant that I will decree with the house of Israelafter those days, says the Lord:I am putting my laws in their mindsand I will write them on their hearts,and I will be ˻their˼ Godand they will be ˻my˼ people.
B058C008V011	58	8	11	And they will not teach each one his fellow citizenand each one his brother, saying, ‘Know the Lord,’because they will all know me,from the least of them to the greatest.
B058C008V012	58	8	12	For I will be merciful toward their wrongdoings,and I will not remember their sins any longer.”
B058C008V013	58	8	13	In calling it new, he has declared the former to be old. Now what is becoming obsolete and growing old is near to disappearing.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	Now even the first covenant had regulations for worship and the earthly sanctuary.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For a tent was prepared, the first one, in which were the lampstand and the table and the presentation of the loaves, which is called the holy place.
B058C009V003	58	9	3	And after the second curtain was a tent called the holy of holies,
B058C009V004	58	9	4	containing the golden incense altar and the ark of the covenant covered on all sides with gold, in which were a golden jar containing the manna and the rod of Aaron that budded and the tablets of the covenant.
B058C009V005	58	9	5	And above it were the cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat, about which it is not now possible to speak in detail.
B058C009V006	58	9	6	Now these things having been prepared in this way, the priests enter into the first tent ˻continually˼as they accomplish their service,
B058C009V007	58	9	7	but only the high priest enters into the second tent once a year, not without blood, which he offers on behalf of himself and the sins of the people committed in ignorance.
B058C009V008	58	9	8	The Holy Spirit was making this clear, that the way into the holy place was not yet revealed, while the first tent was still in existence,
B058C009V009	58	9	9	which was a symbol for the present time, in which both the gifts and sacrifices which were offered were not able to perfect the worshiper with respect to the conscience,
B058C009V010	58	9	10	concerning instead only food and drink and different washings, regulations of outward things imposed until the time of setting things right.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But Christ has arrived as a high priest of the good things to come. Through the greater and more perfect tent not made by hands, that is, not of this creation,
B058C009V012	58	9	12	and not by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood, he entered once for all into the most holy place, obtaining eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of goats and bulls and the ashes of a young cow sprinkled on those who are defiled sanctify them for the ritual purity of the flesh,
B058C009V014	58	9	14	how much more will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without blemish to God, cleanse our consciences from dead works to serve the living God?
B058C009V015	58	9	15	And because of this, he is the mediator of a new covenant, in order that, because a death has taken place for the redemption of transgressions committed during the first covenant, those who are the called may receive the promise of the eternal inheritance.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where there is a will, it is a necessity for the death of the one who made the will to be established.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For a will is in force concerning those who are dead, since it is never in force when the one who made the will is alive.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	Therefore not even the first covenant was ratified without blood.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	For when every commandment had been spoken by Moses to all the people according to the law, he took the blood of calves and goats with water and scarlet wool and hyssop and sprinkled both the scroll itself and all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	saying,“This is the blood of the covenant that God has commanded for you.”
B058C009V021	58	9	21	And likewise he sprinkled both the tabernacle and all the utensils of service with the blood.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	Indeed, nearly everything is purified with blood according to the law, and apart from the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	Therefore it was necessary for the sketches of the things in heaven to be purified with these sacrifices, but the heavenly things themselves to be purified with better sacrifices than these.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For Christ did not enter into a sanctuary made by hands, a mere copy of the true one, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God on our behalf,
B058C009V025	58	9	25	and not in order that he can offer himself many times, as the high priest enters into the sanctuary ˻year by year˼ with blood not his own,
B058C009V026	58	9	26	since it would have been necessary for him to suffer many times from the foundation of the world, but now he has appeared once at the end of the ages for the removal of sin by the sacrifice of himself.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And ˻just as˼ it is destined for people to die once, and after this, judgment,
B058C009V028	58	9	28	thus also Christ, having been offered once in order to bear the sins of many, will appear for the second time without reference to sin to those who eagerly await him for salvation.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For the law, possessing a shadow of the good things that are about to come, not the form of things itself, is never able ˻year by year˼ by means of the same sacrifices which they offer without interruption to make perfect those who draw near.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	For otherwise, would they not have ceased to be offered, because the ones who worship, having been purified once and for all, would no longer have any consciousness of sins?
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But in them there is a reminder of sins ˻year by year˼.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	Therefore, when he came into the world, he said,“Sacrifice and offering you did not want,but a body you prepared for me;
B058C010V006	58	10	6	you did not delight in whole burnt offerings and offerings for sins.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then I said, ‘Behold, I have come—in the roll of the book it is written about me—to do your will, O God.’
B058C010V008	58	10	8	When he says above,“Sacrifices and offerings and whole burnt offerings and offerings for sinyou did not want, nor did you delight in,”which are offered according to the law,
B058C010V009	58	10	9	then he has said,“Behold, I have come to do your will.”He takes away the first in order to establish the second,
B058C010V010	58	10	10	by which will we are made holy through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	And every priest stands every day serving and offering the same sacrifices many times, which are never able to take away sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But this one, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins for all time, sat down at the right hand of God,
B058C010V013	58	10	13	from now on waiting until his enemies are made a footstool for his feet.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by one offering he has perfected for all time those who are made holy.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	And the Holy Spirit also testifies to us, for after saying,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	“This is the covenant that I will decree for themafter those days, says the Lord:I am putting my laws on their hearts,and I will write them on their minds.”
B058C010V017	58	10	17	He also says,“Their sins and their lawless deeds I will never remember again.”
B058C010V018	58	10	18	Now where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer an offering for sin.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Therefore, brothers, since we have confidence for the entrance into the sanctuary by the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	by the new and living way which he inaugurated for us through the curtain, that is, his flesh,
B058C010V021	58	10	21	and since we have a great priest over the house of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	let us approach with a true heart in the full assurance of faith, our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies washed with pure water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us hold fast to the confession of our hope without wavering, for the one who promised is faithful.
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us think about ˻how to stir one another up to love˼ and good works,
B058C010V025	58	10	25	not abandoning ˻our meeting together˼, as is the habit of some, but encouraging each other, and by so much more as you see the day drawing near.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we keep on sinning deliberately after receiving the knowledge of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice for sins,
B058C010V027	58	10	27	but a certain fearful expectation of judgment and a fury of fire that is about to consume the adversaries.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	Anyone who rejected the law of Moses dies without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses.
B058C010V029	58	10	29	How much worse punishment do you think the person will be considered worthy of who treats with disdain the Son of God and who considers ordinary the blood of the covenant by which he was made holy and who insults the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know the one who said,“Vengeance is mine, I will repay,”and again,“The Lord will judge his people.”
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is a terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the living God.
B058C010V032	58	10	32	But remember the former days in which, after you were enlightened, you endured a great struggle with sufferings,
B058C010V033	58	10	33	sometimes being publicly exposed both to insults and to afflictions, and sometimes becoming sharers with those who were treated in this way.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you both sympathized with the prisoners and put up with the seizure of your belongings with joy because you knew that you yourselves had a better and permanent possession.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Therefore do not throw away your confidence, which has great reward.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	For you have need of endurance, in order that after you have done the will of God, you may receive what was promised.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	For yet“a very, very little while,and the one who is coming will come and will not delay.
B058C010V038	58	10	38	But my righteous one will live by faith,and if he shrinks back, my soul is not well pleased with him.”
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not among those who shrink back to destruction, but among those who have faith to the preservation of our souls.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is the realization of what is hoped for, the proof of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by this the people of old were approved.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	By faith we understand the worlds were created by the word of God, in order that what is seen did not come into existence from what is visible.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered to God a greater sacrifice than Cain, by which he was approved that he was righteous, because God approved him for his gifts, and through it he still speaks, although he is dead.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was taken up, so that he did not experience death, and he was not found, because God took him up. For before his removal, he had been approved ˻as having been pleasing˼ to God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	Now without faith it is impossible to please him, for the one who approaches God must believe that he exists and is a rewarder of those who seek him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, having been warned about things not yet seen, out of reverence constructed an ark for the deliverance of his family, by which he pronounced sentence on the world and became an heir of the righteousness that comes by faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham, when he was called, obeyed to go out to a place that he was going to receive for an inheritance, and he went out, not knowing where he was going.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he lived in the land of promise as a stranger, living in tents with Isaac and Jacob, the fellow heirs of the same promise.
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he was expecting the city that has foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	By faith, even though Sarah herself was barren, he received ˻the ability to procreate˼ even ˻past the normal age˼, because he regarded the one who had promised to be faithful.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	And therefore these were fathered from one man, and he being as good as dead, as the stars of heaven in number and like the innumerable sand by the shore of the sea.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	These all died in faith without receiving the promises, but seeing them from a distance and welcoming them, and admitting that they were strangers and temporary residents on the earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For those who say such things make clear that they are seeking a homeland.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And if they had been remembering that land from which they had gone out, they would have had opportunity to return.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	But now they aspire to a better land, that is, a heavenly one. Therefore God is not ashamed of them, to be called their God, for he has prepared for them a city.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered Isaac, and the one who received the promises was ready to offer his one and only son,
B058C011V018	58	11	18	with reference to whom it was said, “In Isaac your descendants will be named,”
B058C011V019	58	11	19	having reasoned that God was able even to raise him from the dead, from which he received him back also as a symbol.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith also Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things that were going to happen.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob, as he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph and worshiped, leaning on the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, as he was dying, mentioned about the exodus of the sons of Israel and gave instructions about his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses, when he was born, was hidden for three months by his parents, because they saw the child was handsome, and they were not afraid of the edict of the king.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses, when he was grown up, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh’s daughter,
B058C011V025	58	11	25	choosing instead to be mistreated with the people of God rather than to experience the transitory enjoyment of sin,
B058C011V026	58	11	26	considering ˻reproach endured for the sake of Christ˼ greater wealth than the treasures of Egypt, for he was looking to the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the anger of the king, for he persevered as if he saw the invisible one.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of blood, in order that the one who destroyed the firstborn would not touch them.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they crossed the Red Sea as if on dry land; the Egyptians, ˻when they made the attempt˼, were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been marched around for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith Rahab the prostitute did not perish with those who were disobedient, because she welcomed the spies in peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what more shall I say? For time would fail me to tell about Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, and Samuel and the prophets,
B058C011V033	58	11	33	who through faith conquered kingdoms, accomplished justice, obtained what was promised, shut the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	extinguished the effectiveness of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, were made strong from weakness, became mighty in battle, put to flight enemy battle lines.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received back their dead by resurrection. But others were tortured, not accepting release, in order that they might gain a better resurrection.
B058C011V036	58	11	36	And others ˻experienced mocking and flogging˼, and in addition bonds and imprisonment.
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, they were sawed in two, they died by murder with a sword, they wandered about in sheepskins, in goatskins, impoverished, afflicted, mistreated,
B058C011V038	58	11	38	of whom the world was not worthy, wandering about on deserts and mountains and in caves and in holes in the ground.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And all these, although they were approved through their faith, did not receive what was promised,
B058C011V040	58	11	40	because God had provided something better for us, so that they would not be made perfect without us.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore, since we also have such a great cloud of witnesses surrounding us, putting aside every weight and ˻the sin that so easily ensnares us˼, let us run with patient endurance the race that has been set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	fixing our eyes on Jesus, the originator and perfecter of faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, disregarding the shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	For consider the one who endured such hostility against himself by sinners, so that you will not grow weary in your souls and give up.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted to the point of shedding your blood as you struggle against sin.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	And have you completely forgotten the exhortation which instructs you as sons?“My son, do not make light of the Lord’s discipline,or give up when you are corrected by him.
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For the Lord disciplines the one whom he loves,and punishes every son whom he accepts.”
B058C012V007	58	12	7	Endure it for discipline. God is dealing with you as sons. For what son is there whom a father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you are without discipline, in which all legitimate sons have become participants, then you are illegitimate and not sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore, we have had ˻our earthly fathers˼ who disciplined us, and we respected them. Will we not much rather subject ourselves to the Father of spirits and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they disciplined us for a few days according to what seemed appropriate to them, but he does so for our benefit, in order that we can have a share in his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	Now all discipline seems for the moment not to be joyful but painful, but later it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness for those who are trained by it.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore strengthen your slackened hands and your weakened knees,
B058C012V013	58	12	13	and make straight paths for your feet, so that what is lame will not be dislocated, but rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Pursue peace with everyone, and holiness, without which no one will see the Lord.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	Take care that no one falls short of the grace of God; that no one growing up like a root of bitterness causes trouble, and by it many become defiled;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	that no one be a sexually immoral or totally worldly person like Esau, who for one meal traded his own birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that also afterwards, when he wanted to inherit the blessing, he was rejected, because he did not find an occasion for repentence, although he sought it with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to something that can be touched, and to a burning fire, and to darkness, and to gloom, and to a whirlwind,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	and to the noise of a trumpet, and to the sound of words which those who heard begged that not another word be spoken to them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not endure what was commanded: “If even an animal touches the mountain, it must be stoned.”
B058C012V021	58	12	21	And the spectacle was so terrifying that Moses said, “I am terrified and trembling.”
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you have come to Mount Zion, and to the city of the living God, to the heavenly Jerusalem, and to tens of thousands of angels, to the festal gathering
B058C012V023	58	12	23	and assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, and to God the judge of all, and to the spirits of righteous people made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	and to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and ˻to the sprinkled blood˼ that speaks better than Abel’s does.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	Watch out that you do not refuse the one who is speaking! For if those did not escape when they refused the one who warned them on earth, much less will we escape, if we reject the one who warns from heaven,
B058C012V026	58	12	26	whose voice shook the earth at that time, but now he has promised, saying,“Yet once more I will shake not only the earth but also heaven.”
B058C012V027	58	12	27	Now the phrase “yet once more” indicates the removal of what is shaken, namely, things that have been created, in order that the things that are not shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore, since we are receiving an unshakable kingdom, let us be thankful, through which let us serve God acceptably, with awe and reverence.
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For indeed our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Brotherly love must continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not neglect hospitality, because through this some have received angels as guests without knowing it.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember the prisoners, as though you were fellow-prisoners; remember the mistreated, as thoughyou yourselves also are being mistreated in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Marriage must be held in honor by all, and the marriage bed be undefiled, because God will judge sexually immoral people and adulterers.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Your lifestyle must be free from the love of money, being content with what you have. For he himself has said, “I will never desert you, and I will never abandon you.”
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So then, we can say with confidence,“The Lord is my helper, and I will not be afraid.What will man do to me?”
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember your leaders, who spoke the word of God to you; ˻considering the outcome of their way of life˼, imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today and ˻forever˼.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be carried away by various and strange teachings, for it is good for the heart to be strengthened by grace, not by foods by which those who participate have not benefited.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar from which those who serve in the tabernacle do not have the right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of those animals whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sins are burned up outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	Therefore Jesus also suffered outside the gate, in order that he might sanctify the people by his own blood.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	So we must go out to him outside the camp, bearing his reproach.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For here we do not have a permanent city, but we seek the city that is to come.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Therefore through him let us offer up a sacrifice of praise ˻continually˼ to God, that is, the fruit of lips that confess his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	And do not neglect doing good and generosity, for God is pleased with such sacrifices.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey your leaders and submit to them, for they keep watch over your souls as those who will give an account, so that they can do this with joy and not with groaning, for this would be unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us, for we are convinced that we have a good conscience, and want to conduct ourselves commendably in every way.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	And I especially urge you to do this, so that I may be restored to you more quickly.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may the God of peace, who brought up from the dead our Lord Jesus, the great shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the eternal covenant,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	equip you with every good thing to do his will, carrying out in us what is pleasing before him through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	Now I urge you, brothers, bear with my word of exhortation, for indeed I have written to you ˻briefly˼.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	Know that our brother Timothy has been released, with whom I will see you, if he comes quickly enough.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all your leaders and all the saints. Those from Italy greet you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with all of you.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	James, a slave of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes in the dispersion. Greetings!
B059C001V002	59	1	2	Consider it all joy, my brothers, whenever you encounter various trials,
B059C001V003	59	1	3	because you know that the testing of your faith produces endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	And let endurance have its perfect effect, so that you may be mature and complete, lacking in nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	Now if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask for it from God, who gives to all without reservation and not reproaching, and it will be given to him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask for it in faith, without any doubting, for the one who doubts is like the surf of the sea, driven by the wind and tossed about.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	For that person must not suppose that he will receive anything from the Lord;
B059C001V008	59	1	8	he is a double-minded man, unstable in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Now let the brother of humble circumstances boast in his high position,
B059C001V010	59	1	10	but the rich person in his humiliation, because he will pass away like a flower of the grass.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun rises with its burning heat and dries up the grass, and its flower falls off, and the beauty of its appearance is lost. So also the rich person in his pursuits will wither away.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the person who endures testing, because when he is approved he will receive the crown of life that he has promised to those who love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	No one who is being tempted should say, “I am being tempted by God,” for God ˻cannot be tempted˼ by evil, and he himself tempts no one.
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But each one is tempted when he is dragged away and enticed by his own desires.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then desire, after it has conceived, gives birth to sin, and sin, when it is brought to completion, gives birth to death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my dear brothers.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shadow of change.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	By his will he gave birth to us through the message of truth, so that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	Understand this, my dear brothers: every person must be quick to hear, slow to speak, slow to anger,
B059C001V020	59	1	20	for human anger does not accomplish the righteousness of God.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore, putting aside all moral uncleanness and wicked excess, welcome with humility the implanted message which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But be doers of the message and not only hearers, deceiving yourselves,
B059C001V023	59	1	23	because if anyone is a hearer of the message and not a doer, this one is like someone staring at ˻his own face˼ in a mirror,
B059C001V024	59	1	24	for he looks at himself and goes away and immediately forgets what sort of person he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But the one who looks into the perfect law of liberty and continues to do it, not being a forgetful hearer but a doer who acts, this one will be blessed ˻in what he does˼.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If anyone thinks he is religious, although he does not bridle his tongue but deceives his heart, this person’s religion is worthless.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	Pure and undefiled religion in the sight of our God and Father is this: to look after orphans and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unstained by the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brothers, do not hold your faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ with partiality.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if someone enters into your assembly in fine clothing with a gold ring on his finger, and a poor person in filthy clothing also enters,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	and you look favorably on the one wearing the fine clothing and you say, “Be seated here in a good place,” and to the poor person you say, “You stand there or be seated by my footstool,”
B059C002V004	59	2	4	have you not made distinctions among yourselves and become judges with evil thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my dear brothers! Did not God choose the poor of the world to be rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom that he has promised to those who love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have dishonored the poor! Are not the rich exploiting you and they themselves dragging you into the courts?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do they themselves not blaspheme the good name ˻of the one to whom you belong˼?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	However, if you carry out the royal law according to the scripture, “You shall love your neighbor as yourself,” you are doing well.
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you show partiality, you commit sin, and thus are convicted by the law as transgressors.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whoever keeps the whole law but stumbles in one point only has become guilty of all of it.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For the one who said “Do not commit adultery” also said “Do not murder.” Now if you do not commit adultery but you do murder, you have become a transgressor of the law.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	Thus speak and thus act as those who are going to be judged by the law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For judgment is merciless to the one who has not practiced mercy. Mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What is the benefit, my brothers, if someone says that he has faith but does not have works? That faith is not able to save him, is it?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	If a brother or a sister is poorly clothed and lacking food for the day,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	and one of you should say to them, “Go in peace, keep warm and ˻eat well˼,” but does not give them what is necessary for the body, what is the benefit?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Thus also faith, if it does not have works, is dead by itself.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	But someone will say, “You have faith and I have works.” Show me your faith apart from your works, and I will show you my faith by my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that God is one; you do well. Even the demons believe, and shudder!
B059C002V020	59	2	20	But do you want to know, O foolish person, that faith apart from works is useless?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered up his son Isaac on the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You see that faith was working together with his works, and by the works the faith was perfected.
B059C002V023	59	2	23	And the scripture was fulfilled that says, “And Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him for righteousness,” and he was called God’s friend.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	And likewise was not Rahab the prostitute also justified by works when she welcomed the messengers and sent them out by a different route?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For just as the body without the spirit is dead, so also faith without works is dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	Not many should become teachers, my brothers, because you know that we will receive a greater judgment.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For we all stumble in many ways. If anyone does not stumble in what he says, he is a perfect individual, able to hold in check his whole body also.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	And if we put bits in the mouths of horses so that they obey us, we also guide their whole bodies.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Behold also ships: although they are so large and are driven by strong winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the inclination of the pilot wishes.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	So also the tongue is a small member of the body and boasts great things. Behold how small a fire sets ablaze how great a forest!
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire! The world of unrighteousness, the tongue, is set among our members, defiling the whole body and setting on fire ˻the course of human existence˼, being set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every species of animals and birds, of reptiles and sea creatures, is being tamed and has been tamed by the human species,
B059C003V008	59	3	8	but no human being is able to tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless the Lord and Father, and with it we curse people who are made in the likeness of God.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	From the same mouth come blessing and cursing. My brothers, these things ought not to be so!
B059C003V011	59	3	11	A spring does not pour forth from the same opening fresh and bitter water, does it?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	A fig tree is not able, my brothers, to produce olives, or a grapevine figs. Neither can a saltwater spring produce fresh water.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show by his good behavior his works, with the humility of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter jealousy and selfish ambition in your hearts, do not boast and tell lies against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This is not the wisdom that comes down from above, but is earthly, unspiritual, demonic.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where there is jealousy and selfish ambition, there is disorder and every evil practice.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peaceful, gentle, obedient, full of mercy and good fruits, nonjudgmental, without hypocrisy,
B059C003V018	59	3	18	And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace among those who make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	From where are conflicts and from where are quarrels among you? Is it not from this, from your pleasures that wage war among your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You desire and do not have; you murder and are filled with envy, and are not able to obtain; you fight and quarrel. You do not have because you do not ask.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask and do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, in order that you may spend it on your pleasures.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	Adulterous people! Do you not know that friendship with the world is enmity with God? Therefore whoever wants to be a friend of the world makes himself an enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Or do you think that in vain the scripture says, “The spirit which he caused to dwell in us desires jealously”?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But he gives greater grace. Therefore it says,“God opposes the proud,but gives grace to the humble.”
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Therefore subject yourselves to God. But resist the devil, and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners, and purify your hearts, you double-minded!
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Lament and mourn and weep! Let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to gloominess.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak evil of one another, brothers. The one who speaks evil of a brother or judges his brother speaks evil of the law and judges the law. But if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law but a judge of the law.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	There is one lawgiver and judge who is able to save and to destroy. But who are you to judge your neighbor?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come now, you who say, “Today or tomorrow we will travel to such and such a city and spend a year there, and carry on business and make a profit,”
B059C004V014	59	4	14	you who do not know ˻what will happen tomorrow˼, ˻what your life will be like˼. For you are a smoky vapor that appears for a short time and then disappears.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	Instead you should say, “If the Lord wills, we will live and do this or that.”
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you boast in your arrogance. All such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	Therefore, to the one who knows to do good and does not do it, to him it is sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Come now, you rich people, weep and cry aloud over the miseries that are coming upon you!
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your wealth has rotted, and your clothing has become moth-eaten.
B059C005V003	59	5	3	Your gold and silver have become corroded, and their corrosion will be a witness against you, and it will consume your flesh like fire. You have stored up treasure in the last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Behold, the wages that were held back by you from the workers who reap your fields cry out, and the cries of the reapers have come to the ears of the Lord of hosts.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived self-indulgently on the earth and have lived luxuriously. You have fattened your hearts in the day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned, you have murdered the righteous person; he does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Therefore be patient, brothers, until the coming of the Lord. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the soil, being patient concerning it until it receives the early and late rains.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You also be patient. Strengthen your hearts, because the coming of the Lord is near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Brothers, do not complain against one another, in order that you may not be judged. Behold, the judge stands before the doors!
B059C005V010	59	5	10	Brothers, take as an example of perseverence and endurance the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Behold, we consider blessed those who have endured. You have heard about the patient endurance of Job, and you saw the outcome from the Lord, that the Lord is compassionate and merciful.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	Now above all, my brothers, do not swear either by heaven or by earth or by any other oath, but let your yes be yes and your no, no, in order that you may not fall under judgment.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is anyone among you suffering misfortune? He should pray. Is anyone cheerful? He should sing praise.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is anyone among you sick? He should summon the elders of the church and they should pray over him, anointing him with olive oil in the name of the Lord.
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith will save the one who is sick, and the Lord will raise him up, and if he has committed sins ˻he will be forgiven˼.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Therefore confess your sins to one another, and pray for one another, so that you may be healed. The effective prayer of a righteous person accomplishes much.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a human being with the same nature as us, and ˻he prayed fervently˼ for it not to rain, and it did not rain on the land for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	And he prayed again, and the sky gave rain and the earth produced its fruit.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	My brothers, if anyone among you should wander away from the truth and someone turns him back,
B059C005V020	59	5	20	he should know that the one who turns a sinner back from the error of his way will save that person’s soul from death, and will cover over a great number of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the chosen who are residing temporarily in the dispersion in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, by the sanctification of the Spirit, for obedience and for sprinkling with the blood of Jesus Christ. May grace and peace be multiplied to you.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to his great mercy has caused us to be born again to a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	into an inheritance imperishable and undefiled and unfading, reserved in heaven for you
B060C001V005	60	1	5	who are being protected by the power of God through faith for a salvation ready to be revealed in the last time,
B060C001V006	60	1	6	in which you rejoice greatly, although now for a short time, if it is necessary, you are distressed by various trials,
B060C001V007	60	1	7	so that the genuineness of your faith, more valuable than gold that is passing away, but is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise and glory and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ,
B060C001V008	60	1	8	whom, although you have not seen, you love; in whom now you believe, although you do not see him, and you rejoice greatly with joy inexpressible and full of glory,
B060C001V009	60	1	9	obtaining the goal of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Concerning this salvation, the prophets who prophesied about the grace meant for you sought and made careful inquiry,
B060C001V011	60	1	11	investigating for what person or which time the Spirit of Christ in them was indicating when he testified beforehand to the sufferings with reference to Christ and the glories after these things,
B060C001V012	60	1	12	to whom it was revealed that they were serving not themselves but you with reference to the same things which now have been announced to you through those who proclaimed the gospel to you by the Holy Spirit sent from heaven, ˻things into which˼ angels desire to look.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore, ˻when you have prepared your minds for action˼by being self-controlled, put your hope completely in the grace that will be brought to you at the revelation of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V014	60	1	14	As obedient children, do not be conformed to the former desires you used to conform to in your ignorance,
B060C001V015	60	1	15	but as the one who called you is holy, you yourselves be holy in all your conduct,
B060C001V016	60	1	16	for it is written, “You will be holy, because I am holy.”
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you call on himas Father who judges impartially according to each one’s work, conduct yourselves with fear during the time of your temporary residence,
B060C001V018	60	1	18	because you know that you were redeemed from your futile way of life inherited from your ancestors not with perishable things like silver or gold,
B060C001V019	60	1	19	but with the precious blood of Christ, like that of an umblemished and spotless lamb
B060C001V020	60	1	20	who was foreknown before the foundation of the world, but has been revealed in these last times for you
B060C001V021	60	1	21	who through him are believing in God, who raised him from the dead and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Having purified your souls by your obedience to the truth for sincere brotherly love, love one another fervently from a pure heart,
B060C001V023	60	1	23	because you have been born again, not from perishable seed but imperishable, through the living and enduring word of God.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For“all flesh is like grass,and all its glory like the flower of the grass.The grass withers and the flower falls off,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	but the word of the Lord endures ˻forever˼.”And this is the word that has been proclaimed to you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Therefore, ridding yourselves of all malice and all deceit and hypocrisy and envy and all slander,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	like newborn infants long for the unadulterated spiritual milk, so that by it you may grow up to salvation,
B060C002V003	60	2	3	if you have tasted that the Lord is kind,
B060C002V004	60	2	4	to whom you are drawing near, a living stone rejected by men but chosen and precious in the sight of God.
B060C002V005	60	2	5	And you yourselves, as living stones, are being built up as a spiritual house for a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	For it stands in scripture,“Behold, I am laying in Zion a stone, a chosen and precious cornerstone,and the one who believes in him will never be put to shame.”
B060C002V007	60	2	7	Therefore the honor is for you who believe, but for those who refuse to believe,“The stone that the builders rejected,this one has become ˻the cornerstone˼,”
B060C002V008	60	2	8	and“A stone of stumbling and a rock of offense,”who stumble because they disobey the word to which also they were consigned.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for God’s possession, so that you may proclaim the virtues of the one who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light,
B060C002V010	60	2	10	who once were not a people, but now are the people of God, the ones who were not shown mercy, but now are shown mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Dear friends, I urge you as foreigners and temporary residents to abstain from fleshly desires which wage war against your soul,
B060C002V012	60	2	12	maintaining your good conduct among the Gentiles, so that in the things in which they slander you as evildoers, by seeing your good deeds they may glorify God on the day of visitation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Subject yourselves to every human authority for the sake of the Lord, whether to a king as having supreme authority,
B060C002V014	60	2	14	or to governors as those sent out by him for the punishment of those who do evil and the praise of those who do good.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For the will of God is as follows: by doing good to silence the ignorance of foolish people.
B060C002V016	60	2	16	Live as free persons, and not using your freedom as a covering for evil, but as slaves of God.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honor all people, love the community of believers, fear God, honor the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Domestic slaves, be subject to your masters with all respect, not only to those who are good and gentle, but also to those who are unjust.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For this finds favor, if because of consciousness of God someone endures sorrows while suffering unjustly.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what credit is it if, when you sin and are beaten for it, you endure? But if you endure when you do good and suffer for it, this finds favor with God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For to this you were called, because Christ also suffered for you, leaving you an example, so that you should follow in his footsteps,
B060C002V022	60	2	22	who did not commit sin, nor was deceit found in his mouth,
B060C002V023	60	2	23	who when he was reviled, did not revile in return; when suffering, he did not threaten, but entrusted himself to the one who judges justly,
B060C002V024	60	2	24	who himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, so that we may die to sins and live to righteousness, by whose wounds you were healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were going astray like sheep, but you have turned back now to the shepherd and guardian of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	In the same way, wives, be subject to your own husbands, so that even if some are disobedient to the word, they may be won over without a word by the conduct of their wives,
B060C003V002	60	3	2	when they see your respectful, pure conduct.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Let your adornment not be the external kind, braiding hair and putting on gold jewelry or putting on fine clothing,
B060C003V004	60	3	4	but the hidden person of the heart, with the imperishable quality of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is highly valuable in the sight of God.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For in the same way formerly the holy women also, who hoped in God, used to adorn themselves by being subject to their own husbands,
B060C003V006	60	3	6	like Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord, whose children you have become when you do good and are not frightened with respect to any terror.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	Husbands, in the same way live with your wives˻knowledgeably˼, as with the weaker female vessel, showing them honor as fellow heirs also of the grace of life, so that your prayers will not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	And finally, all of you be harmonious, sympathetic, showing mutual affection, compassionate, humble,
B060C003V009	60	3	9	not repaying evil for evil or insult for insult, but on the other hand blessing others, because for this reason you were called, so that you could inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For“The one who wants to love lifeand see good daysmust keep his tongue from eviland his lips must not speak deceit.
B060C003V011	60	3	11	And he must turn away from evil and do good;he must seek peace and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous,and his ears are open to their prayer.But the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who is the one who will harm you if you are a zealous adherent for what is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you might suffer for the sake of righteousness, you are blessed. And do not be afraid of their intimidation or be disturbed,
B060C003V015	60	3	15	but set Christ apart as Lord in your hearts, always ready to make a defense to anyone who asks you for an accounting concerning the hope that is in you.
B060C003V016	60	3	16	But do so with courtesy and respect, having a good conscience, so that in the things in which you are slandered, the ones who malign your good conduct in Christ may be put to shame.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better to suffer for doing good, ˻if God wills it˼, than for doing evil.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ also suffered once for sins,the just for the unjust,in order that he could bring you to God,being put to death in the flesh,but made alive in the spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	in which also he went and proclaimed to the spirits in prison,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	who were formerly disobedient, when the patience of God waited in the days of Noah, while an ark was being constructed, in which a few—that is, eight souls—were rescued through water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	And also, corresponding to this, baptism now saves you, not the removal of dirt from the flesh, but an appeal to God for a good conscience through the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	who is at the right hand of God, having gone into heaven, with angels and authorities and powers having been subjected to him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Therefore, because Christ suffered in the flesh, you also equip yourselves with the same way of thinking, because the one who has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin,
B060C004V002	60	4	2	in order to live the remaining time in the flesh no longer for human desires, but for the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For the time that has passed was sufficient ˻to do what the Gentiles desire to do˼, having lived in licentiousness, evil desires, drunkenness, carousing, drinking parties, and wanton idolatries,
B060C004V004	60	4	4	with respect to which they are surprised when you do not run with them into the same flood of dissipation, and so they revile you.
B060C004V005	60	4	5	They will give an account to the one who is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	Because for this reason also the gospel was preached to those who are dead, so that they were judged ˻by human standards˼ in the flesh, but they may live in the spirit ˻by God’s standards˼.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	Now the end of all things draws near. Therefore be self-controlled and sober-minded for your prayers.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all, keep your love for one another constant, because love covers a large number of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Be hospitable to one another without complaining.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	Just as each one has received a gift, use it for serving one another, as good stewards of the varied grace of God.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If anyone speaks, let it be as the oracles of God; if anyone serves, let it be as by the strength that God provides, so that in all things God will be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom is the glory and the power ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Dear friends, do not be surprised at the fiery ordeal among you, when it takes place to test you, as ifsomething strange were happening to you.
B060C004V013	60	4	13	But to the degree that you share in the sufferings of Christ, rejoice, so that also at the revelation of his glory you may rejoice and be glad.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you are reviled on account of the name of Christ, you are blessed, because the Spirit of glory and of God rests on you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	By all means do not let anyone of you suffer as a murderer or a thief or an evildoer or as a meddler.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	But if someone suffers as a Christian, he must not be ashamed, but must glorify God with this name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For it is the time for the judgment to begin out from the household of God. But if it begins out from us first, what will be the outcome for those who are disobedient to the gospel of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And if the righteous are saved with difficulty, ˻what will become of the ungodly and the sinner˼?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	So then also those who suffer according to the will of God must entrust their souls to a faithful Creator in doing good.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	Therefore I, your fellow elder and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and also a sharer of the glory that is going to be revealed, exhort the elders among you:
B060C005V002	60	5	2	shepherd the flock of God among you, exercising oversight not by compulsion but willingly, in accordance with God, and not greedily but eagerly,
B060C005V003	60	5	3	and not as lording it over ˻those under your care˼, but being examples for the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	And when the chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the unfading crown of glory.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	In the same way, younger men, be subject to the elders, and all of you clothe yourselves with humility toward one another, because God opposes the proud, but gives grace to the humble.
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, so that he may exalt you at the right time,
B060C005V007	60	5	7	casting all your cares on him, because ˻he cares˼ for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober; be on the alert. Your adversary the devil walks around like a roaring lion, looking for someone to devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	˻Resist him˼, steadfast in your faith, because you know the same kinds of sufferings are being accomplished by your community of believers in the world.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	And the God of all grace, who called you to his eternal glory in Christ Jesus, after you have suffered for a short time, will himself restore, confirm, strengthen, and establish you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To him be the power ˻forever˼. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	Through Silvanus, the faithful brother (as I consider him), I have written to you ˻briefly˼ to encourage you and to attest that this is the true grace of God. Stand firm in it.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	She who is in Babylon, chosen the same as you, greets you, and so does my son Mark.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a loving kiss. Peace to all of you who are in Christ.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simeon Peter, a slave and apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who have obtained a faith equal in value to ours by the righteousness of our God and Savior Jesus Christ.
B061C001V002	61	1	2	May grace and peace be multiplied to you in the knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord,
B061C001V003	61	1	3	because his divine power has bestowed on us all thingsthat are necessary for life and godliness, through the knowledge of the one who called us by his own glory and excellence of character,
B061C001V004	61	1	4	through which things he has bestowed on us his precious and very great promises, so that through these you may become sharers of the divine nature after escaping from the corruption that is in the world because of evil desire,
B061C001V005	61	1	5	and for this same reason, and by applying all diligence, supply with your faith excellence of character, and with excellence of character, knowledge,
B061C001V006	61	1	6	and with knowledge, self-control, and with self-control, patient endurance, and with patient endurance, godliness,
B061C001V007	61	1	7	and with godliness, brotherly love, and with brotherly love, love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if these things are yours and are increasing, this does not make you useless or unproductive in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	For the one for whom these thingsare not present is blind, being nearsighted, ˻having forgotten the cleansing˼ of his former sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore, brothers, be zealous even more to make your calling and election secure, because if you do these things, you will never ever stumble.
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For in this way entrance into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ will be richly supplied for you.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore I intend to remind you continually concerning these things, although you know them and are established in the truth that you have.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	But I consider it right, for as long as I am in this habitation, to stir you up by a reminder,
B061C001V014	61	1	14	because I know that the removal of my habitation is imminent, as indeed our Lord Jesus Christ made clear to me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	And I will also make every effort that you are able at any time, after my departure, ˻to recall these things to mind˼.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we did not make known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ by following ingeniously concocted myths, but by being eyewitnesses of that one’s majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received honor and glory from God the Father when a voice such as this was brought to him by the Majestic Glory, “This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.”
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And we ourselves heard this voice brought from heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain,
B061C001V019	61	1	19	and we possess as more reliable the prophetic word, to which you do well if you pay attention to it as to a lamp shining in a dark place, until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts,
B061C001V020	61	1	20	recognizing this above all, that every prophecy of scripture does not come about from one’s own interpretation,
B061C001V021	61	1	21	for no prophecy was ever produced by the will of man, but men carried along by the Holy Spirit spoke from God.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But there were also false prophets among the people, as there will be false teachers among you also, who will bring in ˻destructive heresies˼, even denying the Master who bought them, thus bringing on themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And many will follow their licentious ways, because of whom the way of truth will be reviled.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	And in greediness they will exploit you with false words, whose condemnation from long ago is not idle, and their destruction is not asleep.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare the angels who sinned, but held them captive in Tartarus with chains of darkness and handed them over to be kept for judgment,
B061C002V005	61	2	5	and did not spare the ancient world, but preserved Noah, a proclaimer of righteousness, ˻and seven others˼when he brought a flood on the world of the ungodly,
B061C002V006	61	2	6	and condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah to destruction, reducing them to ashes, having appointed themas an example for those who are going to be ungodly,
B061C002V007	61	2	7	and rescued righteous Lot, worn down by the way of life of lawless persons in licentiousness
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(for that righteous man, as he lived among them day after day, was tormenting his righteous soul by the lawless deeds he was seeing and hearing),
B061C002V009	61	2	9	then the Lord knows how to rescue the godly from trials and to reserve the unrighteous to be punished at the day of judgment,
B061C002V010	61	2	10	and especially those who go after the flesh in defiling lust and who despise authority.Bold and arrogant, they do not tremble in awe as they blaspheme majestic beings,
B061C002V011	61	2	11	whereas angels, who are greater in strength and power, do not bring against them a demeaning judgment from the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these persons, like irrational animals born only with natural instincts for capture and killing, blaspheming ˻about things˼ they do not understand, in their destruction will also be destroyed,
B061C002V013	61	2	13	being harmed as the wages of unrighteousness. Considering reveling in the daytime a pleasure, they are stains and blemishes, carousing in their deceitful pleasures when they feast together with you,
B061C002V014	61	2	14	having eyes full of desire for an adulteress and unceasing from sin, enticing unstable persons, and having hearts trained for greediness. Accursed children!
B061C002V015	61	2	15	By leaving the straight path, they have gone astray, because they followed the way of Balaam the son of Bosor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness,
B061C002V016	61	2	16	but received a rebuke for his own lawlessness: a speechless donkey, speaking with a human voice, restrained ˻the prophet’s madness˼.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These people are waterless springs and mists driven by a hurricane, for whom the gloom of darkness has been reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	˻For by speaking high-sounding but empty words˼, they entice with desires of the flesh and with licentiousness those who are scarcely escaping from those who live in error,
B061C002V019	61	2	19	promising them freedom although they themselves are slaves of depravity. For to whatever someone succumbs, by this he is enslaved.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after they have escaped from the defilements of the world through the knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, and they are again entangled in these thingsand succumb to them, the last state has become worse for them than the first.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it would have been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness than having known it, to turn back from the holy commandment that had been delivered to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	The statement of the true proverb has happened to them, “A dog returns to its own vomit,” and “A sow, after washing herself, returns to wallowing in the mud.”
B061C003V001	61	3	1	Dear friends, this is already the second letter I am writing to you, in both of which I am attempting to stir up your sincere mind by a reminder,
B061C003V002	61	3	2	to remember the words proclaimed beforehand by the holy prophets and the commandment of the Lord and Savior through your apostles,
B061C003V003	61	3	3	above all knowing this, that in the last days scoffers will come with scoffing, following according to their own desires
B061C003V004	61	3	4	and saying, “Where is the promise of his coming? For ˻ever since˼ the fathers fell asleep, all things have continued just as they have been from the beginning of creation.”
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For when they maintain this, it escapes their notice that the heavens existed long ago and the earth held together out of water and through water by the word of God,
B061C003V006	61	3	6	by means of which things the world that existed at that time was destroyed by being inundated with water.
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But by the same word the present heavens and earth are reserved for fire, being kept for the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly people.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	Now, dear friends, do not let this one thing escape your notice, that one day with the Lord is like a thousand years, and a thousand years is like one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not delaying the promise, as some consider slowness, but is being patient toward you, because he does not want any to perish, but all to come to repentence.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord will come like a thief, in which the heavens will disappear with a rushing noise, and the celestial bodies will be destroyed by being burned up, and the earth and the deeds done on it will be disclosed.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Because all these things are being destroyed in this way, what sort of people must you be in holy behavior and godliness,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	while waiting for and hastening the coming of the day of God, because of which the heavens will be destroyed by being burned up and the celestial bodies will melt as they are consumed by heat!
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But according to his promise, we are waiting for new heavens and a new earth in which righteousness resides.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, dear friends, because you are waiting for these things, make every effort to be found at peace, spotless and unblemished in him.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	And regard the patience of our Lord as salvation, just as also our dear brother Paul wrote to you, according to the wisdom that was given to him,
B061C003V016	61	3	16	as he does also in all his letters, speaking in them about these things, in which there are some things hard to understand, which the ignorant and unstable distort to their own destruction, as they also do the rest of the scriptures.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	Therefore, dear friends, because you know this beforehand, guard yourselves so that you do not lose your own safe position because you have been led away by the error of lawless persons.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him be the glory, both now and to the day of eternity. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	What was from the beginning, what we have heard, what we have seen with our eyes, what we have looked at and our hands have touched, concerning the word of life—
B062C001V002	62	1	2	and the life was revealed, and we have seen and testify and announce to you the eternal life which was with the Father and was revealed to us—
B062C001V003	62	1	3	what we have seen and heard, we announce to you also, in order that you also may have fellowship with us, and indeed our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And these things we write, in order that our joy may be complete.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	And this is the message which we have heard from him and announce to you, that God is light and there is no darkness in him at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we say that we have fellowship with him and walk in the darkness, we lie and do not practice the truth.
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we walk in the light as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say that we do not have sin, we deceive ourselves and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just, so that he will forgive us our sins and will cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, I am writing these things to you in order that you may not sin. And if anyone sins, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous one,
B062C002V002	62	2	2	and he is the propitiation for our sins, and not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we know that we have come to know him, if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	The one who says “I have come to know him,” and does not keep his commandments is a liar, and the truth is not in this person.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps his word, truly in this person the love of God has been perfected. By this we know that we are in him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	The one who says that he resides in him ought also to walk in this way: just as that one walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Dear friends, I am not writing a new commandment to you, but an old commandment which you have had from the beginning. The old commandment is the message which you have heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again, I am writing a new commandment to you, which is true in him and in you, because the darkness is passing away and the true light already is shining.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	The one who says he is in the light and hates his brother is in the darkness until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	The one who loves his brother resides in the light, and there is no cause for stumbling in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But the one who hates his brother is in the darkness, and walks in the darkness, and does not know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I am writing to you, little children, because your sins have been forgiven you on account of his name.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I am writing to you, fathers, because you have known the One who is from the beginning. I am writing to you, young men, because you have conquered the evil one.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, children, because you have known the Father. I have written to you, fathers, because you have known the One who is from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God resides in you, and you have conquered the evil one.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world or the things in the world. If anyone loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him,
B062C002V016	62	2	16	because everything that is in the world—the desire of the flesh and the desire of the eyes and the arrogance of material possessions—is not from the Father, but is from the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world is passing away, and its desire, but the one who does the will of God remains ˻forever˼.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Children, it is the last hour, and just as you have heard that antichrist is coming, even now many antichrists have arisen, by which we know that it is the last hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would have remained with us. But they went out, in order that it might be shown that all of them are not of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	And you have an anointing from the Holy One, and you all know.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written to you because you do not know the truth, but because you do know it, and because every lie is not of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is the liar except the one who denies that Jesus is the Christ? This person is the antichrist, the one who denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	Everyone who denies the Son does not have the Father either; the one who confesses the Son has the Father also.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	As for you, what you have heard from the beginning must remain in you. If what you have heard from the beginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise which he himself promised us: eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	These things I have written to you concerning the ones who are trying to deceive you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	And as for you, the anointing which you received from him remains in you, and you do not have need that anyone teach you. But as his anointing teaches you about all things, and is true and is not a lie, and just as it has taught you, you reside in him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, little children, remain in him, so that whenever he is revealed we may have confidence and not be put to shame before him at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone also who practices righteousness has been fathered by him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	See what sort of love the Father has given to us: that we should be called children of God, and we are! Because of this the world does not know us: because it did not know him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Dear friends, now we are children of God, and what we will be has not yet been revealed. We know that whenever he is revealed we will be like him, because we will see him just as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And everyone who has this hope in him purifies himself, just as that one is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Everyone who practices sin also practices lawlessness, and sin is lawlessness.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that that one was revealed in order that he might take away sins, and in him there is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Everyone who resides in him does not sin. Everyone who sins has neither seen him nor known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no one deceive you: the one who practices righteousness is righteous, just as that one is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	The one who practices sin is of the devil, because the devil has been sinning from the beginning. For this reason the Son of God was revealed: in order to destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	Everyone who is fathered by God does not practice sin, because his seed resides in him, and he is not able to sin, because he has been fathered by God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	By this the children of God and the children of the devil are evident: everyone who does not practice righteousness is not of God, namely, the one who does not love his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the message that you have heard from the beginning: that we should love one another,
B062C003V012	62	3	12	not as Cain, who was of the evil one and violently murdered his brother. And ˻for what reason˼ did he violently murder him? Because his deeds were evil and the deeds of his brother were righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	And do not marvel, brothers, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed over from death to life because we love the brothers. The one who does not love remains in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Everyone who hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that every murderer does not have eternal life residing in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	We have come to know love by this: that ˻he˼ laid down his life on behalf of us, and we ought to lay down our lives on behalf of the brothers.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But whoever has the world’s material possessions and observes his brother ˻in need˼ and shuts his heart against him, how does the love of God reside in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	Little children, let us not love with word or with tongue, but in deed and truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And by this we know that we are of the truth and will convince our heart before him,
B062C003V020	62	3	20	that if our heart condemns us, that God is greater than our heart and knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Dear friends, if our heart does not condemn us, we have confidence before God,
B062C003V022	62	3	22	and whatever we ask we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do what is pleasing ˻in his sight˼.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his commandment: that we believe in the name of his Son Jesus Christ and love one another, just as ˻he commanded us˼.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	And the one who keeps his commandments resides in him, and he in him. And by this we know that he resides in us: by the Spirit whom he has given to us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Dear friends, do not believe every spirit, but test the spirits to determine if they are from God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this you know the Spirit of God: every spirit that confesses Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is from God,
B062C004V003	62	4	3	and every spirit that does not confess Jesus is not from God, and this is the spirit of the antichrist, of which you have heard that it is coming, and now it is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	You are from God, little children, and have conquered them, because the one who is in you is greater than the one who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are from the world; ˻therefore˼ they speak from the world and the world listens to them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are from God. The one who knows God listens to us; whoever is not from God does not listen to us. By this we know the Spirit of truth and the spirit of deceit.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Dear friends, let us love one another, because love is from God, and everyone who loves has been fathered by God and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	The one who does not love does not know God, because God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	By this the love of God is revealed in us: that God sent his one and only Son into the world in order that we may live through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love: not that we have loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Dear friends, if God loved us in this way, we also ought to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No one has seen God at any time. If we love one another, God resides in us and his love is perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	By this we know that we reside in him and he in us: that he has given us of his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and testify that the Father has sent the Son to be the Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God resides in him and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And we have come to know and have believed the love that God has in us. God is love, and the one who resides in love resides in God, and God resides in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	By this love is perfected with us, so that we may have confidence in the day of judgment, because just as that one is, so also are we in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love, but perfect love drives out fear, because fear includes punishment, and the one who is afraid has not been perfected in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love, because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If anyone says, “I love God,” and hates his brother, he is a liar, for the one who does not love his brother whom he has seen is not able to love God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this is the commandment we have from him: that the one who loves God should love his brother also.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been fathered by God, and everyone who loves ˻the father˼ also loves the child fathered by him.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God: whenever we love God and keep his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God: that we keep his commandments. And his commandments are not burdensome,
B062C005V004	62	5	4	because everyone who is fathered by God conquers the world.And this is the victory which has conquered the world: our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Now who is the one who conquers the world except the one who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is the one who came by water and blood—Jesus Christ, not with the water only, but with the water and with the blood. And the Spirit is the one who testifies, because the Spirit is the truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three that testify,
B062C005V008	62	5	8	the Spirit and the water and the blood, and the three are ˻in agreement˼.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we receive the testimony of people, the testimony of God is greater, because this is the testimony of God that he has testified concerning his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	(The one who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself. The one who does not believe God has made him a liar, because he has not believed in the testimony that God has testified concerning his Son.)
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And this is the testimony: that God has given us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	The one who has the Son has the life; the one who does not have the Son of God does not have the life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of God, in order that you may know that you have eternal life.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the confidence that we have before him: that if we ask anything according to his will, he hears us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he hears us in whatever we ask, we know that we have the requests that we have asked from him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If anyone should see his brother sinning a sin not leading to death, he should ask, and he will grant life to him, to those who sin not leading to death. (There is a sin leading to death; I do not say that he should ask about that.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin, and there is a sin not leading to death.)
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that everyone who is fathered by God does not sin, but the one fathered by God, he protects him, and the evil one does not touch him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are from God, and the whole world lies in the power of the evil one.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of God has come and has given us understanding, in order that we may know the one who is true, and we are in the one who is true, in his Son Jesus Christ. This one is the true God and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, guard yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	The elder, to the elect lady and her children, whom I love in truth—and not I alone, but also all those who know the truth—
B063C001V002	63	1	2	because of the truth that resides in us and will be with us ˻forever˼.
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, peace will be with us from God the Father and from Jesus Christ the Son of the Father in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	˻I was very glad˼ because I found some of your children walking in the truth, just as ˻the Father commanded us˼.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I ask you, lady (not as if I were writing a new commandment to you, but one that we have had from the beginning), that we should love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	And this is love: that we walk according to his commandments. This is the commandment, just as you have heard from the beginning, so that you should walk in it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have gone out into the world, those who do not confess Jesus Christ coming in the flesh. This person is the deceiver and the antichrist!
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Watch yourselves that you do not lose what we have worked for, but receive a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Everyone who goes too far and does not remain in the teaching of Christ does not have God. The one who remains in the teaching—this person has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If anyone comes to you and does not bring this teaching, do not receive him into your house and do not speak a greeting to him,
B063C001V011	63	1	11	because the one who speaks a greeting to him shares in his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Although I have many things to write to you, I do not want to do so by means of paper and ink, but I hope to be with you and to speak ˻face to face˼, so that our joy may be complete.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your elect sister greet you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	The elder, to Gaius the beloved, whom I love in the truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Dear friend, I pray you may prosper concerning everything and be healthy, just as your soul prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced exceedingly when the brothers came and testified to your truth, just as you are walking in the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than this: that I hear my children are walking in the truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Dear friend, you act faithfully in whatever you do for the brothers, ˻even though they are strangers˼.
B064C001V006	64	1	6	They have testified to your love before the church; you will do well to send them on their way in a manner worthy of God.
B064C001V007	64	1	7	For they have gone out on behalf of the name, accepting nothing from the pagans.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	Therefore we ought to support such people, so that we become fellow workers with the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote something to the church, but Diotrephes, who wants to be first among them, does not acknowledge us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	Therefore, if I come, I will call attention to ˻the deeds he is doing˼, disparaging us with evil words. And not being content with these, he does not receive the brothers himself, and he hinders those wanting to do so and throws them out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Dear friend, do not imitate what is evil, but what is good. The one who does good is of God; the one who does evil has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius has been testified to by all, even by the truth itself. And we also testify to him, and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I have many things to write to you, but I do not want to write to you by means of ink and pen.
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I hope to see you right away, and to speak ˻face to face˼. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, a slave of Jesus Christ and brother of James, to those who are called, loved in God the Father and kept for Jesus Christ.
B065C001V002	65	1	2	May mercy and peace and love be multiplied to you.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Dear friends, although I was making every effort to write to you concerning our common salvation, I considered it a necessity to write to you to encourage you to contend for the faith delivered once and for all to the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain men have slipped in stealthily, who were designated long ago for this condemnation, ungodly ones, who change the grace of our God into licentiousness and who deny our only Master and Lord Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	Now I want to remind you, although you know everything once and for all, that the Lord, having saved the people out of the land of Egypt, the second time destroyed those who did not believe.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And the angels who did not keep to their own domain but deserted their proper dwelling place, he has kept in eternal bonds under deep gloom for the judgment of the great day,
B065C001V007	65	1	7	as Sodom and Gomorrah and the towns around them indulged in sexual immorality and ˻pursued unnatural desire˼in the same way as these, are exhibited as an example by undergoing the punishment of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Despite that, in the same way also these men, because of their dreams, defile the flesh and reject authority and blaspheme majestic beings.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	But Michael the archangel, when he argued with the devil, disputing concerning the body of Moses, did not dare to pronounce a blasphemous judgment, but said, “The Lord rebuke you!”
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these persons blaspheme all that they do not understand, and all that they understand by instinct like the irrational animals, by these things they are being destroyed.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe to them! For they have traveled in the way of Cain, and have given themselves up to the error of Balaam for gain, and have perished in the rebellion of Korah.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are the ones feasting together without reverence, hidden reefs at your love feasts, caring for themselves, waterless clouds carried away by winds, late autumn trees without fruit, twice dead, uprooted,
B065C001V013	65	1	13	wild waves of the sea foaming up their own shameful deeds, wandering stars, for whom the deep gloom of darkness has been reserved for eternity.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	And Enoch, the seventh from Adam, also prophesied about these people, saying, “Behold, the Lord came with tens of thousands of his holy ones
B065C001V015	65	1	15	to execute judgment against all, and to convict every soul concerning all their ungodly deeds that they have committed in an ungodly way, and concerning all the harsh things that ungodly sinners have spoken against him.
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These people are grumblers, discontented, proceeding according to their own desires, and their mouths speaking pompous words, ˻showing partiality to gain an advantage˼.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, dear friends, remember the words proclaimed beforehand by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ,
B065C001V018	65	1	18	for they said to you that in the end time there will be scoffers following according to their own ungodly desires.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are the ones who cause divisions, worldly, not having the Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, dear friends, by building yourselves up in your most holy faith, by praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	keep yourselves in the love of God, looking forward to the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	And have mercy on those who doubt,
B065C001V023	65	1	23	and save others by snatching them from the fire, and have mercy on others with fear, hating even the tunic stained by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now to the one who is able to protect you from stumbling and make you to stand before his glory blameless with exultation,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	to the only God our Savior, through Jesus Christ our Lord, be glory, majesty, power, and authority before all time and now and for all eternity. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	The revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave him to show to his slaves the things which must take place in a short time, and communicated itby sending it through his angel to his slave John,
B066C001V002	66	1	2	who testified about the word of God and the testimony of Jesus Christ, all that he saw.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is the one who reads aloud and blessed are those who hear the words of the prophecy and observe the things written in it, because the time is near!
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John, to the seven churches in Asia: grace to you and peace from the one who is and the one who was and the one who is coming, and from the seven spirits who are before his throne,
B066C001V005	66	1	5	and from Jesus Christ the faithful witness, the firstborn from the dead and the ruler of the kings of the earth.To the one who loves us and released us from our sins by his blood
B066C001V006	66	1	6	and made us a kingdom, priests to his God and Father—to him be the glory and the power ˻forever and ever˼. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, he is coming with the clouds,and every eye will see him,even every one who pierced him,and all the tribes of the earth will mourn over him.Yes, amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	I am the Alpha and the Omega, says the Lord God, the one who is and the one who was and the one who is coming, the All-Powerful.
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I, John, your brother and co-sharer in the affliction and kingdom and steadfastness in Jesus, was on the island called Patmos because of the word of God and the testimony about Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in the Spirit on the Lord’s day, and I heard behind me a great sound like a trumpet
B066C001V011	66	1	11	saying, “What you see, write in a book and send it to the seven churches: to Ephesus and to Smyrna and to Pergamum and to Thyatira and to Sardis and to Philadelphia and to Laodicea.”
B066C001V012	66	1	12	And I turned to see the voice which was speaking with me, and when I turned, I saw seven gold lampstands,
B066C001V013	66	1	13	and in the midst of the lampstands one like a son of man, dressed in a robe reaching to the feet and girded around his chest with a golden belt,
B066C001V014	66	1	14	and his head and hair were white like wool, white as snow, and his eyes were like a fiery flame,
B066C001V015	66	1	15	and his feet were like fine bronze when it has been fired in a furnace, and his voice was like the sound of many waters,
B066C001V016	66	1	16	and he had in his right hand seven stars, and a sharp double-edged sword coming out of his mouth, and his face was like the sun shining in its strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	And when I saw him, I fell at his feet like a dead person, and he placed his right hand on me, saying, “Do not be afraid! I am the first and the last,
B066C001V018	66	1	18	and the one who lives, and I was dead, and behold, I am living ˻forever and ever˼, and I hold the keys of death and of Hades.
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Therefore, write the things which you saw, and the things which are, and the things which are about to take place after these things.
B066C001V020	66	1	20	As for the mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand and the seven gold lampstands—the seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven lampstands are the seven churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	“To the angel of the church in Ephesus write:“This is what the one who holds the seven stars in his right hand says, the one who walks in the midst of the seven gold lampstands:
B066C002V002	66	2	2	‘I know your works, and your labor and patient endurance, and that you are not able to tolerate evil, and you put to the test those who call themselves apostles and are not, and you found them to be false.
B066C002V003	66	2	3	And you have patient endurance, and have endured many things because of my name, and have not become weary.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	But I have this against you: that you have left your first love.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Remember therefore from where you have fallen, and repent and do ˻the works you did at first˼. But if you do not, I am coming to you, and I will remove your lampstand from its place, unless you repent.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	But you do have this: that you hate the deeds of the Nicolaitans, things which I also hate.
B066C002V007	66	2	7	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To the one who conquers, I will grant to him to eat from the tree of life which is in the paradise of God.’
B066C002V008	66	2	8	“And to the angel of the church in Smyrna write:“This is what the first and the last says, who was dead and came to life:
B066C002V009	66	2	9	‘I know your affliction and poverty (but you are rich), and the slander of those ˻who call themselves Jews˼ and are not, but are a synagogue of Satan.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Do not be afraid of the things which you are about to suffer. Behold, the devil is about to throw some of you into prison so that you may be tested, and you will experience affliction ten days. Be faithful until death, and I will give you the crown of life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. The one who conquers will never be harmed by the second death.’
B066C002V012	66	2	12	“And to the angel of the church in Pergamum write:“This is what the one who has the sharp double-edged sword says:
B066C002V013	66	2	13	‘I know where you live, where the throne of Satan is. And you hold fast to my name and did not deny your faith in me, even in the days of Antipas my faithful witness, who was killed among you, where Satan lives.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	But I have a few things against you: that you have there those who hold fast to the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to put a stumbling block before the sons of Israel, to eat food sacrificed to idols and to commit sexual immorality.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	So likewise you also have those who hold fast to the teaching of the Nicolaitans.
B066C002V016	66	2	16	Therefore repent! But if you do not, I am coming to you quickly, and I will make war with them with the sword from my mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches. To the one who conquers, I will give to him some of the hidden manna, and I will give to him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written, that no one knows except the one who receives it.’
B066C002V018	66	2	18	“And to the angel of the church in Thyatira write:“This is what the Son of God says, the one who has his eyes like a fiery flame and his feet like fine bronze:
B066C002V019	66	2	19	‘I know your works, and your love, and faith, and service, and patient endurance—and your last works are greater than the first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	But I have against you that you tolerate the woman Jezebel, the one who calls herself a prophetess, and teaches and deceives my slaves to commit sexual immorality and to eat food sacrificed to idols.
B066C002V021	66	2	21	And I have given her time in order to repent, and she did not want to repent from her sexual immorality.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	Behold, I am throwing her into a sickbed and those who committed adultery with her into great affliction, unless they repent from her deeds.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	And I will kill her children with deadly disease, and all the churches will know that I am the one who searches minds and hearts, and I will give to each one of you according to your deeds.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But I say to you, to the rest who are in Thyatira, all those who do not hold this teaching, who have not known the deep things of Satan, as they say, I do not put upon you any other burden.
B066C002V025	66	2	25	Nevertheless, hold fast to what you have until I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	And the one who conquers and who keeps my works until the end, I will give him authority over the nations,
B066C002V027	66	2	27	and “he will shepherd them with an iron rod; he will break them in pieces like jars made of clay,”
B066C002V028	66	2	28	as I also have received from my Father, and I will give him the morning star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.’
B066C003V001	66	3	1	“And to the angel of the church in Sardis write:“This is what the one who has the seven spirits of God and the seven stars says: ‘I know your works, that you have a name that you are alive, and you are dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Be on the alert and strengthen the remaining things that are about to die, for I have not found your works completed before my God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Therefore remember how you have received and heard, and observe it, and repent. If therefore you are not on the alert, I will come like a thief, and you will never know at what hour I will come against you.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	But you have a few ˻people˼ in Sardis who have not defiled their clothing, and they will walk with me in white, because they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	The one who conquers in this way will be dressed in white clothing, and I will never erase his name from the book of life, and I will declare his name before my Father and before his angels.
B066C003V006	66	3	6	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.’
B066C003V007	66	3	7	“And to the angel of the church in Philadelphia write:“This is what the holy one, the true one, the one who has the key of David, the one who opens and no one can shut, and who shuts and no one can open, says:
B066C003V008	66	3	8	‘I know your works (behold, I have put before you an opened door that no one is able to shut) that you have a little strength, and have kept my word, and did not deny my name.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	Behold, I am causing those of the synagogue of Satan, the ones who call themselves Jews and are not, but are lying—behold, I will make them ˻come˼ and kneel down before your feet and acknowledge that I have loved you.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because you have kept the word of my patient endurance, I also will keep you from the hour of testing that is about to come upon the whole inhabited world, to put to the test those who live on the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	I am coming quickly! Hold fast to what you have, so that no one may take away your crown.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	The one who conquers, I will make him a pillar in the temple of my God, and he will never go outside again, and I will write on him the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem that comes down from heaven from my God, and my new name.
B066C003V013	66	3	13	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.’
B066C003V014	66	3	14	“And to the angel of the church in Laodicea write:“This is what the Amen, the faithful and true witness, the originator of God’s creation, says:
B066C003V015	66	3	15	‘I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot. Would that you were cold or hot!
B066C003V016	66	3	16	Thus, because you are lukewarm and neither hot nor cold, I am about to vomit you out of my mouth!
B066C003V017	66	3	17	Because you are saying, “I am rich, and have become rich, and I have need of nothing,” and you do not know that you are wretched and pitiable and poor and blind and naked,
B066C003V018	66	3	18	I advise you to buy from me gold refined by fire, in order that you may become rich, and white clothing, in order that you may be clothed and the shame of your nakedness may not be revealed, and eye salve to smear on your eyes, in order that you may see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	As many as I love, I reprove and discipline. Be zealous, therefore, and repent!
B066C003V020	66	3	20	Behold, I stand at the door and knock! If anyone hears my voice and opens the door, indeed I will come in to him and dine with him, and he with me.
B066C003V021	66	3	21	The one who conquers, I will grant to him to sit down with me on my throne, as I also have conquered and have sat down with my Father on his throne.
B066C003V022	66	3	22	The one who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.’ ”
B066C004V001	66	4	1	After these things I looked, and behold, an open door in heaven, and the former voice that I had heard like a trumpet speaking with me was saying, “Come up here and I will show you the things which must take place after these things.”
B066C004V002	66	4	2	Immediately I was in the Spirit, and behold, a throne was set in heaven, and one was seated on the throne.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	And the one seated was similar in appearance to jasper and carnelian stone, and a rainbow was around the throne similar in appearance to emerald.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	And around the throne were twenty-four thrones, and seated on the thrones were twenty-four elders dressed in white clothing, and on their heads were gold crowns.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And from the throne came out lightnings and sounds and thunders, and seven torches of fire were burning before the throne, which are the seven spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And before the throne was something like a sea of glass, like crystal, and in the midst of the throne and around the throne were four living creatures full of eyes in front and in back.
